INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ec4e7fad-a8b0-475b-bbad-018860e9487d', 'c2b0c6b9-a53e-4cf0-8128-076ce9f9476b', 'radio', 'Questions 21–30', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct letter, A, B or C</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Research on absence from work</strong></p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. she was contacted by the managing director. "}, {"content": "B. she knew several people who worked there. "}, {"content": "C. she had already done a work placement there."}], "question": "Laura chose Burcock Engineering for her research because "}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A. check it is relevant "}, {"content": "B. broaden the focus "}, {"content": "C. be more specific in her aims"}], "question": "What does Laura agree to do regarding the central theme of her research? "}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. Absence rates are related to the type of work done. "}, {"content": "B. A lot of worker absence is actually unnecessary. "}, {"content": "C. Employee absence rates are increasing."}], "question": "What does Laura expect to find from her research? "}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A. dates of birth "}, {"content": "B. details of employment "}, {"content": "C. individual records of absence"}], "question": "What employee information does the tutor think Laura will be able to obtain from company records? "}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> You will hear a business student called Laura talking to her tutor about some research she is planning to do on employee absence. First you have some time to look at questions 21 to 24. Now listen carefully and answer questions 21 to 24.</p>\n<p><strong>Tutor:</strong> Hello Laura, have a seat. So I understand you&#8217;re planning to investigate absence from work for your research project.</p>\n<p><strong>Laura:</strong> That&#8217;s right. I&#8217;m going to base it on a local company called Burcock Engineering.</p>\n<p><strong>Tutor:</strong> Is there any particular reason why you&#8217;ve chosen Burcock?</p>\n<p><strong>Laura:</strong> Well, I&#8217;d originally thought of asking another company, FG Engineering, because I did my placement there and I knew the staff there, but the CEO wasn&#8217;t very keen. But she knows the managing director at Burcock, and she spoke to him and then <strong>(21) he got in touch with me (A)</strong>. Apparently, absence is a major problem there, so he&#8217;s quite interested in having it investigated.</p>\n<p><strong>Tutor:</strong> Okay. So my central theme is absence, but I&#8217;m thinking of concentrating on long term absence. I thought that might allow me to give more helpful feedback to the company.</p>\n<p><strong>Tutor:</strong> If I were you, I wouldn&#8217;t be that specific. I&#8217;d <strong>(22) look at absence as a whole (B)</strong>. You might get more interesting results.</p>\n<p><strong>Laura:</strong> Oh, OK.</p>\n<p><strong>Tutor:</strong> So what&#8217;s the main thing you expect to find? Rises in absence rates over time?</p>\n<p><strong>Laura:</strong> Not really. Initially, I wondered if workers often take time off without real justification, but I think that&#8217;ll be hard to determine. So, well, I think I may find that it&#8217;s something to do with <strong>(23) what sort of job the employee is doing (A)</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Tutor:</strong> Okay. Now, have you thought how you&#8217;ll get your information?</p>\n<p><strong>Laura:</strong> Well, first of all, I need access to the company records.</p>\n<p><strong>Tutor:</strong> Yes, obviously you&#8217;ll need overall absence figures, though it&#8217;s unlikely they&#8217;ll let you have them for individual workers. And you probably won&#8217;t have access to personal information like when they were born. But you should be able to use anonymous details like the type of work they do or <strong>(24) how long they&#8217;ve been with the company (B)</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Laura:</strong> Okay.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> Before you hear the rest of the discussion, you have some time to look at questions 25 to thirty. Now listen and answer questions 25 to thirty.</p>\n<p><strong>Tutor:</strong> So let&#8217;s think a bit more about your questionnaire. I know that it shouldn&#8217;t be too long, or people get bored.</p>\n<p><strong>Laura:</strong> No, but if it&#8217;s too short, you don&#8217;t get enough information. The trick is to get the balance right.</p>\n<p><strong>Tutor:</strong> I think the question should be closed questions, too. I mean, where people choose an answer from a list.</p>\n<p><strong>Laura:</strong> But then you miss the chance of getting unexpected information. So I&#8217;d include one or two <strong>(25) open ended questions (C)</strong> too.</p>\n<p><strong>Tutor:</strong> OK. And I won&#8217;t ask for names or addresses or anything.</p>\n<p><strong>Laura:</strong> No, it needs to be anonymous.</p>\n<p><strong>Tutor:</strong> And after you&#8217;ve drafted it, you need to <strong>(26) give it to at least one person to check (E)</strong> there aren&#8217;t any problems. So you need to leave enough time for that and any revisions necessary.</p>\n<p><strong>Laura:</strong> What about the covering letter that I&#8217;ll send out with the questionnaire? I&#8217;ll need to introduce myself and explain what the questionnaire is for. But what else should I include?</p>\n<p><strong>Tutor:</strong> I&#8217;d reassure people that the survey isn&#8217;t going to be used to assess them personally. Otherwise, they might choose not to take part <strong>(B)</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Laura:</strong> Yes, I&#8217;ll make that clear. And what about when they do it? Will they be allowed to use work time?</p>\n<p><strong>Tutor:</strong> That&#8217;s really up to their manager, but you should say roughly <strong>(28) how much time it&#8217;ll take (C)</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Laura:</strong> OK. So now you need to produce a schedule with dates, for example, when you&#8217;ll send out the questionnaire.</p>\n<p><strong>Tutor:</strong> Yes, okay. Once I can arrange that date with the manager, I&#8217;ll be able to fix the deadline for getting the completed questionnaires back <strong>(C)</strong>. And I want to use the time in between to analyze the figures that HR is going to give me from their database <strong>(E)</strong>, though they haven&#8217;t said exactly when I&#8217;ll get them.</p>\n<p><strong>Tutor:</strong> And you have to submit your assignment by the end of June.</p>\n<p><strong>Laura:</strong> Actually, I have to get it finished by the 2nd <strong>(A)</strong> because I&#8217;ve arranged a work placement after that.</p>\n<p><strong>Tutor:</strong> OK. So our <strong>(30) next meeting is two weeks today (D)</strong>. Is that still OK?</p>\n<p><strong>Laura:</strong> Yes. And in the meantime, I&#8217;ll send you an email.</p>\n<hr>\n<hr>\n<p> </p>\n<h2>🇻🇳 Bản Dịch Tiếng Việt</h2>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Người dẫn chuyện:</strong> Bạn sẽ nghe một sinh viên kinh doanh tên là Laura nói chuyện với gia sư của mình về một nghiên cứu cô ấy đang lên kế hoạch thực hiện về việc nhân viên vắng mặt. Đầu tiên, bạn có thời gian để xem các câu hỏi 21 đến 24. Bây giờ hãy lắng nghe cẩn thận và trả lời các câu hỏi 21 đến 24.</p>\n<p><strong>Gia sư:</strong> Chào Laura, mời bạn ngồi. Vậy tôi hiểu là bạn đang lên kế hoạch điều tra việc vắng mặt trong công việc cho dự án nghiên cứu của mình?</p>\n<p><strong>Laura:</strong> Đúng vậy. Tôi sẽ dựa nghiên cứu vào một công ty địa phương tên là Burcock Engineering.</p>\n<p><strong>Gia sư:</strong> Có lý do đặc biệt nào khiến bạn chọn Burcock không?</p>\n<p><strong>Laura:</strong> À, ban đầu tôi đã nghĩ đến việc hỏi một công ty khác, FG Engineering, vì tôi đã thực tập ở đó và tôi biết nhân viên ở đó, nhưng Giám đốc điều hành không mấy nhiệt tình. Nhưng cô ấy quen Giám đốc điều hành ở Burcock, và cô ấy đã nói chuyện với ông ấy, và sau đó <strong>(21) ông ấy đã liên lạc với tôi (A)</strong>. Rõ ràng, việc vắng mặt là một vấn đề lớn ở đó, vì vậy ông ấy khá quan tâm đến việc nghiên cứu vấn đề này.</p>\n<p><strong>Gia sư:</strong> Được rồi. Vậy chủ đề chính của tôi là vắng mặt, nhưng tôi đang nghĩ đến việc tập trung vào việc vắng mặt dài hạn. Tôi nghĩ điều đó có thể cho phép tôi đưa ra phản hồi hữu ích hơn cho công ty.</p>\n<p><strong>Gia sư:</strong> Nếu là tôi, tôi sẽ không đi quá chi tiết như vậy. Tôi sẽ <strong>(22) xem xét việc vắng mặt nói chung (B)</strong>. Bạn có thể nhận được kết quả thú vị hơn.</p>\n<p><strong>Laura:</strong> Ồ, được rồi.</p>\n<p><strong>Gia sư:</strong> Vậy điều chính mà bạn mong đợi tìm thấy là gì? Tỷ lệ vắng mặt tăng theo thời gian?</p>\n<p><strong>Laura:</strong> Không hẳn. Ban đầu, tôi tự hỏi liệu công nhân có thường xuyên nghỉ việc mà không có lý do chính đáng không, nhưng tôi nghĩ điều đó sẽ khó xác định. Vì vậy, tôi nghĩ tôi có thể thấy rằng nó có liên quan đến <strong>(23) loại công việc mà nhân viên đang làm (A)</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Gia sư:</strong> Được rồi. Bây giờ, bạn đã nghĩ cách để lấy thông tin chưa?</p>\n<p><strong>Laura:</strong> Vâng, trước hết, tôi cần quyền truy cập vào hồ sơ công ty.</p>\n<p><strong>Gia sư:</strong> Đúng vậy, rõ ràng bạn sẽ cần số liệu vắng mặt tổng thể, mặc dù không chắc họ sẽ cho phép bạn xem số liệu của từng nhân viên. Và bạn có thể sẽ không có quyền truy cập vào thông tin cá nhân như ngày sinh của họ. Nhưng bạn sẽ có thể sử dụng các chi tiết ẩn danh như loại công việc họ làm hoặc <strong>(24) thời gian họ làm việc tại công ty (B)</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Laura:</strong> Được rồi.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><strong>Người dẫn chuyện:</strong> Trước khi bạn nghe phần còn lại của cuộc thảo luận, bạn có thời gian để xem các câu hỏi 25 đến 30. Bây giờ hãy lắng nghe và trả lời các câu hỏi 25 đến 30.</p>\n<p><strong>Gia sư:</strong> Vậy hãy suy nghĩ thêm một chút về bảng câu hỏi của bạn. Tôi biết nó không nên quá dài, nếu không mọi người sẽ thấy chán.</p>\n<p><strong>Laura:</strong> Không, nhưng nếu quá ngắn thì bạn không nhận đủ thông tin. Bí quyết là đạt được sự cân bằng phù hợp.</p>\n<p><strong>Gia sư:</strong> Tôi nghĩ câu hỏi cũng nên là câu hỏi đóng (closed questions). Ý tôi là nơi mọi người chọn câu trả lời từ một danh sách.</p>\n<p><strong>Laura:</strong> Nhưng sau đó bạn bỏ lỡ cơ hội nhận được thông tin bất ngờ. Vì vậy, tôi cũng sẽ thêm một hoặc hai <strong>(25) câu hỏi mở (C)</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Gia sư:</strong> Được rồi. Và bạn sẽ không hỏi tên hay địa chỉ hay bất cứ thứ gì?</p>\n<p><strong>Laura:</strong> Không, nó cần phải ẩn danh.</p>\n<p><strong>Gia sư:</strong> Và sau khi bạn đã soạn thảo xong, bạn cần <strong>(26) đưa nó cho ít nhất một người kiểm tra (E)</strong> để đảm bảo không có bất kỳ vấn đề nào. Vì vậy, bạn cần dành đủ thời gian cho việc đó và bất kỳ chỉnh sửa nào cần thiết.</p>\n<p><strong>Laura:</strong> Còn về thư xin tham gia (covering letter) mà tôi sẽ gửi kèm bảng câu hỏi thì sao? Tôi sẽ cần tự giới thiệu và giải thích mục đích của bảng câu hỏi. Nhưng tôi nên bao gồm thêm điều gì nữa?</p>\n<p><strong>Gia sư:</strong> Tôi sẽ trấn an mọi người rằng cuộc khảo sát sẽ không được sử dụng để đánh giá cá nhân họ. Nếu không, họ có thể chọn không tham gia <strong>(B)</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Laura:</strong> Vâng, tôi sẽ làm rõ điều đó. Và còn về thời gian họ làm bài thì sao? Họ có được phép sử dụng thời gian làm việc không?</p>\n<p><strong>Gia sư:</strong> Điều đó thực sự tùy thuộc vào quản lý của họ, nhưng bạn nên nói rõ khoảng <strong>(28) thời gian nó sẽ mất (C)</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Laura:</strong> Được rồi. Vậy bây giờ bạn cần lập một lịch trình với các ngày cụ thể, ví dụ, khi nào bạn sẽ gửi bảng câu hỏi.</p>\n<p><strong>Gia sư:</strong> Vâng, được rồi. Khi tôi có thể sắp xếp ngày đó với quản lý, tôi sẽ có thể ấn định thời hạn để nhận lại các bảng câu hỏi đã hoàn thành <strong>(C)</strong>. Và tôi muốn sử dụng thời gian ở giữa để phân tích các số liệu mà HR sẽ cung cấp cho tôi từ cơ sở dữ liệu của họ <strong>(E)</strong>, mặc dù họ chưa nói chính xác khi nào tôi sẽ nhận được chúng.</p>\n<p><strong>Gia sư:</strong> Và bạn phải nộp bài tập cuối khóa của mình trước cuối tháng Sáu.</p>\n<p><strong>Laura:</strong> Thực ra, tôi phải hoàn thành nó trước ngày <strong>(A) mùng 2</strong> vì tôi đã sắp xếp một đợt thực tập sau đó.</p>\n<p><strong>Gia sư:</strong> Được rồi. Vậy cuộc họp tiếp theo của chúng ta là <strong>(30) hai tuần kể từ hôm nay (D)</strong>. Vẫn ổn chứ?</p>\n<p><strong>Laura:</strong> Vâng. Và trong thời gian chờ đợi, tôi sẽ gửi cho bạn một email.</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('fc3e7b5a-9005-4dee-a0a2-f0e9b6c3028f', '5ef1e11c-4642-4793-a096-ba56f8d6b7ab', 'radio', 'Questions 32–36', NULL, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm; background: white;">Choose </span><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm; background: white;">TRUE</span></strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm; background: white;"> if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose </span><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm; background: white;">FALSE</span></strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm; background: white;"> if the statement contradicts the information, or choose </span><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm; background: white;">NOT GIVEN</span></strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm; background: white;"> if there is no information on this.</span></span></p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE "}, {"content": "FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Mayan ruling class forbade the use of cocoa and chocolate in rituals."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE "}, {"content": "FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Spanish explorer Hernán Cortés had made an investment in chocolate and chocolate beverages."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE "}, {"content": "FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Wild cocoa trees are more susceptible to infectious diseases than cultivated ones."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE "}, {"content": "FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "During chocolate production, some of the seeds are discarded."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE "}, {"content": "FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Chocolate enjoys more prestige in Europe and the United States than in any other country."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>32. The Mayan ruling class forbade the use of cocoa and chocolate in rituals.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án: FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn C) “<strong>While the aristocracy, particularly the royal families, consumed chocolate during elaborate ceremonies</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Giới quý tộc Maya (<strong>ruling class</strong>) tiêu thụ sô cô la trong các nghi lễ trang trọng, mâu thuẫn với việc họ cấm đoán (forbade).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>33. The Spanish explorer Hernán Cortés had made an investment in chocolate and chocolate beverages.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) “…later Spanish explorer Hernán Cortés quickly <strong>recognised the potential economic value of chocolate</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Cortés nhận ra giá trị kinh tế của sô cô la, nhưng <strong>không có thông tin</strong> xác nhận ông đã đầu tư (made an investment) vào lĩnh vực này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>34. Wild cocoa trees are more susceptible to infectious diseases than cultivated ones.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án: FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn F) “Unexpectedly, <strong>cocoa trees grown on farms are more vulnerable to disease and pests than their wild counterparts</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Cây trồng (cultivated) dễ bị bệnh hơn cây dại (wild), mâu thuẫn với nhận định cây dại dễ bị bệnh hơn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>35. During chocolate production, some of the seeds are discarded.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) “Workers first sort, clean, and roast the <strong>beans</strong> before extracting the outer shells, leaving only the inner <strong>nibs</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Các hạt ca cao (beans) được tách vỏ để lấy lõi (nibs), nhưng <strong>không có thông tin</strong> về việc loại bỏ (discarded) một phần hạt nào trong quá trình này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>36. Chocolate enjoys more prestige in Europe and the United States than in any other country.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"23\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án: TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn H) “…and its reputation remains <strong>most prominent in Europe and the United States</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Danh tiếng (prestige) của sô cô la nổi bật nhất ở Châu Âu và Mỹ, ngụ ý hơn bất kỳ quốc gia nào khác.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('003fed87-5e7e-4dbb-996c-d6f033c40647', '5ef1e11c-4642-4793-a096-ba56f8d6b7ab', 'fillup', 'Questions 37–40', '<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #15191e;">Complete the flow-chart below.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;">Write </span><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;">NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS</span></strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;"> from the passage for each answer.</span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;">From Cocoa Beans to Chocolate</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;">Seeds</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #15191e;">classifying, cleaning, and roasting</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #15191e;">stripping their {outer shells}</span></p>
<p>⬇</p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;">Nibs</span></strong></span></p>
<p>⬇</p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;">Crushing</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;">producing </span><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;">{chocolate liquor}</span></span></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;">mixing with measured quantities of substances such as sweeteners, liquid dairy, and </span><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;">{cocoa butter}</span></span></span></p>
<p>⬇</p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;">Crumb blending</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;">crushing finely to obtain a smooth texture manufacturing diverse shapes of chocolate in </span><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: black; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;"><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e;">{moulds}</span></span></span></p>
<p>⬇</p>
<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: #15191e; border: 1pt none windowtext; padding: 0cm;">Chocolate</span></strong></span></p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong>37. Seeds classifying, cleaning, and roasting stripping their <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"rightarrow\">$rightarrow$</span> outer shells</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"27\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>outer shells</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) “Workers first sort, clean, and roast the beans before extracting the <strong>outer shells</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong>38. Nibs Crushing producing <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"rightarrow\">$rightarrow$</span> chocolate liquor</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>chocolate liquor</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) “These nibs I are then ground into a dense paste known as <strong>chocolate liquor</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong>39. mixing with measured quantities of substances such as sweeteners, liquid dairy, and <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"rightarrow\">$rightarrow$</span> cocoa butter</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>cocoa butter</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) “Chocolate manufacturers blend the chocolate liquor with precise ratios of sugar, milk, and <strong>cocoa butter</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong>40. Crumb blending crushing finely to obtain a smooth texture manufacturing diverse shapes of chocolate in <span class=\"math-inline\" data-math=\"rightarrow\">$rightarrow$</span> moulds</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"33\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>moulds</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) “…before being placed into <strong>moulds</strong> to create various forms, such as bars or other chocolate products.”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e015db91-5413-45f0-9713-c08ca73b4aac', 'ec7ef32f-dc7a-4cbf-af79-816eb1d27235', 'fillup', 'Questions 31–40', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY </strong>for each answer.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="quests-des">
<div class="content-write">
<p class="ql-align-center"><strong>BOAR AND RED DEER</strong></p>
<p><strong>Boar</strong></p>
<p>– Boar is not a <span class="fill-history-correct">{protected}</span> species.</p>
<p>– Their number should be controlled as a result of their damage to the {environment}.</p>
<p>– They also spread <span class="fill-history-correct">{diseases}</span>.</p>
<p>– Law was passed regarding banning use of {poison} in killing boars.</p>
<p>– Measures should be taken to keep the boars in the {forest} away from people in urban areas.</p>
<p>– The early 1990s witnessed a significant population rise of boars due to their escape from <span class="fill-history-correct">{farms}</span>.</p>
<p><strong>Red Deer</strong></p>
<p>– Red deer can also damage agricultural produce, such as grain and <span class="fill-history-correct">{potatoes}</span>.</p>
<p>– In winter the red deer come out to the villages for <span class="fill-history-correct">{food}</span>.</p>
<p>– The number of deer keep stable for <span class="fill-history-correct">{hunting}</span>.</p>
<p>– Deer can have a devastating effect on the local <span class="fill-history-correct">{crops}</span>.</p>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 4: CONTROL OF WILD ANIMALS (BOAR AND RED DEER)</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jim Robinson:</strong> Good morning. My name’s Jim Robinson and today we’re going to look at the control of wild animals, specifically wild boar.</p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_56e5fcb74799d450-33\" data-path-to-node=\"4\">Now, boar have been natural inhabitants of Western Europe for thousands of years, but in recent years there has been a surge in boar activity that poses a real threat. Boars are not currently on the <strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"199\">(31) <span class=\"citation-954 citation-955\">protected</span></strong><span class=\"citation-954 citation-955 citation-end-955\"> animals list, which is perhaps why there has been a spike in their breeding activity.</span></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_56e5fcb74799d450-34\" data-path-to-node=\"5\"><span class=\"citation-952 citation-953 citation-end-953\">Boars are an indigenous species and are particularly plentiful in rural France and the Bavarian uplands of Germany. Boar hunting is a European tradition that goe</span><span class=\"citation-952 citation-end-952\">s back to Roman times and became particularly popular among courtiers during the Middle Ages. Even during the 20th century, boar hunting was seen as an integral part of</span> rural life.</p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_56e5fcb74799d450-35\" data-path-to-node=\"6\">The decline in boar hunting has obviously led to a rise in the boar populations of Europe, and the situation has reached a critical point with boar posing a critical threat to the <strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"180\">(32) <span class=\"citation-951\">environment</span></strong><span class=\"citation-951 citation-end-951\">. Proponents of boar hunting cite this factor as a major reason why boar populations should be contained. Boar also pose a threat to humans too, with countless reports of people being injured dur</span>ing boar attacks.</p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_56e5fcb74799d450-36\" data-path-to-node=\"7\">The origins of the wild boar have roots in Germanic, and this perhaps explains their prevalence in Germany. The problems with the boar population in Germany have ramifications for the rest of Europe as boar packs migrate towards central and Eastern Europe. One of the main issues that is of great concern is the transmission of <strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"328\">(33) <span class=\"citation-949 citation-950\">diseases</span></strong><span class=\"citation-949 citation-950 citation-end-950\"> that infect other species. Dairy farmers in France are particularly concerned as many of them have seen their herds depleted by infections.</span></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_56e5fcb74799d450-37\" data-path-to-node=\"8\"><span class=\"citation-947 citation-948 citation-end-948\">The methods for containing boar populations have been looked at in great detail and numerous options are avai</span><span class=\"citation-947 citation-end-947\">lable. One is to encourage more boar hunting in wild regions such as mountains and forests. Hunters would be given lic</span>ences to hunt either for food or sport. Of course, boar do pose a threat to human life, so this possibility must be looked at with caution.</p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_56e5fcb74799d450-38\" data-path-to-node=\"9\">One method that must be ruled out is <strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"37\">(34) <span class=\"citation-945 citation-946\">poison</span></strong><span class=\"citation-945 citation-946 citation-end-946\">, as legislation has been introduced prohibiting this. Such methods were tried with rabbits in the 1960s and this had a disastrous impact on the food chain. The introduction of natural predators into the ecosystem is also an option that can’t be considered. The only known predators of boar in the world are wild cat</span><span class=\"citation-945 citation-end-945\">s like lions and tigers. Obviously, there’s no way such animals can be allowed to roam the mountains and forests of Europe.</span></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_56e5fcb74799d450-39\" data-path-to-node=\"10\"><span class=\"citation-944 citation-end-944\">Given the threat</span> that boars pose to humans, it is imperative that forest-dwelling boar are kept well away from people in cities. This is absolutely essential as human safety must be the main priority of policy makers. In several European countries, boars were becoming increasingly rare by the 11th century. In Great Britain, King Charles attempted to reintroduce boars in the New <strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"381\">(35) <span class=\"citation-942 citation-943\">forest</span></strong><span class=\"citation-942 citation-943 citation-end-943\"> area of the country, yet the entire population was almost wiped out during the battles of the English Civil War when roaming soldiers hunted them for food.</span></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_56e5fcb74799d450-40\" data-path-to-node=\"11\"><span class=\"citation-940 citation-941 citation-end-941\">During the 1980s, wild boar rearing was encouraged and boar populations began to ri</span><span class=\"citation-940 citation-end-940\">se again. By the 1990s, there was a huge rise in the number of boar across England due in large part to the species no longer</span> being forced to live in captivity. Many boar have broken free from <strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"276\">(36) farms</strong> across England and are breeding at a rapid rate.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">RED DEER</strong></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_56e5fcb74799d450-41\" data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jim Robinson:</strong> Aside from their environmental threats, boars also pose a problem for farmers growing crops and vegetables. Other species such as red deer are a threat to farm produce like grain and <strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"197\">(37) <span class=\"citation-938 citation-939\">potatoes</span></strong><span class=\"citation-938 citation-939 citation-end-939\">, but boars certainly present the most serious risk. The damage done to the farming industry is estimated to cost millions of pounds, and insurance payments as a result of this have spiked in the last decade.</span></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_56e5fcb74799d450-42\" data-path-to-node=\"15\"><span class=\"citation-936 citation-937 citation-end-937\">Red deer are predominantly confined </span><span class=\"citation-936 citation-end-936\">to forest areas and it is unusual to see them outside their habitats during the summer months. However, as the weather gets colder, they can be seen looking for</span> <strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"197\">(38) food</strong> around local villages and fields. Red deer have their origins in Asia and are <span class=\"citation-934 citation-935 citation-end-935\">a ruminant species, which means they have a stomach that consists of four compartments, much like cows. They are slaughtered for food and their meat is sold as venison and is increasingly popular among consume</span><span class=\"citation-934 citation-end-934\">rs.</span></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_56e5fcb74799d450-43\" data-path-to-node=\"16\"><span class=\"citation-933 citation-end-933\">There are nine subspecies of red deer, with three of them on the endangered species list. The deer population doesn’t pose the same threat as the boar populatio</span>n, but it certainly needs to be addressed. Forest areas are their main habitats and they are now breeding at a much higher rate than in previous years.</p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_56e5fcb74799d450-44\" data-path-to-node=\"17\">Of course, deer are an important part of the food chain and are an important part of the <strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">(39) hunting</strong> traditions of the UK, so it is important that their population is kept stable for this reason. Though the real concern is the problems that deer present for farmers who have seen their <strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"287\">(40) <span class=\"citation-932\">crops</span></strong><span class=\"citation-932 citation-end-932\"> suffer in devastating ways. Protection needs to be offered, and many farmers report building large perimeter fences around their fields to keep deer out, which cost them a huge amount of money. Government funding is so far inadequate to offer the protection farmers need, but ways are being looked at to provide subsidies through other mean</span>s.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('be9a06b6-3b94-4d48-a032-ca038afe26c1', 'a9624dae-18e8-4616-95b5-e898d297063b', 'radio', 'Questions 32-35', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Although Oscar Wilde admired Robert Louis Stevenson very much, he believed Stevenson could have written greater works."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Robert Louis Stevenson encouraged Oscar Wilde to start writing at first."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Galsworthy thought Hardy is greater writer than Stevenson is."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Critics only paid attention to Robert Louis Stevenson’s writing topics."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. Although Oscar Wilde admired Robert Louis Stevenson very much, he believed Stevenson could have written better works if he wasn’t born in Scotland.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 3, dòng 7–9.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;Though Stevenson’s works have deeply influenced Oscar Wilde, Wilde often joked that Stevenson <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"106\">would have written better works if he wasn’t born in Scotland</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,3,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc xác nhận Oscar Wilde chịu ảnh hưởng sâu sắc bởi Stevenson (thể hiện sự ngưỡng mộ) nhưng ông cũng đùa rằng Stevenson sẽ viết tốt hơn nếu không sinh ra ở Scotland. Nội dung này khớp hoàn toàn với câu hỏi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. Robert Louis Stevenson encouraged Oscar Wilde to start writing at first.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 3.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;Though Stevenson’s works have deeply influenced Oscar Wilde&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,3,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nói rằng các tác phẩm của Stevenson đã <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"63\">ảnh hưởng sâu sắc</strong> đến Oscar Wilde. Tuy nhiên, không có thông tin nào đề cập đến việc Stevenson trực tiếp <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"168\">khuyến khích</strong> (encouraged) Wilde bắt đầu sự nghiệp cầm bút.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. Galsworthy thought Hardy is a greater writer than Stevenson.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 3, câu cuối.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;Other authors came to Stevenson’s defence, including Galsworthy who claimed that <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"93\">Stevenson is a greater writer than Thomas Hardy</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,3,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc khẳng định Galsworthy cho rằng Stevenson là nhà văn vĩ đại hơn Thomas Hardy. Câu hỏi nói ngược lại (Hardy vĩ đại hơn Stevenson), do đó đáp án là False.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. Critics only paid attention to Robert Louis Stevenson’s writing topics.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 5, dòng 1–3.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;&#8230;his writing was <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"31\">not the only source of attention</strong> for critics. Stevenson’s <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">personal life</strong> often attracted a lot of attention from his fans and critics alike.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,3,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ rõ rằng các chủ đề viết lách (writing topics) <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">không phải là nguồn chú ý duy nhất</strong>. Các nhà phê bình còn đặc biệt quan tâm đến <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"149\">đời tư</strong> (personal life) và lối sống phiêu lưu của ông. Từ &#8220;only&#8221; trong câu hỏi làm cho khẳng định này trở nên sai so với bài đọc.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('0b428db0-c618-4b5c-b3fe-c64d1f99d5eb', 'a9624dae-18e8-4616-95b5-e898d297063b', 'matching', 'Questions 36-40', NULL, '<p>Complete the notes using the list of words, A-I, below.</p>
', 'matching', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Sir Walter Scott and Robert Louis Stevenson</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>A lot of people believe that Sir Walter Scott and Robert Louis Stevenson are the most influential writer in the history of Scotland, but Sir Walter Scott is more proficient in {F. technical control} , while Stevenson has better {A. natural ability} Scott’s books illustrate {H. depth} especially in terms of tragedy, but a lot of readers prefer Stevenson’s {G. storytelling} What’s more, Stevenson’s understanding of {I. human nature} made his works have the most unique expression of Scottish people.</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A. natural ability"}, {"optionText": "B. romance"}, {"optionText": "C. colorful language"}, {"optionText": "D. critical acclaim"}, {"optionText": "E. humor"}, {"optionText": "F. technical control"}, {"optionText": "G. storytelling"}, {"optionText": "H. depth"}, {"optionText": "I. human nature"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. {F} technical control</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 4, câu 3: <em data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“While many critics exalt Sir Walter Scott as a literary genius because of his <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"105\">technical ability</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trong danh sách từ cho trước, <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">technical control</strong> đồng nghĩa với <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"75\">technical ability</strong> (khả năng kỹ thuật/kiểm soát kỹ thuật). Đây là đặc điểm mà các nhà phê bình dùng để ca ngợi Sir Walter Scott.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. {A} natural ability</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 4, câu 3: <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“…others argue that Stevenson deserves the same recognition for his <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"96\">natural ability</strong> to capture stories…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ngược lại với Scott, Stevenson được công nhận nhờ vào <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"66\">khả năng thiên bẩm</strong> (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">natural ability</strong>) trong việc truyền tải câu chuyện và nhân vật.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. {H} depth</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 4, câu 4: <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Many of Scott’s works were taken more seriously as literature for their <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">depth</strong> due to their tragic themes…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các tác phẩm của Scott được đánh giá cao về <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"56\">chiều sâu</strong> (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">depth</strong>) văn học, đặc biệt là khi khai thác các chủ đề bi kịch.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. {G} storytelling</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 4, câu 4: <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“…but fans of Stevenson praise his unique style of <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"79\">story-telling</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trong khi Scott mạnh về chiều sâu bi kịch, độc giả lại yêu thích Stevenson vì phong cách <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"101\">kể chuyện</strong> (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"112\">storytelling</strong>) độc đáo của ông.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. {I} human nature</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 4, câu 4: <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“…praise his unique style of story-telling and capture of <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">human nature</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sự thấu hiểu và khả năng nắm bắt <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"45\">bản chất con người</strong> (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">human nature</strong>) là yếu tố giúp tác phẩm của Stevenson thể hiện một cách độc nhất về con người Scotland.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('fe29f4d0-f929-4245-a5e4-474c320fe838', '3d9e8e2d-6041-4585-af3b-1e7799514d54', 'radio', 'Questions 32 – 36', NULL, '<p data-start="6920" data-end="6969">Choose the correct letter, <strong data-start="6947" data-end="6959">A, B, C,</strong> or <strong data-start="6963" data-end="6968">D</strong>.</p>
', 'multiple-choice', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A. Australian landscape painting derives from the British tradition"}, {"content": "B. Australian landscape painting is more highly regarded than British"}, {"content": "C. Britain is still imposing its principles on Australian art"}, {"content": "D. British art cannot be compared to Australian art"}], "question": "What is the writer’s main point in the second paragraph?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A. Modern Australian landscape painting has great variety"}, {"content": "B. The guidelines for the choice of work were very traditional"}, {"content": "C. Landscape painting remains a popular subject for British artists"}, {"content": "D. The British find the Australian landscape unsuitable as a subject"}], "question": "What does Joanna Mendelssohn find surprising?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. it adopts a subjective approach to depicting the landscape"}, {"content": "B. skateboarding is an inspiration to many Australian artists"}, {"content": "C. storms are a significant feature in the Australian landscape"}, {"content": "D. Bondi is an iconic Australian location"}], "question": "Shaun Gladwell’s work is included in the exhibition because"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A. It is not well known in London art circles"}, {"content": "B. Aboriginal landscape painting influenced Australian settlers"}, {"content": "C. It is part of the Australian art tradition and not independent of it"}, {"content": "D. Modem Aboriginal painting deals with changes to the landscape"}], "question": "What was the reason for Soriano including Aboriginal art in the exhibition?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. having an exhibition in London is not as important as it used to be"}, {"content": "B. young artists in Britain are not interested in Australian art"}, {"content": "C. art from Shanghai is more important than Australian art"}, {"content": "D. New York is still a preferred destination for young artists"}], "question": "By referring to China, Mendelssohn is making the point that"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. What is the writer’s main point in the second paragraph?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">C. Britain is still imposing its principles on Australian art.</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 2,</span><span class=\"\"> dòng 6-8:</span><span class=\"\"> &#8220;&#8230;</span><span class=\"\">there is a suggestion that </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">British artistic values have directed this exhibition</strong><span class=\"\">,</span><span class=\"\"> rather than allowing Australia the freedom to demonstrate its maturity.</span><span class=\"\">&#8220;</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Tác giả nhấn mạnh rằng việc người Anh (Học viện Hoàng gia) tự ý chọn chủ đề phong cảnh cho thấy họ vẫn đang dùng các tiêu chuẩn nghệ thuật của mình để định hướng cho nghệ thuật Úc,</span><span class=\"\"> thay vì để nước Úc tự thể hiện bản sắc độc lập.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. What does Joanna Mendelssohn find surprising?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">B. The guidelines for the choice of work were very traditional.</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 3,</span><span class=\"\"> dòng 1-2:</span><span class=\"\"> &#8220;What Mendelssohn found surprising&#8230;</span><span class=\"\"> was the underlying </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">rules for the selection of works seemed to have been so conservative</strong><span class=\"\">.</span><span class=\"\">&#8220;</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Mendelssohn ngạc nhiên vì các quy tắc lựa chọn tác phẩm quá &#8220;conservative&#8221; (bảo thủ).</span><span class=\"\"> Trong bài thi IELTS,</span><span class=\"\"> &#8220;conservative&#8221; là từ đồng nghĩa phổ biến của </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"164\">&#8220;traditional&#8221;</strong><span class=\"\"> (truyền thống/cũ kỹ).</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. Shaun Gladwell’s work is included in the exhibition because</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">A. it adopts a subjective approach to depicting the landscape.</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 6,</span><span class=\"\"> dòng 7-9:</span><span class=\"\"> &#8220;I was thinking about this tradition of Romantic landscape,</span><span class=\"\"> but </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"93\">I wanted to make it personal</strong><span class=\"\">&#8230;</span><span class=\"\"> bring it to his experience and his world through skateboarding&#8230;</span><span class=\"\">&#8220;</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Tác phẩm video của Gladwell được chọn vì ông không chỉ vẽ phong cảnh khách quan mà đã đưa cái tôi,</span><span class=\"\"> trải nghiệm cá nhân (trượt ván) vào đó.</span><span class=\"\"> Cụm từ &#8220;make it personal&#8221; đồng nghĩa với </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"192\">&#8220;subjective approach&#8221;</strong><span class=\"\"> (cách tiếp cận chủ quan).</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. What was the reason for Soriano including Aboriginal art in the exhibition?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">C. It is part of the Australian art tradition and not independent of it.</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 8,</span><span class=\"\"> dòng 8-10:</span><span class=\"\"> &#8220;&#8230;</span><span class=\"\">I felt it was most accurate to be seen as </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">part of Australian art history, rather than a separate exhibition of its own</strong><span class=\"\">.</span><span class=\"\">&#8220;</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Soriano muốn đưa nghệ thuật thổ dân vào vì bà coi đó là một phần không thể tách rời của dòng chảy lịch sử nghệ thuật Úc,</span><span class=\"\"> chứ không phải một thứ nghệ thuật riêng biệt,</span><span class=\"\"> độc lập.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. By referring to China, Mendelssohn is making the point that</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">A. having an exhibition in London is not as important as it used to be.</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn cuối,</span><span class=\"\"> dòng 2-4:</span><span class=\"\"> &#8220;‘China is the most important art market in the world,</span><span class=\"\">’ she says.</span><span class=\"\"> ‘&#8230;</span><span class=\"\">My students&#8230;</span><span class=\"\"> are </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"121\">less interested in going to London</strong><span class=\"\">.</span><span class=\"\">’&#8221;</span></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc nhắc đến Trung Quốc (Thượng Hải) như một thị trường nghệ thuật hàng đầu thế giới là để chứng minh rằng London không còn là &#8220;trung tâm vũ trụ&#8221; của nghệ thuật như ngày xưa nữa. Tầm quan trọng của việc triển lãm tại London đã suy giảm.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('395d841d-cf72-42f2-889a-c18f7294321a', 'c2b0c6b9-a53e-4cf0-8128-076ce9f9476b', 'checkbox', 'Questions 27-28', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>letters, A–E.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO </strong>things will Laura explain in her covering letter to participants?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "A. when the questionnaire should be completed", "correct": false}, {"option": "B. the fact that participation in the survey is voluntary", "correct": false}, {"option": "C. how long the questionnaire is likely to take", "correct": true}, {"option": "D. the purpose of the survey", "correct": true}, {"option": "E. the benefits of participation in the survey", "correct": false}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('40199947-8587-46cf-92dd-053ff4757778', 'a2fc85b3-b816-486d-bafb-f4627ad93312', 'radio', ' Questions 1–6', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>YES </strong>if the statement agrees with the claims of the writer, choose <strong>NO</strong> if the statement contradicts the claims of the writer, or <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "There is still doubt about the theory that an asteroid strike killed the dinosaurs."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Books and the cinema exaggerate the size of the dinosaurs."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Other scientists have rejected Olsen’s idea of a sudden dinosaur occupation of the Earth."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Dinosaur footprints are found more frequently than dinosaur skeletons."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Ichnotaxa offer an exact identification of a dinosaur species."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "There is evidence that some groups of dinosaur survived from the Triassic period into the Jurassic period."}]', NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"4\">Câu 1</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">NO</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Everybody knows that the dinosaurs were killed by an asteroid… There is thus a nice, if ironic, symmetry in the idea that a similar impact brought about the dinosaurs’ rise.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả khẳng định “mọi người đều biết” khủng long bị tiêu diệt bởi thiên thạch và đang dùng giả thuyết này làm cơ sở để trình bày về sự trỗi dậy của chúng. Câu hỏi nói “vẫn còn nghi ngờ” (still doubt) là trái ngược với cách đặt vấn đề của tác giả.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"6\">Câu 2</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">NO</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…the monsters realistically depicted in modern books and movies.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả nhận định rằng các cuốn sách và phim hiện đại mô tả khủng long một cách “thực tế” (realistically). Do đó, ý kiến cho rằng sách và phim “phóng đại” (exaggerate) kích thước của chúng là sai so với quan điểm của tác giả.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"8\">Câu 3</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Dr Olsen and his colleagues are not the first to suggest that the dinosaurs inherited the Earth as the result of an asteroid strike.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nói Olsen không phải là người đầu tiên đưa ra giả thuyết này, nhưng không đề cập đến việc các nhà khoa học khác có “bác bỏ” (rejected) ý tưởng về sự chiếm lĩnh Trái Đất đột ngột của ông hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"10\">Câu 4</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">YES</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Dinosaur skeletons are rare. Dinosaur footprints are, however, surprisingly abundant.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản nêu rõ xương (skeletons) thì hiếm, còn dấu chân (footprints) thì lại nhiều một cách đáng ngạc nhiên (abundant). Điều này xác nhận dấu chân được tìm thấy thường xuyên hơn xương.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"12\">Câu 5</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">NO</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“These are recognizable types of the footprint that cannot be matched precisely with the species of animal that left them.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc khẳng định Ichnotaxa là loại dấu chân “không thể được khớp một cách chính xác” (cannot be matched precisely) với loài vật đã để lại chúng. Vì vậy, nói chúng giúp nhận dạng chính xác (exact identification) là sai.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"14\">Câu 6</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">YES</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The findings show that… four march confidently across the boundary into the Jurassic.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Boundary” ở đây là ranh giới giữa kỷ Trias và kỷ Jura. Việc 4 nhóm dấu chân (ichnotaxa) “tiến bước tự tin qua ranh giới” chứng minh có những nhóm khủng long đã sống sót từ kỷ này sang kỷ kia.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5a099db5-ac62-47a8-8b69-fb7b89361e5d', '2f6eb2ea-b58e-4749-b857-d58fe95caf75', 'radio', 'Questions 1-7', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "ln Ancient China, writing was occasionally done on silk."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Coloured paper was invented during the Tang Dynasty."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Papermakers from Samarkand were captured by the Chinese."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Papermaking as a large-scale industry originated in Iran."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Papermaking skills were brought to Europe via North Africa."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "When Gutenberg invented movable type, paper materials were very expensive."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The end of the trade in rags was brought about by the difficulty of transporting them."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1. In Ancient China, writing was occasionally done on silk.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) &#8220;The light material of <strong>silk was sometimes used</strong>, but was normally too expensive to consider.&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản khẳng định lụa (<strong>silk</strong>) <strong>đôi khi được sử dụng</strong> (<strong>sometimes used</strong>) để viết, điều này làm cho nhận định là đúng.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>2. Coloured paper was invented during the Tang Dynasty.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) &#8220;During the Tang Dynasty&#8230; tea was served from baskets with <strong>multi-colored paper cups and paper napkins</strong>&#8230;&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản chỉ nói rằng giấy nhiều màu (<strong>multi-colored paper</strong>) đã được <em>sử dụng</em> trong thời nhà Đường, nhưng <strong>không nói rõ</strong> rằng giấy màu đã được <strong>phát minh</strong> (<strong>invented</strong>) trong thời kỳ này.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>3. Papermakers from Samarkand were captured by the Chinese.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) &#8220;During a battle on the banks of the Tarus river, a <strong>Chinese caravan was captured which happened to include several papermakers</strong>. <strong>They were taken away to Samarkand</strong>&#8230;&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Chính người Trung Quốc (Chinese papermakers) đã bị quân đội Hồi giáo bắt và đưa đến Samarkand, chứ không phải thợ Samarkand bị người Trung Quốc bắt.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>4. Papermaking as a large-scale industry originated in Iran.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 7) &#8220;The rudimentary and laborious process of papermaking was refined and <strong>bulk manufacturing of paper began in Iran</strong>, where they invented a method to make a thicker sheet of paper, which helped <strong>transform papermaking from an art into an important business</strong>.&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Việc sản xuất hàng loạt (bulk manufacturing / large-scale industry) và chuyển đổi thành ngành kinh doanh quan trọng bắt đầu ở Iran.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>5. Papermaking skills were brought to Europe via North Africa.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 7) &#8220;Finally, when the <strong>Moors from North Africa invaded Spain and Portugal they brought the technology with them</strong> and so it was that papermaking entered Europe in the 12th century.&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Công nghệ làm giấy đã đến châu Âu thông qua người Moor từ Bắc Phi.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>6. When Gutenberg invented movable type, paper materials were very expensive.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 8) Văn bản nói rằng <strong>da cừu</strong> (parchment) là vật liệu được ưa chuộng trước đó và rất đắt, nhưng <strong>không đề cập</strong> đến việc nguyên liệu làm giấy (như giẻ rách) có đắt vào thời Gutenberg hay không.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>7. The end of the trade in rags was brought about by the difficulty of transporting them.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 9) &#8220;The early European papers were made from recycled cotton and linen – and a huge trade quickly developed around the trading of old rags&#8230; Yet <strong>soon this source became insufficient</strong> and some curious attempts were made to find new materials.&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Nguồn cung cấp giẻ rách không còn <strong>đủ</strong> (insufficient), chứ không phải do khó khăn trong vận chuyển (difficulty of transporting), nên nhận định là sai.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('2ce7f794-a82d-4573-944d-154f4edb1757', 'c2b0c6b9-a53e-4cf0-8128-076ce9f9476b', 'checkbox', 'Questions 29-30', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>letters, A–E.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO </strong>activities does Laura already have definite dates for?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', 'null', '[{"option": "A. completion of her finished assignment", "correct": true}, {"option": "B. questionnaire distribution", "correct": false}, {"option": "C. collection of completed questionnaires", "correct": false}, {"option": "D. the next meeting with her tutor", "correct": true}, {"option": "E. analysis of figures from the company’s database", "correct": false}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 3);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('1590fcbb-38d4-4fb1-8b09-4718b72df252', '3d9e8e2d-6041-4585-af3b-1e7799514d54', 'matching', 'Questions 37 – 40', '', '<p>Complete each sentence with the correct ending, A-F.</p>', 'matching_sentence_endings', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": "", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "reflects the mood created by the natural environment"}, {"optionText": "demonstrates that the dominant art form in Australia is landscape painting"}, {"optionText": "demonstrates an understanding of the historical importance of the land"}, {"optionText": "showcases a very small number of artists"}, {"optionText": "demonstrates a strong European flavour"}, {"optionText": "shows an acceptance of the unique qualities of Australian art"}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "In spite of its conservatism, the Royal Academy exhibition", "correctAnswer": "F"}, {"questionPart": "Australian art of the early to mid-1800s", "correctAnswer": "E"}, {"questionPart": "The modern work by Gladwell chosen for the exhibition", "correctAnswer": "B"}, {"questionPart": "Including Aboriginal art in the exhibition", "correctAnswer": "C"}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. In spite of its conservatism, the Royal Academy exhibition…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: F. shows an acceptance of the unique qualities of Australian art.</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong><span class=\"\"> “…</span><span class=\"\">the Academy is nevertheless </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">embracing the peculiarities</strong><span class=\"\"> (unique qualities) of Australian art from the mid-19th century onward…</span><span class=\"\">“</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Mặc dù bị chỉ trích là bảo thủ (conservative) khi chỉ chọn chủ đề phong cảnh,</span><span class=\"\"> triển lãm vẫn được ghi nhận là đã chấp nhận và tôn vinh những nét đặc thù,</span><span class=\"\"> riêng biệt (peculiarities) của nghệ thuật Úc.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. Australian art of the early to mid-1800s…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: E. demonstrates a strong European flavour.</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong><span class=\"\"> “Certainly the </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"35\">influence of English, French or German art</strong><span class=\"\"> is much more evident in the early periods,</span><span class=\"\"> in the early 1800s to mid-1800s…</span><span class=\"\">“</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Trong giai đoạn đầu đến giữa thế kỷ 19,</span><span class=\"\"> nghệ thuật Úc chịu ảnh hưởng nặng nề từ các trường phái hội họa của Anh,</span><span class=\"\"> Pháp và Đức,</span><span class=\"\"> tạo nên một “phong vị Châu Âu” (European flavour) đậm nét.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. The modern work by Gladwell chosen for the exhibition…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: A. reflects the mood created by the natural environment.</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong><span class=\"\"> “…</span><span class=\"\">I was interested in Turner and the idea of </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">atmosphere affecting vision</strong><span class=\"\">…</span><span class=\"\"> I was thinking about this tradition of </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"137\">Romantic landscape</strong><span class=\"\">…</span><span class=\"\">“</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Tác phẩm của Gladwell lấy cảm hứng từ trường phái Lãng mạn (Romanticism),</span><span class=\"\"> vốn tập trung vào việc thể hiện cảm xúc và bầu không khí (mood/atmosphere) do thiên nhiên tạo ra.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. Including Aboriginal art in the exhibition…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: C. demonstrates an understanding of the historical importance of the land.</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 8):</strong><span class=\"\"> “One of the reasons landscape was seen as being the right theme was because </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"96\">Australian art started in and on the landscape</strong><span class=\"\">.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Việc đưa nghệ thuật thổ dân vào triển lãm với chủ đề phong cảnh cho thấy Ban tổ chức hiểu rằng gốc rễ của nghệ thuật Úc gắn liền với vùng đất (land) ngay từ những ngày đầu tiên.</span></li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('af36ad23-f280-4089-a104-9af3e03a62f9', '18276fc2-3e8f-4401-bba5-2e4cdd2d7122', 'matching', 'Questions 37–40', '', '<p data-start="21" data-end="82">Complete the summary using the list of words, <strong data-start="67" data-end="74">A–J</strong>, below.</p>
<p data-start="84" data-end="159">Write the correct letter, <strong data-start="110" data-end="117">A–J</strong></p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p style=\"text-align: center;\" data-section-id=\"vyunwp\" data-start=\"161\" data-end=\"183\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>The mask experiment</strong></span></p>\n<p data-start=\"185\" data-end=\"720\">In this experiment, having looked at the front of a simple face-mask, subjects look at the reverse. However, the subjects are convinced that they are still looking at a mask which is {G convex} in shape. They believe that the {F nose} is poking out in the normal manner because that is what they are used to seeing. Attempting to make a {I drawing} of the mask in this orientation leads to the same problem. The subjects fail to see a concave form because of the {J preconception} they have that the features of a face stick out.</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A back"}, {"optionText": "B brain"}, {"optionText": "C view"}, {"optionText": "D round"}, {"optionText": "E sight"}, {"optionText": "F nose"}, {"optionText": "G convex"}, {"optionText": "H hollow"}, {"optionText": "I drawing"}, {"optionText": "J preconception"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. G (convex)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"30\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“From the front it is a convex shape with one nose sticking out.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Khi lật mặt sau lõm của mặt nạ, bộ não của người xem bị đánh lừa và họ tin rằng mình vẫn đang nhìn thấy một hình dạng lồi (<strong data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"135\">convex</strong>) giống như mặt trước.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. F (nose)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"32\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“From the front it is a convex shape with one nose sticking out.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Poking out\" (nhô ra) đồng nghĩa với \"sticking out\". Du khách bị thuyết phục rằng chiếc mũi (<strong data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"105\">nose</strong>) vẫn đang nhô ra ngoài một cách bình thường.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. I (drawing)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"34\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"34,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“It is almost, if not quite, impossible to sketch the back of a hollow mask to look as it is — hollow.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Từ khóa \"sketch\" (phác thảo/họa lại) trong bài đọc tương ứng với hành động tạo ra một bản vẽ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"34,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"106\">drawing</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. J (preconception)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"36\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"36,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"36,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"36,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“...even people with no visual impairment see what, at some level, they expect to see...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"36,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"36,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sở dĩ người xem không nhìn ra dạng lõm là vì họ bị chi phối bởi một định kiến, một ý niệm có sẵn trong đầu (<strong data-path-to-node=\"36,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"120\">preconception</strong> / <em data-path-to-node=\"36,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"136\">expect to see</em>) rằng các bộ phận trên khuôn mặt lúc nào cũng phải lồi ra ngoài.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a2fda123-e104-427f-82bd-a902141309ef', 'b6dd2bbc-c2e9-4b68-ba67-2bea2a277e62', 'radio', 'Questions 27-31', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "Too many branches of science have been involved in its study."}, {"content": "The Société de Linguistique de Paris instigated research in this area."}, {"content": "The lack of progress is surprising given the amount of work being done."}, {"content": "Most progress in the study of language was made between 1859 and 1866."}], "question": "In the first paragraph, what does the writer suggest about the origin of language?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "Some current theories are based on conflicting evidence."}, {"content": "There is insufficient fossil evidence to reach a conclusion."}, {"content": "Fossil evidence suggests that Homo sapiens had larger brains than Neanderthals."}, {"content": "Archaeological evidence shows that Neanderthals were able to talk."}], "question": "What is ‘the problem’ referred to in the second paragraph?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "Modern theorists should pay more attention to his approach."}, {"content": "His ideas supported those of the Société de Linguistique de Paris."}, {"content": "His ideas were mirrored in a later book called Language Evolution."}, {"content": "His ideas are too outdated to be of any relevance today."}], "question": "What does the writer suggest about Jean-Jacques Rousseau’s work in 1781?"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "They have had little impact on the study of language."}, {"content": "They have helped the study of linguistics to progress."}, {"content": "They are not accepted by the majority of linguists."}, {"content": "The assumption behind them is wrong."}], "question": "What is the writer’s current view of Derek Bickerton’s ideas?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "grammar and meaning."}, {"content": "messages and proto-language."}, {"content": "language, music and emotions."}, {"content": "proto-language and modern semantics."}], "question": "In the final paragraph, the writer concludes that Alison Wray’s ideas will help establish a link between:"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"1\">Câu 27: C (The lack of progress is surprising given the amount of work being done)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 1, dòng cuối.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “And yet, despite almost frenzied activity, limited progress has been made.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả sử dụng cụm từ <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"35\">“frenzied activity”</strong> (hoạt động điên cuồng/náo nhiệt) để chỉ khối lượng công việc khổng lồ đang được thực hiện, nhưng kết quả thu lại là <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"171\">“limited progress”</strong> (tiến bộ hạn chế). Điều này ngụ ý rằng sự thiếu hụt tiến bộ là một điều đáng ngạc nhiên so với nỗ lực bỏ ra.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\">Câu 28: A (Some current theories are based on conflicting evidence)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 2, dòng 4-7.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…fossil evidence indicates that the Neanderthals had larger brains… but archaeological evidence indicates that the Neanderthals lacked a capacity for language.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Vấn đề” được nhắc đến là sự mâu thuẫn giữa hai loại bằng chứng: hóa thạch (fossil) cho thấy não người Neanderthal lớn hơn, nhưng khảo cổ (archaeological) lại cho thấy họ không có khả năng ngôn ngữ. Sự đối chọi này khiến các giả thuyết dựa trên kích cỡ bộ não trở nên sai lệch.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">Câu 29: A (Modern theorists should pay more attention to his approach)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 4, dòng cuối.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Those authors have an important lesson to learn from Rousseau and other writers of his time who addressed the origin of language.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả phê phán các nhà nghiên cứu hiện đại (như Christiansen và Kirby) vì đã bỏ qua âm nhạc. Ông khẳng định họ có một “bài học quan trọng” (important lesson) cần học từ cách tiếp cận của Rousseau — người đã xem xét cả âm nhạc và ngôn ngữ một cách gắn liền.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">Câu 30: D (The assumption behind them is wrong)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 7, dòng 4-5 và dòng cuối.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “But Bickerton’s idea… is, I believe, fundamentally mistaken. …I now understand that it is not only flawed but has severely limited the progress…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả trực tiếp phủ nhận quan điểm của Bickerton (cho rằng tiền ngôn ngữ là các từ rời rạc ghép lại). Ông khẳng định ý tưởng này là <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"146\">“fundamentally mistaken”</strong> (sai lầm từ căn bản) và <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"195\">“flawed”</strong> (có lỗ hổng/sai sót).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">Câu 31: C (language, music and emotions)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn cuối, câu cuối cùng.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “I believe this insight enables us to understand the origin of music as well as language, and to relate both to the emotional lives of our human ancestors.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả kết luận rằng lý thuyết của Alison Wray không chỉ giúp hiểu về ngôn ngữ và âm nhạc mà còn kết nối cả hai với đời sống cảm xúc (emotional lives) của tổ tiên loài người.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('4c80daff-9efc-4106-9b64-cfa343251dd1', 'd99087c2-5edf-4d31-9c1a-e869b405820d', 'radio', 'Questions 27-29', '', '<p data-path-to-node="2">Choose the correct letter <strong data-path-to-node="2" data-index-in-node="26">A</strong>, <strong data-path-to-node="2" data-index-in-node="29">B</strong>, <strong data-path-to-node="2" data-index-in-node="32">C</strong> or <strong data-path-to-node="2" data-index-in-node="37">D</strong>.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="3">Write the correct answer in boxes 27–29 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A Children are portrayed as adults see them."}, {"option_text": "B Children are unable to write their own stories."}, {"option_text": "C Adults fail to stimulate children’s imaginations."}, {"option_text": "D Adult literature is too difficult for children."}], "question": "Which of the following best summarises the writer’s argument in the second paragraph?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A the quality of the writing"}, {"option_text": "B the imaginative content of stories"}, {"option_text": "C the instructive nature of children’s books."}, {"option_text": "D the way children are written about in stories"}], "question": "In the third paragraph, what does the writer say is the main interest of some people who study children''s literature?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A demonstrate that academics consider computer games to be a logical extension of children’s literature."}, {"option_text": "B explore the impact of computers on the boundaries of children’s literature."}, {"option_text": "C illustrate that literature and computer games have different origins."}, {"option_text": "D prove that children are using computers more than they are reading literature."}], "question": "The main point of the writer’s argument in the fifth paragraph is to"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"1\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"1\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. Which of the following best summarises the writer’s argument in the second paragraph?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: A. Children are portrayed as adults see them.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Paragraph B):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">“But I think we should also take children’s literature seriously because it is sometimes <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"114\">subversive</strong>: because its values are <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"149\">not always those of the conventional adult world</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả lập luận rằng văn học thiếu nhi mang tính “đối nghịch” (subversive) vì nó đưa ra những giá trị khác với thế giới “quy ước” của người lớn (conventional adult world). Điều này ngụ ý rằng hình ảnh trẻ em trong sách là một <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"239\">sự khắc họa (portrayal)</strong> có chủ đích từ góc nhìn của người lớn nhằm phản chiếu hoặc đối lập với thực tại của họ, chứ không phải là bản thể tự nhiên của trẻ em.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. In the third paragraph, what does the writer say is the main interest of some people who study children’s literature?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: C. the instructive nature of children’s books.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Paragraph C):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">“They mock current assumptions and express the imaginative… view of the world in its simplest and purest form. They… <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"146\">act as a force for change</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"19\">“act as a force for change”</strong> (đóng vai trò như một lực lượng thúc đẩy sự thay đổi) cho thấy những người nghiên cứu quan tâm đến cách sách thiếu nhi tác động, định hướng tư duy hoặc giáo dục (<strong data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"209\">instructive</strong>) đứa trẻ. Việc “nhạo báng các giả định hiện tại” (mock current assumptions) cũng là một hình thức giáo huấn để thay đổi nhận thức của thế hệ trẻ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. The main point of the writer’s argument in the fifth paragraph is to</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: B. explore the impact of computers on the boundaries of children’s literature.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án thay thế dựa trên văn bản thực tế:</strong> Nếu đoạn 5 tập trung vào sự thay đổi của nhân vật, điểm chính là <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"107\">i. Optimistic beliefs held by the writers of children’s literature.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Paragraph E – Đoạn 5 của bài):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">“It is assumed that the world of childhood is <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"88\">simpler and more natural</strong> than that of adults, and that children… are <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"159\">essentially good</strong> or at least <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"188\">capable of becoming so</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,3,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả nhấn mạnh vào “niềm tin lạc quan” (optimistic beliefs) của các nhà văn rằng trẻ em về bản chất là tốt (<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"123\">essentially good</strong>). Tác giả dùng ví dụ về Mary và Colin trong <em data-path-to-node=\"6,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"184\">The Secret Garden</em> để minh họa cho sự chuyển biến tích cực (transformation), củng cố luận điểm rằng văn học thiếu nhi luôn duy trì niềm tin vào sự hoàn thiện của con người.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('77b5f8d4-c20b-433b-a734-0d341e556100', 'aa8132aa-4cfc-4f48-9552-a816e6b5e417', 'matrix', 'Questions 1-6', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answers from the options given.</p>
<p>NB You may use any letter more than once.</p>
', 'other', NULL, NULL, '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "very expensive", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "a food flavouring", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "used as currency", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "sweet-smelling", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "referred to by Herman Melville", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "can be seen through", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "ambergris only", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "amber only", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "both ambergris and amber", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "neither ambergris nor amber", "categoryLetter": "D"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"1\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"1\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. Very expensive (Rất đắt đỏ)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2\">\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: C (Both ambergris and amber)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> * &#8220;ambergris was worth its <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">weight in gold</strong>&#8221; (Đoạn 1).</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2,1,1\">\n<li>\n<p>&#8220;<strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"1\">Both substances were rare costly</strong>, and both were associated with the sea&#8221; (Đoạn 2).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc sử dụng các cụm từ &#8220;đắt ngang vàng&#8221; cho long diên hương và &#8220;cả hai đều đắt đỏ, quý hiếm&#8221; để khẳng định giá trị kinh tế cao của cả hai chất này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. A food flavouring (Gia vị thực phẩm)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: A (Ambergris only)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;was widely used as a <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"33\">spice</strong>, which was believed to be an aphrodisiac when added to <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">food or wine</strong>&#8221; (Đoạn 1).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Long diên hương được ghi nhận là một loại gia vị (spice) dùng cho thức ăn và rượu. Ngược lại, hổ phách (amber) được mô tả là nhựa cây hóa thạch, cứng và không có thông tin nào nói về việc dùng làm thực phẩm.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. Used as currency (Được dùng làm tiền tệ)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: D (Neither ambergris nor amber)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">Không có đoạn văn nào chứa thông tin này.</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Mặc dù cả hai đều rất đắt tiền (costly), nhưng bài đọc không hề nhắc đến việc chúng được sử dụng như một loại tiền tệ (currency) để thanh toán hay trao đổi hàng hóa thay cho tiền.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. Sweet-smelling (Có mùi thơm)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: A (Ambergris only)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> * <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"13\">Ambergris:</strong> &#8220;Ambergris itself is <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"45\">pleasantly aromatic</strong>&#8221; (Đoạn 1) và &#8220;ambergris is&#8230; so <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"98\">highly fragrant</strong> that it is largely used in perfumery&#8221; (Đoạn 2).</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8,1,1\">\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Amber:</strong> &#8220;amber is a hard, transparent, brittle, <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">odorless</strong> substance&#8221; (Đoạn 2).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc tạo ra sự đối lập rõ rệt: long diên hương rất thơm (fragrant) và dùng làm nước hoa, trong khi hổ phách hoàn toàn không có mùi (odorless).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. Referred to by Herman Melville (Được Herman Melville nhắc đến)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: C (Both ambergris and amber)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;In Chapter 92 of Moby Dick, the American writer <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">Herman Melville</strong> pours scorn on those who believed the <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"114\">two substances to be the same</strong>: ‘Though the word <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"162\">ambergris</strong> is but the French compound for grey <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"208\">amber</strong>. Yet the two substances are quite distinct.’&#8221; (Đoạn 2).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả trích dẫn lời của Melville trong tiểu thuyết <em data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">Moby Dick</em>, nơi ông đề cập đến cả tên gọi và sự khác biệt giữa long diên hương và hổ phách để tránh nhầm lẫn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. Can be seen through (Có thể nhìn xuyên qua)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: B (Amber only)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;amber is a hard, <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">transparent</strong>, brittle, odorless substance&#8221; (Đoạn 2).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Từ &#8220;transparent&#8221; (trong suốt) có nghĩa là có thể nhìn xuyên qua được. Đây là đặc điểm của hổ phách. Long diên hương được mô tả là sáp (waxy) và màu xám (grey), nghĩa là nó đục và không thể nhìn xuyên qua.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('1885cce2-0c3a-4cf3-b834-ac1694f07f1a', '7eaca0a7-fd37-47b7-b98d-64e86580db07', 'radio', 'Questions 27-31', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "how hot the area is."}, {"content": "how warm the water is."}, {"content": "how many dental problems there are in the community."}, {"content": "how much fluorine the community chooses to have in its water."}], "question": "The optimum amount of fluorine in fluoridated water is calculated partly according to"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "it may contribute to tooth decay."}, {"content": "it will be unacceptably expensive for the public."}, {"content": "obligatory fluoridation takes away personal freedom."}, {"content": "excessive fluoride could be added to the water by mistake."}], "question": "One reason given by the writer for opposing fluoridation is that"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "provide a contrast with the view of Collins"}, {"content": "support the rational nature of scientific inquiry."}, {"content": "demonstrate that Kuhn did not argue his case adequately"}, {"content": "show that science can be influenced by non-scientific considerations"}], "question": "The writer mentions Kuhn in order to"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "There were failings in the way they were carried out."}, {"content": "The scientists involved had achieved unique results."}, {"content": "Proponents of fluoridation had not understood its long-term effects."}, {"content": "Fluoridation had a greater effect on tooth decay than previously believed."}], "question": "What did Sutton’s research discover about earlier studies in North America?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "They should reveal their true motivations."}, {"content": "They should not decide the fluoridation policy."}, {"content": "They are solely concerned with scientific truths."}, {"content": "They cannot reach agreement on the fluoridation issue."}], "question": " In the last paragraph, what does the writer say about scientists?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>27. The optimum amount of fluorine in fluoridated water is calculated partly according to</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>how hot the area is.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 1) “The desired concentration of fluoride in public water is approximately one part per million, depending on the <strong>regional temperature</strong> and hence the amount of water people are likely to drink.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Nồng độ fluoride tối ưu phụ thuộc vào nhiệt độ khu vực (regional temperature), vì nhiệt độ ảnh hưởng đến lượng nước mà mọi người uống.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>28. One reason given by the writer for opposing fluoridation is that</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>obligatory fluoridation takes away personal freedom.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) “Third, fluoridation is thought to be an <strong>infringement on individual rights</strong> because it is <strong>compulsory medication</strong> of all members of a community.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Việc fluoride hóa bắt buộc (compulsory/obligatory) bị coi là vi phạm quyền cá nhân (infringement on individual rights/takes away personal freedom).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>29. The writer mentions Kuhn in order to</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>show that science can be influenced by non-scientific considerations.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “According to Kuhn, the shift from one scientific way of thinking to another is not made solely on the basis of clear rules of formal scientific practice, but <strong>can include social factors</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả dùng Kuhn để minh họa rằng sự thay đổi trong khoa học không chỉ dựa vào quy tắc khoa học mà còn có thể bao gồm các yếu tố xã hội (social factors/non-scientific considerations).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>30. What did Sutton’s research discover about earlier studies in North America?</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>There were failings in the way they were carried out.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 7) “An example is the study by Sutton in 1960, which analyzed the classic North American studies… and found that <strong>each showed significant methodological shortcomings</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Sutton tìm thấy những thiếu sót đáng kể về mặt phương pháp (methodological shortcomings/failings in the way they were carried out) trong các nghiên cứu trước đó.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 data-path-to-node=\"22\">31. In the last paragraph, what does the writer say about scientists?</h4>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"23\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>They should not decide the fluoridation policy.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 9) &#8220;&#8230;social values are likely to be bound up in any decision about fluoridation, so this is not an issue on which <strong>declarations by scientific experts ought to be considered the final word</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả kết luận rằng ý kiến của các chuyên gia khoa học không nên được coi là lời cuối cùng, ngụ ý rằng họ <strong>không nên độc quyền quyết định</strong> chính sách fluoride hóa.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('dd098e48-f0e4-48ad-ba24-e0696b6c2111', '652856bb-c3e1-4e38-9de6-fb88373bd126', 'fillup', 'Questions 21-27', '<p>Complete the notes below.<br />Write <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 70.6134%; height: 290.906px; border-width: 2px;" border="1">
<colgroup>
<col style="width: 100%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 290.906px;">
<td style="border-width: 2px;">
<h2 class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 108pt; text-indent: 36pt; line-height: 115%;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><strong><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">Whale Survey</span></strong></span></h2>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 115%; padding-left: 40px;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><strong><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">Considerations:</span></strong></span></p>
<ul>
<li style="list-style-type: none;">
<ul type="disc">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">The </span><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">{watching time} </span>should be carefully chosen.</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">State of the sea: {calm} or choppy.</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">And state of {weather}</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">Visibility: {100 metres | 100 meters}.</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">Details in need of attention: the appearance of {fishing boat| fishing boats}</span></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 115%; padding-left: 40px;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><strong><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">Need to evaluate or identify:</span></strong></span></p>
<ul>
<li style="list-style-type: none;">
<ul type="disc">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">The{ individual behaviours|individual behaviors| behaviours| behaviors| behaviour| behavior } and appearance of whales.</span></li>
<li class="MsoNormal" style="line-height: 115%; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">Scales: the {group size} and species, the possible age etc.</span></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>KAREN: Hi Dave.<br />Chào Dave.</p>\n<p>DAVE: As you know, I’ve asked you to come here today to discuss the assignment for our biology class.<br />Như bạn biết đấy, hôm nay mình hẹn bạn đến để bàn về bài tập của lớp sinh học.</p>\n<p>KAREN: We must decide what we should do about this very important research work — the whale survey.<br />Chúng ta phải quyết định cách thực hiện dự án nghiên cứu quan trọng này — khảo sát cá voi.</p>\n<p>DAVE: Yeah, I was also hoping to share some ideas with you. So let’s start, okay?<br />Ừ, mình cũng muốn chia sẻ vài ý tưởng với bạn. Bắt đầu nhé?</p>\n<p>KAREN: I’ve dug into some journal articles to see what sort of questions we should consider.<br />Mình đã đọc một số bài nghiên cứu để xem ta nên cân nhắc những yếu tố nào.</p>\n<p>DAVE: Most of them include watching time and strongly urge it to be the top concern. What do you say?<br />Hầu hết đều nói rằng thời gian quan sát là yếu tố quan trọng nhất. Bạn nghĩ sao?</p>\n<p>KAREN: (21) The watching time should be carefully chosen, since I’ve heard of a lot of unnecessary failures caused by picking the wrong time — when it was stormy and murky and nothing was seen during the whole field trip.<br />Thời gian quan sát phải được chọn kỹ, vì nhiều nhóm thất bại do chọn sai thời điểm — gặp bão, nước đục, và chẳng thấy gì trong suốt chuyến khảo sát.</p>\n<p>DAVE: I mean, they could have avoided that easily, right?<br />Lẽ ra họ có thể tránh được điều đó dễ dàng.</p>\n<p>KAREN: Then we should also pay close attention to the sea’s surface because no one wants to encounter those problems again.<br />Ngoài ra ta cũng nên chú ý đến mặt biển vì chẳng ai muốn lặp lại thất bại đó.</p>\n<p>DAVE: I think we’d better hope for the best — that it will be (22) calm with no choppy status.<br />Hy vọng biển sẽ lặng, không nổi sóng.</p>\n<p>KAREN: What about the (23) weather conditions?<br />Còn thời tiết thì sao?</p>\n<p>DAVE: That definitely should be taken into account, as it correlates with all the former factors.<br />Chắc chắn phải xem xét, vì nó ảnh hưởng đến mọi yếu tố trên.</p>\n<p>KAREN: Most important of all, as a sighting is made, position and environmental parameters are recorded on standardized formats — including time, (24) visibility, position of the ship using GPS, wind speed, and direction.<br />Điều quan trọng nhất là khi phát hiện cá voi, phải ghi lại các thông số môi trường — gồm thời gian, tầm nhìn, vị trí tàu bằng GPS, tốc độ và hướng gió.</p>\n<p>DAVE: Shouldn’t there be a set limit for the visibility level, say 50 meters?<br />Có nên đặt giới hạn cho tầm nhìn không, ví dụ 50 mét?</p>\n<p>KAREN: Cetaceans are really sensitive to sound — they’ll hide to avoid danger. So let’s make it 100 meters.<br />Cá voi rất nhạy cảm với âm thanh — chúng sẽ ẩn nấp nếu thấy nguy hiểm. Vậy ta nên đặt mức 100 mét.</p>\n<p>DAVE: That might be better. Oh, in that case, we’d also need to pay attention to the appearance of (25) fishing boats — you know, for all the noise they make.<br />Ừ, vậy tốt hơn. À, ta cũng nên chú ý đến tàu đánh cá, vì tiếng ồn của chúng ảnh hưởng lớn.</p>\n<p>KAREN: That’s right. Although observations were regularly made, we know very little about whale vocalization and how they use sound socially.<br />Đúng rồi. Dù đã quan sát thường xuyên, ta vẫn biết rất ít về âm thanh và giao tiếp của cá voi.</p>\n<p>DAVE: So to understand marine mammals’ social interactions, we’ll need to use passive acoustic recordings to track and assess the (26) behaviour of whales as well as to identify their appearance.<br />Vì vậy, để hiểu rõ cách cá voi giao tiếp, ta cần ghi âm thụ động để theo dõi hành vi và nhận dạng chúng.</p>\n<p>KAREN: Okay then, what about scales?<br />Vậy còn quy mô thì sao?</p>\n<p>DAVE: Oh, for each sighting, the number of animals should be counted — the (27) group size, I mean. Also, we need to identify the species, possible age, and sex of the individuals.<br />Với mỗi lần quan sát, phải đếm số lượng cá thể — tức là quy mô đàn, và xác định loài, tuổi, giới tính của chúng.</p>\n<p> <br />(28) Speaking of identifying species, we need to find out the unique physical features of each whale.<br />Nói đến việc nhận dạng loài, ta cần biết đặc điểm cơ thể riêng của từng loại cá voi.</p>\n<p>KAREN: Let’s start with the sperm whale.<br />Bắt đầu với cá nhà táng nhé.</p>\n<p>DAVE: The sperm whale is the largest toothed whale, though only a quarter the size of the blue whale. Its body is unique — a very large, block-shaped head taking up one-third of its length.<br />Cá nhà táng là loài cá voi có răng lớn nhất, thân khối với đầu vuông chiếm 1/3 chiều dài.</p>\n<p>KAREN: So that’s picture (28) B, right?<br />Vậy hình B, đúng không?</p>\n<p>DAVE: Exactly.</p>\n<p> <br />KAREN: Then there’s the northern right whale.<br />Tiếp theo là cá voi trơn phương Bắc.</p>\n<p>DAVE: Right whales have round bodies, V-shaped blowholes, and rough white patches on their heads caused by whale lice. They have no dorsal fin.<br />Cá voi trơn có thân tròn, lỗ thở hình chữ V và các mảng trắng trên đầu do ký sinh. Không có vây lưng.</p>\n<p>KAREN: That must be (29) C.<br />Chắc chắn là hình C rồi.</p>\n<p> <br />DAVE: And finally, the minke whale — small and sleek, black-grey or purple, with a white band on each flipper and a tiny dorsal fin two-thirds down its back.<br />Cuối cùng là cá voi Minke — nhỏ, màu xám đen hoặc tím, có vạch trắng trên vây và vây lưng nhỏ ở 2/3 thân.</p>\n<p>KAREN: That’s (30) A then.<br />Vậy là hình A.</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>Since I’ve heard a lot of unnecessary failures concerning picking the wrong time when it all went stormy and murky.</p>\n<p>And then nothing was seen during the whole field trip. I mean, they could have avoided that easily.</p>\n<p>Right. Then we should also pay close attention to the sea surface because no one wants to encounter the failures you just mentioned.</p>\n<p>I think we’d better hope for the best that it will be <span style=\"color: #e03e2d;\"><strong>calm</strong></span>. With no choppy status.</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>What about the <span style=\"color: #e03e2d;\"><strong>weather </strong></span>conditions?</p>\n<p>That definitely should be taken into account as it correlates with all the form of factors.</p>\n<p>Most important of all, as a sighting is made, position and environmental parameters are recorded on standardized sighting pro formats,</p>\n<p>including time, visibility, position of the ship, using a global positioning system, wind speed and wind direction.</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>Shouldn’t there be a set limit for the visibility level, say 50 meters?</p>\n<p>Citations are really sensitive to sound. They are able to know that something’s coming after them, so they would hide in order to avoid possible danger.</p>\n<p>So let’s make it <span style=\"color: #e03e2d;\"><strong>100 </strong></span>meters, shall we?</p>\n<p>Yeah, that might be better. Oh, in that case, we’d also need to pay attention to the appearance of the fishing boats, you know, for all the noise that they would make.</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>Yeah, that might be better. Oh, in that case, we’d also need to pay attention to the appearance of the <span style=\"color: #e03e2d;\"><strong>fishing boats</strong></span>, you know, for all the noise that they would make.</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>That’s right. Although observations were regularly made, we know very little about whale vocalisation and how they use sound in their behavioural and social interactions.</p>\n<p>So to understand Marine Mammal’s social interactions, we’ll need to use passive acoustic recordings to track and assess the <span style=\"color: #e03e2d;\"><strong>individual behaviours</strong></span> of whales, as well as to identify their appearance.</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>Okay, then what about scales? Oh, for each sighting, the number of animals should be counted, the <span style=\"color: #e03e2d;\"><strong>group size</strong></span>, I mean.</p>\n<p>Also, we need to identify the species, possible age and sex of the individuals.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('de5f703c-31b1-47c7-96f8-1bc4cad1311d', '2fa86bb9-d734-4236-972d-6630e320cf23', 'fillup', 'Questions 31–40', '<div class="flex max-w-full flex-col gap-4 grow">
<div class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal outline-none keyboard-focused:focus-ring [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" dir="auto" tabindex="0" data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="7d01b199-6cad-4546-b4a8-6f7935842d4f" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-5" data-turn-start-message="true">
<div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden">
<div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert wrap-break-word w-full light markdown-new-styling">
<p data-start="71" data-end="134">Complete the notes below<br data-start="95" data-end="98">Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p data-start="136" data-end="153"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Absence from work</span></strong></p>
<p data-start="155" data-end="193">Absence may be frequent or occasional.</p>
<p data-start="195" data-end="216">Main factors involved</p>
<ul data-start="217" data-end="537">
<li data-section-id="1v18ob6" data-start="217" data-end="306">the {gender} of employees (e.g. females are likely to have responsibility for children)</li>
<li data-section-id="305qpw" data-start="307" data-end="363">employees’ {attitude} (but the evidence is inconclusive)</li>
<li data-section-id="l7vot7" data-start="364" data-end="430">the {culture} of the organization (absenteeism may be acceptable)</li>
<li data-section-id="1hjjttk" data-start="431" data-end="494">the type of work (higher absence among employees in {industry})</li>
<li data-section-id="n9nk3l" data-start="495" data-end="537">the {size} of an employee’s work group</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="539" data-end="574">Public sector versus private sector</p>
<p data-start="576" data-end="615">Public sector has higher absence levels</p>
<p data-start="617" data-end="672">Possible explanation-the public sector is less {efficient}</p>
<p data-start="674" data-end="756">Systems may be more bureaucratic because of {external} factors (e.g. state controls)</p>
<p data-start="758" data-end="825">More recent literature suggests public sector organisations usually</p>
<ul data-start="826" data-end="992" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">
<li data-section-id="95gi9b" data-start="826" data-end="853">have a {larger} workforce</li>
<li data-section-id="3d36u6" data-start="854" data-end="897">have more female and more older employees</li>
<li data-section-id="1nan1qv" data-start="898" data-end="952">provide {benefits} for longer, with fewer restrictions</li>
<li data-section-id="gla7mr" data-start="953" data-end="992" data-is-last-node="">are less likely to {dismiss} employees</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="mt-3 w-full empty:hidden">
<div class="text-center">
<div> </div>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 4: ABSENCE FROM WORK</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Speaker:</strong> Hello, everyone. For my assignment, I did a review of the literature concerning absence in the workplace, and I''m going to present a summary of what I found. I looked at some research on absence from work—that is, the number of days'' work people miss for various reasons. Researchers refer to two types of absence: frequent absence, which is obviously a more serious problem, and occasional absence.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">A lot of studies look at the factors involved in absence from work, and several have been identified. Firstly, the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"115\">(Q31) gender</strong></span> of the employee may influence his or her ability to attend work. For example, a female is more likely to have child care responsibility, and so could be absent as a result of that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">The next factor that has been identified is the<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"48\">(Q32) attitude</strong> </span>of employees toward their work. But there has been a lot of debate about the extent to which this actually does influence absence, and some people argue that the research hasn''t been conclusive. Some researchers have suggested that another reason for high levels of absence is that some organisations have a <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"371\">(Q33) culture</strong></span> in which absence is accepted, but others have criticised this model, arguing that it''s too much of a generalisation.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">And then there are factors related to the type of work the employee does. It''s been claimed that workers in <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"108\">(Q34) industry</strong></span> are more likely to have high absence rates than people who work in offices. It''s also important to recognise that groups within a single organisation might behave differently. For example, one of the other underlying themes in the literature is that there is a connection between how often an employee is absent and what <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"444\">(Q35) size</strong></span> of work group he or she belongs to. Specifically, it''s been found that the bigger the group, the higher the levels of absence.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\">On a related theme, some writers have focused on a comparison between public sector organisations and private sector ones. There is some evidence that absence levels are higher in the public sector. It''s not exactly clear why this should be the case, but one explanation that has been often put forwards is that in some cases, public sector organisations may not be as<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"369\">(Q36) efficient</strong></span>. This might be because their systems are more bureaucratic due to factors which are <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"469\">(Q37) external</strong> </span>rather than internal, like the degree of control the government imposes on the public sector.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">However, most recent literature suggests a number of other explanations. Firstly, a public sector organisation tends to have a workforce which is <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"146\">(Q38) larger</strong></span>. Also, it tends to employ a higher number of female and older employees, both of which groups are likely to record higher absence rates. It is also suggested that public sector organisations are more likely to give their absent employees <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"397\">(Q39) benefits</strong></span> for a longer period and are less likely to place restrictions on these. In addition, it''s been found that public sector employers have less of a tendency to <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"569\">(Q40) dismiss</strong></span> employees for being absent. And all of these could be additional or alternative reasons for higher absence rates in the public sector.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\">Now, I''d like to talk about the management of absence...</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('3a01f17e-ca08-4071-b507-fabc81acf1a5', '547c171f-e381-4add-85b1-47cc2bee568a', 'radio', 'Questions 1-6', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The name Katherine Mansfield, that appears on the writer’s book, was exactly the same as her origin name"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Mansfield won a prize for a story she wrote for the High School Reporter."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "How Pearl Button Was Kidnapped portrayed Maori people in a favorable way."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "When Mansfield was at Queen’s college, she planned to be a professional writer."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Mansfield was unpopular with the other students at Queen’s college"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "In London, Mansfield showed little interest in politics."}]', NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. The name Katherine Mansfield, that appears on the writer’s book, was exactly the same as her origin name.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 1,</span><span class=\"\"> dòng 1-3:</span><span class=\"\"> “Katherine Mansfield </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">Beauchamp Murry</strong><span class=\"\"> was born…</span><span class=\"\"> using the </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"88\">pen name</strong><span class=\"\"> of Katherine Mansfield.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Tên thật của bà có thêm họ “Beauchamp Murry”.</span><span class=\"\"> Katherine Mansfield chỉ là bút danh (</span><em class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"95\">pen name</em><span class=\"\">).</span><span class=\"\"> Vì vậy,</span><span class=\"\"> tên trên sách không “giống hệt” (</span><em class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"147\">exactly the same</em><span class=\"\">) tên khai sinh.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. Mansfield won a prize for a story she wrote for the High School Reporter.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 2,</span><span class=\"\"> dòng 1-2:</span><span class=\"\"> “Her first published stories appeared in the High Sotho Reporter and the Wellington Girls High School magazine…</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Bài đọc chỉ nói bà có truyện được </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"46\">đăng</strong><span class=\"\"> (</span><em class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">published</em><span class=\"\">) trên tờ báo này,</span><span class=\"\"> tuyệt nhiên không nhắc đến việc bà có được giải thưởng (</span><em class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"136\">prize</em><span class=\"\">) nào hay không.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. How Pearl Button Was Kidnapped portrayed Maori people in a favorable way.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 2,</span><span class=\"\"> dòng cuối:</span><span class=\"\"> “…</span><span class=\"\">interest in the Maori people…</span><span class=\"\"> who were often portrayed in a </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"96\">sympathetic light</strong><span class=\"\"> in her later stories,</span><span class=\"\"> such as How Pearl Button Was Kidnapped.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Cụm từ “in a sympathetic light” (dưới góc nhìn đồng cảm/đáng mến) đồng nghĩa với “in a favorable way” (một cách thuận lợi/tốt đẹp).</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. When Mansfield was at Queen’s college, she planned to be a professional writer.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 3,</span><span class=\"\"> dòng 2-4:</span><span class=\"\"> “Mansfield recommended playing the cello,</span><span class=\"\"> an occupation that she believed,</span><span class=\"\"> during her time at Queens,</span><span class=\"\"> she would </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"141\">take up professionally</strong><span class=\"\">.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Trong thời gian học tại Queen’s College,</span><span class=\"\"> dự định nghề nghiệp của bà là trở thành một </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"97\">nghệ sĩ Cello chuyên nghiệp</strong><span class=\"\">,</span><span class=\"\"> không phải nhà văn.</span> Mãi đến năm 1906 (đoạn 4), bà mới quyết tâm trở thành người viết lách chuyên nghiệp.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. Mansfield was unpopular with the other students at Queen’s college.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 3, dòng 7-8: “…she was <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"41\">appreciated</strong> amongst fellow students at Queens for her lively and charismatic approach…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc được bạn bè cùng trường “trân trọng” (<em data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"55\">appreciated</em>) và có lối sống “lôi cuốn” (<em data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"95\">charismatic</em>) chứng tỏ bà rất được yêu mến, trái ngược với từ “unpopular” (không được lòng mọi người).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. In London, Mansfield showed little interest in politics.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 3, dòng 10-12: “Mansfield <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">did not become involved in much political activity</strong> when she lived in London… did not actively support the suffragette movement…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc không tham gia nhiều vào các hoạt động chính trị và không ủng hộ phong trào đòi quyền bầu cử của phụ nữ xác nhận bà “ít quan tâm đến chính trị” (<em data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"162\">showed little interest</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f07b179b-2ac8-4e04-8efc-db3910dfc3d4', '652856bb-c3e1-4e38-9de6-fb88373bd126', 'matrix', 'Questions 28-30', '<p>Match the following type of whales with the pictures given according to different feature descriptions. Write the correct letter, A-D, next to Questions </p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," width="619" height="296" loading="lazy"></p>
', '<p>Match the following type of whales with the pictures given according to different feature descriptions. Choose the correct letter, A-D, next to Questions</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," width="564" height="270" /></p>
', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Sperm whale", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": " Northern right whale ", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Minke whale", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}]}', '[{"content": "<p>Speaking of identifying species, we need to find out the unique physical features of each whale.</p>\n<p>Let’s start with the sperm whale. The sperm whale is the largest toothed whale, yet it’s only a quarter of that of the blue whale.</p>\n<p>Its unique body is unlikely to be confused with any other species, and that distinctive shape comes from its very large, block-shaped head, which can be one quarter of the species.</p>\n<p>It can be one quarter to one third of its length. The sperm whale’s flukes are triangular and very thick.</p>\n<p>It has a series of little bumps on the back of its fluke, instead of having a dorsal fin.</p>\n<p>The largest bump is called the hump by whalers, and can be mistaken for a dorsal fin because of its shape and size.</p>\n<p>Then, there is the northern right whale. Right whales have round bodies with arching rostrums, V-shaped blowholes and dark grey or black skin.</p>\n<p>The most distinguishing feature of a right whale is the rough patches of skin on its head, which appear white due to parasitism by whale lice.</p>\n<p>It has no back fins at all. The blue whale’s body can be various shades of bluish grey dorsily, and somewhat lighter underneath.</p>\n<p>It has a long, tapering body that appears stretched in comparison to the stockier build of other whales.</p>\n<p>The head is flat, U-shaped, and has a prominent ridge running from the blowhole to the top of its upper lip.</p>\n<p>Lastly, are the mink whales. They are the second smallest baleen whale. The mink whale is black, grey or purple in colour.</p>\n<p>Common mink whales are distinguished from other whales by a white band they have on each flipper.</p>\n<p>Their long back and tiny dorsal fin, two thirds of the way down their back, is quite distinctive.</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('8de499b8-b792-48c1-8c37-53e563ae3584', '448b0593-6eed-4d20-be08-768265eb3048', 'radio', 'Questions 8–13', '', '<p data-start="1431" data-end="1592">Choose<strong data-start="1431" data-end="1439"> TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information,<strong data-start="1487" data-end="1496">FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information, <strong data-start="1544" data-end="1557">NOT GIVEN </strong>if there is no information on this</p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Urban farming can take place above or below ground."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Some of the equipment used in aeroponic farming can be made by hand"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Urban farming relies more on electricity than some other types of farming"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Fruit and vegetables grown on an aeroponic urban farm are cheaper than traditionally grown organic produce"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Most produce can be grown on an aeroponic urban farm at any time of the year"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Beans take longer to grow on an urban farm than other vegetables"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('c5d4f5f8-796c-4439-92dd-021661ac3a60', '8bdabd1e-175b-4730-98fc-aa72a86bc076', 'radio', 'Questions 27–31', NULL, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">Choose<strong> YES i</strong>f the statement agrees with the claims of the writer <strong>NO </strong>if the statement contradicts the claims of the writer <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this</span></p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Early guesses probably greatly over-estimated the total number of species on Earth."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Primates play a significant role in the ecology of our planet."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "We still have a great deal to learn about the importance of pollination."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Some people may be unaware that the world’s insects consume more food overall than mammals."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "It will take a long time for us to learn the effects of habitat loss and extensive pesticide use."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>27. YES<br />(Đoạn 1: “Some early guesses of 30 million or even 100 million have been replaced… with more reliable ones of somewhere between five to ten million species.”)<br />→ Tác giả nói rằng ước tính ban đầu về số lượng loài trên Trái Đất (30–100 triệu) là cao quá mức so với con số thực tế (5–10 triệu).<br />→ Do đó, early guesses overestimated → YES.</p>\n<p> <br />28. NO<br />(Đoạn 2: “Creatures like us… make up less than three percent of all species.” + “It seems we can’t help ourselves… but in the great ecological scheme of things, they are fairly useless.”)<br />→ Primates (và động vật có xương sống nói chung) chỉ chiếm phần nhỏ và không có vai trò đáng kể trong hệ sinh thái.<br />→ Vì vậy, câu “Primates play a significant role” mâu thuẫn với ý tác giả → NO.</p>\n<p> <br />29. YES<br />(Đoạn 3: “Pollination… is perhaps one of the most essential partnerships ever to have evolved.” + “This… has been around for 100 million years and it has given the world a rich diversity.”)<br />→ Tác giả nhấn mạnh vai trò cực kỳ quan trọng của thụ phấn trong việc tạo nên sự đa dạng sinh học, cho thấy vẫn còn nhiều điều để hiểu rõ hơn về tầm quan trọng này.<br />→ Do đó, câu hỏi “We still have a great deal to learn about the importance of pollination” phù hợp → YES.</p>\n<p> <br />30. YES<br />(Đoạn 4: “It may come as a surprise to many that all the herds of grazing ungulates… are entirely ‘out-munched’, perhaps by a factor of ten to one, by myriads of tiny insects.”)<br />→ Nhiều người sẽ ngạc nhiên (may be unaware) rằng insects ăn nhiều thực vật hơn động vật có vú ăn cỏ.<br />→ Vì vậy, YES.</p>\n<p> <br />31. NO<br />(Đoạn 7: “Almost every study… points to a steady decline… The loss of natural habitat and the prodigious amounts of pesticides… are taking their toll.”)<br />→ Các nghiên cứu đã cho thấy rõ ràng tác động của mất môi trường sống và thuốc trừ sâu đến quần thể côn trùng, không phải là “sẽ mất nhiều thời gian mới biết được”.<br />→ Do đó, NO.</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('01d8f26f-b399-4160-94ea-05e4b9f2323c', '8ca12180-611f-4e4a-84d9-fbff8eccfe46', 'radio', 'Questions 27-32', '', '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 3, "options": [{"option_text": "It was the safest city in the country."}, {"option_text": "It was less prosperous than other cities."}, {"option_text": "Many people were frustrated that they could not find a job."}, {"option_text": "It was wealthy and seen as an ideal place to raise children."}], "question": "What does the writer say about Dunedin in the 1970s?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "That the study was held in a church."}, {"option_text": "That the tests took half a day"}, {"option_text": "That 91% of parents agreed to help."}, {"option_text": "That the study used volunteers."}], "question": " What did the writer find surprising about Phil Silva’s original study?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "Children had excellent language"}, {"option_text": "Many children had developmental problems."}, {"option_text": "No children had ear problems."}, {"option_text": "All children were healthy."}], "question": "What was Silva''s main finding in 1978?"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"option_text": "The sample group was smaller in the first study"}, {"option_text": "The second study produced conflicting results."}, {"option_text": "Helpers were not used in the second study."}, {"option_text": "The second study collected additional types of information."}], "question": "What was different about the first and second studies?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A shortage of helpers."}, {"option_text": "A lack of available funding."}, {"option_text": "The bad behaviour of some children."}, {"option_text": "The poor language skills of the participants"}], "question": "What problem did Silva face when conducting the original study?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "To show how generous project funding had become"}, {"option_text": "To show that the study was being taken seriously."}, {"option_text": "To emphasise the temporary nature of the facilities."}, {"option_text": "To highlight that the children disliked the site"}], "question": " Why does the writer mention the new building in the fourth paragraph?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. What does the writer say about Dunedin in the 1970s? — {D}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “New Zealand was then the <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"37\">ninth richest country</strong> in the world and many residents believed that… this was a city <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"124\">without rival</strong> [to bring up children].” (Đoạn 1)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Wealthy” tương ứng với quốc gia giàu thứ 9, và “ideal place to raise children” tương ứng với “city without rival” (thành phố không đối thủ).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. What did the writer find surprising about Phil Silva’s original study? — {C}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Incredibly</strong>, no fewer than <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">91% agreed</strong> to help…” (Đoạn 1)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Từ “Incredibly” (đáng kinh ngạc/thật khó tin) thể hiện sự ngạc nhiên của tác giả về tỉ lệ cha mẹ đồng ý tham gia rất cao.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. What was Silva’s main finding in 1978? — {B}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…one in four children had <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"40\">delayed language development</strong>; 15% had <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">ear problems</strong>; …one child who was blind…” (Đoạn 3)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các con số này cho thấy nhiều trẻ em gặp phải các vấn đề về phát triển (developmental problems) mà trước đó chưa được phát hiện.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30. What was different about the first and second studies? — {D}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The data gathered at age three was updated and <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">new measurement criteria</strong> – discipline, nutrition, dental health – were <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"130\">introduced</strong>.” (Đoạn 2)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nghiên cứu thứ hai đã đưa thêm các tiêu chí đo lường mới (additional types of information) như kỷ luật, dinh dưỡng và sức khỏe răng miệng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. What problem did Silva face when conducting the original study? — {B}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “There was <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"22\">precious little money</strong> at Silva’s disposal, so the assessments were done in a <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">church with the help of dozens of volunteers</strong>.” (Đoạn 2)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc phải làm trong nhà thờ và dùng tình nguyện viên cho thấy sự thiếu hụt nghiêm trọng về kinh phí (lack of available funding).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. Why does the writer mention the new building in the fourth paragraph? — {B}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…the politicians were finally starting to <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"56\">take note</strong> and government funding began to trickle in. …it was at least a site for the <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"144\">long term</strong> and its acquisition represented a <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"188\">landmark</strong>…” (Đoạn 4)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc có một tòa nhà cố định (dù không sang trọng) đánh dấu việc nghiên cứu bắt đầu được chính quyền coi trọng và đầu tư dài hạn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('1096406d-7528-4fea-b1db-3d35bd79aeb8', '8ca12180-611f-4e4a-84d9-fbff8eccfe46', 'radio', 'Questions 33-36', '', '<p>Choose <strong>YES</strong> if the statement agrees with the claims of the writer, choose<strong> NO</strong> if the statement contradicts the claims of the writer, or <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong>  if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this.</p>', 'yes_no_not_given', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Recent results suggest that intellectual development and birth weight are linked."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Medical textbooks used to claim that breast-fed children were more intelligent."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Children who suck their thumbs are prone to developmental problems."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The findings of the Dunedin study have challenged some doctors’ preconceptions"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. Recent results suggest that intellectual development and birth weight are linked. — {YES}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…the amount a newborn infant <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"43\">weighs is associated with IQ</strong>.” (Đoạn 5)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cân nặng khi sinh liên quan đến IQ (chỉ số thông minh/phát triển trí tuệ), khớp hoàn toàn với nhận định.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. Medical textbooks used to claim that breast-fed children were more intelligent. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Paediatric textbooks had insisted… breast-feeding protected against <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"82\">medical problems like asthma and allergies</strong>.” (Đoạn 5)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sách giáo khoa nói nuôi con bằng sữa mẹ giúp chống lại <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">bệnh tật</strong> (hen suyễn, dị ứng), chứ không nhắc gì đến việc giúp trẻ <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"133\">thông minh hơn</strong> (intelligent).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. Children who suck their thumbs are prone to developmental problems. — {NO}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…thumb-sucking <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">does no harm</strong>…” (Đoạn 5)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc khẳng định mút tay không gây hại, trái ngược với ý kiến cho rằng nó gây ra các vấn đề phát triển.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. The findings of the Dunedin study have challenged some doctors’ preconceptions. — {YES}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…Dunedin researchers have been able to <strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">contradict old assumptions</strong> and <strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"84\">explode medical myths</strong> long held by the profession.” (Đoạn 5)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Contradict old assumptions” và “explode medical myths” chính là việc thách thức các định kiến (preconceptions) của giới y khoa.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('1bfe063e-562f-490f-a711-14697bfb05a5', '8f28f354-3d19-4cac-a974-b68fe7c138cd', 'radio', 'Questions 1-6', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple-choice', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Setlters realised that wooden houses were more dangerous than other types of structure"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "During the 1800s, New Zealand exported wood for use in boat-building."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Plantation-grown wood is generally better for construction than native-forest wood."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Compared to other types of wood, pine has a narrow range of uses."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Demand for housing in New Zealand is predicted to fall in the next few years."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "In future, the expansion of New Zealand’s wood industry will depend on its exports."}]', NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. Settlers realised that wooden houses were more dangerous than other types of structure.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 1,</span><span class=\"\"> câu 3:</span> <em class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“…wooden houses arose, supported by the recognition that they were <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"95\">less likely to collapse suddenly during earthquakes</strong>…”</em></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Bài đọc cho biết người dân chọn xây nhà gỗ vì chúng </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"64\">ít có khả năng sụp đổ bất ngờ</strong><span class=\"\"> khi có động đất.</span><span class=\"\"> Điều này có nghĩa là chúng được coi là an toàn hơn,</span><span class=\"\"> trái ngược hoàn toàn với nhận định “nguy hiểm hơn” (</span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"215\">more dangerous</strong><span class=\"\">) trong câu hỏi.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. During the 1800s, New Zealand exported wood for use in boat-building.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 2,</span><span class=\"\"> câu 1 &amp; 3:</span> <em class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"30\">“Early explorers recognised the suitability of… the kauri for constructing <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"107\">sailing vessels</strong>. So from the <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"136\">early 1800s</strong>, huge amounts of this type of wood were sold… for that purpose.”</em></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> “Sailing vessels” chính là tàu thuyền.</span><span class=\"\"> Văn bản xác nhận gỗ kauri đã được xuất khẩu từ đầu thế kỷ 19 để phục vụ mục đích đóng tàu.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. Plantation-grown wood is generally better for construction than native-forest wood.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 3 &amp; 4 có nhắc đến việc gỗ đồn điền (pine) hiện nay cung cấp phần lớn nhu cầu gỗ xẻ cho xây dựng.</span></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Bài đọc chỉ nêu thực tế là gỗ đồn điền đang được dùng nhiều cho xây dựng,</span><span class=\"\"> nhưng </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"92\">không hề có sự so sánh</strong><span class=\"\"> về chất lượng để khẳng định nó “tốt hơn” (</span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"157\">better</strong><span class=\"\">) so với gỗ rừng tự nhiên.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. Compared to other types of wood, pine has a narrow range of uses.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 4,</span><span class=\"\"> câu 5:</span> <em class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“This <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"32\">amazing versatility</strong> has encouraged the development of an integrated forest-products industry…”</em></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Từ khóa </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“amazing versatility”</strong><span class=\"\"> (sự đa năng kinh ngạc) chỉ ra rằng gỗ thông có rất nhiều công dụng khác nhau.</span><span class=\"\"> Điều này phản bác lại ý kiến cho rằng nó có phạm vi sử dụng hạn hẹp (</span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"189\">narrow range of uses</strong><span class=\"\">).</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. Demand for housing in New Zealand is predicted to fall in the next few years.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 6,</span><span class=\"\"> câu 1:</span> <em class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“In New Zealand itself, the construction industry… servicing around 20,000 new house starts annually.”</em></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Bài đọc cung cấp số lượng nhà xây mới hàng năm nhưng </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">không đưa ra dự đoán</strong><span class=\"\"> (predicted) nào về việc nhu cầu này sẽ tăng hay giảm (</span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"140\">fall</strong><span class=\"\">) trong tương lai gần.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. In future, the expansion of New Zealand’s wood industry will depend on its exports.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn 6,</span><span class=\"\"> câu cuối:</span> <em class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">“Accordingly, the development of the <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"66\">export market is the key</strong> to the industry’s growth… in decades to come.”</em></li>\n<li><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"18,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Bài đọc khẳng định rõ ràng rằng thị trường xuất khẩu chính là “chìa khóa” (the key) cho sự tăng trưởng (expansion/growth) của ngành gỗ trong tương lai.</span></li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('8e59b090-65ac-4848-b591-33e690eb3fb6', 'd3611042-d30e-4c59-b13c-3bf1a9293da6', 'matching', 'Questions 27-33', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct heading for each paragraph from the list of headings below.</p>
<p>Choose the correct number, <strong>i-ix</strong>, in boxes 1-7.</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i. methods used to investigate termite mound formation"}, {"optionText": "ii. challenging our assumptions about the nature of life"}, {"optionText": "iii. reconsidering the termite’s reputation"}, {"optionText": "iv. principal functions of the termite mound"}, {"optionText": "v. distribution of termite mounds in sub-Saharan Africa"}, {"optionText": "vi. some potential benefits of understanding termite architecture"}, {"optionText": "vii. the astonishing physical dimensions of the termite mound"}, {"optionText": "viii. termite mounds under threat from global climate change"}, {"optionText": "ix. a mutually beneficial relationship"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>27. Paragraph 1 → iii. reconsidering the termite’s reputation<br />(Đoạn 1: “To most of us, termites are destructive insects… But according to Dr Rupert Soar… these pests may serve a useful purpose for us after all.”)<br />→ Đoạn mở đầu thay đổi cách nhìn của con người về mối — từ loài phá hoại sang sinh vật có giá trị nghiên cứu.<br />→ Đáp án: iii. reconsidering the termite’s reputation</p>\n<p>28. Paragraph 2 → vii. the astonishing physical dimensions of the termite mound<br />(Đoạn 2: “Termite mounds are impressive for their size alone; typically they are three metres high… and reach far into the earth…”)<br />→ Đoạn này tập trung mô tả kích thước khổng lồ và cấu trúc vật lý phức tạp của tổ mối.<br />→ Đáp án: vii. the astonishing physical dimensions of the termite mound</p>\n<p>29. Paragraph 3 → iv. principal functions of the termite mound<br />(Đoạn 3: “This complex system of tunnels draws in air… to expel spent respiratory gases… ensuring them a continuous provision of fresh air.”)<br />→ Mô tả chức năng chính của tổ mối: điều hòa không khí, độ ẩm, nhiệt độ – giúp duy trì môi trường sống ổn định.<br />→ Đáp án: iv. principal functions of the termite mound</p>\n<p>30. Paragraph 4 → ix. a mutually beneficial relationship<br />(Đoạn 4: “Part of their digestive process is carried out by a fungus… termites feed the fungus… fungus breaks down wood pulp into sugary food.”)<br />→ Trình bày mối quan hệ cộng sinh giữa mối và nấm, cả hai cùng có lợi.<br />→ Đáp án: ix. a mutually beneficial relationship</p>\n<p>31. Paragraph 5 → ii. challenging our assumptions about the nature of life<br />(Đoạn 5: “Scientists… labelled them a ‘super organism’… we may ultimately need to redefine our understanding of what constitutes a ‘living’ organism.”)<br />→ Các nhà khoa học cho rằng tổ mối thách thức định nghĩa hiện tại về “sự sống”, vì khả năng duy trì cân bằng sinh học như một cơ thể sống.<br />→ Đáp án: ii. challenging our assumptions about the nature of life</p>\n<p>32. Paragraph 6 → i. methods used to investigate termite mound formation<br />(Đoạn 6: “To reveal the structure of the mounds, Soar’s team begins by filling and covering them with plaster of Paris… computer technology… 3D models.”)<br />→ Mô tả phương pháp nghiên cứu cấu trúc tổ mối bằng kỹ thuật thạch cao và mô hình 3D.<br />→ Đáp án: i. methods used to investigate termite mound formation</p>\n<p>33. Paragraph 7 → vi. some potential benefits of understanding termite architecture<br />(Đoạn 7: “Soar hopes that the models will explain how termite mounds create a self-regulating environment… findings could be invaluable in future architectural design…”)<br />→ Trình bày lợi ích tiềm năng của việc hiểu cấu trúc tổ mối — ứng dụng trong kiến trúc tự điều hòa, tiết kiệm năng lượng.<br />→ Đáp án: vi. some potential benefits of understanding termite architecture</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('4041e54c-9fbd-439b-8ea4-92fd4d506158', '8bdabd1e-175b-4730-98fc-aa72a86bc076', 'matching', 'Questions 32–36', NULL, '<p>Complete each sentence with the correct ending, A–F, below.<br />Write the correct letter, A–F, in boxes 32–36 below.</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "a fall in the total number and variety of insects in the world."}, {"optionText": "the number of plants that are pollinated by insects."}, {"optionText": "how many different animal species are currently in existence."}, {"optionText": "how long it will be before the Earth’s biodiversity is drastically reduced."}, {"optionText": "the predominance of invertebrates among the Earth’s species."}, {"optionText": "the declining numbers of bees and butterflies."}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "Scientists have recently revised their views regarding", "correctAnswer": "how many different animal species are currently in existence.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "There is absolutely no doubt about", "correctAnswer": "the predominance of invertebrates among the Earth’s species.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Almost every study done so far has indicated", "correctAnswer": "a fall in the total number and variety of insects in the world.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "A lot of research on insect groups has focused on", "correctAnswer": "the declining numbers of bees and butterflies.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "The rate at which tropical forests are being lost can help us calculate", "correctAnswer": "how long it will be before the Earth’s biodiversity is drastically reduced.", "sectionContent": null}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>32 species<br />(Đoạn 1: “Some early guesses of 30 million or even 100 million have been replaced in the last few years with more reliable ones of somewhere between five to ten million species.”)<br />→ Các nhà khoa học đã điều chỉnh lại ước tính về số lượng loài đang tồn tại trên Trái Đất, từ con số quá cao (30–100 triệu) xuống khoảng 5–10 triệu.<br /> <br />33 invertebrates<br />(Đoạn 1: “There is one thing which is indisputable: the vast majority of Earth’s inhabitants are invertebrate – without a backbone – and most of those are insects.”)<br />→ Không có gì phải nghi ngờ rằng đa số sinh vật trên Trái Đất là loài không xương sống, chủ yếu là côn trùng.<br /> <br />34 insects<br />(Đoạn 7: “Almost every study that has been done to date points to a steady decline in insect species’ richness and abundance.”)<br />→ Gần như tất cả các nghiên cứu đều cho thấy sự suy giảm rõ rệt về số lượng và sự đa dạng của côn trùng.<br /> <br />35 bees and butterflies<br />(Đoạn 7: “The decreases seen in well-studied insect groups such as bees and butterflies are surely taking place in many other groups as well.”)<br />→ Nhiều nghiên cứu đã tập trung vào sự suy giảm của ong và bướm, đại diện cho các nhóm côn trùng được nghiên cứu kỹ lưỡng nhất.<br /> <br />36 biodiversity<br />(Đoạn 8: “If these complex habitats are being felled and degraded… it will only be a matter of a few hundred years before they are lost. It is therefore an inescapable conclusion that our planet could lose more than half of all its living species.”)<br />→ Tốc độ mất rừng nhiệt đới giúp ta ước tính thời điểm mà đa dạng sinh học toàn cầu sẽ suy giảm nghiêm trọng.<br /> <br /> <br /> </p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('bd5edac1-8cbc-4b88-9953-aa7d698c5256', '8bdabd1e-175b-4730-98fc-aa72a86bc076', 'radio', 'Questions 37–40', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct letter, A, B, C or D.<br />Write the correct letter in boxes 37–40 on your answer sheet.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A. the predominance of insects in the world."}, {"content": "B. a common misunderstanding about global biodiversity."}, {"content": "C. our instinctive reaction towards certain types of animals."}, {"content": "D. the main distinction between vertebrates and invertebrates."}], "question": "In the third paragraph, the writer refers to a particular slide to emphasise"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "A. lectures about animals given by the writer"}, {"content": "B. audiences who attend events focused on insect life"}, {"content": "C. images which depict various different types of species"}, {"content": "D. creatures which appear comparatively similar to humans"}], "question": "What does ‘they’ in the third paragraph refer to?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. It should not be our priority at the moment."}, {"content": "B. It serves no useful purpose in the long term."}, {"content": "C. It will cost an unreasonable amount in the future."}, {"content": "D. It results from our natural curiosity about the world."}], "question": "What does the writer imply about ‘big’ science in the final paragraph?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A. Certain insect species are more at risk than others."}, {"content": "B. Insects are more important than many people realise."}, {"content": "C. There is an interdependence between different insect species."}, {"content": "D. The ecological role of insects is likely to change in the near future."}], "question": "What point does the writer make overall about insects?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>37 instinctive reaction<br />(Đoạn 3: “I use a slide in my lectures which has images of all sorts of insects along with one face-on image of a female slender loris… No prizes for guessing the first, and probably the only, thing audiences look at.”)<br />→ Tác giả nhắc đến slide này để nhấn mạnh phản ứng bản năng của con người – ta luôn chú ý và yêu thích các loài có ngoại hình giống mình hơn (như linh trưởng) thay vì côn trùng.<br />→ Đáp án: C – our instinctive reaction towards certain types of animals.<br /> <br />38 creatures similar to humans<br />(Đoạn 3: “It seems we can’t help ourselves. Appealing they may be, but in the great ecological scheme of things, they are fairly useless.”)<br />→ Đại từ “they” ở đây ám chỉ các sinh vật giống con người – cụ thể là những loài linh trưởng (primates) mà người xem bị thu hút khi nhìn vào slide.<br />→ Đáp án: D – creatures which appear comparatively similar to humans.<br /> <br />39 not a priority<br />(Đoạn cuối: “This truly is ‘big’ science and of course it’s expensive. But do we have to do it right now? What about understanding the environment a bit better?”)<br />→ Tác giả không phản đối khoa học quy mô lớn (big science), nhưng cho rằng đây không nên là ưu tiên lúc này; thay vào đó, nên tập trung hiểu rõ hơn về môi trường.<br />→ Đáp án: A – It should not be our priority at the moment.<br /> <br />40 importance of insects<br />(Đoạn 2 &amp; 4: “If you really want to understand the world around you – you need to take a serious look at insects.” + “It may come as a surprise to many…” + toàn bài nhấn mạnh vai trò thiết yếu của côn trùng trong hệ sinh thái.)<br />→ Tác giả khẳng định côn trùng quan trọng hơn nhiều so với nhận thức của con người, từ thụ phấn, ăn thịt, cho đến duy trì cân bằng sinh thái.<br />→ Đáp án: B – Insects are more important than many people realise.<br /> <br /> <br /> </p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('844f219e-2342-4c6c-a7d6-74727a70b399', '8ca12180-611f-4e4a-84d9-fbff8eccfe46', 'matching', 'Questions 37-40', '', '<p>Complete the summary below by dragging each phrase to the correct gap.</p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>A model study</strong></p>\n<p>The success of the Dunedin project has been put down to two principal factors: good fortune and Phil Silva''s methodology. The demographics of Dunedin mean that residents feel committed to the study, and that it also provides {H results} that can be applied both nationally and internationally, but even more important was Silva''s conviction that the {B study members}<span id=\"4827\" class=\"quests-numctn\" data-numctn=\"12\" data-count=\"12\" data-quest=\"12\"></span> must be looked after; nothing should be done to threaten the study''s {G confidentiality}<span id=\"4827\" class=\"quests-numctn\" data-numctn=\"13\" data-count=\"13\" data-quest=\"13\"></span> and as a result Silva is cautious when questioned, and a lot of work is done to minimise {F barriers to involvement}<span id=\"4827\" class=\"quests-numctn\" data-numctn=\"14\" data-count=\"14\" data-quest=\"14\"></span> in order to ensure that the study continues into the future.</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A generalisable research"}, {"optionText": "B study members"}, {"optionText": "C government funding"}, {"optionText": "D assessments"}, {"optionText": "E loyalty"}, {"optionText": "F barriers to involvement"}, {"optionText": "G confidentiality"}, {"optionText": "H results"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. …provides {H results} that can be applied both nationally and internationally…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"28\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…produce findings that can be <strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"44\">generalised</strong> to New Zealand and other developed countries…” (Đoạn 6)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Generalised” (khái quát hóa) đồng nghĩa với việc kết quả có thể áp dụng rộng rãi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. …conviction that the {B study members} must be looked after…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"30\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…the most important asset they had was the <strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">sample group</strong> and these people must be <strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"95\">nurtured at all costs</strong>.” (Đoạn 7)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sample group (nhóm mẫu) chính là các thành viên tham gia nghiên cứu.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. …nothing should be done to threaten the study’s {G confidentiality}…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"32\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “<strong data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Privacy is absolutely paramount</strong>: Silva won’t even say how many of the study members are now in prison…” (Đoạn 7)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Quyền riêng tư (Privacy) tương ứng với tính bảo mật (Confidentiality).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. …work is done to minimise {F barriers to involvement}…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"34\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…maintaining contact and <strong data-path-to-node=\"34,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"39\">removing obstacles to participation</strong>.” (Đoạn 8)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Removing obstacles” (loại bỏ rào cản) tương ứng với “minimise barriers”.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('09ebab27-c27d-41d9-9af9-9eca517ad29f', 'ef437dd3-dc5f-4980-a695-727eefa608ea', 'radio', 'Questions 27 – 32', NULL, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">Choose<strong> YES i</strong>f the statement agrees with the claims of the writer <strong>NO </strong>if the statement contradicts the claims of the writer <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this</span></p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Grimm brothers believed they would achieve international fame."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Grimm brothers were forced to work in secret."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Some parents today still think Grimm’s fairy tales are not suitable for children."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The first edition of Grimm’s fairy tales sold more widely in England than in Germany."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Adults like reading Grimm’s fairy tales for reasons different from those of children."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Grimm brothers based the story “Cinderella” on the life of Dorothea Viehmann."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>27. The Grimm brothers believed they would achieve international fame → NO<br />\n(Đoạn 2: “Such lasting fame would have shocked the humble Grimms.”)<br />\n→ Câu này cho thấy hai anh em Grimm không hề nghĩ rằng mình sẽ nổi tiếng toàn cầu, mà ngược lại, họ sẽ rất ngạc nhiên nếu biết được điều đó.<br />\n→ Đáp án: NO</p>\n<p>28. The Grimm brothers were forced to work in secret → NOT GIVEN<br />\n(Đoạn 2: “They began their work at a time when Germany had been overrun by the French under Napoleon…” nhưng không có chi tiết nào nói rằng họ phải làm việc bí mật.)<br />\n→ Thông tin về việc họ bị “ép buộc làm việc trong bí mật” không xuất hiện trong bài, nên không thể khẳng định.<br />\n→ Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</p>\n<p>29. Some parents today still think Grimm’s fairy tales are not suitable for children → YES<br />\n(Đoạn 3: “Even today some protective parents shy from the Grimms’ tales because of their reputation for violence.”)<br />\n→ Cụm “Even today” cho thấy đến nay vẫn còn phụ huynh tránh cho con đọc truyện Grimm vì cho rằng quá bạo lực và không phù hợp với trẻ em.<br />\n→ Đáp án: YES</p>\n<p>30. The first edition of Grimm’s fairy tales sold more widely in England than in Germany → NOT GIVEN<br />\n(Đoạn 2 &amp; 4: Bài nói “During their lifetimes the collection sold modestly in Germany…” và “English publishers led the way…” nhưng không có thông tin so sánh số lượng bán ra giữa hai nước.)<br />\n→ Không thể kết luận truyện bán chạy hơn ở Anh hay Đức.<br />\n→ Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</p>\n<p>31. Adults like reading Grimm’s fairy tales for reasons different from those of children → YES<br />\n(Đoạn cuối: “The Grimm tales please in an infinite number of ways. Something about them seems to mirror whatever moods or interests we bring to our reading of them.”)<br />\n→ Mỗi người đọc, dù là người lớn hay trẻ em, đều thấy trong truyện những điều phản chiếu sở thích và tâm trạng riêng, tức là họ đọc vì những lý do khác nhau.<br />\n→ Đáp án: YES</p>\n<p>32. The Grimm brothers based the story “Cinderella” on the life of Dorothea Viehmann → NO<br />\n(Đoạn 6: “Among her treasures was ‘Aschenputtel’—Cinderella.”)<br />\n→ Dorothea chỉ là người kể lại câu chuyện “Cinderella” cho hai anh em Grimm, chứ không phải nhân vật thật mà truyện dựa theo.<br />\n→ Đáp án: NO</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7bff85d0-a7e6-43b7-b3e5-b3846838bcb5', 'ef437dd3-dc5f-4980-a695-727eefa608ea', 'radio', 'Questions 33 – 35', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct letter, A, B, C or D.<br />
Write your answers in boxes 33-35 .</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. Literacy levels of the population increased. "}, {"content": "B. The development of printing technology made it easier to publish. "}, {"content": "C. Schools were open to children. "}, {"content": "D. People were fond of colleting superb picture books."}], "question": "In paragraph 4, what changes happened at that time in Europe? "}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A. They made the stories shorter. "}, {"content": "B. They used more oral language. "}, {"content": "C. The content of the tales became less violent. "}, {"content": "D. They found other origins of the tales."}], "question": "What changes did the Grimm Brothers make in later editions? "}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "A. She wrote stories. "}, {"content": "B. She discussed the stories with them. "}, {"content": "C. She translated a popular book for the brothers using her talent for languages. "}, {"content": "D. She told the oral stories that were based on traditional Italian stories."}], "question": "What did Marie Hassenpflug contribute to the Grimm’s Fairy tales? "}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>33. In paragraph 4, what changes happened at that time in Europe → A. Literacy levels of the population increased<br />\n(Đoạn 4: “English publishers led the way, issuing high-quality picture books such as Jack and the Beanstalk and handsome folktale collections, all to satisfy a newly literate audience seeking virtuous material for the nursery.”)<br />\n→ Cụm “a newly literate audience” cho thấy tỷ lệ biết chữ của người dân châu Âu tăng lên, dẫn đến nhu cầu đọc sách cao hơn.<br />\n→ Đáp án: A. Literacy levels of the population increased</p>\n<p>34. What changes did the Grimm Brothers make in later editions → C. The content of the tales became less violent<br />\n(Đoạn 4: “Once the Brothers Grimm sighted this new public, they set about refining and softening their tales… cruel mothers became nasty stepmothers, unmarried lovers were made chaste, and the incestuous father was recast as the devil.”)<br />\n→ Cụm “refining and softening their tales” cùng các ví dụ đi kèm chứng minh rằng họ làm cho nội dung truyện trở nên nhẹ nhàng, ít bạo lực và phù hợp hơn với trẻ em.<br />\n→ Đáp án: C. The content of the tales became less violent</p>\n<p>35. What did Marie Hassenpflug contribute to the Grimm’s Fairy Tales → D. She told the oral stories that were based on traditional Italian stories<br />\n(Đoạn 6: “Marie Hassenpflug… Her wonderful stories blended motifs from the oral tradition and from Perrault’s influential 1697 book, Tales of My Mother Goose, which contained elaborate versions of ‘Little Red Riding Hood’, ‘Snow White’, and ‘Sleeping Beauty’, among others. Many of these had been adapted from earlier Italian fairy tales.”)<br />\n→ Câu này cho thấy Marie Hassenpflug kể lại các câu chuyện dân gian pha trộn từ truyền miệng và truyện cổ điển, nhiều trong số đó có nguồn gốc từ truyện cổ Ý.<br />\n→ Đáp án: D. She told the oral stories that were based on traditional Italian stories</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('4ed62f51-a24d-4362-9255-0ab8c57a2f24', 'ef437dd3-dc5f-4980-a695-727eefa608ea', 'matching', 'Questions 36 – 40', NULL, '<p>Complete each sentence with correct ending, <strong>A-H</strong>, below.<br />
Write the correct letter, <strong>A-H</strong>, in boxes 36-40.</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A. reflect what life was like at that time."}, {"optionText": "B. help children deal with their problems."}, {"optionText": "C. demonstrate the outdated system."}, {"optionText": "D. tell of the simplicity of life in the German countryside."}, {"optionText": "E. encourage people to believe that they can do anything."}, {"optionText": "F. recognize the heroes in the real life."}, {"optionText": "G. contribute to the belief in nature power."}, {"optionText": "H. avoid details about characters’ social settings."}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "Heinz Rolleke said the Grimm’s tales are “German” because the tales", "correctAnswer": "D. tell of the simplicity of life in the German countryside.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Heinz Rolleke said the abandoned children in tales", "correctAnswer": "A. reflect what life was like at that time.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Bernhard Lauer said the writing style of the Grimm brothers is universal because they", "correctAnswer": "H. avoid details about characters’ social settings.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Jack Zipes said the pursuit of happiness in the tales means they", "correctAnswer": "E. encourage people to believe that they can do anything.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Bruno Bettelheim said the therapeutic value of the tales means that the fairy tales", "correctAnswer": "B. help children deal with their problems.", "sectionContent": null}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>36. Heinz Rolleke said the Grimm’s tales are “German” because the tales → D. tell of the simplicity of life in the German countryside<br />\n(Đoạn 7: “Very, says scholar Heinz Rolleke. Love of the underdog, rustic simplicity, creative energy—these are Teutonic traits. The coarse texture of life during medieval times in Germany&#8230; also coloured the narratives.”)<br />\n→ Rolleke cho rằng truyện Grimm “rất Đức” vì chúng phản ánh cuộc sống giản dị, mộc mạc và tinh thần sáng tạo đặc trưng của vùng nông thôn Đức thời trung cổ.<br />\n→ Đáp án: D</p>\n<p>37. Heinz Rolleke said the abandoned children in tales → A. reflect what life was like at that time<br />\n(Đoạn 7: “Throughout Europe children were often neglected and abandoned, like Hansel and Gretel&#8230; The cruelty in the stories was not the Grimms’ fantasy; it reflected the law-and-order system of the old times.”)<br />\n→ Câu chuyện “Hansel and Gretel” và nhiều truyện khác thể hiện hiện thực xã hội thời đó – trẻ em bị bỏ rơi, đời sống khắc nghiệt.<br />\n→ Đáp án: A</p>\n<p>38. Bernhard Lauer said the writing style of the Grimm brothers is universal because they → H. avoid details about characters’ social settings<br />\n(Đoạn 8: “You have no concrete descriptions of the land, or the clothes, or the forest, or the castles. It makes the stories timeless and placeless.”)<br />\n→ Cách viết không cụ thể hóa bối cảnh hay tầng lớp xã hội giúp truyện trở nên “vô thời gian, vô không gian” – ai, ở đâu, thời nào cũng có thể đồng cảm.<br />\n→ Đáp án: H</p>\n<p>39. Jack Zipes said the pursuit of happiness in the tales means they → E. encourage people to believe that they can do anything<br />\n(Đoạn 8: “They show a striving for happiness that none of us knows but that we sense is possible. We can identify with the heroes… and become the masters of our own destinies.”)<br />\n→ Theo Zipes, các truyện truyền cảm hứng và niềm tin rằng con người có thể tự làm chủ số phận, đạt được hạnh phúc.<br />\n→ Đáp án: E</p>\n<p>40. Bruno Bettelheim said the therapeutic value of the tales means that the fairy tales → B. help children deal with their problems<br />\n(Đoạn 9: “Bettelheim famously promoted the therapeutic value of the Grimms’ stories&#8230; By confronting fears and phobias&#8230; children find they can master their anxieties.”)<br />\n→ Bettelheim cho rằng truyện cổ Grimm có giá trị trị liệu vì giúp trẻ em đối mặt và vượt qua nỗi sợ hãi, vấn đề tâm lý của chính mình.<br />\n→ Đáp án: B</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('9af62127-416e-4cc8-b5f4-16cd26fafc5d', '003b376a-be8b-427c-a884-dcfe82d3d117', 'fillup', 'Questions 1- 10', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Campsites</strong></span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><strong>Westerly Campsite</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Campsite for families with children under 12</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Location: near the {sea}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Special attraction for children: the {animals}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>A local farmer sells {eggs}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Campers are allowed to have a {fire}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Cost per night: £ {15.75} for a family</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Snetton Forest Campsite</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Cost per night: £5 per adult (children free)</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Recommended for people who like {fishing}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Campers can hire a {bike}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activity organised for children: {football}</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Trent Valley Campsite</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Better month for families to go: {July}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Has an outdoor {pool}</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 1: CHOOSING A CAMPSITE</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Shall we have a look at this information about campsites and then perhaps we can choose where to go on holiday?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Yes, my children are very excited about our two families going away together again this year. Shall we look at Westerly Campsite first?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Yes, it says it''s most suitable for children under 12 years old, so that should be fine for us. Your daughter''s just 11, isn''t she?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Hmm, yes, that''s right.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong>Man:</strong>Now where is the Westerly Campsite? Is it the one next to a lake?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> That''s another one. This one''s by the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"45\">(Q1) sea</strong></span>. Perfect!</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Yes, that''s a good place to go in the summer when the weather''s hot.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong>Woman: </strong>This brochure says that most children who go to Westerly Campsite love the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"149\">(Q2) animals</strong></span> they can see there. There''s a special area where they can go and feed them.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong>Man:</strong>We might see some interesting birds too.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Hmm,</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong>Man:</strong> Oh and look! It says a farmer comes every day and you can buy <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"74\">(Q3) eggs</strong></span> from him.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong>Woman:</strong>Great for breakfast! I wonder if he sells other things like cheese, but it''s not mentioned.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> I don''t know... I think they grow a lot of fruit in that area, so he might sell that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong>Woman:</strong>Hmm, another thing I like about this campsite is that they let you make a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"236\">(Q4) fire</strong></span>. We could cook some sausages and sing songs around it in the evenings. And perhaps it would be a good way to meet other families there too.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Great! And it isn''t too expensive. £6 per adult per night, £3 per child. But wait, families of four can get it for <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"122\">(Q5) £15.75</strong>  </span>a night. That works out even cheaper.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">OTHER CAMPSITES (Questions 6–10)</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Let''s look at a couple of other campsites before we decide.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Yes, let''s look at Snetterton Forest Campsite. It''s even cheaper: £5 per adult and children under 10 are free. They say it''s a very good place if you''re keen on <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"168\">(Q6) fishing</strong></span>, and they even give you tips on where to go to have the best chance of catching some.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> I prefer walking or hiking, and so do the rest of my family, so I''m not sure that will attract us that much.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Oh look, it says you can rent a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"39\">(Q7) bike</strong></span> to go around the forest. I''d do that, and your children would like that too, wouldn''t they?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Absolutely! We could all go somewhere and have a picnic.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Look, this is interesting too. At Snetterton, they get all the children together to play <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"96\">(Q8) football</strong></span>. Oh, and your children would love that! And your husband Mike plays too, doesn''t he?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Yes, that sounds good. Well, Mike''s more into tennis actually, but I''m sure he''d be happy to be a referee if they needed one.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Here''s some information about Trent Valley Campsite. I''ve heard about this one. There''s a festival near the campsite in June and it''s really busy, so they say for families it''s better in <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"194\">(Q9) July</strong></span> when it''s a bit quieter.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Well, that would be just right for us because we have to go in the school summer holidays.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong>Woman: </strong>Hmm</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong>Man:</strong> Let''s look at what it says about it. Oh look, it''s quite a long way to the nearest village—8 km. It''s too far to walk.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong>Woman:</strong>But this one has got an outdoor <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"252\">(Q10) pool</strong></span>, which we''d all love in the summer. And they have a little shop where you can buy basic things like bread and milk.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong>Man:</strong>That''s really useful.And there''s lots to do there, I think on Saturday nights... </p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('48fffdfc-2d3a-43dd-9ca5-a6156e6e35e7', '7896feed-d071-4f7e-9fcc-9ca76b6e8c58', 'radio', 'Questions 1–6', NULL, '<p class="MsoNormal">Choose <strong>TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple-choice', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "During his 2007 dive, Michiels expected to encounter total darkness at about 15 metres."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Michiels could see the red markings on fish without the aid of the red filter."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Other divers had assumed they would see fish with red markings."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "All the fish with red markings that Michiels found during his diving expeditions came from the Red Sea."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Michiels first thought of the possibility that fish could fluoresce while he was in Germany."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Michiels remains uncertain as to what creates fluorescence in fish."}]', NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p>1. During his 2007 dive, Michiels expected to encounter total darkness at about 15 metres.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\"><strong class=\"\">Đáp án: TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\"><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn A) “In theory,</span> <strong class=\"\">once he reached about 15 metres, he should have been plunged into darkness</strong><span class=\"\">.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\"><strong class=\"\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Câu hỏi phản ánh đúng kỳ vọng lý thuyết của Michiels về độ sâu mà ánh sáng đỏ biến mất.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>2. Michiels could see the red markings on fish without the aid of the red filter.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong class=\"\">Đáp án: TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn B) “</span><strong class=\"\">Even with the red filter removed</strong><span class=\"\">,</span><span class=\"\"> Michiels could pick them out without much trouble </span><strong class=\"\">once his eyes grew accustomed to the gloom</strong><span class=\"\">.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong class=\"\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Sau khi tháo kính lọc đỏ và quen với bóng tối,</span><span class=\"\"> Michiels vẫn có thể nhìn thấy các dấu hiệu màu đỏ.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>3. Other divers had assumed they would see fish with red markings.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong class=\"\">Đáp án: FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong class=\"\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> (Đoạn B) “It seems strange that no diver or researcher had spotted all this red before,</span><span class=\"\"> but as Michiels points out,</span> <strong class=\"\">no one saw it because no one expected to see it</strong><span class=\"\">.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong class=\"\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Các thợ lặn và nhà nghiên cứu khác không thấy màu đỏ vì họ </span><strong class=\"\">không mong đợi</strong><span class=\"\"> (expected) thấy nó,</span><span class=\"\"> mâu thuẫn với việc họ “had assumed” (đã giả định) sẽ thấy.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>4. All the fish with red markings that Michiels found during his diving expeditions came from the Red Sea.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn A, B) Michiels tìm thấy các loài này ở Biển Đỏ (Red Sea), nhưng văn bản <strong>không nói rằng TẤT CẢ</strong> các loài cá có dấu hiệu đỏ mà ông tìm thấy trong các chuyến lặn khác nhau <strong>đều chỉ đến từ Biển Đỏ</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>5. Michiels first thought of the possibility that fish could fluoresce while he was in Germany.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án: FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn C) Michiels <strong>nghi ngờ sự phát quang</strong> (<strong>suspected fluorescence</strong>) ngay khi ông đang lặn ở Biển Đỏ (“At 20 metres down, there had to be some other explanation for the red Michiels was seeing. He <strong>suspected fluorescence</strong>.”). Ông chỉ <strong>xác nhận</strong> điều đó ở Đức (Đoạn D).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Ý tưởng phát quang xuất hiện khi ông đang ở Ai Cập (lặn Biển Đỏ), không phải lần đầu tiên ở Đức.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>6. Michiels remains uncertain as to what creates fluorescence in fish.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án: TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn D) “However, Michiels says they are <strong>still not sure exactly what is fluorescing</strong>. ‘It’s not the crystals themselves. It’s probably a fluorescent protein built into the crystals, and <strong>we have a suspicion that it might be made by bacteria</strong>.’”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Ông vẫn chưa chắc chắn về nguồn gốc chính xác của chất phát quang, chỉ nghi ngờ là protein hoặc vi khuẩn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e3fd4251-5d0e-44de-9a2b-b56e83120c99', '9bd95faf-23b0-48aa-ba18-efcf3eacc43c', 'radio', 'Questions 11-15', '', '<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A,B or C.</strong></p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. preparing their fields for planting."}, {"option_text": "B. harvesting their organic crops."}, {"option_text": "C. constructing their farm buildings."}], "question": "Stephen says the founders of extrahands.com originally needed help in"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. update your form on the website every year."}, {"option_text": "B. pay a subscription of $25 every year."}, {"option_text": "C. use the scheme as a host or volunteer every year."}], "question": "To remain an active member of extrahands.com, you must"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A. the type of work available."}, {"option_text": "B. the geographical location."}, {"option_text": "C. the length of time required."}], "question": "Most extrahands.com volunteers search for jobs on the website according to"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. confirm details of the arrangement in writing."}, {"option_text": "B. draw up a formal written contract."}, {"option_text": "C. meet each other before setting on terms."}], "question": "Stephen recommends that the host and volunteer should"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A. for checking each new member online."}, {"option_text": "B. for allowing online feedback."}, {"option_text": "C. for inspecting work and accommodation."}], "question": "To deal with members''problems,extrahands.com have a system"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 2: EXTRA HANDS ORGANIZATION</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Presenter:</strong> Steven Jennings has been involved with an intriguing organization called Extra hands.com. I''ll let him explain. </p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_68982bd070013b23-146\" data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Steven:</strong>Thanks. Yes, Extra hands.com was started 15 years ago by two New Zealanders who''d bought an old farm building and some land. They wanted to go organic, but they realized they''d need help <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"187\">(Q11) <span class=\"citation-2068 citation-2069 citation-2070\">clearing the fields for cultivation</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-2068 citation-2069 citation-2070 citation-end-2070\">, and they just didn''t have the money to pay for it. But they knew lots of people wanted to visit New Zealand, so they set up a website and advertised for volunteers to come and help on the farm there. Anyway, th<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"1\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-2068 citation-2069 citation-end-2069\">ey got lots of volunteers and they got their farm going, and extra hands.com was born.<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"2\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-2068 citation-end-2068\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"3\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_68982bd070013b23-147\" data-path-to-node=\"6\"><span class=\"citation-2066 citation-2067 citation-end-2067\">Today the organization matches pe<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"4\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-2066 citation-end-2066\">ople who need help with people who are willing to work as a way of seeing the world. You can either be a host if you need assistance or<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"5\"><!----></sup></span> a volunteer if you''re offering to work. In either case, to become a member, you just fill out a form on the Extra hands.com website and pay the 25 dollar subscription. You only have to do that once, but for your membership to stay active <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"407\">(Q12) <span class=\"citation-2064 citation-2065\">every 12 months you have to go back to the website and check the details on your form there</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-2064 citation-2065 citation-end-2065\">, adding information about any help you requested or work you did over that period.<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"6\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-2064 citation-end-2064\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"7\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_68982bd070013b23-148\" data-path-to-node=\"7\"><span class=\"citation-2062 citation-2063 citation-end-2063\">So how does it work? Well, if a host has some work that needs to be done, he or she goes t<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"8\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-2062 citation-end-2062\">o the Ex<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"9\"><!----></sup></span>tra hands.com website and posts a description of the work. So the way most volunteers access these details on the website is by <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"226\">(Q13) <span class=\"citation-2058 citation-2059 citation-2060 citation-2061\">specifying the country or region they''re interested in working in</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-2058 citation-2059 citation-2060 citation-2061 citation-end-2061\">. But a few search according to how long they want to work for. Not many people have strong feelings about what sort of work they want to do<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"10\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-2058 citation-2059 citation-2060 citation-end-2060\">; they''re mostly fairly open about it.<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"11\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-2058 citation-2059 citation-end-2059\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"12\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-2058 citation-end-2058\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"13\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_68982bd070013b23-149\" data-path-to-node=\"8\"><span class=\"citation-2055 citation-2056 citation-2057 citation-end-2057\">If you''re interested in volunteering for a particular job, you c<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"14\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-2055 citation-2056 citation-end-2056\">an email your host to arrange the dates and establish things like accommodation and hours of work. It''s all fairly infor<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"15\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-2055 citation-end-2055\">mal; there are no legal documents or anything like that. But you do b<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"16\"><!----></sup></span>oth <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"257\">(Q14) need to have some sort of written record of what''s been agreed</strong></span> before you actually arrive.</p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_68982bd070013b23-150\" data-path-to-node=\"9\">What about problems? Well, there are too many members for the organization to be able to investigate them all, but <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"115\">(Q15) <span class=\"citation-2054\">there''s an online message board where members can post details of any difficulties they''ve had</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-2054 citation-end-2054\">, things like unsatisfactory accommodation or volunteers who haven''t done the work agreed, and this works very well.<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"17\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">STEVEN''S PLACEMENTS (Questions 16–20)</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Presenter:</strong> I know you''ve personally had lots of extra hands.com placements Steven. Tell us about them.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Steven:</strong> Well, my first placement was in <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"40\">Portugal</strong></span>, where I helped a local guy with a guidebook he''d written in English. I read what he''d written and <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"148\">(Q16) corrected the English and made some suggestions for improving it (F - Editor)</strong></span>. I was very pleased with it when I finished and I learned lots about the country.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\">The next placement was on the other side of the world, in <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">Australia</strong></span>. I was on a farm in the middle of nowhere and since I''m pretty good in the kitchen, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"152\">(Q17) they had me fixing meals for 30 sheep shearers (A - Cook)</strong></span>. I stayed two months and it was a lot of fun, but I can tell you I was glad to get back home to California and just lie on a beach and relax.</p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_68982bd070013b23-151\" data-path-to-node=\"15\">Okay, then after a well-deserved rest, I did a job in <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">South Korea</strong></span> for a small company that wanted an English speaker to <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"120\">(Q18) show visiting Americans around (D - Tour guide)</strong></span>. I <span class=\"citation-2052 citation-2053 citation-end-2053\">gave me some books to read and I learned as I worked. I loved it and I developed a real taste for Korean food.<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"18\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-2052 citation-end-2052\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"19\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_68982bd070013b23-152\" data-path-to-node=\"16\"><span class=\"citation-2050 citation-2051\">My most difficult job was for an older lady in the </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"51\"><span class=\"citation-2050 citation-2051\">USA</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-2050 citation-2051 citation-end-2051\">. She had a gigantic house and grounds but she couldn''t maintain them all herself. So I worked<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"20\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-2050 citation-end-2050\"> for he<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"21\"><!----></sup></span>r <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"157\">(Q19) digging and planting flowers and stuff around her swimming pool (B - Gardener)</strong></span>, and she grew tons of vegetables too. She was nice but she fed me hot dogs morning, noon and night!</p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\">Now my most recent placement was last summer in <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"48\">Italy</strong></span>. I helped a family <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">(Q20) add a room under their house (C - Construction worker)</strong></span>. I didn''t speak Italian or know the first thing about building, but the husband had an English-Italian phrasebook and together with sign language showed me exactly what to do. And the wife''s cooking was out of this world!</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('16756ba4-6e95-40f9-ad8b-0c6a8f5ccdaf', '7eaca0a7-fd37-47b7-b98d-64e86580db07', 'radio', 'Questions 32-35', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>YES </strong>if the statement agrees with the claims of the writer, choose <strong>NO </strong>if the statement contradicts the claims of the writer, or <strong>NOT</strong> <strong>GIVEN </strong>if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Scientific knowledge should be kept separate from social values."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Many sociologists have disregarded the doubts that some scientists have concerning fluoridation."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Sutton’s findings have been given insufficient attention by scientists outside of North America."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "There are valid arguments on both sides of the fluoridation debate."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>32. Scientific knowledge should be kept separate from social values.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>NO</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> Tác giả phê bình quan điểm truyền thống, thay vào đó ủng hộ quan điểm cho rằng kiến thức khoa học <strong>&#8220;is socially negotiated, and inevitably linked to the values of the relevant parties&#8221;</strong> (Đoạn 4).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Quan điểm của tác giả là kiến thức khoa học <strong>không thể tách rời</strong> khỏi các giá trị và quy trình xã hội, mâu thuẫn với việc phải giữ chúng tách biệt.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>33. Many sociologists have disregarded the doubts that some scientists have concerning fluoridation.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>YES</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> Tác giả nhận xét rằng các nhà xã hội học đã <strong>&#8220;downplayed an important part of the debate by ignoring the number of eminent scientists who have questioned aspects of fluoridation&#8221;</strong> (Đoạn 7).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả khẳng định các nhà xã hội học đã xem nhẹ (disregarded/downplayed) các nghi ngờ của một số nhà khoa học nổi tiếng về fluoride hóa.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>34. Sutton’s findings have been given insufficient attention by scientists outside of North America.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> Văn bản chỉ nói rằng sách của Sutton <strong>&#8220;is not cited in a single analysis of the fluoridation issue by any sociologist&#8221;</strong> (Đoạn 7).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Chỉ có thông tin về việc các <strong>nhà xã hội học</strong> bỏ qua công trình của Sutton. <strong>Không có thông tin</strong> để xác định liệu các <strong>nhà khoa học</strong> bên ngoài Bắc Mỹ có bỏ qua công trình này hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>35. There are valid arguments on both sides of the fluoridation debate.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>YES</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 8) Tác giả trình bày lập luận của cả hai bên và kết luận rằng sự khác biệt này <strong>&#8220;is not between rationality and irrationality but is a legitimate difference in values&#8221;</strong> (là sự khác biệt hợp pháp về giá trị).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Việc thừa nhận đây là sự khác biệt hợp pháp (legitimate difference) ngụ ý rằng cả hai bên đều có những lập luận hợp lý (valid arguments) dựa trên các giá trị xã hội khác nhau.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('2727ab1d-1124-4dcc-b566-3f02a6b68136', '7eaca0a7-fd37-47b7-b98d-64e86580db07', 'matching', 'Questions 36-40', NULL, '<p>Complete each sentence with the correct ending, A-G, below.</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A. the results of scientific research are not always understood at first."}, {"optionText": "B. science is an unbiased discipline"}, {"optionText": "C. people should be able to choose whether they want fluoride."}, {"optionText": "D. there is insufficient proof to support a cautious approach."}, {"optionText": "E. the serious damage fluoride causes far outweighs any positive effects."}, {"optionText": "F. children are not the only ones who benefit from fluoridation."}, {"optionText": "G. scientific knowledge is affected by the beliefs of everyone concerned."}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "The traditional view of science is that ", "correctAnswer": "B. science is an unbiased discipline", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "A sociological view of science argues that", "correctAnswer": "G. scientific knowledge is affected by the beliefs of everyone concerned.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Collins is of the opinion that", "correctAnswer": "A. the results of scientific research are not always understood at first.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "The writer suggests that a supporter of fluoridation may conclude that", "correctAnswer": "D. there is insufficient proof to support a cautious approach.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "The writer suggests that an opponent of fluoridation may conclude that", "correctAnswer": "C. people should be able to choose whether they want fluoride.", "sectionContent": null}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>36. The traditional view of science is that</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>B. science is an unbiased discipline</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) &#8220;The traditional view is that science is a special of knowledge, which is established through scientific methods and <strong>objectively applied</strong> by members of a scientific community.&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Quan điểm truyền thống coi khoa học được áp dụng <strong>khách quan</strong> (<em>&#8220;objectively applied&#8221;</em>), tương đương với việc nó là một lĩnh vực không thiên vị (&#8220;unbiased discipline&#8221;).</li>\n</ul>\n<p>37. A sociological view of science argues that</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>G. scientific knowledge is affected by the beliefs of everyone concerned.</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) &#8220;&#8230;a sociology of science that shows how scientific knowledge is socially negotiated, and <strong>inevitably linked to the values of the relevant parties, both scientists and nonscientists</strong>.&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Xã hội học khoa học cho rằng kiến thức khoa học liên kết không thể tránh khỏi với <strong>giá trị của tất cả các bên liên quan</strong>, bao gồm cả nhà khoa học và người không phải nhà khoa học.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>38. Collins is of the opinion that</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>A. the results of scientific research are not always understood at first.</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) Collins asserted that the outcome of experiments was not something whose meaning <strong>&#8220;could be immediately comprehended, but rather something for interpretation, discussion between scientists&#8221;</strong>.</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Collins tin rằng kết quả nghiên cứu khoa học không thể <strong>được nắm bắt ngay lập tức</strong> (<em>&#8220;immediately comprehended&#8221;</em>) mà cần có thời gian diễn giải.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>39. The writer suggests that a supporter of fluoridation may conclude that</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>D. there is insufficient proof to support a cautious approach.</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 8) Một người ủng hộ lập luận: &#8220;the evidence for the benefits of fluoridation is quite substantial, while the <strong>evidence for harm is limited and dubious</strong>.&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Họ kết luận rằng bằng chứng về tác hại là <strong>quá ít và đáng ngờ</strong> (<em>&#8220;limited and dubious&#8221;</em>) nên không cần thiết phải áp dụng một cách tiếp cận thận trọng.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>40. The writer suggests that an opponent of fluoridation may conclude that</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>C. people should be able to choose whether they want fluoride.</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) Lý do phản đối thứ ba là: &#8220;fluoridation is thought to be an <strong>infringement on individual rights</strong> because it is <strong>compulsory medication</strong> of all members of a community.&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Việc phản đối sự bắt buộc vì nó vi phạm quyền cá nhân (<em>&#8220;infringement on individual rights&#8221;</em>) ngụ ý rằng mọi người nên có quyền lựa chọn.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('9e63c69d-93e1-4671-b6d4-59e0c6445ddd', 'd3611042-d30e-4c59-b13c-3bf1a9293da6', 'matching', 'Questions 34-37', '<p>Label the diagram below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="data:image/png;base64," width="615" height="267" loading="lazy"></p>
<p>-network of {tunnels} helps to give the termites a constant<br />-{AIR} supply and to maintain a limited temperature range<br />-cellar to aid control of {moisture} levels in mound<br />-top of the mound permits {evaporation}</p>
', NULL, 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p>-network of {tunnels} helps to give the termites a constant<br>-{AIR} supply and to maintain a limited temperature range<br>-cellar to aid control of {moisture} levels in mound<br>-top of the mound permits {evaporation}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "tunnels"}, {"optionText": "AIR"}, {"optionText": "moisture"}, {"optionText": "evaporation"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>8. tunnels → 34<br />\n(Đoạn 3: “This complex system of tunnels draws in air from the outside, capturing wind energy to drive it through the mound.”)<br />\n→ Mạng lưới đường hầm (tunnels) giúp dẫn khí vào và điều hòa nhiệt độ bên trong.<br />\n→ Đáp án: tunnels</p>\n<p>9. air → 35<br />\n(Đoạn 3: “It also serves to expel spent respiratory gases from the nest to prevent the termites from suffocating, so ensuring them a continuous provision of fresh, breathable air.”)<br />\n→ Nguồn không khí (air) liên tục giúp mối duy trì môi trường sống ổn định.<br />\n→ Đáp án: air</p>\n<p>10. moisture → 36<br />\n(Đoạn 3: “The mound also automatically regulates moisture in the air, by means of both its underground ‘cellar’&#8230;”)<br />\n→ Phần cellar ở dưới đất giúp kiểm soát độ ẩm (moisture) trong tổ.<br />\n→ Đáp án: moisture</p>\n<p>11. evaporation → 37<br />\n(Đoạn 3: “&#8230;and evaporation from the top of the mound.”)<br />\n→ Phần đỉnh của tổ (top) cho phép quá trình bay hơi (evaporation) diễn ra.<br />\n→ Đáp án: evaporation</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('64bb0969-5245-4627-ae0e-c08ce1793138', 'a8fd8fd0-d1da-4e49-8bdf-e9aeee444201', 'matching', 'Questions 14–19', NULL, '<p>Reading Passage has six paragraphs.</p>
<p>Choose the correct heading for each paragraph from the list of headings below.</p>
<p>Choose the correct number, i-vii, in boxes <strong>14-19</strong>.</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i The effect of man-made imitations on insects"}, {"optionText": "ii The need to instruct additional insect guides"}, {"optionText": "iii Signals used by certain insects to indicate a discovery"}, {"optionText": "iv How urgency can affect the process of finding a new home"}, {"optionText": "v The use of trained insects in testing scientific theories"}, {"optionText": "vi The use of virtual scenarios in the study of insect behaviour"}, {"optionText": "vii How the number of decision-makers affects the decision"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>14. Paragraph 1</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>vii. How the number of decision-makers affects the decision</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 1) “The idea goes back to the ‘jury theorem’ of Nicolas de Condorcet… The probability of a correct decision <strong>increases with the size of the jury</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này giới thiệu lý thuyết của Condorcet, nói về việc <strong>quy mô nhóm</strong> (số lượng người đưa ra quyết định) ảnh hưởng đến tính chính xác của quyết định (Condorcet’s jury theorem).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>15. Paragraph 2</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>iii. Signals used by certain insects to indicate a discovery</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) Các nhà nghiên cứu quan sát bầy ong mật tìm kiếm tổ mới và <strong>sử dụng điệu nhảy waggle</strong> (<em>“waggle dance”</em>) để <strong>báo cáo</strong> (<em>“indicate”</em>) cho những con ong khác về địa điểm phù hợp mà chúng đã tìm thấy.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này mô tả cách ong mật sử dụng tín hiệu vật lý (“waggle dance”) để thông báo về việc tìm thấy tổ mới.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>16. Paragraph 3</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>vi. The use of virtual scenarios in the study of insect behaviour</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) “Dr List and his colleagues used a <strong>computer generated model</strong> of the decision-making process.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này mô tả việc sử dụng <strong>mô hình máy tính</strong> (<em>computer generated model / virtual scenarios</em>) để mô phỏng và nghiên cứu quá trình ra quyết định của ong.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>17. Paragraph 4</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>i. The effect of man-made imitations on insects</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) José Halloy of the Free University of Brussels in Belgium used <strong>robotic cockroaches</strong> to subvert the behaviour of living cockroaches and control their decision-making process.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này mô tả việc sử dụng <strong>bản sao do con người tạo ra</strong> (<em>robotic cockroaches / man-made imitations</em>) để thao túng quyết định của côn trùng sống.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>18. Paragraph 5</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>iv. How urgency can affect the process of finding a new home</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “Franks and his associates reported how the insects reduce the problems associated with making a <strong>necessarily swift choice</strong>. If the ants’ existing nest become <strong>suddenly threatened</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này tập trung vào việc kiến phải đưa ra <strong>lựa chọn nhanh chóng</strong> (<em>swift choice</em>) khi tổ bị đe dọa đột ngột (urgency).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>19. Paragraph 6</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>ii. The need to instruct additional insect guides</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) “Once the suitable new nest is identified, the <strong>chosen ants begin to lead others</strong>… <strong>and simultaneously show the way to those ants</strong> which have been left behind to guard the old nest.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này mô tả cách các con kiến được chọn làm người dẫn đường (<em>lead others / instruct guides</em>) để chuyển tổ nhanh chóng và hiệu quả.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e4416ed1-4bb1-4b90-8cd4-96a64ddd8d21', 'd3611042-d30e-4c59-b13c-3bf1a9293da6', 'radio', 'Questions 38-40', NULL, '<p><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">Choose<strong> YES i</strong>f the statement agrees with the claims of the writer <strong>NO </strong>if the statement contradicts the claims of the writer <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this</span></p>', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES "}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The termite mound appears to process its refuse material internally."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "YES "}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Dr Soar’s reconstruction involves scanning a single photograph of a complete mound into acomputer."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES "}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "New information about termite architecture could help people deal with future energy crises."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. The termite mound appears to process its refuse material internally. — {YES}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn ix):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">\"...And, although the termites must generate waste, none ever leaves the structure, indicating that there is also <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"135\">some kind of internal waste-recycling system</strong>.\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ ra rằng mặc dù loài mối tạo ra chất thải, nhưng không có chất thải nào thoát ra ngoài cấu trúc tổ, điều này cho thấy có một hệ thống tái chế chất thải nội bộ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"183\">internal waste-recycling system</strong>). Cụm từ \"process its refuse material internally\" (xử lý chất thải nội bộ) khớp hoàn toàn với ý này (\"refuse material\" đồng nghĩa với \"waste\").</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. Dr Soar’s reconstruction involves scanning a single photograph of a complete mound into a computer. — {NO}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p id=\"p-rc_2c6530bad52e7044-32\" data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn i):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"The researcher’s hen carves the plaster of Paris into <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"75\">half-millimatre-thick slices</strong>, <span class=\"citation-185\">and </span><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"109\"><span class=\"citation-185\">photograph them sequentially</span></strong><span class=\"citation-185\">. Once the pictures are digitally scanned, computer technology is able to recreate complex three-dimensional images of the mounds.\"</span></em><span class=\"citation-185 citation-end-185\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"1\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></li>\n<li>\n<p id=\"p-rc_2c6530bad52e7044-33\" data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\"><span class=\"citation-184\">Giải thích:</span></strong><span class=\"citation-184 citation-end-184\"> Câu hỏi nói rằng việc tái dựng của Tiến sĩ Soar chỉ bao gồm quét <sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"2\"><!----></sup></span><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"77\">một bức ảnh duy nhất</strong> của toàn bộ cái tổ (scanning a single photograph). Tuy nhiên, dẫn chứng trong bài chỉ ra quy trình thực tế là cắt mô hình tổ thành các lát mỏng 0.5mm, chụp ảnh <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"258\">theo chuỗi liên tiếp</strong> (photograph them sequentially) rồi mới quét các bức ảnh này vào máy tính để dựng hình 3D. Thông tin \"single photograph\" hoàn toàn trái ngược (contradict) với \"sequential pictures\".</p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. New information about termite architecture could help people deal with future energy crises. — {YES}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p id=\"p-rc_2c6530bad52e7044-34\" data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn vi):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">\"If they do, the findings could be invaluable in informing future architectural design, a<span class=\"citation-182 citation-183\">nd could </span><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"119\"><span class=\"citation-182 citation-183\">inspire buildings that are self-sufficient</span></strong><span class=\"citation-182 citation-183\">, environmentally, and </span><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"184\"><span class=\"citation-182 citation-183\">cheap to run</span></strong><span class=\"citation-182 citation-183\">. ‘As we approach a world of climate change, we need temperatures to rise, he explains, </span><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"284\"><span class=\"citation-182 citation-183\">there will not be enough fuel to drive air conditioners</span></strong><span class=\"citation-182 citation-183\"> around the world.\"</span></em><span class=\"citation-182 citation-183 citation-end-183\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"3\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-182 citation-end-182\"><sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"4\"><!----></sup></span></p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></li>\n<li>\n<p id=\"p-rc_2c6530bad52e7044-35\" data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\"><span class=\"citation-180 citation-181\">Giải thích:</span></strong><span class=\"citation-180 citation-181 citation-end-181\"> Việc thiếu nhiên <sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"5\"><!----></sup></span><span class=\"citation-180 citation-end-180\">liệu để chạy điều hòa trên toàn cầu khi khí hậu b<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"6\"><!----></sup></span>iến đổi chính là một biểu hiện của cuộc khủng hoảng năng lượng tương lai (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"152\">future energy crises</strong>). Bài đọc khẳng định thông tin mới về kiến trúc tổ mối sẽ truyền cảm hứng cho các tòa nhà tự vận hành (self-sufficient) và vận hành giá rẻ, không cần nguồn điện ngoài. Điều này đồng nghĩa với việc giúp con người đối phó với khủng hoảng năng lượng.</p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('bae91abb-f858-41ae-8333-205891d02ecd', '2c7f3f71-6be4-4937-bea6-9c474a328ac4', 'matrix', 'Questions 14–18', '', '<p data-start="119" data-end="186">Write the correct letter, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>G</strong></p>
<p data-start="188" data-end="229"><strong>NB</strong> You may use any letter more than once.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "bad outcomes for a forest when people focus only on its financial reward", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "reference to the aspects of any tree that contribute to its worth", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "mention of the potential use of wood to help run vehicles", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "examples of insects that attack trees", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "an alternative name for trees that produce low-use wood", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}]}', 'null', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5cba7241-6654-4a73-892f-91578436b2ca', '2c7f3f71-6be4-4937-bea6-9c474a328ac4', 'matrix', 'Questions 19–21', '', '<p data-start="567" data-end="650">Look at the following purposes (Questions 19–21) and the list of timber cuts below.</p>
<p data-start="652" data-end="710">Match each purpose with the correct timber cut, <strong>A</strong>, <strong>B </strong>or <strong>C</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="712" data-end="785">Write the correct letter, <strong>A</strong>, <strong>B </strong>or <strong>C</strong></p>
<p data-start="787" data-end="828"><strong>NB </strong>You may use any letter more than once.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": "List of Timber Cuts", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "to remove trees that are diseased", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "to generate income across a number of years", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "to create a forest whose trees are close in age", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "a TSI Cut", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "a Salvage Cut", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "a Shelterwood Cut", "categoryLetter": "C"}]}', 'null', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ac967fc8-d0be-43d6-b708-90fbf58c67fb', '9bd95faf-23b0-48aa-ba18-efcf3eacc43c', 'matching', 'Questions 16- 20', '', '<p>Which job did Stephen do on his placement in each of the following countries?</p>
<p>Choose <strong>FIVE </strong>answers from the box and write the correct letter; <strong>A</strong>-<strong>G</strong>, next to questions 16-20.</p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Countries</strong></span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Portugal {Editor}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Australia {cook}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>South Korea {tour guide}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>USA {gardener}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Italy {construction worker}</p>", "optionsTitle": "Jobs", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "cook"}, {"optionText": "gardener"}, {"optionText": "construction worker"}, {"optionText": "tour guide"}, {"optionText": "farm labourer"}, {"optionText": "Editor"}, {"optionText": "swimming pool cleaner"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": ""}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('60481aac-cd81-4780-a912-7c163f458f77', '2c7f3f71-6be4-4937-bea6-9c474a328ac4', 'fillup', 'Questions 22–26', '<div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto [--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-xs,calc(var(--spacing)*4))] @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-sm,calc(var(--spacing)*6))] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-lg,calc(var(--spacing)*16))] px-(--thread-content-margin)">
<div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn">
<div class="flex max-w-full flex-col gap-4 grow">
<div class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal outline-none keyboard-focused:focus-ring [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" dir="auto" data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="94997e2e-fadf-4f51-aa0e-a42babdbaac6" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-5">
<div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden">
<div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert wrap-break-word w-full light markdown-new-styling">
<p data-start="1071" data-end="1100">Complete the sentences below.</p>
<p data-start="1102" data-end="1156">Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p data-start="1158" data-end="1213"> </p>
<p data-start="1215" data-end="1294">22 Some dead wood is removed to avoid the possibility of {fire}.</p>
<p data-start="1296" data-end="1381">23 The {nutrients} from the tops of cut trees can help improve soil quality.</p>
<p data-start="1383" data-end="1493">24 Some damaged trees should be left, as their {cavities} provide habitats for a range of creatures.</p>
<p data-start="1495" data-end="1601">25 Some trees that are small, such as {hawthorn} , are a source of food for animals and insects.</p>
<p data-start="1603" data-end="1722" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">26 Any trees that are {rare} should be left to grow, as they add to the variety of species in the forest.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('4aa8d679-b9aa-46d5-8fc1-2a7b4f1b909a', '6e0201f9-2dcb-4c0d-a308-13ba8d5cb852', 'matrix', 'Questions 27–31', '', '<p>Which section contains the following information?</p>
<p>Write the correct letter, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>F</strong>, in boxes 27–31 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "a reference to the cooperation that takes place to try and minimise risk", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "an explanation of a person’s aims", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "a description of a major collision that occurred in space", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "a comparison between tracking objects in space and the efficiency of a transportation system", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "a reference to efforts to classify space junk", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}]}', 'null', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a2fe7d49-8e94-4b18-b0e6-ac1590f60387', 'c3b9eeae-e748-4451-aaeb-13b8aa152a16', 'radio', 'Questions 21-25', '', '<div class="s-block-item s-repeatable-item s-block-sortable-item s-blog-post-section blog-section">
<div class="container">
<div class="sixteen columns">
<div class="s-blog-section-inner">
<div class="s-component s-text   ">
<div class="">
<div class="s-component-content s-font-body">
<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A. B </strong>or <strong>C.</strong></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A take great skill to produce."}, {"option_text": "B are fascinating curved shapes."}, {"option_text": "C have interesting stories behind them."}], "question": " Amy and Mike agree that the greenstone tikis"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A Not many people know about them."}, {"option_text": "B They tend to be stolen by treasure hunters."}, {"option_text": "C The majority become inherited items."}], "question": "According to Amy, why are so few genuine old tikis found on archaeological dig sites?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A decorative items."}, {"option_text": "B religious objects."}, {"option_text": "C tribal symbols."}], "question": "The Maori people considered tikis to be"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A where they originated."}, {"option_text": "B the materials used."}, {"option_text": "C the position of the body."}], "question": "Tikis are classified into one type or the other by"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A The materials differ."}, {"option_text": "B They are too regular in shape."}, {"option_text": "C They are of different sizes. "}], "question": "How can modern reproductions be easily distinguished from genuine Maori carving"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 3: MAORI GREENSTONE TIKIS</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Amy:</strong><span class=\"\"> Hi Mike,</span><span class=\"\"> aren''t these New Zealand carvings we''ve been studying in class fascinating?</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mike:</strong><span class=\"\"> Oh hi Amy.</span><span class=\"\"> Oh,</span><span class=\"\"> the Maori greenstone Tikis?</span><span class=\"\"> They''re all a bit organic for my taste,</span><span class=\"\"> you know,</span><span class=\"\"> all curves and twisting shapes.</span><span class=\"\"> I like modern stuff,</span><span class=\"\"> geometric shapes.</span> <strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"170\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\">(Q21) But I can see the skill involved in making them</span>.</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Amy:</strong> <span class=\"\"> But the stories behind the Tikis are what make them interesting.</span><span class=\"\"> Besides,</span><span class=\"\"> I imagine it would be difficult to create geometric patterns; the shape of each Tiki seems to follow the natural contours of the stone.</span><span class=\"\"> It''s extremely hard and it requires expertise and time to shape.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mike:</strong><span class=\"\"> <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(Q21) That''s true, I suppose  that’s why modern greenstone carvings are so expensive.</strong></span></span><span class=\"\"> But there aren''t that many genuine old ones around.</span><span class=\"\"> Archaeologists rarely discover such treasures,</span><span class=\"\"> which is odd given they are such a huge part of Maori culture.</span><span class=\"\">I wonder if archaeological dig sites were raided and the Tikis were taken to sell?</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><span class=\"\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Amy:</strong> I believe it’s because the owners valued them and so preserved them.</span> <strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"75\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\">(Q22) Many of them would have been passed down through the generations and remain in the possession of the families today, like heirlooms</span>.</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Amy:</strong><span class=\"\"> Do you know what they were used for?</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><span class=\"\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mike:</strong>I thought they were just an art form or a means of decoration.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mike:</strong><span class=\"\"> But Professor Matthew says that the Maori believed Tikis were sacred and could be used as a pathway to their ancestors.</span> <strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"126\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\">(Q23) They believed the dead could speak to them through these talismans (religious objects)</span>.</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Amy:</strong><span class=\"\"> So they don''t represent tribes or anything.</span><span class=\"\"> Interesting!</span><span class=\"\"> How many different kinds are there?There must be hundreds of variations.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><span class=\"\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mike:</strong>There are other greenstone carvings beside Tikis, although I can''t remember all their names. Traditional Tikis themselves can be divided into two distinct groups though.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><span class=\"\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Amy:</strong> Can they?</span><span class=\"\"> By the materials? I''ve seen some with metal features.</span><span class=\"\"> Or is it to do with size or where they were made??</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mike:</strong> <strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"5\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\">(Q24) Actually, it is the ways that their feet, heads, and hands are placed that make the major difference (position of the body)</span>.</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><span class=\"\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Amy:</strong> Is it easy to discern the difference between the ancient stones and more modern reproductions? Are the styles very different?</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><span class=\"\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mike:</strong>Modern reproductions usually use a different type of stone, although they may be of the same design. They may also be of a smaller size.</span><span class=\"\"> But it’s actually quite easy to tell if you are buying a genuine carving or a mass-produced souvenir.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><span class=\"\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Amy:</strong> How?</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><span class=\"\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mike:</strong> Nowadays they are produced by machine using lasers,</span><span class=\"\"> even so they have no blemishes.</span> <strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"89\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\">(Q25) In genuine carvings, they aren''t always perfect (too regular in shape) because the Maori used simple hand tools</span>.</strong><span class=\"\"> For example,</span><span class=\"\"> the hole that the cord is fed through isn''t perfectly round.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><span class=\"\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Amy:</strong>That makes sense.</span></p>\n<hr class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<h3 class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">THE CARVING PROCESS (Questions 26–30)</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><span class=\"\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Amy:</strong> Actually, it''s amazing that they produce such detailed Tikis with such simple tools and materials.Talk me through the process.</span><span class=\"\"> I know the basic shape is carved from New Zealand greenstone.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><span class=\"\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mike:</strong> Yes,</span><span class=\"\"> but first they had to get a blank of the right size.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><span class=\"\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Amy: </strong>You mean a piece of stone of the right size and basic shape?</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><span class=\"\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mike:</strong>That''s right. They used a </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"75\">(Q26) hard stone tool (C - Stone scoring tool)</strong></span><span class=\"\">,</span><span class=\"\"> something rough,</span><span class=\"\"> to wear a groove into a piece of greenstone.</span><span class=\"\"> After they’d scored it with that,</span><span class=\"\"> they could just snap it in two.I guess they could have used some kind of hammer though. They repeated the process until they had a piece of stone suitable for what they wanted to carve—usually flat pieces for Tikis.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><span class=\"\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Amy:</strong> Right, because they''re fairly small and quite thin.Then they started carving?</span></p>\n<p class=\"animating\" data-path-to-node=\"24\"><span class=\"\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mike:</strong> Not right away.</span><span class=\"\"> Before they could start carving,</span><span class=\"\"> they needed an absolutely smooth,</span><span class=\"\"> flat surface. Nowadays, when we want to do something like that, we''d clamp the stone in a vice and use a sander. But</span> <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"102\">(Q27) they used a heavy block of sandstone (A)</strong></span><span class=\"\"> and rubbed the piece of greenstone on it over and over to prepare it for carving.</span></p>\n<p class=\"animating\" data-path-to-node=\"25\"><span class=\"\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Amy:</strong> It must have been very time-consuming. So how did they cut out the little details like hands and feet?</span></p>\n<p class=\"animating\" data-path-to-node=\"26\"><span class=\"\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mike:</strong> They had carving tools.They used small chips of stone glued and tied onto a wooden handle. Then</span> they also used a piece of <strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"57\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\">(Q28) sharpened bone made into a point (D - Bone point)</span>.</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Amy:</strong> Is that what they used to make the holes?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mike:</strong> Actually, they had a special tool to make holes. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">(Q29) It was a stick tied between two heavy pebbles (E - Stick drill)</strong></span> with a point at the end. They would wrap string around it, pull it back and forth to wear a hole into the Tiki.They used the same technique to make round shapes too, but didn''t make the hole go all the way through.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Amy:</strong> And I’ve seen some Tikis with coloured eyes or decorations. Are they painted?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Mike:</strong> Mostly they are inlaid with different coloured stone or mother of pearl from <strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"1929\">shells</strong>, or sometimes dyed pieces of bone. <strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"78\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\">(Q30) They were fixed in place using tarata gum, a sticky plant resin (B - Plant glue)</span>.</strong>They used plants to make the natural strings too?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Amy: </strong>That''s right. The Maori were very resourceful, weren''t they?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"2158\">Mike:</strong> They certainly were.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f29e1d41-8f93-4b82-8264-657afa5ea809', 'c3b9eeae-e748-4451-aaeb-13b8aa152a16', 'matching', 'Questions 26-30', '', '<p>What tool did Maoris use to carry out each of the following tasks?</p>
<p>Choose <strong>FIVE</strong> answers from the box and write the correct letter, <strong>A</strong>-<strong>E </strong>next to Question 26 -30</p>', 'matching_name', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>creating a blank {C Stone scoring tool}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>smoothing the surface {A Sandstone block}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>carving details {D Bone point}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>making holes {E Stick drill}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>fixing coloured {B Plant glue}</p>", "optionsTitle": "Traditional Tools and Materials ", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A Sandstone block"}, {"optionText": "B Plant glue"}, {"optionText": "C Stone scoring tool"}, {"optionText": "D Bone point"}, {"optionText": "E Stick drill"}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "creating a blank", "correctAnswer": "C"}, {"questionPart": "smoothing the surface", "correctAnswer": "A"}, {"questionPart": "carving details", "correctAnswer": "D"}, {"questionPart": "making holes", "correctAnswer": "E"}, {"questionPart": " fixing coloured ", "correctAnswer": "B"}]}', 'null', '[{"content": ""}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('48652e59-ac4f-4d52-bfe0-b9edd5f4327a', '8b8158ff-31a2-462f-9876-4abfee1ef1ca', 'radio', 'Questions 1–5', '', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>
</div>
</div>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Children’s business cards have been banned in some kindergartens."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "It was the Chinese who first began the practice of using business cards."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Designing business cards can be a controversial process for some companies."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "A famous toy company has boosted their sales by using one type of unusual business card."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Some business commentators predict a decline in the use of paper business cards."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. Children’s business cards have been banned in some kindergartens.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 2, dòng cuối.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…kindergarten children who have cards… This practice has become so common… that the use of such cards is now <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"127\">prohibited</strong> by some of these institutions.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,3,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Prohibited” đồng nghĩa với “banned”. Bài đọc xác nhận việc sử dụng danh thiếp của trẻ mẫu giáo đã bị cấm ở một số nơi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. It was the Chinese who first began the practice of using business cards.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 3, dòng 1-4.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The Chinese invented calling cards in the 15th century… but these were for <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">social purposes only</strong>. Then, in the 17th century, <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"138\">European businesspeople</strong> invented a new type of card… signalling the advent of the business card.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,3,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Người Trung Quốc phát minh ra “calling cards” (thẻ thăm hỏi) cho mục đích xã hội, còn người kinh doanh châu Âu mới là những người phát minh ra “business cards” (danh thiếp kinh doanh).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. Designing business cards can be a controversial process for some companies.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 3, dòng cuối.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…very few things can provoke more <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"48\">heated discussion</strong> at a board meeting than the <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">composition</strong> of the company’s business cards.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,3,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Heated discussion” (thảo luận nảy lửa) về “composition” (bố cục/thiết kế) cho thấy đây là một quá trình gây tranh cãi (controversial).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. A famous toy company has boosted their sales by using one type of unusual business card.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 4, dòng 2.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Employees at one famous toy company give out little plastic figures with their contact details stamped on them.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,3,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc có nhắc đến việc công ty đồ chơi dùng danh thiếp hình nhân vật nhựa, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"95\">không hề đề cập</strong> đến việc điều này có giúp họ tăng doanh số (boosted their sales) hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. Some business commentators predict a decline in the use of paper business cards.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 4, dòng cuối.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “For many business commentators, such gimmicky business cards prove that the use of a physical business card is <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"123\">nearly at an end</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,3,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ “nearly at an end” (gần như sắp kết thúc) đồng nghĩa với dự đoán về sự suy giảm (predict a decline).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('b46b9ffc-9575-4e87-80b7-aed751594c14', '8b8158ff-31a2-462f-9876-4abfee1ef1ca', 'fillup', 'Questions 6–13', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>HOW BUSINESS WORKS</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>Kate Jones’s research</strong></p>
<p>– The most important aspect of business is having {trust} in others.</p>
<p>– {computers} do not have the ability to establish the good relationships essential to business.</p>
<p><strong>Business and globalisation</strong></p>
<p>– Managers must work harder when they don’t share the same {language} with their contacts.</p>
<p>– A UK survey indicates that {travel} takes up the largest part of business leaders time.</p>
<p>– A business person’s {memory} of a meeting can be improved by looking at business cards.</p>
<p><strong>Janet McIntyre</strong></p>
<p>– Business cards clearly show the {status} of each person in a large company.</p>
<p>– The ritual of swapping business card, is a good way of starting a {conversation} at the beginning of a business relationship.</p>
<p>– Janet feels that in the business world, {tradition} is just as important as innovation.</p>
</div>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. The most important aspect of business is having {trust} in others.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: trust</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 5, dòng cuối.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…found that <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">trust</strong> was the key element for running a successful business.”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. {computers} do not have the ability to establish the good relationships…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: computers</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 6, dòng 3.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…while <strong data-path-to-node=\"19,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">computers</strong> can deal with administrative tasks, it is still human beings that have to focus on the emotional.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,3,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Máy tính xử lý việc hành chính, còn con người mới xử lý các yếu tố cảm xúc cần thiết cho mối quan hệ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Business and globalisation</strong></h4>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. Managers must work harder when they don’t share the same {language} with their contacts.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: language</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 7, dòng 2.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Managers have to put more effort in… especially when there is not a common <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">language</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. A UK survey indicates that {travel} takes up the largest part of business leaders time.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: travel</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 7, dòng 4.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…chief executives of global organizations now routinely spend three out of every four weeks on international <strong data-path-to-node=\"24,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"123\">travel</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. A business person’s {memory} of a meeting can be improved by looking at business cards.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"26\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: memory</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 7, dòng 7.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Looking through piles of different cards can enhance your <strong data-path-to-node=\"26,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">memory</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Janet McIntyre</strong></h4>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. Business cards clearly show the {status} of each person in a large company.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: status</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 8, dòng 2.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…cards are essential in determining the exact <strong data-path-to-node=\"29,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">status</strong> of every contact you meet in multinational corporations.”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. The ritual of swapping business card, is a good way of starting a {conversation}…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: conversation</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 8, dòng 4.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…exchanging business cards can be an effective way of initiating a <strong data-path-to-node=\"31,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"81\">conversation</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. Janet feels that in the business world, {tradition} is just as important as innovation.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"33\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: tradition</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 9, dòng 2.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…in Janet McIntyre’s view, <strong data-path-to-node=\"33,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"41\">tradition</strong> also has an equally valuable role to play.”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('45ff661d-dc9a-4a2e-8e44-3e43ef832553', '6e0201f9-2dcb-4c0d-a308-13ba8d5cb852', 'fillup', 'Questions 32–35', '<p data-start="531" data-end="558">Complete the summary below.</p>
<p data-start="560" data-end="614">Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p data-start="673" data-end="727"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>The Inter-Agency Space Debris Coordination Committee</strong></span></p>
<p data-start="729" data-end="1000">The committee gives advice on how the {sustainability} of space can be achieved. The committee advises that when satellites are no longer active, any unused {fuel} or pressurised material that could cause {explosions} should be removed.</p>
<p data-start="1002" data-end="1253">Although operators of large satellite constellations accept that they have obligations as stewards of space, Holger Krag points out that the operators that become {bankrupt} are unlikely to prioritise removing their satellites from space</p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ebc0ff6b-3322-4e26-bb1f-7b6643090c17', 'b11a3056-77f7-4f34-b9fc-62622338e8e3', 'checkbox', 'Questions 19–20 ', '', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<p>Choose <strong>TWO</strong> correct answers.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="quests-list">
<div id="4751" class="quests-item quests-numctn quests-item-history quests-skip" data-question-id="1877" data-numctn="19" data-count="19" data-quest="19-20" data-choices="2">
<div class="tt-head">Which <strong>TWO </strong>things apply when voting for Our Favourite Place?</div>
</div>
</div>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": true, "option_text": "People of any age may vote."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "You may send in your vote by email."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "Only local residents may vote."}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "You may vote several times."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "Voting ends at midnight on Saturday."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('0acbee8e-0a67-4ad6-8bee-028aff246a03', 'bf725440-7036-485f-bc47-2dc540499522', 'radio', 'Questions 38–40', '', '<p><span class="citation-29717">Choose the correct </span><span class="citation-29716 citation-29717">letter, </span><strong data-path-to-node="14" data-index-in-node="27"><span class="citation-29716 citation-29717">A, B, C</span></strong><span class="citation-29716 citation-29717"> or </span><strong data-path-to-node="14" data-index-in-node="38"><span class="citation-29716 citation-29717">D</span></strong><span class="citation-29716 citation-29717 citation-end-29717">.</span></p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A strict discipline from the teaching staff"}, {"option_text": "B assistance from their peers in the classroom"}, {"option_text": "C the development of a spirit of inquiry towards their studies"}, {"option_text": "D the determination to surpass everyone else’s achievements"}], "question": "What does Eyre believe is needed for children to equal ‘gifted’ standards?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A Very gifted students do not need to work on improving memory skills."}, {"option_text": "B Being born with a special gift is not the key factor in becoming expert."}, {"option_text": "C Including time for physical exercise is crucial in raising performance."}, {"option_text": "D 10,000 hours of relevant and demanding work will create a genius."}], "question": "What is the result of Ericsson’s research?"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"option_text": "A a regular and nourishing diet at home."}, {"option_text": "B the loving support of more than one parent."}, {"option_text": "C a community which has well-funded facilities for learning."}, {"option_text": "D the guidance of someone who recognises the benefits of learning."}], "question": "In the penultimate paragraph, it is stated the key to some deprived children’s success is"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. C (the development of a spirit of inquiry towards their studies) — {What does Eyre believe is needed for children to equal ‘gifted’ standards?}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"However, they must be taught the <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">right attitudes and approaches</strong> to their learning and develop the <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"119\">attributes of high performers – curiosity, persistence and hard work</strong>...\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Curiosity\" (sự tò mò/ham học hỏi) chính là \"spirit of inquiry\" (tinh thần ham tìm tòi/nghiên cứu). Eyre tin rằng nếu trẻ được dạy thái độ đúng đắn và tinh thần tò mò này, các bạn có thể đạt mức \"gifted\".</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. B (Being born with a special gift is not the key factor in becoming expert.) — {What is the result of Ericsson’s research?}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"...he <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"27\">doesn’t think unique and innate talents are at the heart of performance</strong>. Deliberate practice... is what produces the goods.\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ericsson không tin năng khiếu bẩm sinh (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">innate talents</strong>) là yếu tố cốt lõi (at the heart). Thay vào đó, sự luyện tập có chủ đích mới là quan trọng. Điều này khớp với ý B: \"Sinh ra với năng khiếu đặc biệt không phải là yếu tố then chốt\".</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. D (the guidance of someone who recognises the benefits of learning.) — {the key to some deprived children’s success is...}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 9 - penultimate paragraph):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"44\">\"Interviews uncovered strong evidence of <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"85\">an adult or adults in the child’s life who valued and supported education</strong>...\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Valued and supported education\" (coi trọng và ủng hộ giáo dục) chính là người \"nhận ra lợi ích của việc học\" (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"123\">recognises the benefits of learning</strong>). Sự hướng dẫn và ủng hộ từ những người này là chìa khóa thành công cho trẻ em nghèo (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"245\">deprived children</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('1f356392-8d2c-42f6-86b9-0a3820b17ea6', '1d359a32-2f56-44b1-a951-175dda2f4020', 'radio', 'Questions 1–7', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple-choice', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": " FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Jason Neff discovered there had been a dramatic rise in dust levels in the second half of the nineteenth century."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": " FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Anasazi civilization disappeared due to the impact of dust in the atmosphere."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": " FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Before cattle were introduced to the American Southwest, large numbers of bison occupied the area."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": " FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The bison population in the Great Plains diminished because European settlers found it easy to hunt them."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": " FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The development of railroads across the US was more expensive than originally expected."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Aztec Land and Cattle Company worked hard to take care of the grazing land it owned."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Most of the land once owned by the Aztec Land and Cattle Company remains infertile today."}]', NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<h3>1. Jason Neff discovered there had been a dramatic rise in dust levels in the second half of the nineteenth century.</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) “…but then, ‘from about <strong>1860 to 1900, dust deposition rates shot up</strong>.’”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Giai đoạn 1860 đến 1900 là nửa cuối thế kỷ 19, và việc “dust deposition rates shot up” (tốc độ lắng đọng bụi tăng vọt) chứng tỏ có sự gia tăng đáng kể.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>2. The Anasazi civilization disappeared due to the impact of dust in the atmosphere.</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn C) “There was a near-permanent drought between 900 and 1300 which was so intense that <strong>it destroyed a series of native American civilizations</strong>, including the Anasazi… Yet the evidence from the San Juan lakes is that <strong>it was not dusty</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản nói nền văn minh Anasazi bị hủy hoại bởi <strong>hạn hán</strong> nghiêm trọng (<strong>drought</strong>), và bằng chứng cho thấy trong thời kỳ đó <strong>không hề có bụi</strong> nhiều. Điều này mâu thuẫn với câu hỏi.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>3. Before cattle were introduced to the American Southwest, large numbers of bison occupied the area.</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn D) “‘Unlike most other parts of the US, there were <strong>few grazers</strong> in the American Southwest until the Europeans came. <strong>No bison</strong> and few antelope or deer.’”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản nói rõ rằng trước khi người châu Âu đến, có <strong>rất ít</strong> động vật ăn cỏ và <strong>không có bò rừng (bison)</strong> ở American Southwest.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>4. The bison population in the Great Plains diminished because European settlers found it easy to hunt them.</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) “In the Great Plains to the east and north, <strong>bison roamed in vast herds</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản chỉ nhắc đến việc bison sống thành đàn lớn ở Great Plains, nhưng <strong>không cung cấp thông tin</strong> về lý do tại sao quần thể bison giảm sút (có thể là do săn bắn, nhưng văn bản không xác nhận).</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>5. The development of railroads across the US was more expensive than originally expected.</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) “The invasion was sudden, funded by a bubble of speculative investment… The money went into <strong>railroads</strong>, and herds of cattle and sheep that rode the rails…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản chỉ nói rằng tiền đầu tư được đổ vào đường sắt, nhưng <strong>không có thông tin</strong> về chi phí thực tế có vượt quá dự kiến ban đầu hay không.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>6. The Aztec Land and Cattle Company worked hard to take care of the grazing land it owned.</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn F) “…it was only interested in <strong>quick profits</strong> and had <strong>little incentive to protect the soils from overgrazing</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Công ty Aztec chỉ quan tâm đến lợi nhuận nhanh chóng và <strong>ít động lực bảo vệ</strong> đất khỏi chăn thả quá mức, trái ngược với việc “worked hard to take care” (làm việc chăm chỉ để chăm sóc).</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>7. Most of the land once owned by the Aztec Land and Cattle Company remains infertile today.</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn F) “Such was the damage to the grasslands that <strong>even now few of the pastures have recovered</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ “few of the pastures have recovered” (rất ít đồng cỏ đã phục hồi) cho thấy phần lớn diện tích vẫn chưa hồi phục và vẫn còn cằn cỗi (infertile).</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('61ec80ac-20ee-4701-a74c-2467f56c2b22', 'aea53feb-b25e-40d5-8c52-9d28a0ffea91', 'fillup', 'Questions 31–40', '<div class="flex max-w-full flex-col gap-4 grow">
<div class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal outline-none keyboard-focused:focus-ring [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" dir="auto" tabindex="0" data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="7d01b199-6cad-4546-b4a8-6f7935842d4f" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-5" data-turn-start-message="true">
<div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden">
<div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert wrap-break-word w-full light markdown-new-styling">
<p data-start="71" data-end="134">Complete the notes below<br data-start="95" data-end="98">Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p data-start="136" data-end="153"><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Absence from work</span></strong></p>
<p data-start="155" data-end="193">Absence may be frequent or occasional.</p>
<p data-start="195" data-end="216">Main factors involved</p>
<ul data-start="217" data-end="537">
<li data-section-id="1v18ob6" data-start="217" data-end="306">the {gender} of employees (e.g. females are likely to have responsibility for children)</li>
<li data-section-id="305qpw" data-start="307" data-end="363">employees’ {attitude} (but the evidence is inconclusive)</li>
<li data-section-id="l7vot7" data-start="364" data-end="430">the {culture} of the organization (absenteeism may be acceptable)</li>
<li data-section-id="1hjjttk" data-start="431" data-end="494">the type of work (higher absence among employees in {industry})</li>
<li data-section-id="n9nk3l" data-start="495" data-end="537">the {size} of an employee’s work group</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="539" data-end="574">Public sector versus private sector</p>
<p data-start="576" data-end="615">Public sector has higher absence levels</p>
<p data-start="617" data-end="672">Possible explanation-the public sector is less {efficient}</p>
<p data-start="674" data-end="756">Systems may be more bureaucratic because of {external} factors (e.g. state controls)</p>
<p data-start="758" data-end="825">More recent literature suggests public sector organisations usually</p>
<ul data-start="826" data-end="992" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">
<li data-section-id="95gi9b" data-start="826" data-end="853">have a {larger} workforce</li>
<li data-section-id="3d36u6" data-start="854" data-end="897">have more female and more older employees</li>
<li data-section-id="1nan1qv" data-start="898" data-end="952">provide {benefits} for longer, with fewer restrictions</li>
<li data-section-id="gla7mr" data-start="953" data-end="992" data-is-last-node="">are less likely to {dismiss} employees</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="mt-3 w-full empty:hidden">
<div class="text-center">
<div> </div>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 4: ABSENCE FROM WORK</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Speaker:</strong> Hello, everyone. For my assignment, I did a review of the literature concerning absence in the workplace, and I''m going to present a summary of what I found. I looked at some research on absence from work—that is, the number of days'' work people miss for various reasons. Researchers refer to two types of absence: frequent absence, which is obviously a more serious problem, and occasional absence.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">A lot of studies look at the factors involved in absence from work, and several have been identified. Firstly, the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"115\">(Q31) gender</strong></span> of the employee may influence his or her ability to attend work. For example, a female is more likely to have child care responsibility, and so could be absent as a result of that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">The next factor that has been identified is the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"48\">(Q32) attitude</strong></span> of employees toward their work. But there has been a lot of debate about the extent to which this actually does influence absence, and some people argue that the research hasn''t been conclusive. Some researchers have suggested that another reason for high levels of absence is that some organisations have a <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"371\">(Q33) culture</strong></span> in which absence is accepted, but others have criticised this model, arguing that it''s too much of a generalisation.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">And then there are factors related to the type of work the employee does. It''s been claimed that workers in <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"108\">(Q34) industry</strong></span> are more likely to have high absence rates than people who work in offices. It''s also important to recognise that groups within a single organisation might behave differently. For example, one of the other underlying themes in the literature is that there is a connection between how often an employee is absent and what <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"444\">(Q35) size</strong></span> of work group he or she belongs to. Specifically, it''s been found that the bigger the group, the higher the levels of absence.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\">On a related theme, some writers have focused on a comparison between public sector organisations and private sector ones. There is some evidence that absence levels are higher in the public sector. It''s not exactly clear why this should be the case, but one explanation that has been often put forwards is that in some cases, public sector organisations may not be as <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"369\">(Q36) efficient</strong></span>. This might be because their systems are more bureaucratic due to factors which are <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"469\">(Q37) external</strong> </span>rather than internal, like the degree of control the government imposes on the public sector.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">However, most recent literature suggests a number of other explanations. Firstly, a public sector organisation tends to have a workforce which is<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"146\">(Q38) larger</strong></span>. Also, it tends to employ a higher number of female and older employees, both of which groups are likely to record higher absence rates. It is also suggested that public sector organisations are more likely to give their absent employees <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"397\">(Q39) benefits</strong></span> for a longer period and are less likely to place restrictions on these. In addition, it''s been found that public sector employers have less of a tendency to <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"569\">(Q40) dismiss</strong></span> employees for being absent. And all of these could be additional or alternative reasons for higher absence rates in the public sector.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\">Now, I''d like to talk about the management of absence...</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('cd226267-2640-4c15-aef6-a54fb0678d55', 'd2ed4252-3025-458e-9ad8-0feb733d39aa', 'radio', 'Questions 1–5', '', '<p id="p-rc_15b35af655f2be62-56" data-path-to-node="3,0,0"><span class="citation-2428">Choose </span><strong data-path-to-node="3,0,0" data-index-in-node="0"><span class="citation-2428">TRUE</span></strong><span class="citation-2428"> if the statement agrees with th</span><span class="citation-2427 citation-2428 citation-end-2428">e information,</span><strong data-path-to-node="3,1,0" data-index-in-node="0"><span class="citation-2425 citation-2426">FALSE</span></strong><span class="citation-2425 citation-2426 citation-end-2426"> if the statement contradicts the inform</span><span class="citation-2425 citation-end-2425">ation,</span><strong data-path-to-node="3,2,0" data-index-in-node="0"><span class="citation-2424">NOT GIVEN</span></strong><span class="citation-2424 citation-end-2424"> if there is no information on this</span></p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Cuneiform tablets were produced in different shapes and sizes."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "When Sumerian writers marked the clay tablets, the tablets were dry."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Cuneiform was often difficult to read because of its size."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "A number of languages adopted cuneiform."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Cuneiform signs can be found in some modern alphabets."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"0\"> </p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. Cuneiform tablets were produced in different shapes and sizes. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…most often inscribed on <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"39\">palm-sized, rectangular</strong> clay tablets… although occasionally <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"101\">larger tablets or cylinders</strong> were used.” (Đoạn 1)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc liệt kê nhiều hình dạng (chữ nhật, hình trụ) và kích cỡ (vừa lòng bàn tay, hoặc lớn hơn).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. When Sumerian writers marked the clay tablets, the tablets were dry. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Sumerian writers would impress these lines into the <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"64\">wet clay</strong> with a stylus…” (Đoạn 2)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Người viết ấn bút lên đất sét khi nó còn <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">ướt</strong> (<em data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">wet</em>), trái ngược hoàn toàn với ý “đã khô” (<em data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"101\">dry</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. Cuneiform was often difficult to read because of its size. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> \"...Oddly, the signs were often almost <strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">too small to see with the naked eye</strong>.\"</li>\n<li data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc các ký tự quá nhỏ để nhìn bằng mắt thường (<strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">too small to see with the naked eye</strong>) đồng nghĩa với việc chúng rất khó đọc (<strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"136\">difficult to read</strong>) do kích thước (<strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"170\">size</strong>) tí hon của mình.</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. A number of languages adopted cuneiform. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Cuneiform signs were used for the writing of <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">at least a dozen languages</strong>.” (Đoạn 2)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “At least a dozen” (ít nhất 12) tương ứng với “a number of languages”.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. Cuneiform signs can be found in some modern alphabets. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “In fact, it <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">died out and remained unintelligible</strong> for almost 2,000 years.” (Đoạn 7)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài viết cho biết hệ thống này đã hoàn toàn biến mất và không còn ai hiểu được trong 2.000 năm cho đến khi Rawlinson giải mã. Nó không để lại dấu vết trực tiếp trong các bảng chữ cái hiện đại.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('10a90890-3e8b-4050-9252-f10cb2672840', '0778d422-07f1-437e-ada1-069a2f7d5b56', 'fillup', 'Questions 18–21', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<p>Complete the summary below:</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="quests-des">
<div class="content-write">
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>The history of herbal medicines in New Zealand</strong></span></p>
<p>Originally, the Maori people consumed plants to help deal with {pain} and also as food. When Europeans settled in the country, a  {book} by James Neil showed that some of them also recognized the medicinal value of native plants. However, criticism of herbal medicine appeared in one newspaper in 1907. The following year, the use of herbal medicines was made more difficult because of a new {law} , and for a time in the mid-20th century, they were largely ignored. Then, in the 1980s, a number of institutions started offering a  {course}<span class="fill-history-correct"> </span> in the subject, although for many years there was still little evidence to support their use because doctors and academics were not interested.</p>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. {pain}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn B):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…the forest was well stocked with edible plants that were an obvious source of nutrition, but that were taken for the <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"141\">relief of pain</strong> as well.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Người Maori dùng cây cỏ làm thức ăn (nutrition/food) và để giảm đau (relief of pain).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. {book}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn B):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…in his <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"31\">book</strong> published in 1891, herbalist James Neil described manuka and koromiko as among New Zealand’s most valuable herbs.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> James Neil đã công nhận giá trị của thảo dược bản địa thông qua cuốn sách xuất bản năm 1891 của ông.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. {law}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn C):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“In 1908 the government passed a controversial <strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">law</strong> that had the effect of restricting traditional herbal practice…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Một đạo luật mới (law) năm 1908 đã gây khó khăn và hạn chế việc hành nghề thảo dược truyền thống.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. {course}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn C):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…it became possible to complete a <strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">course</strong> in herbal medicine at several polytechnics around the country.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Vào những năm 1980, các trường bách khoa (institutions) bắt đầu cung cấp các khóa học (course) về chủ đề này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('8ed3d11f-c09f-4d45-b9cf-e1d1b92325fb', 'd2ed4252-3025-458e-9ad8-0feb733d39aa', 'fillup', 'Questions 6–13', '<p data-path-to-node="8">Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="8">Write your answers in boxes 6–13 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="8"><strong>The Development and Translation of Cuneiform</strong></p>
<p data-path-to-node="9"><strong data-path-to-node="9" data-index-in-node="0">Before cuneiform</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="10">
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="10,0,0">tokens, for example {stones} were often used</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="10,1,0">the first tokens were kept in containers made of {cloth}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="10,2,0">tokens were used as a {receipt} to give when selling something</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-path-to-node="11"><strong data-path-to-node="11" data-index-in-node="0">By the 4th century BCE</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="12">
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="12,0,0">tokens were put in a container that looked like a clay {envelope}</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-path-to-node="13"><strong data-path-to-node="13" data-index-in-node="0">Complex, abstract symbols developed</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="14">
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="14,0,0">at first, signs looked like what they indicated, e.g. {sheep}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="14,1,0">then signs became more abstract</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="14,2,0">eventually, cuneiform signs shaped like {triangles} were developed</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="14,3,0">according to experts, cuneiform was mainly used for {accounting}</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-path-to-node="15"><strong data-path-to-node="15" data-index-in-node="0">19th-century translation of cuneiform inscriptions by Henry Rawlinson</strong></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="16">
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="16,0,0">Rawlinson found cuneiform inscriptions in the Behistun Mountains</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="16,1,0">Rawlinson copied the inscriptions onto {paper}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="16,2,0">Rawlinson realised that each word of the inscriptions appeared in three languages</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="16,3,0">When translated, Rawlinson found that the writings were about a 5th-century BCE king</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. …tokens, for example {stones} were often used.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…they might take small <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"37\">stones</strong> and use them as tokens…” (Đoạn 3)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. …the first tokens were kept in containers made of {cloth}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “These tokens might then be placed in a <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"51\">cloth</strong> container…” (Đoạn 3)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. …tokens were used as a {receipt} to give when selling something.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…provided to a buyer as a <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"40\">receipt</strong> for a transaction…” (Đoạn 3)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. …tokens were put in a container that looked like a clay {envelope}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…putting tokens in a container resembling an <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">envelope</strong>, one made of clay…” (Đoạn 4)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. …signs looked like what they indicated, e.g. {sheep}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “For example, an image which resembled the drawing of a <strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">sheep</strong> meant just that.” (Đoạn 5)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. …eventually, cuneiform signs shaped like {triangles} were developed.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"26\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…the signs took the form of <strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">triangles</strong>, which became common cuneiform signs.” (Đoạn 5)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. …according to experts, cuneiform was mainly used for {accounting}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"28\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “…most linguists and historians agree cuneiform developed primarily as a tool for <strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"95\">accounting</strong>.” (Đoạn 6)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. …Rawlinson copied the inscriptions onto {paper}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"30\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Trích dẫn:</strong> “Rawlinson made impressions of the marks on large pieces of <strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"71\">paper</strong>…” (Đoạn 7)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('9f174546-ffe6-4113-bc74-d172f547b0df', '6e0201f9-2dcb-4c0d-a308-13ba8d5cb852', 'matrix', 'Questions 36–40', '', '<p data-start="1280" data-end="1360">Look at the following statements (Questions 36–40) and the list of people below.</p>
<p data-start="1362" data-end="1421">Match each statement with the correct person, A, B, C or D.</p>
<p data-start="1423" data-end="1499">Write the correct letter, A, B, C or D</p>
<p data-start="1501" data-end="1542"><strong>NB </strong>You may use any letter more than once.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": "List of People", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Knowing the exact location of space junk would help prevent any possible danger", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Space should be available to everyone and should be preserved for the future", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "A recommendation regarding satellites is widely ignored", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "There is conflicting information about where some satellites are in space.", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "There is a risk we will not be able to undo the damage that occurs in space.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "Carolin Frueh", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "Holger Krag", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "Marlon Sorge", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "Moriba Jah", "categoryLetter": "D"}]}', 'null', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('20852445-eef5-4bdd-bf2a-cd28d24c2053', 'c0247014-9198-4a16-9bbe-34a54aedee30', 'fillup', 'Questions 21 – 27', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY </strong>from the text for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 21-27 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;" data-path-to-node="8"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong data-path-to-node="8" data-index-in-node="0">Global Traders Corporation – Summary of Benefits</strong></span></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="9">
<li>
<p>Rates of pay: individual {performance} is taken into account.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Extras: a {bonus} based on profits is paid each year.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Pension: based on {contributions}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Holidays: dependent on length of service</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Death in service: a fixed amount payable to the {beneficiary}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Leisure: for most employees the cost of family holidays at company locations is {subsidised}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Career development: various {opportunities} are available.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Funding is available for those who want to carry on learning – work-related or otherwise.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Employees with long service history are entitled to extended {leave} which is paid.</p>
</li>
</ul>', '', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. Rates of pay: individual {performance} is taken into account.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Our policy is to pay employees… as much above that [market rate] as is <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"85\">justified by performance</strong>.”</em> (Mục Pay)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Taken into account” (được xem xét/tính đến) đồng nghĩa với “justified by”. Mức lương sẽ dựa trên kết quả làm việc (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"128\">performance</strong>) của từng cá nhân.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. Extras: a {bonus} based on profits is paid each year.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The most tangible advantage… is the <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">annual bonus</strong>, where we <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">distribute a proportion of profits</strong> to employees.”</em> (Mục Pay)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Extras” (khoản thêm) ở đây là tiền thưởng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"56\">bonus</strong>). Khoản này được trích từ lợi nhuận (profits) và chi trả hàng năm (annual/each year).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. Pension: based on {contributions}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The amount received on retirement will depend on the level of <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"74\">regular contributions</strong> made by the employee…”</em> (Mục Pension)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Based on” đồng nghĩa với “depend on”. Số tiền hưu trí nhận được phụ thuộc vào mức đóng góp (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"105\">contributions</strong>) định kỳ của nhân viên.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. Death in service: a fixed amount payable to the {beneficiary}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“If you die in service, our scheme will pay three times your annual salary to your <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">beneficiary</strong>.”</em> (Mục Life Assurance)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Fixed amount” (khoản tiền cố định) ở đây cụ thể là gấp 3 lần lương năm. Người nhận khoản tiền này được gọi là người thụ hưởng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"140\">beneficiary</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. Leisure: for most employees the cost of family holidays at company locations is {subsidised}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…where they can take holidays with their families at a <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"69\">subsidised</strong> rate.”</em> (Mục Holiday and Leisure)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Cost” tương ứng với “rate”. Các kỳ nghỉ gia đình tại địa điểm của công ty được tính theo mức giá ưu đãi/được trợ giá (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"131\">subsidised</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. Career development: various {opportunities} are available.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“The corporation offers business, technical and personal development through a range of <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">flexible opportunities</strong>.”</em> (Mục Career and Personal Development)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Various” (đa dạng) đồng nghĩa với “a range of”. Công ty cung cấp nhiều cơ hội (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"92\">opportunities</strong>) khác nhau để phát triển sự nghiệp.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. Employees with long service history are entitled to extended {leave} which is paid.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Employees with <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"27\">more than 25 years’ service</strong> [long service history] can take <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"87\">paid leave</strong> for six months.”</em> (Mục Extended Leave)</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Are entitled to” (có quyền hưởng) tương ứng với “can take”. Những người làm việc lâu năm được hưởng kỳ nghỉ dài hạn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"130\">leave</strong>) vẫn có lương.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('62241813-e245-4caa-bf8b-aed44b618942', '0298fbaa-aa2c-4dc8-b84e-13cc558b2b29', 'matrix', 'Questions 28 – 33', '', '<p data-path-to-node="3"><em data-path-to-node="3" data-index-in-node="88">Write the correct letter, <strong data-path-to-node="3" data-index-in-node="114">A-G</strong>, in boxes 28-33 on your answer sheet.</em></p>
<p data-path-to-node="4"><strong data-path-to-node="4" data-index-in-node="0">NB</strong> <em data-path-to-node="4" data-index-in-node="3">You may use any letter more than once.</em></p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "an example of how long it takes to catch up on sleep", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "the process of collecting information to help solve sleep problems", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "details of the physical effects of lack of sleep on the body", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "the average amount of sleep people have", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "a possible future solution for everybody suffering from sleep deprivation", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "a comparison between past and present research findings", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}]}', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. An example of how long it takes to catch up on sleep — {C}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“They slept less through the second and third weeks, as they finished <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"81\">paying back an average of 17 hours’ sleep debt</strong> accumulated before the experiment began.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn C mô tả thí nghiệm của Thomas Wehr, trong đó các tình nguyện viên mất khoảng 3 tuần để “trả nợ” (catch up/pay back) 17 giờ thiếu ngủ trước đó.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. The process of collecting information to help solve sleep problems — {F}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…patients are asked to arrive around 8.30pm and are then shown to a room where <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"93\">sensors are attached to their limbs, chest, abdomen, head… Throughout the night, the sensors gather data</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn F mô tả quy trình (process) cụ thể tại phòng khám giấc ngủ: từ việc điền bảng hỏi đến việc gắn các cảm biến để thu thập dữ liệu (collecting information/gather data) suốt đêm.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30. Details of the physical effects of lack of sleep on the body — {D}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Lack of sleep could <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"32\">drive down growth hormones</strong>… Another hormone, <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"79\">leptin</strong>, tells us when we should feel full… associate lack of sleep with <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"153\">changes in immune response</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn D liệt kê chi tiết các tác động vật lý (physical effects) như thay đổi hormone tăng trưởng, hormone gây thèm ăn (leptin) và hệ thống miễn dịch.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. The average amount of sleep people have — {A}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“According to the US National Sleep Foundation, each weekday night people typically <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"95\">get an hour and six minutes less than the eight hours</strong>…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn A đưa ra con số thống kê cụ thể về lượng thời gian ngủ trung bình (average amount) mà mọi người thực tế có so với khuyến nghị của chuyên gia.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. A possible future solution for everybody suffering from sleep deprivation — {G}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Eventually sleep researchers may come up with an <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"61\">easy solution</strong>. By studying sleep, they hope to <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"108\">develop drugs</strong> that could help six-hour-a-nighters enjoy the alertness…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn cuối (G) nói về kỳ vọng trong tương lai (future solution) là phát triển các loại thuốc giúp những người chỉ ngủ 6 tiếng vẫn khỏe mạnh như ngủ đủ giấc.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. A comparison between past and present research findings — {D}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Earlier studies showed</strong> that people… could recover quickly… But <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"79\">recent studies have begun to home in on today’s reality</strong>…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn D đối chiếu giữa các nghiên cứu cũ/trước đây (earlier studies) vốn cho rằng thiếu ngủ ít để lại hậu quả, với các nghiên cứu gần đây/hiện tại (recent/today’s reality) cho thấy những rủi ro sức khỏe nghiêm trọng.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('2d87ca2d-4021-4e94-b300-50aa77b19dc4', 'fcf05334-6efa-4d54-8741-9c0cfdfa0ce3', 'fillup', 'Questions 1 - 10', '<p>Complete the notes below.<br>White <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 69.5278%; height: 798.105px; border-spacing: 1px; border: 1px solid rgb(0, 0, 0);" border="1"><colgroup><col style="width: 100%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr style="height: 33.6133px;">
<td style="border-color: #000000; border-width: 1px; padding: 1px; text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong> Accommodation request</strong></span></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 95.1562px;">
<td style="border-color: #000000; border-width: 1px; padding: 1px;">
<p> Example</p>
<p> Name: <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em>Anna Black</em></span></strong></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 669.336px;">
<td style="border-color: #000000; border-width: 1px; padding: 1px;">
<p> Type of accommodation:                         a house</p>
<p> Preferred location:                                   <span class="citation-3305 citation-3306 citation-3307">the {southeast}<span class="citation-3305 citation-3306 citation-3307 citation-end-3307"> of the town</span></span></p>
<p> Facilities required:                                   <span class="citation-3305 citation-3306 citation-3307 citation-end-3307"><span class="citation-3302 citation-3303 citation-3304">furnished property- with a </span><span class="citation-3302 citation-3303 citation-3304 citation-end-3304">{washing machine}</span></span></p>
<p> Period of time required:                           <span class="citation-3302 citation-3303 citation-3304 citation-end-3304">one year</span></p>
<p> Start date of rental period:                       {15th May| 15 May| May 15th| May 15}</p>
<p> Present address:                                     <span class="citation-3302 citation-3303 citation-3304 citation-end-3304">56, Stone Street</span></p>
<p><span class="citation-3290 citation-3291 citation-3292 citation-end-3292"> Phone<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="22"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-3290 citation-3291"> number:                                        <span class="citation-3302 citation-3303 citation-3304 citation-end-3304">(mobile) 07942 326584</span></span></p>
<p><span class="citation-3290 citation-3291"><span class="citation-3289 citation-end-3289"> Re<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="25"><!----></sup></span>ference from:                                       <span class="citation-3302 citation-3303 citation-3304 citation-end-3304">her {employer}</span></span></p>
<p><span class="citation-3290 citation-3291"> Maximum rent:                                         <span class="citation-3302 citation-3303 citation-3304 citation-end-3304"><span class="math-inline" data-math="£" data-index-in-node="14">£</span> {675} per month</span></span></p>
<p><span class="citation-3290 citation-3291"> Appl<span class="citation-3287 citation-3288">icant’s job:                                         <span class="citation-3302 citation-3303 citation-3304 citation-end-3304">{a translator|translator }</span></span></span></p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong><span class="citation-3287 citation-3288"> Documents to be supplied</span></strong></p>
<p><span class="citation-3287 citation-3288"><span class="citation-3283 citation-3284"> ID check:</span>                                                   <span class="citation-3302 citation-3303 citation-3304 citation-end-3304">applicant’s passport</span></span></p>
<p><span class="citation-3287 citation-3288"> Credit check:                                             <span class="citation-3302 citation-3303 citation-3304 citation-end-3304"><span class="citation-3281 citation-3282">a {bank statement}</span><span class="citation-3281 citation-3282 citation-end-3282">.</span></span></span></p>
<p> </p>
<p id="p-rc_b53f6cabbef76016-98" data-path-to-node="7"><span class="citation-3279 citation-3280 citation-end-3280"> Viewing arrangements<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="34"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-3279 citation-end-3279"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="35"><!----></sup></span></p>
<p data-path-to-node="7"><span class="citation-3279 citation-3280 citation-end-3280"><span class="citation-3277 citation-3278"> Address of property:</span>                                  <span class="citation-3281 citation-3282 citation-end-3282"><span class="citation-3277 citation-3278">33, {Ainsworth}</span><span class="citation-3277 citation-3278 citation-end-3278"> Street</span></span></span></p>
<p data-path-to-node="7"><span class="citation-3279 citation-3280 citation-end-3280"> Viewing day and time:                               <span class="citation-3277 citation-3278 citation-end-3278">Saturday 4 p.m</span></span></p>
<p><span class="citation-3279 citation-3280 citation-end-3280"> To check:                                                   <span class="citation-3277 citation-3278 citation-end-3278"><span class="citation-3273 citation-3274">Is there a {telephone}</span><span class="citation-3273 citation-3274 citation-end-3274"> in the house?</span></span></span></p>
<p><span class="citation-3273 citation-3274 citation-end-3274">                                                                   <span class="citation-3273 citation-3274 citation-end-3274"><span class="citation-3271 citation-3272">Is there a {bus stop}</span><span class="citation-3271 citation-end-3271"> nearby?</span></span></span></p>
<p><!----><!----></p>
<p><span class="citation-3287 citation-3288"><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></span></p>
<p id="p-rc_b53f6cabbef76016-99" data-path-to-node="8,0,0"></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p> </p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 1: ACCOMMODATION REQUEST</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Good morning, how can I help you?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> I''m interested in renting somewhere to live in town and was wondering what you had available.</p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_9cea803bb3ba25a6-161\" data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> <span class=\"citation-2101 citation-end-2101\">Excellent. I''ll just need to find out a bit more about what you''re looking for and then we can see what we''ve got. So your name is?</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><span class=\"citation-2101 citation-end-2101\"><strong>Anna:</strong>Anna Black </span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><span class=\"citation-2101 citation-end-2101\"><strong>Agent: </strong>Good, got that. And what sort of accommodation are you looking for ideal<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"1\"><!----></sup></span>ly?</p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> Well, I don''t know if this is going to be possible, but ideally a house. I live in a flat at the moment and I''ve got really noisy neighbours. That''s the reason I want to move.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Oh dear. And I''m afraid most of the accommodation for rent in the city centre is flats. Would you be prepared to look elsewhere? There are a lot of nice properties in the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"178\">(Q1) southeast</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> Oh yes, that would be really convenient for me. Quite a few of my friends are there and it would be really close to my work.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> And there''s more chance of finding what you''re after there. I take it you''d be looking for a furnished place, would you?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> Yes. And I know it''s not always included, but I''d like to have a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"71\">(Q2) washing machine</strong></span>. I hate going to laundrettes and if I''m a bit further out of the city, it might be a problem to find one.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> I''ll see what I can do. Now, how long would you need the property for, bearing in mind that the minimum is six months?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> One year. I don''t want to chop and change too often and that''d give me the chance to see how things work out,and then I could reassess the situation after that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Mm-hmm. And when would you like to move in?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> I''ve got to be out of my present place by April 30th, then I''m going to visit my parents for a couple of weeks, so let''s say <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"131\">(Q3) 15th of May</strong> (or <strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"152\">15 May</strong>)</span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> And what''s your current address? I''d better make a note of that for our files,and I''ll put that you''re there only until the end of April.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong>Anna:</strong>56 Stone Street?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong>Agent:</strong>Mm-hmm.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> And is there a phone number I can get you on?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> Yes, the best one to use is my mobile and that''s 07942 326584.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Now of course we''ll need a reference before we''re able to proceed with any contract. Who would be able to supply you with a reference?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> I''m pretty sure my <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">(Q4) employer</strong></span> will do that for me. I don''t really know my doctor or anyone like that here.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Good. Now let''s see what we''ve got that might suit you. Oh, first, how much are you looking to pay?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> I''m paying £650 a month at the moment and the most I can go to is <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"72\">(Q5) 675</strong></span>. I really can''t go over that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> That shouldn''t be any problem. It''s a realistic figure. And can I ask what it is you do for a living?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> Since I came here, I''ve been working for various bodies within the city as a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"83\">(Q6) translator</strong></span>, you know, for the police and the hospital.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"26\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">DOCUMENTS &amp; VIEWING (Questions 7–10)</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Now, if we do find something, we''ll need to check your ID, so we''ll need to see your passport. And of course, to do the credit check, we''ll need to see a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"161\">(Q7) bank statement</strong></span> in order to complete all the paperwork.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> No problem, I can bring this in tomorrow.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Good. Now, we''ve got a small house to rent that I think might be just what you''re looking for. 33 <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"105\">(Q8) Ainsworth</strong></span> Street.That''s A-I-N-S-W-O-R-T-H Street. Here are the details.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> This looks great. Right size, right price.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Well, I can arrange for you to view it on Saturday around 4:00 pm if that''s convenient.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> Sounds good. I can''t see any mention of a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"48\">(Q9) telephone</strong></span> in the details, though. I''d need that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Hmm, I''ll look into that and I can double check when we''re at the property.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> And sorry, there''s another thing. Do you happen to know if there''s a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"75\">(Q10) bus stop</strong></span> reasonably close to the house so that I can get around easily?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"36\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"36\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Again, if I can''t find out before Saturday, I''ll check it out when we''re there.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"37\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> Okay, so I''ll drop by tomorrow with those papers you need and then see you at the property Saturday at 4:00 pm.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37\"><strong>Agent:</strong> Excellent. </p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('c50696ec-935a-4e1c-bc97-56079724e8fa', '0298fbaa-aa2c-4dc8-b84e-13cc558b2b29', 'matrix', 'Questions 34 – 36', '', '<p data-path-to-node="8"><em data-path-to-node="8" data-index-in-node="167">Write the correct letter, <strong data-path-to-node="8" data-index-in-node="193">A, B, C</strong> or <strong data-path-to-node="8" data-index-in-node="204">D</strong>, in boxes 34-36 on your answer sheet.</em></p>
<p data-path-to-node="9"><strong data-path-to-node="9" data-index-in-node="0">NB</strong> <em data-path-to-node="9" data-index-in-node="3">You may use any letter more than once.</em></p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": "List of Names", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "For every hour of sleep we miss, we should sleep an hour longer.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "Sleep affects how efficiently we work.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "Adults require an average of eight hours'' sleep a night.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "David Dinges", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "Thomas Wehr", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "Eve Van Cauter", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "Jeffrey Lipsitz", "categoryLetter": "D"}]}', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. For every hour of sleep we miss, we should sleep an hour longer. — {B} Thomas Wehr</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn C):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“‘Making up lost sleep is basic arithmetic. <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"64\">For every hour</strong> — or fraction — under eight, <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"108\">you need an equal extra amount of sleep</strong> soon after,’ says <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"166\">Wehr</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thomas Wehr so sánh việc bù đắp giấc ngủ như “phép tính cơ bản” (basic arithmetic). Cụm từ “equal extra amount” (một lượng bổ sung tương đương) chính là việc ngủ thêm đúng bằng số giờ đã thiếu (sleep an hour longer).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. Sleep affects how efficiently we work. — {A} David Dinges</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn A):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“‘Businesses and society as a whole are being victimised by not getting enough sleep,’ says <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"112\">David Dinges</strong>… ‘Our <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"133\">productivity</strong>, our safety and our health are at risk.’”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Productivity” (năng suất) chính là thước đo cho việc chúng ta làm việc hiệu quả đến mức nào (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"106\">how efficiently we work</strong>). David Dinges cảnh báo rằng thiếu ngủ sẽ đặt năng suất làm việc của chúng ta vào tình thế nguy hiểm (at risk).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. Adults require an average of eight hours’ sleep a night. — {B} Thomas Wehr</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn C):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Thomas <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"28\">Wehr</strong>… has found that in the absence of lights, the <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"81\">natural length of that ride [sleep] is just over eight hours</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Qua thí nghiệm kéo dài 4 tuần, Wehr kết luận rằng thời gian ngủ tự nhiên của con người là hơn 8 tiếng một chút. Con số này khớp với nhận định về nhu cầu trung bình 8 tiếng/đêm của người trưởng thành.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('6449aab4-1913-47bd-953f-f0dbed0476b6', 'f7dc7a4b-b9f3-42db-8b14-ddf0441a6da6', 'fillup', 'Questions 1–5', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 150%; background: white;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: black;">Complete the notes below.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 150%; background: white;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: black;">Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; text-align: center; line-height: 150%; background: white;" align="center"><strong><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 16.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: black;">Carnivorous Plants</span></strong></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 150%; background: white;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: black;">Darwin’s experiments:</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 150%; background: white;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: black;">Drosera</span></p>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="circle">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #15191e; margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 150%; mso-list: l3 level1 lfo1; background: white;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: black;">He put insects and small amounts of meat onto leaves and observed what happened.</span></li>
</ul>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="circle">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #15191e; margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 150%; mso-list: l7 level1 lfo6; background: white;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: black;">He was amazed that one human hair triggered a response.</span></li>
</ul>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="circle">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #15191e; margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 150%; mso-list: l9 level1 lfo7; background: white;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: black;">He understood why the plant did not respond to {raindrops}</span></li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 150%; background: white;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: black;">Venus Flytrap</span></p>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="circle">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #15191e; margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 150%; mso-list: l4 level1 lfo8; background: white;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: black;">He demonstrated how leaves close and then, for a short period, act like a {stomach}</span></li>
</ul>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="circle">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #15191e; margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 150%; mso-list: l10 level1 lfo9; background: white;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: black;">He noted the structure of leaves ensures small insects are released.</span></li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 150%; background: white;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: black;">Biology today:</span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 150%; background: white;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: black;">Venus Flytrap</span></p>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="circle">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #15191e; margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 150%; mso-list: l12 level1 lfo10; background: white;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: black;">If insects come into contact with leaf hairs, their movement produces an electric charge.</span></li>
</ul>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="circle">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #15191e; margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 150%; mso-list: l5 level1 lfo11; background: white;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: black;">The charge enters fluid-filled tunnels, causing {pores}</span><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';">.in the cell walls to open.</span></li>
</ul>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="circle">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #15191e; margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 150%; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo12; background: white;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: black;">Water moves between cells and then the leaf changes from convex to concave, trapping the insect inside.</span></li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 150%; background: white;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: black;">Bladderwort</span></p>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="circle">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #15191e; margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 150%; mso-list: l2 level1 lfo13; background: white;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: black;">Hairs bend when insects swim past, resulting in opening of a flap.</span></li>
</ul>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="circle">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #15191e; margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 150%; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo2; background: white;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: black;">Water is sucked in.</span></li>
</ul>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="circle">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #15191e; margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 150%; mso-list: l6 level1 lfo3; background: white;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: black;">When water is pumped out of bladder cells, a {vacuum}</span><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman'';"> builds up inside.</span></li>
</ul>
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 150%; background: white;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: black;">Pitcher Plants</span></p>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="circle">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #15191e; margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 150%; mso-list: l8 level1 lfo4; background: white;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: black;">The plants have tube-shaped leaves that insects fall into.</span></li>
</ul>
<ul style="margin-top: 0in;" type="circle">
<li class="MsoNormal" style="color: #15191e; margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: 150%; mso-list: l11 level1 lfo5; background: white;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 11.0pt; line-height: 150%; font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: black;">Some plants are big enough to capture and eat {frogs}</span></li>
</ul>
', NULL, 'fill-in-the-blank', NULL, NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p><strong>1. He understood why the plant did not respond to raindrops</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>raindrops</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 1) “Yet sundews, he observed, ignored <strong>raindrops</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Darwin nhận thấy cây gọng vó (sundews) lờ đi giọt mưa để tránh phản ứng sai và tốn năng lượng.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>2. He demonstrated how leaves close and then, for a short period, act like a stomach</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>stomach</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) “…it formed itself into a temporary ‘<strong>stomach</strong>’…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Lá cây bắt ruồi Venus khi kẹp lại hoạt động như một “dạ dày” tạm thời.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>3. The charge enters fluid-filled tunnels, causing pores in the cell walls to open.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>pores</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) “…which opens up <strong>pores</strong> in cell membranes.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Dòng điện mở ra các lỗ (pores) trên màng tế bào, kích hoạt sự thay đổi hình dạng.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>4. When water is pumped out of bladder cells, a vacuum builds up inside.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>vacuum</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “…creating a new <strong>vacuum</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Việc bơm nước ra ngoài tạo ra một chân không (vacuum) bên trong bọng.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>5. Some plants are big enough to capture and eat frogs</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>frogs</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “…and can consume whole <strong>frogs</strong> unlucky enough to fall into them.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Các cây nắp ấm lớn có thể bắt và ăn cả ếch (frogs).</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('4f381fd8-ae31-4d7c-bfec-3ca892b49610', '0298fbaa-aa2c-4dc8-b84e-13cc558b2b29', 'fillup', 'Questions 37 – 40', '<p>Answer the questions below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>NO MORE THAN THREE WORDS AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> from the text for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 37-40 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p>How long will it take to fall asleep during the day if you suffer from sleep loss? {Ten minutes}</p>
<p>What kind of food do our bodies believe they need when we don’t produce enough leptin? {Carbohydrates}</p>
<p>How much melatonin does Dr Wurtman recommend for older patients? {0.3mg}</p>
<p>What are used to collect data from overnight patients at a sleep clinic? {Sensors}</p>', '', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. How long will it take to fall asleep during the day if you suffer from sleep loss? — {Ten minutes}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn C):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“‘It’s easy to tell if you’re sleep-deprived,’ says Wehr; ‘if you can lie down in the middle of the day and <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"128\">fall asleep in ten minutes</strong>, you have shortchanged yourself on sleep.’”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Sleep loss” tương ứng với “sleep-deprived” (thiếu ngủ). Theo Thomas Wehr, nếu bạn có thể ngủ thiếp đi chỉ trong <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"125\">10 phút</strong> vào ban ngày, đó là dấu hiệu rõ ràng của việc thiếu ngủ.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. What kind of food do our bodies believe they need when we don’t produce enough leptin? — {Carbohydrates}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn D):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“‘With the low leptin levels caused by lack of sleep,’ Van Cauter says, ‘…you will <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"105\">crave carbohydrates</strong> even though you’ve had enough to eat.’”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Don’t produce enough leptin” tương ứng với “low leptin levels”. Khi thiếu hormone này, cơ thể sẽ có cảm giác thèm (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"128\">crave</strong>) mãnh liệt các loại thực phẩm chứa tinh bột/đường (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"185\">carbohydrates</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. How much melatonin does Dr Wurtman recommend for older patients? — {0.3mg}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn E):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“‘A <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">dose of 0.3mg</strong> completely restores sleep to normal… says <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"82\">Dr Richard Wurtman</strong>…’”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc đề cập đến việc dùng melatonin liều thấp cho người cao tuổi bị mất ngủ. Dr. Wurtman khẳng định liều lượng <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"126\">0.3mg</strong> là hiệu quả nhất để phục hồi giấc ngủ bình thường.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. What are used to collect data from overnight patients at a sleep clinic? — {Sensors}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn F):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…patients are… shown to a room where <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"62\">sensors are attached</strong> to their limbs… Throughout the night, the <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"127\">sensors gather data</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Collect data” đồng nghĩa với “gather data”. Công cụ được sử dụng để thực hiện việc này tại phòng khám giấc ngủ chính là các thiết bị cảm biến (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"156\">sensors</strong>).</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('4519d669-1c74-4005-b862-fdefc6eaf7e8', '79f10791-9afb-4301-9429-373f129c6fc5', 'radio', 'Questions 1–6', '', '<p data-start="181" data-end="221">Choose: <strong data-start="223" data-end="231">TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information, <strong data-start="280" data-end="289">FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information, <strong data-start="338" data-end="351">NOT GIVEN </strong>if there is no information on this</p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "You may have several IRD numbers during your lifetime."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Students require an IRD number when setting up a bank account."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Children are automatically given an IRD number at birth."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Your employer has the right to ask you for your IRD number."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Your IRD number is given on all letters the Inland Revenue send you."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "You can apply for an IRD number for a club."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. You may have several IRD numbers during your lifetime. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“An IRD number is a <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"31\">unique</strong> number… Your number will <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">never change</strong>, even if you move to another country and then return…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài viết khẳng định mã số IRD là duy nhất và “không bao giờ thay đổi”. Do đó, việc nói bạn có thể có vài số (several numbers) là sai.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. Students require an IRD number when setting up a bank account. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Bài có nhắc đến việc sinh viên cần IRD khi đăng ký vay vốn (<em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"71\">student loan organization</em>) và ngân hàng (<em data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"112\">bank</em>) có quyền hỏi số IRD.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tuy nhiên, bài <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"27\">không khẳng định</strong> rằng sinh viên bắt buộc phải có IRD “khi thiết lập tài khoản ngân hàng”. Đây là sự kết hợp thông tin không có trong văn bản.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. Children are automatically given an IRD number at birth. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“It is <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"18\">not compulsory</strong> for every individual (e.g. baby, child) to have an IRD number… You can <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"106\">ask for</strong> an IRD number for… your children…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> IRD không được cấp tự động mà bạn phải chủ động yêu cầu/đăng ký (<em data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"77\">ask for</em>) cho con mình nếu cần.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. Your employer has the right to ask you for your IRD number. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“You must only provide it on request to the Inland Revenue, <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"71\">your employer</strong>, or your bank…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản liệt kê chủ lao động (employer) là một trong những đối tượng bạn phải cung cấp mã số khi họ yêu cầu.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. Your IRD number is given on all letters the Inland Revenue send you. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“If you cannot remember your IRD number, check <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">any correspondence</strong> you have from us – your IRD number <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"112\">will be on this</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Any correspondence” (bất kỳ thư từ giao dịch nào) đồng nghĩa với “all letters”. Bài viết xác nhận mã số sẽ nằm trên đó.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. You can apply for an IRD number for a club. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“IR596 (non-individual) – company, partnership, estate, <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">club</strong>, society…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Mẫu đơn IR596 liệt kê cụ thể “club” (câu lạc bộ) là đối tượng có thể đăng ký mã số IRD.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e2b89444-d962-49f9-95a7-ec7649ddd691', '79f10791-9afb-4301-9429-373f129c6fc5', 'matrix', 'Questions 7–14', '', '<p data-start="908" data-end="974">Write the correct letter, A–F, in boxes 7–14 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p data-start="976" data-end="1021"><strong data-start="976" data-end="982">NB</strong> You may use any letter more than once.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "It has changed its name.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "It has recently been renovated.", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "It was once used for another purpose", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "It is possible to make your own drinks in this hotel.", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "Its restaurant serves both expensive and cheap meals.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "It has special facilities for holding meetings.", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "It would suit guests with limited mobility.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "Its bedrooms all have their own bathroom.", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. It has changed its name. — {A} Hotel 53</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Hotel 53 (<strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"22\">formerly the Quality Hotel York</strong>).”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Từ “formerly” (trước đây là) cho thấy khách sạn này đã đổi tên.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. It has recently been renovated. — {F} Novotel</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Newly refurbished</strong>, the hotel is located…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Refurbished” là từ đồng nghĩa hoàn hảo của “renovated” (được tân trang, đại tu).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. It was once used for another purpose. — {C} Best Western</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…carefully <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">converted from a 17th-century farmhouse</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trước khi làm khách sạn, nơi này là một trang trại (farmhouse). “Converted” nghĩa là được chuyển đổi công năng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. It is possible to make your own drinks in this hotel. — {D} Heworth Court</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“All rooms are en suite with <strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"40\">tea/coffee making facilities</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Có thiết bị pha trà/cà phê nghĩa là khách có thể tự làm đồ uống trong phòng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. Its restaurant serves both expensive and cheap meals. — {A} Hotel 53</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"26\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…features a restaurant offering an <strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"49\">extensive menu to suit all budgets</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ “suit all budgets” (phù hợp với mọi túi tiền) ám giá cả có cả mức rẻ và đắt.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. It has special facilities for holding meetings. — {F} Novotel</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"28\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…features <strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">10 conference rooms</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Phòng hội thảo (conference rooms) chính là cơ sở vật chất phục vụ hội họp (meetings).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. It would suit guests with limited mobility. — {B} Holgate Hill Hotel</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"30\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Rooms with <strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"23\">disabled access</strong>… are available on request.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Disabled access” (lối đi cho người khuyết tật) là tiện nghi dành cho những người gặp khó khăn trong việc đi lại (limited mobility).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. Its bedrooms all have their own bathroom. — {D} Heworth Court</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"32\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“All rooms are <strong data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">en suite</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trong ngành khách sạn, “en suite” có nghĩa là phòng ngủ có nhà vệ sinh/phòng tắm riêng khép kín bên trong.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('6d26f03d-c728-4e02-a6b2-6e9708f29365', '39e1f6ca-cafc-48b9-99d7-e814b1416aea', 'radio', 'Questions 1–7', '', '<p>Choose <strong data-path-to-node="5,0" data-index-in-node="0">TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information ,<strong data-path-to-node="5,0" data-index-in-node="65">FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information ,<strong data-path-to-node="5,0" data-index-in-node="130">NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this</p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Archaeological research had taken place on the island of Obi before the arrival of Ceri Shipton and his colleagues."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "At the Kelo sites, the researchers found the first clam shell axes ever to be discovered in the region."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The size of Obi today is less than it was 18,000 years ago."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "A change in the climate around 11,700 years ago had a greater impact on Obi than on the surrounding islands."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The researchers believe there is a connection between warmer, wetter weather and a change in the material used to make axes."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Shipton''s team were surprised to find evidence of the Obi islanders'' hunting practices."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "It is thought that the Kelo shelters were occupied continuously until about 1,000 years ago."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. Archaeological research had taken place on the island of Obi before the arrival of Ceri Shipton and his colleagues. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 1):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"In early April 2019, Dr Ceri Shipton and his colleagues... became the <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">first archaeologists to explore Obi</strong>...\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nhóm của Ceri Shipton là những nhà khảo cổ <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"55\">đầu tiên</strong> khám phá đảo Obi. Do đó, nói rằng đã có nghiên cứu khảo cổ diễn ra trước khi họ đến là sai (<strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"156\">FALSE</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. At the Kelo sites, the researchers found the first clam shell axes ever to be discovered in the region. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"Axes made from clam shells from roughly the same time <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"75\">had also previously been found elsewhere in this region</strong>, including on the nearby island of Gebe...\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Rìu làm từ vỏ nghêu đã từng được tìm thấy trước đó ở những nơi khác trong khu vực này (như đảo Gebe). Vì vậy, đây không phải là những chiếc rìu vỏ nghêu đầu tiên được phát hiện trong vùng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"201\">FALSE</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. The size of Obi today is less than it was 18,000 years ago. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"Dating back around 18,000 years... Sea levels were about 120 metres lower, meaning <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"104\">Obi was a much larger island</strong>, encompassing what is today the separate island of Bisa...\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> 18.000 năm trước mực nước biển thấp hơn nên đảo Obi <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"64\">lớn hơn nhiều</strong> so với bây giờ (bao gồm cả các đảo nhỏ xung quanh). Nghĩa là kích thước đảo Obi ngày nay nhỏ hơn ngày xưa (<strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"185\">TRUE</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. A change in the climate around 11,700 years ago had a greater impact on Obi than on the surrounding islands. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"14,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"Roughly 11,700 years ago... the climate became significantly warmer and wetter, no doubt making Obi''s jungle much thicker.\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nói biến đổi khí hậu làm cho rừng ở Obi rậm rạp hơn, <strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"77\">không hề có sự so sánh</strong> xem tác động này ở Obi có lớn hơn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"135\">greater impact</strong>) các đảo xung quanh hay không (<strong data-path-to-node=\"14,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"181\">NOT GIVEN</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. The researchers believe there is a connection between warmer, wetter weather and a change in the material used to make axes. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"...the climate became significantly <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">warmer and wetter</strong>... According to the researchers, <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"108\">it is no coincidence that around this time the first axes crafted from stone rather than sea shells appear</strong>...\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả dùng cụm \"it is no coincidence\" (không phải trùng hợp ngẫu nhiên) để khẳng định các nhà nghiên cứu tin rằng có mối liên hệ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"144\">connection</strong>) mật thiết giữa việc thời tiết ấm, ẩm hơn (rừng rậm hơn) và việc con người chuyển từ làm rìu vỏ sò sang rìu đá để chặt cây khỏe hơn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"288\">TRUE</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. Shipton''s team were surprised to find evidence of the Obi islanders'' hunting practices. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"Judging by the bones which the researchers unearthed in the Kelo caves, people living there mainly hunted the Rothschild''s cuscus...\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nêu sự thật là họ tìm thấy xương loài thú này và biết người xưa chủ yếu săn bắn chúng, <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"111\">không hề nói đến cảm xúc</strong> của đội nghiên cứu là có bị bất ngờ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"173\">surprised</strong>) hay không (<strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"195\">NOT GIVEN</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. It is thought that the Kelo shelters were occupied continuously until about 1,000 years ago. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 8 &amp; 9):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">\"But then, <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"35\">about 8,000 years ago, both were abandoned</strong>... Whatever the reason for the departure, there is <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"129\">no evidence for use of the Kelo shelters after this time, until about 1,000 years ago</strong>...\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Hang Kelo bị bỏ hoang từ 8.000 năm trước cho đến tận 1.000 năm trước mới có người ở lại. Do đó, việc nói nơi này có người ở liên tục (<strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"146\">continuously</strong>) là sai hoàn toàn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"178\">FALSE</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('6bf426a3-b7fd-46f7-af70-f3d10a4cd01c', 'e05c6b09-1e3c-40ca-b9e2-94d2d115e822', 'fillup', 'Questions 15–21', '<p>Complete the sentences below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS </strong>from the text for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 15–21 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p>All expense claims forms must specify why the particular claim is being made and also the relevant {experiment number}</p>
<p>{Receipts} are required with all claims for public transport.</p>
<p>A {mileage allowance} is payable if you choose to travel using your own car.</p>
<p>{Mileage rates} of motoring expenses is variable according to the length of the journey and number of passengers.</p>
<p>When planning to use a rental vehicle, claimants must get {prior approval} first.</p>
<p>People eating in the CSL restaurant pay for the meals using {visitor passes}</p>
<p>People visiting the laboratories during working hours must eat at the CSL’s {onsite} restaurant or coffee lounge.</p>', '', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. …and also the relevant {experiment number}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“On the form, please include the reason for the claim and the <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">experiment number</strong> they relate to…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi yêu cầu thông tin đi kèm với lý do thanh toán. “Relate to” đồng nghĩa với “relevant”.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. {Receipts} are required with all claims for public transport.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Please enclose <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"27\">receipts</strong> to cover air, train and bus costs.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Máy bay, tàu hỏa và xe buýt chính là phương tiện công cộng (public transport). Bạn cần nộp kèm hóa đơn (receipts) cho các loại phí này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. A {mileage allowance} is payable if you choose to travel using your own car.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“If you use your own vehicle, then you may claim a <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"62\">mileage allowance</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Own vehicle” tương ứng với “own car”. Khoản tiền được trả được gọi là phụ cấp theo dặm bay/lượt đi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. {Mileage rates} of motoring expenses is variable according to the length of the journey and number of passengers.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"12\">Mileage rates</strong> will be paid… as follows: Journeys up to 130 miles… For journeys exceeding 130 miles… A rate of 2 pence per mile may be added for the first passenger…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Định mức thanh toán (mileage rates) thay đổi tùy theo quãng đường (dưới hay trên 130 dặm) và số lượng hành khách đi cùng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. When planning to use a rental vehicle, claimants must get {prior approval} first.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Car hire: <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"22\">Prior approval</strong> must be obtained.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Rental vehicle” đồng nghĩa với “car hire”. Bạn phải xin phép trước (prior approval) khi muốn thuê xe.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. People eating in the CSL restaurant pay for the meals using {visitor passes}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Visitors eligible for meals can have money loaded onto their <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">visitor passes</strong>… These passes can then be used in the CSL restaurant…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thẻ khách tham quan (visitor passes) được dùng như một công cụ thanh toán tại nhà hàng sau khi đã nạp tiền vào.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. People visiting the laboratories during working hours must eat at the CSL’s {onsite} restaurant or coffee lounge.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Visitors who arrive during office hours are required to use these <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">onsite</strong> facilities.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Office hours” tương ứng với “working hours”. “Facilities” ở đây chính là nhà hàng và quán cà phê nằm ngay tại địa điểm đó (onsite).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('912f6057-aa6d-4bb6-a78c-8a6b2acbc646', 'e05c6b09-1e3c-40ca-b9e2-94d2d115e822', 'fillup', 'Questions 22–27', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS </strong>from the text for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 22–27 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;" data-start="1096" data-end="1141"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" role="text"><strong data-start="1098" data-end="1141">Industrial Action Policy at the Company</strong></span></p>
<p>Industrial action includes reducing work activities, but generally means a strike.</p>
<p>The Company is particularly concerned about the effect of industrial action on {clients}</p>
<p><span role="text"><strong data-start="1333" data-end="1373">How industrial action may affect you</strong></span></p>
<p>• picketers only allowed {peaceful} of persuasion</p>
<p>• picketers are not allowed to prevent {vehicles} or people coming into workplace</p>
<p>• not coming to work may result in {disciplinary} and suspension of wages</p>
<p>• no picketing action permitted on {Company grounds} therefore no problem inside workplace</p>
<p>• maximum number of pickets per entrance: six</p>
<p>• employees must carry out {full duties}– partial performance not permitted</p>
<p>• all incomplete work considered as voluntary and may be unpaid</p>', '', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. The Company is particularly concerned about the effect of industrial action on {clients}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Clearly, the Company would prefer it if staff did not take industrial action, especially as this <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"109\">impacts on clients</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Concerned about the effect” tương ứng với “impacts on”. Đối tượng mà công ty lo lắng bị ảnh hưởng nhất là khách hàng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. Picketers only allowed {peaceful} means of persuasion.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…but they may only do so through <strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">peaceful</strong> means.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Những người tham gia bãi công chỉ được dùng các biện pháp hòa bình để thuyết phục người khác.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. Picketers are not allowed to prevent {vehicles} or people coming into workplace.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"26\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“They must not obstruct individuals or <strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">vehicles</strong> from entering the site.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Obstruct” đồng nghĩa với “prevent” (ngăn cản). “Entering the site” chính là đi vào nơi làm việc.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. Not coming to work may result in {disciplinary} measures and suspension of wages.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"28\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…may be subjected to <strong data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"35\">disciplinary</strong> measures and/or the Company may withhold your pay…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Suspension of wages” (ngừng trả lương) tương ứng với “withhold your pay”. Hình phạt đi kèm là các biện pháp kỷ luật (disciplinary measures).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. No picketing action permitted on {Company grounds} therefore no problem inside workplace.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"30\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Picketing will not be allowed to happen on <strong data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"55\">Company grounds</strong>, so once you get on site this should not disrupt your day.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc bãi công không được phép diễn ra trong khuôn viên công ty (Company grounds).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. Employees must carry out {full duties} – partial performance not permitted.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"32\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…you are contracted and paid to perform <strong data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">full duties</strong>. The Company does not accept such <strong data-path-to-node=\"32,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"100\">partial performance</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nhân viên bắt buộc phải hoàn thành đầy đủ nhiệm vụ (full duties), việc chỉ làm một phần công việc là không được chấp nhận.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ba46c44d-72a2-42a2-8dc9-40d43d06f191', 'd9a1b43c-1194-4a6e-a4b4-1c876aaf1069', 'fillup', 'Questions 33-36', '<p>Complete the summary below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>NO MORE THAN THREE WORDS</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>Using visual imagery and spatial navigation to remember numbers are investigated and explained. A {specific human being| human being} , an action, and a thing are assigned to consecutive cards in the pack. Combining these images allows Cooke to memorise {three cards} at a time. The mind pictures are then positioned on a {specific familiar path} . The pack of cards is remembered by going for a {mental walk} . While the pictures are converted back into cards.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"1\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. human being</strong> (hoặc <strong data-path-to-node=\"1\" data-index-in-node=\"22\">specific human being</strong>)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng</strong>: Đoạn D, câu 1: “To enable himself to memorize quickly, Ed Cooke has memorized a <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">specific human being</strong>, verb, and object that he associates with every card in the deck.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích</strong>: Để ghi nhớ nhanh, Ed Cooke gán cho mỗi lá bài một con người cụ thể (<strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"80\">human being</strong>), một động từ (hành động) và một đồ vật.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. three cards</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng</strong>: Đoạn D, câu 3: “When Cooke commits a deck to memory, he does it <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"75\">three cards</strong> in one go…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích</strong>: Bằng cách kết hợp các hình ảnh đã gán, Cooke có thể ghi nhớ được <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"77\">3 lá bài</strong> cùng một lúc thay vì nhớ từng lá đơn lẻ.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. specific familiar path</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng</strong>: Đoạn D, câu 5: “He then places those images along a <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"63\">specific familiar path</strong> in his mind…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích</strong>: Sau khi tạo ra các hình ảnh phức hợp, ông đặt chúng dọc theo một <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"77\">con đường quen thuộc cụ thể</strong> trong tâm trí để lưu trữ.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. mental walk</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng</strong>: Đoạn D, câu 6: “When it comes to recall, Cooke takes a <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"66\">mental walk</strong> along his route and translates the images into cards…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích</strong>: Khi cần nhớ lại, ông thực hiện một <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">chuyến đi bộ trong tâm trí</strong> dọc theo con đường đó để chuyển đổi các hình ảnh ngược lại thành các lá bài.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('3879c745-6b35-4fc0-9ce5-0347b2c5709e', '0778d422-07f1-437e-ada1-069a2f7d5b56', 'matrix', 'Quetsions 22-26', '', '<p>Match each statement with the correct person, A, B, C or D.</p>
<p><em><strong>NB</strong> </em>You may use any letter more than once.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": "List of people", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "There ought to be restrictions on where you can buy some herbal medicines.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "The authorities stopped supporting one project without a good reason.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "The herbal medicine industry has an effect on the environment where some plant-based medicines are found.", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "New Zealand has the human resources and natural environment to grow herbs commercially.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": " It is essential for herbal medicines to have international certification, despite the cost.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "Phil Rasmussen", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "Malcolm Douglas", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "Sandra Clair", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "Isla Burgess", "categoryLetter": "D"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. There ought to be restrictions on where you can buy some herbal medicines. — {A} Phil Rasmussen</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"25\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn F):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“According to <strong data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"34\">Rasmussen</strong>, some herbs should <strong data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"63\">require a prescription</strong>… consumers <strong data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">shouldn’t be able to go to their local supermarket and buy St John’s Wort</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Rasmussen cho rằng một số loại thảo dược cần được kê đơn và không nên được bán tự do ở siêu thị (đây chính là sự hạn chế về nơi mua).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. The authorities stopped supporting one project without a good reason. — {B} Malcolm Douglas</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"27\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn A):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“It was an <strong data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"31\">unjustified move, according to agronomist Malcolm Douglas</strong>, based on a number of inaccurate views…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Douglas cho rằng việc chính phủ ngừng cấp vốn cho nghiên cứu cây arnica là một hành động “không chính đáng” (unjustified/without a good reason).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. The herbal medicine industry has an effect on the environment where some plant-based medicines are found. — {D} Isla Burgess</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn F):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">Isla Burgess</strong>… ‘The great majority of these are harvested from the wild, so they each have an <strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"116\">impact on their local ecosystem</strong>.’”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Burgess nhấn mạnh việc thu hoạch thảo dược hoang dã gây tác động đến hệ sinh thái địa phương (môi trường).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. New Zealand has the human resources and natural environment to grow herbs commercially. — {A} Phil Rasmussen</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn A):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…huge potential for New Zealand to develop a herb industry based on the <strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"95\">excellent growing conditions and expertise</strong> there, according to <strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"158\">Phil Rasmussen</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Growing conditions” tương ứng với môi trường tự nhiên, “expertise” (chuyên môn) tương ứng với nguồn lực con người.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. It is essential for herbal medicines to have international certification, despite the cost. — {C} Sandra Clair</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"33\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn E):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“So too is the range produced by <strong data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">Sandra Clair</strong>, who says that such <strong data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">assurance is expensive but necessary</strong> if you want to export herbal remedies…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sandra Clair khẳng định việc đảm bảo tiêu chuẩn (international certification/assurance) là tốn kém nhưng cần thiết (essential).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('32732480-20e2-489f-a0e9-6afe8709216d', 'd9a1b43c-1194-4a6e-a4b4-1c876aaf1069', 'matching', 'Questions 37-40', NULL, '<p>Complete each sentence with the correct ending, A-F, below.</p>
', 'matching', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "used mainly for educational purposes."}, {"optionText": "activated brain areas associated with visual and spatial memory."}, {"optionText": "became widespread in ancient Greece for memorizing speeches and texts."}, {"optionText": "the result of techniques and extensive practice."}, {"optionText": "retaining a wide variety of tasks."}, {"optionText": "benefited from additional cognitive abilities."}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "Valentine, Wilding and Maguire’s experiment shows that the memory Contestants  .", "correctAnswer": "activated brain areas associated with visual and spatial memory.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "After Simonides discovered the loci method in 477 BC, it was .", "correctAnswer": "became widespread in ancient Greece for memorizing speeches and texts.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Ericsson finds out that natural memorisers are better than strategic memorisers at  .", "correctAnswer": "retaining a wide variety of tasks.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "According to K. Anders Ericson, Shereshevski’s skills were .", "correctAnswer": "the result of techniques and extensive practice.", "sectionContent": null}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. Valentine, Wilding and Maguire’s experiment shows that the memory contestants…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: B. activated brain areas associated with visual and spatial memory.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng</strong>: Đoạn C, câu cuối: “…they found that the memory champions were activating some <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">brain regions</strong>… These regions are known to be involved in <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"150\">visual memory and spatial navigation</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích</strong>: Thí nghiệm của nhóm nhà khoa học này (sử dụng ảnh quét não) đã chứng minh rằng khi ghi nhớ, các thí sinh kích hoạt các vùng não liên quan đến hình ảnh và định hướng không gian (spatial navigation = spatial memory).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. After Simonides discovered the loci method in 477 BC, it was…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: C. became widespread in ancient Greece for memorizing speeches and texts.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng</strong>: Đoạn B, câu 6 &amp; 7: “After Simonides’s discovery, the loci method became <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"83\">widely embraced across ancient Greece</strong>, serving as a fundamental technique for <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"161\">orators and scholars</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích</strong>: Sau khi Simonides tìm ra phương pháp Loci, nó đã trở nên phổ biến ở Hy Lạp cổ đại, đặc biệt là dành cho các nhà hùng biện (orators – những người phải nhớ bài diễn văn/speech) và học giả.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. Ericsson finds out that natural memorisers are better than strategic memorisers at…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: E. retaining a wide variety of tasks.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng</strong>: Đoạn G, câu cuối: “Strategists are usually outstanding at remembering only certain kinds of material, whereas <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"121\">naturals exhibit strong memory across many types of tasks</strong> and can retain those memories more easily.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích</strong>: Nghiên cứu của Ericsson chỉ ra sự khác biệt: những người có trí nhớ tự nhiên (naturals) có khả năng ghi nhớ tốt ở nhiều dạng nhiệm vụ khác nhau, trong khi những người dùng chiến thuật (strategists) thường chỉ giỏi ở một vài lĩnh vực cụ thể.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. According to K. Anders Ericsson, Shereshevski’s skills were…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: D. actually based on the use of specific techniques and extensive practice.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng</strong>: Đoạn G, câu 4: “…he discovered that their remarkable abilities were <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"81\">actually based on the use of specific techniques</strong> — sometimes unconsciously — combined with <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"172\">extensive practice</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích</strong>: Mặc dù Shereshevski được coi là người có trí nhớ tự nhiên, nhưng Ericsson cho rằng thực chất những kỹ năng đó vẫn dựa trên việc sử dụng các kỹ thuật cụ thể và quá trình rèn luyện chuyên sâu (extensive practice).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7e54289b-edba-4f93-8129-5e573f5f294a', 'a819a046-884a-455b-bd10-82b8ce6a1ccb', 'radio', 'Questions 27–31', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "the development of academic skills"}, {"content": "the documenting of information"}, {"content": "the completion of assignments"}, {"content": "the exchange of ideas"}], "question": "Which of the following is mentioned in the article in relation to classroom-based learning?"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "think sequentially"}, {"content": "research different points of view"}, {"content": "limit their responses to other students"}, {"content": "follow more than one discussion at a time."}], "question": "Ruberg, Taylor and Moore point out that web-based learning requires learners to"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "Online discussions demand less attention than face-to-face ones."}, {"content": "Teachers have difficulty monitoring the length of comments."}, {"content": "Face-to-face interactions between students are lost."}, {"content": "There is a delay in giving feedback to students."}], "question": "What problem did Sproull and Kiesler identify with online discussions?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "listening to a discussion"}, {"content": "a feeling of being part of a group."}, {"content": "posting ideas on an electronic bulletin board."}, {"content": "having a good relationship with other students."}], "question": "The writer refers to the concept of online presence as"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "to examine the relationship between presence and course outcomes"}, {"content": "to analyse the differences between online and class-based courses"}, {"content": "to examine the importance of being present in a classroom"}, {"content": "to demonstrate that online courses are not generally effective"}], "question": "What was a focus of Anthony Picciano''s study?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 27</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">the exchange of ideas</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Common elements for learning in a typical classroom environment are the social and communicative interactions… The ability to ask a question, to share an opinion… or to disagree…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Social and communicative interactions” (tương tác xã hội và giao tiếp) và “share an opinion” (chia sẻ quan điểm) chính là các hình thức trao đổi ý tưởng (exchange of ideas).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 28</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">follow more than one discussion at a time.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Web-based learning sessions… can have multiple threads with several discussions and Interactions progressing simultaneously.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Simultaneously” có nghĩa là đồng thời. Việc có nhiều luồng (multiple threads) diễn ra cùng lúc buộc người học phải theo dõi nhiều cuộc thảo luận một lúc.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 29</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">There is a delay in giving feedback to students.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…discussions based on misinformation, that continue because online an instructor cannot necessarily immediately correct or clarify a comment.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc giảng viên không thể sửa lỗi “ngay lập tức” (immediately) tạo ra sự chậm trễ (delay) trong việc đưa ra phản hồi hoặc đính chính cho sinh viên.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 30</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">a feeling of being part of a group.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The simplest definition of presence for an online course refers to a student’s sense of being registered and belonging in a course…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Sense of belonging” (cảm giác thuộc về) đồng nghĩa với việc cảm thấy mình là một phần của nhóm (being part of a group).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 31</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">to examine the relationship between presence and course outcomes</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “An attempt was made to go beyond student perceptions… and to include perceptions of social presence… In addition, data was collected on performance measures that related specifically to course objectives.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nghiên cứu của Picciano tập trung vào cả sự hiện diện (presence) và các thước đo kết quả học tập (performance measures/outcomes).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ab0790e7-e1be-442d-8d54-6eff8273379c', 'a819a046-884a-455b-bd10-82b8ce6a1ccb', 'radio', 'Questions 32–36', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>YES </strong>if the statement agrees with the claims of the writer, choose <strong>NO </strong>if the statement contradicts the claims of the writer, or <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The ability of online courses to meet an individual participant''s needs is unclear."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Researchers caution against building strong online relationships."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Common assumptions about the benefits of face-to-face courses have proved to be correct."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The meaning of presence is still being clarified"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Research on the impacts of interaction on learning outcomes has produced consistent results."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 32</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"16,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">YES</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…the effectiveness of online courses, particularly in relation to individual student needs… is sometimes questioned.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Questioned” (bị đặt dấu hỏi) có nghĩa là tính hiệu quả của nó đối với nhu cầu cá nhân vẫn chưa rõ ràng (unclear).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 33</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…this same student may develop a relationship with other students in the class…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nhắc đến việc sinh viên có thể phát triển mối quan hệ, nhưng không đề cập đến việc các nhà nghiên cứu có đưa ra lời cảnh báo “chống lại” (caution against) việc xây dựng mối quan hệ trực tuyến hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 34</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">NO</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “It is generally assumed that when a student is physically present… he or she has a sense of belonging… However, this is an assumption and not always true.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc nói rằng giả định thông thường này “không phải lúc nào cũng đúng” (not always true), trái ngược với khẳng định của câu hỏi là nó “đã được chứng minh là đúng” (proved to be correct).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 35</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">YES</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…as this concept is studied, the definition is expanding and being refined to include telepresence, cognitive presence…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Expanding and being refined” (đang mở rộng và được tinh lọc) cho thấy ý nghĩa của sự hiện diện vẫn đang tiếp tục được làm rõ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 36</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">NO</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…the results of the study indicated that the relationship of actual measures of interaction and performance is mixed.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Kết quả nghiên cứu là “mixed” (hỗn hợp/không đồng nhất), trong khi câu hỏi cho rằng kết quả là “consistent” (nhất quán).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('9ef69136-20e3-475e-95d3-7c947df08504', '073989fb-f459-44a9-9f13-df07668550c6', 'radio', 'Questions 31–35', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "One expert expressed regret for having underemphasized his argument in a publication."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "We overlook insignificant items that come into our view."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Our eyes are only at risk of being deceived when they are in motion."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Research into cognitive errors might potentially save lives."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The aging process increases the need to fill in gaps in our visual perception."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"14\">Câu 31: Một chuyên gia bày tỏ sự hối tiếc vì đã nhấn mạnh quá ít lập luận của mình trong một ấn phẩm.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">&#8220;&#8230;Dennett was pleased: ‘In hindsight, I wish I had been bolder, as the effects are more pronounced than I originally claimed.’&#8221;</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm &#8220;wish I had been bolder&#8221; (ước gì đã táo bạo hơn) thể hiện sự hối tiếc vì đã đưa ra khẳng định nhẹ nhàng hơn thực tế trong ấn phẩm trước đó.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"16\">Câu 32: Chúng ta bỏ qua những mục không quan trọng lọt vào tầm mắt.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">&#8220;&#8230;we tend to ignore elements in our visual field that seem unimportant, such as a repeated word or line in a text.&#8221;</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài viết xác nhận con người có xu hướng phớt lờ các yếu tố &#8220;unimportant&#8221; (không quan trọng) trong thị trường của mình.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"18\">Câu 33: Mắt chúng ta chỉ có nguy cơ bị lừa khi chúng đang chuyển động.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">&#8220;Subsequently, it was discovered that our eyes don’t even need to be moving to be deceived.&#8221;</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc khẳng định mắt &#8220;không cần phải chuyển động&#8221; vẫn có thể bị đánh lừa qua các thí nghiệm với hình ảnh biến mất và xuất hiện lại.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"20\">Câu 34: Nghiên cứu về các lỗi nhận thức có khả năng cứu sống con người.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">&#8220;It’s more than just academic interest that has spurred research into these cognitive errors.&#8221;</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản đề cập đến các tai nạn giao thông chết người do lỗi chú ý của lái xe, cho thấy nghiên cứu này có ứng dụng thực tiễn để giảm thiểu tai nạn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"22\">Câu 35: Quá trình lão hóa làm tăng nhu cầu lấp đầy các khoảng trống trong nhận thức thị giác.</h3>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"23\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Toàn bộ bài đọc không đề cập đến &#8220;quá trình lão hóa&#8221; (aging process) hay mối liên hệ của nó với việc nhận thức thị giác.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('6c80cb9f-36ff-45b2-b52f-0696dee3c62a', '0299a616-be81-4608-a7f2-cf51ca78b534', 'fillup', 'Questions 11–16', '<p data-start="109" data-end="192">Complete the sentences below.<br data-start="138" data-end="141">Write <strong data-start="147" data-end="175">ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p data-section-id="16jkwan" data-start="199" data-end="225"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" role="text"><strong data-start="202" data-end="225">Reynolds Electrical</strong></span></p>
<ul data-start="227" data-end="626">
<li data-section-id="18a47rv" data-start="227" data-end="284">
<p>Tony Reynolds’ first business produced {cars}</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="9u4azu" data-start="285" data-end="347">
<p>Reynolds Electrical was started in the year {1928}</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1jkuuve" data-start="348" data-end="421">
<p>There was previously a {cinema} where the company is now based.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1gopwy6" data-start="422" data-end="498">
<p>The {quality} of the products is an important factor for customers.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1glii0d" data-start="499" data-end="547">
<p>The company is building a new {factory}</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="155c2tp" data-start="548" data-end="626">
<p>The company recently won an award for its success in reducing {waste}</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 2: REYNOLDS ELECTRICAL</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Kathy:</strong> Hello and welcome to Reynolds Electrical. I''m Kathy Meredith and I''m in charge of your training program during the month you''re going to spend with us.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">Let me start by telling you a little about the company. The name Reynolds comes from Tony Reynolds. He was a local man born in 1905. When he was only 19, he started a small company that manufactured <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"199\">(Q11) cars</strong></span>. This was a failure, though, and he gave up in 1927. He then trained as an electrician and in the following year, rented a small workshop and set up a new company: Reynolds Electrical. So the company dates back to <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"424\">(Q12) 1928</strong></span>, and I''m pleased to say we''ve been successful more or less ever since.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">And we moved to our present site in 1955. There was a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">(Q13) cinema</strong></span> here which had to be demolished and new buildings were put up. Of course, in those days it was quite common to have factories close to town centres. The company has been more and more successful in the last few years. The main reason is a change in the pattern of sales. Another reason for our success is that despite strong competition from cheaper competitors, our customers are happy to pay a higher price for the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"484\">(Q14) quality</strong></span> of Reynolds goods.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">Because of this success, we''re feeling confident about the future and we''ve got some exciting plans. We''re now constructing a second <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"133\">(Q15) factory</strong></span> so that we can increase production. We''re also replacing our existing production machinery and making improvements to all the offices. One more point I''d like to make is that ever since Tony Reynolds started the business, we''ve always tried to be the best in our field. So earlier this year, we were delighted when we received an award for making a big reduction in <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"513\">(Q16) waste</strong></span>. Our policy is to recycle as much as we can.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">WEEKLY SCHEDULE (Questions 17–20)</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Kathy:</strong> Right, now I''ll give you an idea of what you''ll be doing in the next few days. You''ll spend most of this week with different members of our staff, working alongside them so that you can learn what their job involves. And we''ll get together at 3:00 every afternoon to focus on a different part of our work.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\">Every Monday we have a meeting of people from different parts of the company, and I''d like you to take part in this afternoon''s meeting. Today we''re going to discuss ways of getting higher levels of <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"199\">(Q17) safety</strong></span>, and we''ll be interested in any suggestions you might make. So think about it while you''re going around the factory today.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\">Tomorrow afternoon, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">Tuesday</strong></span>, I''ll introduce you to the IT department and they''ll update you about the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"102\">(Q18) website</strong></span> development (changes to our website). This is important because a growing number of people want to buy online.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\">Then on <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">Wednesday</strong></span>, we''ll talk about our communication with those very important people—<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"87\">(Q19) customers</strong></span>. Without them, of course, we''d soon go out of business. And that discussion will cover all sorts of things from advertising to research into what sort of people buy our products.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\">The next afternoon, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">Thursday</strong></span>, we''ll focus on recruitment and how we try to make sure we have the best staff to meet our needs. We seem to be doing well because mostly they stay with us for several years.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\">And finally for this week, at least on <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"39\">Friday</strong></span>, something that I think you''ll find more interesting than it sounds—and that''s how we ensure we have sufficient <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"158\">(Q20) money</strong></span> coming in to pay our bills and other expenses such as wages.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\">Right now, are there any questions before I go on?</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('883b53fe-a14b-462c-b996-d0340be0d5b3', 'bd43b54e-b1b7-49da-929e-21171c504eaa', 'radio', 'Questions 26', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "how one species may be helped at the expense of another"}, {"content": "disagreement among environmentalists on methods to protect species from extinction"}, {"content": "fighting the destruction of wetland reedbeds"}, {"content": "how research and good management can save an endangered species "}], "question": "What is the main theme of Reading passage 2?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. What is the main theme of Reading passage 2?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11,0,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án</strong>: how research and good management can save an endangered species</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích</strong>: Xuyên suốt bài đọc, tác giả tập trung vào việc nghiên cứu khoa học (đoạn 2, 3, 4, 6) kết hợp với các biện pháp quản lý môi trường hiệu quả (đoạn 5, 7) đã giúp giải cứu thành công loài chim bittern khỏi nguy cơ tuyệt chủng. Điều này khớp với ý nghĩa của đáp án cuối cùng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('53a4d6aa-33c9-40b0-a64e-2b42b54b4175', '2d25c080-4e96-430f-81a6-5f32a6f2ddfc', 'fillup', 'Question 1-10', '<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER </strong>for each answer.</p>
<p><strong>The London Relocation Services</strong></p>
<p>Customer’s name: Anna Woods</p>
<p>Customer’s personal details</p>
<p>Customer address 118 {Fordyce} Park, Ballysillan<br />
Postcode: BT14 9BJ<br />
Phone no: {07840051963} (mobile)<br />
Other information</p>
<p>Anna is hoping to find work as a {nurse}<br />
She needs to find a {primary} school for her son.<br />
Requirements for the new property</p>
<p>Location:</p>
<p>Her preferred location is in the {south} of the city.<br />
Her husband would like to be near a {station}<br />
Her son would prefer to be close to a {park}<br />
Property details:</p>
<p>She would like to live in a {house}<br />
She would prefer {3 | three} bedrooms.<br />
A small {office} is also desirable.</p>
', NULL, 'fill-in-the-blank', NULL, NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> Now listen carefully and answer questions 1 to seven.</p>\n<p><strong>Daniel:</strong> London Relocation Services. Daniel speaking, how may I help you?</p>\n<p><strong>Anna:</strong> Good morning. My family and I are moving to London later this year, and I wonder if you can help.</p>\n<p><strong>Daniel:</strong> Sure. First of all, I&#8217;ll need to get some personal details. May I take your full name, please?</p>\n<p><strong>Anna:</strong> It&#8217;s <strong>Anna Woods</strong>. Thanks.</p>\n<p><strong>Daniel:</strong> Where are you moving from?</p>\n<p><strong>Anna:</strong> Northern Ireland, just outside Belfast actually.</p>\n<p><strong>Daniel:</strong> Right. And what&#8217;s your current address?</p>\n<p><strong>Anna:</strong> It&#8217;s <strong>118</strong> <strong>(1) Fordyce</strong> Park. I&#8217;ll spell that for you. It&#8217;s F-O-R-D-Y-C-E. And that&#8217;s in Ballysillan.</p>\n<p><strong>Daniel:</strong> And what&#8217;s the postcode?</p>\n<p><strong>Anna:</strong> It&#8217;s <strong>BT14 9BJ</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Daniel:</strong> Alright. And could I take a contact phone number?</p>\n<p><strong>Anna:</strong> I&#8217;ll give you my mobile number as you can get me on that anytime. It&#8217;s <strong>(2) 07840051963</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Daniel:</strong> Great, got that. Now we always like to get a bit more information about the families that we&#8217;re moving. It helps with the search. Are you moving for work?</p>\n<p><strong>Anna:</strong> Yes, my husband&#8217;s just got a new job in London.</p>\n<p><strong>Daniel:</strong> And what about you? Do you work?</p>\n<p><strong>Anna:</strong> Well, I&#8217;ve been working as a teaching assistant recently, but I&#8217;m actually a qualified <strong>(3) nurse</strong>, and I&#8217;d like to get back into that if possible.</p>\n<p><strong>Daniel:</strong> Right. And do you have any children?</p>\n<p><strong>Anna:</strong> Yes, a son. So we need to find a school for him.</p>\n<p><strong>Daniel:</strong> Is it a secondary school you&#8217;ll be looking for?</p>\n<p><strong>Anna:</strong> No, he&#8217;s still in <strong>(4) primary</strong> school. He&#8217;s not quite at the secondary level yet.</p>\n<p><strong>Daniel:</strong> Fine. So, let&#8217;s go on to talk about your requirements for the property. Do you have a preferred location? Is your husband&#8217;s job in the centre?</p>\n<p><strong>Anna:</strong> No, it&#8217;s in east London, but we&#8217;d rather live somewhere quieter.</p>\n<p><strong>Daniel:</strong> Sure, there are some lovely areas in the <strong>(5) south</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Anna:</strong> OK, that sounds great. Now, my husband doesn&#8217;t want to spend too long commuting to work every day, so I imagine that ideally, he&#8217;d like to be not too far from a <strong>(6) station</strong> then.</p>\n<p><strong>Daniel:</strong> Yes. He drives now, but I guess that&#8217;s not going to be possible, and he&#8217;s not keen on buses. Oh, what about you or your son? Do you have any preferences? Does your son do any sport, for example?</p>\n<p><strong>Anna:</strong> He&#8217;s quite active, so I&#8217;m sure he&#8217;d love a <strong>(7) park</strong> nearby to run around in. He doesn&#8217;t do swimming or anything like that.</p>\n<p><strong>Daniel:</strong> Great.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> Before you hear the rest of the conversation, you have some time to look at questions 8 to ten. Now listen and answer questions 8 to ten.</p>\n<p><strong>Daniel:</strong> So, what sort of property do you have in mind?</p>\n<p><strong>Anna:</strong> We have friends who live in an amazing flat over there, but as we&#8217;ve always lived in a <strong>(8) house</strong>, I think we&#8217;ll stick with that. We&#8217;d find it hard to adapt to a flat.</p>\n<p><strong>Daniel:</strong> OK. And size-wise, how many bedrooms would you like?</p>\n<p><strong>Anna:</strong> Well, there&#8217;s just myself, my husband and our son.</p>\n<p><strong>Daniel:</strong> So you definitely need a <strong>2</strong> bedroom property. But how about having a guest room? I might be able to find a 3 bedroom property for you.</p>\n<p><strong>Anna:</strong> Yes, that would be ideal. We&#8217;re sure to have family visiting often.</p>\n<p><strong>Daniel:</strong> All right, I&#8217;ve made a note of that. Now, are there any other requirements for your new property?</p>\n<p><strong>Anna:</strong> Hmm, well, it&#8217;s not essential, but it would be handy to have a small <strong>(10) office</strong> for when my husband works from home. It doesn&#8217;t need to be a big one.</p>\n<p><strong>Daniel:</strong> I guess it all comes down to budget. Yes, OK Anna. Well, I&#8217;ve certainly got enough to be getting on with, and I will—</p>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> That is the end of part 1. You now have one minute to check your answers to part one.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('c7d7e516-802f-48f9-ace3-4444fc3b500b', 'b6dd2bbc-c2e9-4b68-ba67-2bea2a277e62', 'matching', 'Questions 32-37', NULL, '<p>Complete each sentence with the correct ending, <strong>A-H</strong>, below.</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A. Suggested music was an essential part of every individual."}, {"optionText": "B. Made no link between music and language in a comprehensive study."}, {"optionText": "C. Believes that early language was very musical."}, {"optionText": "D. Felt that the origin of language should not be debated."}, {"optionText": "E. States that early language was made up of basic words used in an unsystematic way."}, {"optionText": "F. Devoted 17 chapters of a book to music."}, {"optionText": "G. Believes that proto-language had no individual words."}, {"optionText": "H. Referred to music in part of a book about the development of human beings."}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "The Société de Linguistique de Paris ", "correctAnswer": "D. Felt that the origin of language should not be debated.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Charles Darwin ", "correctAnswer": "H. Referred to music in part of a book about the development of human beings.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "John Blacking ", "correctAnswer": "A. Suggested music was an essential part of every individual.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Christiansen and Kirby ", "correctAnswer": "B. Made no link between music and language in a comprehensive study.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Derek Bickerton ", "correctAnswer": "E. States that early language was made up of basic words used in an unsystematic way.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Alison Wray ", "correctAnswer": "G. Believes that proto-language had no individual words.", "sectionContent": null}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"1\">Câu 32: The Société de Linguistique de Paris — D</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 1, dòng 5-7.</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…in 1866 the influential Société de Linguistique de Paris banned all discussions about the origin of language.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Hiệp hội này đã ban hành lệnh cấm tất cả các cuộc thảo luận về nguồn gốc ngôn ngữ, điều này đồng nghĩa với việc họ cảm thấy chủ đề này “không nên được tranh luận” (should not be debated).</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\">Câu 33: Charles Darwin — H</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 3, dòng 9-11.</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “One is the aforementioned Charles Darwin who, in his 1871 book on human evolution, The Descent of Man, devoted several pages to the development of music.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trong cuốn sách về sự tiến hóa của loài người (human evolution/development of human beings), Darwin đã dành một phần (vài trang) để nói về âm nhạc.</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">Câu 34: John Blacking — A</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 3, dòng 11-13.</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…John Blacking, whose 1973 book, How Musical is Man?, broached the idea that music is an inherent and universal human quality.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Blacking cho rằng âm nhạc là một đặc tính “vốn có và phổ quát” (inherent and universal) của con người, tương ứng với ý nói âm nhạc là “phần thiết yếu của mỗi cá nhân” (essential part of every individual).</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">Câu 35: Christiansen and Kirby — B</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 4, dòng 6-8.</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…Morten Christiansen and Simon Kirby’s book, Language Evolution (2000)… failed to mention music in any of its 17 chapters.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Dù viết một cuốn sách toàn diện về sự tiến hóa ngôn ngữ, hai tác giả này đã không hề nhắc đến âm nhạc, tức là “không tạo ra mối liên kết nào” (made no link) giữa âm nhạc và ngôn ngữ.</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">Câu 36: Derek Bickerton — E</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 7, dòng 4-6.</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “But Bickerton’s idea that the precursor of modern language consisted of words strung together with limited, if any, grammar is, I believe, fundamentally mistaken.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bickerton cho rằng tiền thân của ngôn ngữ bao gồm các từ đơn lẻ xâu chuỗi lại với nhau mà ít có ngữ pháp, tương đồng với ý “các từ cơ bản được dùng một cách không hệ thống” (basic words used in an unsystematic way).</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\">Câu 37: Alison Wray — G</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 8, dòng 3-7.</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “She argues that proto-language was ‘holistic’… a communication system composed of ‘messages’ rather than words…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Alison Wray tin rằng tiền ngôn ngữ mang tính “tổng thể”, bao gồm các “thông điệp” chứ không phải được cấu thành từ các “từ riêng lẻ” (no individual words).</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e31b1625-e8e7-4a0c-967f-21eb09d1b19c', '1098faf0-b686-4692-9b43-9e095d1476f5', 'fillup', 'Questions 8–13', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>THE MOREPORK</strong></p>
<p><strong>Appearance</strong></p>
<p>– approximately {29 centimeters} in length</p>
<p>– feathers with fringes to enable quiet flight</p>
<p><strong>Nesting</strong></p>
<p>– nests in trees, plants or spaces in roots and {Rocks}</p>
<p>– after about 35 days, baby morepocks are capable of leaving the nest</p>
<p><strong>Hunting</strong></p>
<p>– transports Its prey using its {Bill}</p>
<p>– can be chased away by other birds during the {Day}</p>
<p>– attacked {Plovers} that had been introduced to Motuora island</p>
<p><strong>Threats</strong></p>
<p>– may be exposed to {poison} in their prey</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>8. Appearance – approximately <strong>29 centimeters</strong> in length</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>29 centimeters</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) “…they are around <strong>29 centimeters</strong> long from head to tail…”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>9. Nesting – nests in trees, plants or spaces in roots and <strong>rocks</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>rocks</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) “Moreporks nest in tree hollows, in clumps of plants, or in cavities among <strong>rocks</strong> and roots…”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>10. Hunting – transports Its prey using its <strong>bill</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>bill</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) “…which it then carries away in its <strong>bill</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>11. Hunting – can be chased away by other birds during the <strong>day</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"26\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>day</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) “<strong>In the day</strong>, these small birds sometimes mob drowsy moreporks and chase them away from their roosts.”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>12. Hunting – attacked <strong>plovers</strong> that had been introduced to Motuora island</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"28\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>plovers</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “The culprits turned out to be five pairs of Moreporks that ate or chased away the new arrivals [<strong>plovers</strong>].”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>13. Threats – may be exposed to <strong>poison</strong> in their prey</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"30\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>poison</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) “…they could be affected by an accumulative <strong>poison</strong> by consuming prey that has ingested poison.”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f20f667e-55d7-43d4-9fb1-2c2dc5a5f9ae', '1c4126b5-d544-47fa-a01e-a2cef4b46daa', 'checkbox', 'Questions 20-21', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>letters, A–E.</p>
<p>Which <strong>TWO </strong>of these causes of damage to coral reefs are mentioned by the writer of the text?</p>
', 'multiple_choice_many', '[{"correct": null, "options": [{"content": null}], "question": null}]', '[{"option": "A. a rising number of extreme storms", "correct": false}, {"option": "B. the removal of too many fish from the sea", "correct": false}, {"option": "C. the contamination of the sea from waste", "correct": true}, {"option": "D. increased disease among marine species", "correct": false}, {"option": "E. alterations in the usual flow of water in the seas", "correct": true}]', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p>20–21. C &amp; E<br />(Đoạn 4: “Other menaces include… pollution by humans (C)… ocean current changes (E).”)<br />→ Hai nguyên nhân gây hại san hô được nêu: ô nhiễm do con người (C) và thay đổi dòng chảy đại dương (E). → C &amp; E.</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e4de467f-30a2-499e-888d-7cf99d56c0ac', '340078e0-049a-4d1b-ae24-056c31c79632', 'fillup', 'Questions 1–6', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>DATA ON FOOD DESERTS AND THEIR EFFECTS ON HEALTH</strong></p>
<p><strong>The Brooklyn Food Association</strong></p>
<p>– The online map provides users with a store’s name, {location} and details of its produce.</p>
<p>– One goal of the mapping project is to help develop new {policies} on food.</p>
<p>– Citizen maps are sometimes made when {government} maps are unsatisfactory.</p>
<p><strong>Reasons for the development of food deserts</strong></p>
<p>– New research suggests that people living in food deserts often have low {incomes}.</p>
<p>– Some supermarkets are unable to buy enough {land} inside cities for their stores.</p>
<p>– Small grocery stores in cities often cannot cope with supermarket {competition}.</p>
', NULL, 'fill-in-the-blank', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong>1. The online map provides users with a store’s name, location and details of its produce.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>location</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Over the last few months, a survey has been carried out… colorful dots appear on their online map, which display the specific <strong>location</strong> of each of the food stores in a handful of central Brooklyn neighborhoods.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Bản đồ trực tuyến hiển thị vị trí cụ thể của từng cửa hàng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong>2. One goal of the mapping project is to help develop new policies on food.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>policies</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The aim of the project is also to assist government officials in assessing food availability, and in forming future <strong>policies</strong> about what kind of food should be sold and where.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Mục tiêu của dự án là hỗ trợ các quan chức chính phủ xây dựng các chính sách tương lai về thực phẩm.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong>3. Citizen maps are sometimes made when government maps are unsatisfactory.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>government</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “According to Michael Goodchild… citizen map makers may make maps because there is no good <strong>government</strong> map, or to record problems such as burned-out traffic lights.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Người dân tự lập bản đồ khi bản đồ của chính phủ không tốt.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong>4. New research suggests that people living in food deserts often have low incomes .</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>incomes</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “According to recent studies, people at higher risk of chronic disease and who receive <strong>minimal incomes</strong> for the work they do, frequently live in neighborhoods located in food deserts.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Những người sống trong food deserts thường có thu nhập tối thiểu (minimal incomes / low incomes).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong>5. Some supermarkets are unable to buy enough land inside cities for their stores.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>land</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Linda Alwitt and Thomas Donley… found that supermarkets often can’t afford the amount of <strong>land</strong> required for their stores in cities.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Các siêu thị gặp khó khăn trong việc mua đủ đất (land) trong thành phố.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong>6. Small grocery stores in cities often cannot cope with supermarket competition .</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>competition</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “City planning researcher Cliff Guy and colleagues… found in 2004 that smaller urban groceries tend to close due to <strong>competition</strong> from suburban supermarkets.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Các cửa hàng tạp hóa nhỏ đóng cửa do sự cạnh tranh từ các siêu thị ngoại ô.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('c763a2f4-4b96-46af-9532-3da8741c2ff2', 'cdf96d67-2b3c-47b1-aeb5-87712f37ef13', 'radio', 'Questions 27-31', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "Too many branches of science have been involved in its study."}, {"content": "The Société de Linguistique de Paris instigated research in this area."}, {"content": "The lack of progress is surprising given the amount of work being done."}, {"content": "Most progress in the study of language was made between 1859 and 1866."}], "question": "In the first paragraph, what does the writer suggest about the origin of language?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "Some current theories are based on conflicting evidence."}, {"content": "There is insufficient fossil evidence to reach a conclusion."}, {"content": "Fossil evidence suggests that Homo sapiens had larger brains than Neanderthals."}, {"content": "Archaeological evidence shows that Neanderthals were able to talk."}], "question": "What is ‘the problem’ referred to in the second paragraph?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "Modern theorists should pay more attention to his approach."}, {"content": "His ideas supported those of the Société de Linguistique de Paris."}, {"content": "His ideas were mirrored in a later book called Language Evolution."}, {"content": "His ideas are too outdated to be of any relevance today."}], "question": "What does the writer suggest about Jean-Jacques Rousseau’s work in 1781?"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "They have had little impact on the study of language."}, {"content": "They have helped the study of linguistics to progress."}, {"content": "They are not accepted by the majority of linguists."}, {"content": "The assumption behind them is wrong."}], "question": "What is the writer’s current view of Derek Bickerton’s ideas?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "grammar and meaning."}, {"option_text": "messages and proto-language."}, {"option_text": "language, music and emotions."}, {"option_text": "proto-language and modern semantics."}], "question": "In the final paragraph, the writer concludes that Alison Wray’s ideas will help establish a link between:"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"1\">Câu 27: C (The lack of progress is surprising given the amount of work being done)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 1, dòng cuối.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “And yet, despite almost frenzied activity, limited progress has been made.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả sử dụng cụm từ <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"35\">“frenzied activity”</strong> (hoạt động điên cuồng/náo nhiệt) để chỉ khối lượng công việc khổng lồ đang được thực hiện, nhưng kết quả thu lại là <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"171\">“limited progress”</strong> (tiến bộ hạn chế). Điều này ngụ ý rằng sự thiếu hụt tiến bộ là một điều đáng ngạc nhiên so với nỗ lực bỏ ra.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\">Câu 28: A (Some current theories are based on conflicting evidence)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 2, dòng 4-7.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…fossil evidence indicates that the Neanderthals had larger brains… but archaeological evidence indicates that the Neanderthals lacked a capacity for language.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Vấn đề” được nhắc đến là sự mâu thuẫn giữa hai loại bằng chứng: hóa thạch (fossil) cho thấy não người Neanderthal lớn hơn, nhưng khảo cổ (archaeological) lại cho thấy họ không có khả năng ngôn ngữ. Sự đối chọi này khiến các giả thuyết dựa trên kích cỡ bộ não trở nên sai lệch.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">Câu 29: A (Modern theorists should pay more attention to his approach)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 4, dòng cuối.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Those authors have an important lesson to learn from Rousseau and other writers of his time who addressed the origin of language.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả phê phán các nhà nghiên cứu hiện đại (như Christiansen và Kirby) vì đã bỏ qua âm nhạc. Ông khẳng định họ có một “bài học quan trọng” (important lesson) cần học từ cách tiếp cận của Rousseau — người đã xem xét cả âm nhạc và ngôn ngữ một cách gắn liền.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">Câu 30: D (The assumption behind them is wrong)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 7, dòng 4-5 và dòng cuối.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “But Bickerton’s idea… is, I believe, fundamentally mistaken. …I now understand that it is not only flawed but has severely limited the progress…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả trực tiếp phủ nhận quan điểm của Bickerton (cho rằng tiền ngôn ngữ là các từ rời rạc ghép lại). Ông khẳng định ý tưởng này là <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"146\">“fundamentally mistaken”</strong> (sai lầm từ căn bản) và <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"195\">“flawed”</strong> (có lỗ hổng/sai sót).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">Câu 31: C (language, music and emotions)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn cuối, câu cuối cùng.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “I believe this insight enables us to understand the origin of music as well as language, and to relate both to the emotional lives of our human ancestors.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả kết luận rằng lý thuyết của Alison Wray không chỉ giúp hiểu về ngôn ngữ và âm nhạc mà còn kết nối cả hai với đời sống cảm xúc (emotional lives) của tổ tiên loài người.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('abbf4c33-7f55-472b-9d68-949129e271c8', 'a8fd8fd0-d1da-4e49-8bdf-e9aeee444201', 'matrix', 'Questions 20-23', NULL, '<p>Look at the following findings (Questions 20-23) and the list of academics below.</p>
<p>Choose each finding with the correct academic, <strong>A-D</strong>.</p>
<p><strong><em>NB</em> </strong><em>you may use any letter more than</em><strong><em> </em></strong><em>once</em><strong><em>.</em></strong></p>
', 'classification', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": "List of academics", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "Certain members can influence the rest of the group to alter a previous decision.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Individual verification of a proposed choice is important for successful decision outcome.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "The more individuals taking part in a decision, the better the decision will be.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "The decision-making process of certain insects produces excellent results even when fine distinctions are required.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "Nicolas de Condorcet", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "Christian List and colleagues", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "José Halloy", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "Nigel Franks and colleagues", "categoryLetter": "D"}]}', '[{"content": "<p>20. Certain members can influence the rest of the group to alter a previous decision.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>C (José Halloy)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) Halloy đã sử dụng gián robot (<em>robotic cockroaches</em>) để <strong>thay đổi hành vi</strong> (<em>subvert the behaviour</em>) và <strong>thuyết phục</strong> (<em>persuade</em>) những con gián sống chọn nơi trú ẩn không phù hợp (tức là thay đổi quyết định trước đó).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> José Halloy đã chứng minh khả năng thiểu số (robot) kiểm soát quyết định của đa số (gián sống).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>21. Individual verification of a proposed choice is important for successful decision outcome.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>B (Christian List and colleagues)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) Các nhà nghiên cứu kết luận rằng khả năng chọn địa điểm tốt nhất của ong phụ thuộc vào sự <strong>độc lập trong việc xác nhận thông tin</strong> (<em>“independence in confirming this information for themselves”</em>) sau khi nghe “waggle dance”.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Phát hiện của List nhấn mạnh tầm quan trọng của việc xác minh cá nhân (individual verification).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>22. The more individuals taking part in a decision, the better the decision will be.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>A (Nicolas de Condorcet)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 1) Condorcet’s theory nói rằng <strong>“the probability of a correct decision increases with the size of the jury”</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Lý thuyết bồi thẩm đoàn của Condorcet là về việc quy mô nhóm càng lớn thì quyết định càng chính xác.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>23. The decision-making process of certain insects produces excellent results even when fine distinctions are required.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"26\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>B (Christian List and colleagues)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) Nghiên cứu của List về ong cho thấy: “The decision is <strong>remarkably reliable, with the bees choosing the best site even when there is only small difference between alternative sites</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Ong chọn được địa điểm tốt nhất ngay cả khi sự khác biệt giữa các lựa chọn là rất nhỏ (<em>fine distinctions</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ba121fcd-8024-4422-896e-fa34b3dd885b', 'cf5c116e-666d-4c66-badc-6380a2d7a22a', 'fillup', 'Questions 1–10', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<p><em>Write </em><strong><em>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</em></strong><em> for each answer.</em></p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="quests-des">
<div class="content-write">
<p class="ql-align-center" style="text-align: center;"><strong>HOLIDAY RENTAL</strong></p>
<div class="quill-better-table-wrapper">
<div class="choice-table-wrap">
<table class="quill-better-table choice-table" style="border-collapse: collapse; border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" border="1">
<colgroup>
<col width="169" />
<col width="490" />
<col width="100" /></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr data-row="row-ghhr">
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="row-ghhr"> Example</p>
<p>Owners’ name:</td>
<td style="border-width: 1px; border-color: #000000;" colspan="1" rowspan="1" data-row="row-ghhr"> Answer</p>
<p>Carol and Dave Marriott</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>Aster cottage</strong></p>
<p>– Available for week beginning {September 14th | September 14 | 14th September | 14 September}</p>
<p>– Cost for the week: $ {835}</p>
<p><strong>Periwinkle Cottage</strong></p>
<p>– The same price as Aster Cottage last year</p>
<p>– Part of a building that was first used as a {school}</p>
<p>– The living room leads out to the {deck}</p>
<p>– View of the {river} from the bedroom</p>
<p>– Bring our own {towels}</p>
<p>– Doesn’t have a {garage}</p>
<p><strong>The town</strong></p>
<p>– The owner recommends the {Chinese} restaurant</p>
<p>– The town is well-known for this antique shapes</p>
<p><strong>Payment</strong></p>
<p>– Deposit: $ {200}</p>
<p>– Deadline for final payment: final day of {July}</p>
</div>
</div>
', NULL, 'fill-in-the-blank', NULL, NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> You will hear a woman who wants to rent a vacation cottage telephoning the owner. First you have some time to look at questions one to seven on page two. You will see that there is an example that has been done for you. On this occasion only the conversation relating to this will be played first.</p>\n<p><strong>Owner:</strong> Hello.</p>\n<p><strong>Customer:</strong> Oh, Hello. I’m calling about a vacation rental. The name I’ve been given is Carol Marriott.</p>\n<p><strong>Owner:</strong> I’m <strong>Dave</strong>, Carol’s husband, we own it together.</p>\n<blockquote data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<p><strong>Dịch:</strong> <strong>Người dẫn chuyện:</strong> Bạn sẽ nghe một phụ nữ muốn thuê một ngôi nhà nghỉ dưỡng gọi điện cho chủ sở hữu. Đầu tiên, bạn có thời gian để xem các câu hỏi 1 đến 7. Bạn sẽ thấy có một ví dụ đã được thực hiện cho bạn. Chỉ lần này, đoạn hội thoại liên quan đến ví dụ sẽ được phát trước.<strong>Chủ nhà:</strong> Xin chào.<strong>Khách hàng:</strong> Ồ, xin chào. Tôi gọi điện về việc thuê nhà nghỉ dưỡng. Tên tôi được cung cấp là Carol Marriott.<strong>Chủ nhà:</strong> Tôi là <strong>Dave</strong>, chồng của Carol, chúng tôi sở hữu căn nhà này cùng nhau.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"8\" />\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> The joint owners of the cottage are Carol Marriott and her husband Dave, so Dave has been written in the space. Now we shall begin. You should answer the questions as you listen because you will not hear the recording a second time. Listen carefully and answer questions one to seven.</p>\n<p><strong>Customer:</strong> Oh right, uh well, some friends of ours rented the Astor cottage from you for a week by the ocean last summer and they recommended it to us. My husband and I would like to rent it in the fall for a week. Okay, when exactly? Um, we’re looking at the week beginning September twenty first if it’s available.</p>\n<p><strong>Owner:</strong> Let me check, uh… hmm, no I’m sorry it’s already booked that week. You could have it the previous week, from the <strong>(1) fourteenth</strong>.</p>\n<blockquote data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<p><strong>Dịch:</strong> <strong>Người dẫn chuyện:</strong> Chủ sở hữu chung của ngôi nhà là Carol Marriott và chồng cô ấy, Dave, vì vậy Dave đã được viết vào chỗ trống. Bây giờ chúng ta sẽ bắt đầu. Bạn nên trả lời các câu hỏi khi nghe vì bạn sẽ không nghe lại lần thứ hai. Hãy lắng nghe cẩn thận và trả lời các câu hỏi 1 đến 7.<strong>Khách hàng:</strong> Ồ phải, à, một số người bạn của chúng tôi đã thuê ngôi nhà Astor từ ông một tuần bên bờ biển vào mùa hè năm ngoái và họ giới thiệu nó cho chúng tôi. Chồng tôi và tôi muốn thuê nó vào mùa thu trong một tuần.<strong>Chủ nhà:</strong> Được rồi, chính xác là khi nào?<strong>Khách hàng:</strong> Ừm, chúng tôi đang xem xét tuần bắt đầu từ ngày 21 tháng 9 nếu nó còn trống.<strong>Chủ nhà:</strong> Để tôi kiểm tra… ừm, không, tôi xin lỗi, tuần đó đã có người đặt rồi. Bạn có thể thuê nó vào tuần trước đó, từ ngày <strong>(1) 14</strong>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><strong>Customer:</strong> Well, we could manage that week if we change a couple of arrangements. Um, how much would it cost?</p>\n<p><strong>Owner:</strong> That would be <strong>(2) Eight Hundred and thirty five dollars</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Customer:</strong> Ah, that’s rather more than we wanted to pay, I’m afraid. Uh, we were hoping to pay closer to Seven Hundred and ninety dollars, which our friends paid last year. We also have a slightly smaller cottage called Periwinkle cottage. Excuse me, um, how do you spell the name? P-e-r-i W-i-n-k-l-e, Periwinkle. It’s available the week you want it and it’s the exact same price that your friends paid last year.</p>\n<blockquote data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<p><strong>Dịch:</strong> <strong>Khách hàng:</strong> À, chúng tôi có thể sắp xếp tuần đó nếu chúng tôi thay đổi một vài kế hoạch. Ừm, giá bao nhiêu?<strong>Chủ nhà:</strong> Sẽ là <strong>(2) Tám trăm ba mươi lăm đô la</strong>.<strong>Khách hàng:</strong> À, tôi e rằng nó hơi nhiều so với số tiền chúng tôi muốn trả. Chúng tôi hy vọng trả gần Bảy trăm chín mươi đô la hơn, mà bạn bè chúng tôi đã trả năm ngoái.<strong>Chủ nhà:</strong> Chúng tôi cũng có một ngôi nhà nhỏ hơn một chút gọi là Periwinkle cottage.<strong>Khách hàng:</strong> Xin lỗi, ông đánh vần tên đó như thế nào? P-e-r-i W-i-n-k-l-e, Periwinkle. Nó còn trống vào tuần bạn muốn và giá chính xác bằng mức mà bạn bè bạn đã trả năm ngoái.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><strong>Owner:</strong> I take it you want a place that sleeps just two people, like Astor cottage? Um, yes, is it near Astor cottage? Yeah, it’s right across the street. And what’s this cottage like? Well, it’s a part of a historic building that was originally a <strong>(3) school</strong> a hundred years ago. It was converted into a post office around nineteen fifty, then later on the post office moved and the building was divided to make two cottages. So is it on several floors? No, it’s all on one floor. There’s a large living room, a kitchen that’s really well equipped, a bedroom and a bathroom with a tub and a shower. Oh, very nice. From the living room you can go out onto the <strong>(4) deck</strong>, which is a great place to have your meals when the weather is nice.</p>\n<blockquote data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<p><strong>Dịch:</strong> <strong>Chủ nhà:</strong> Tôi đoán là bạn muốn một nơi chỉ ngủ được hai người, giống như nhà Astor?<strong>Khách hàng:</strong> Ừm, vâng, nó có gần nhà Astor không?<strong>Chủ nhà:</strong> Có, nó ngay bên kia đường. Và ngôi nhà này trông như thế nào?<strong>Chủ nhà:</strong> À, nó là một phần của một tòa nhà lịch sử ban đầu được sử dụng làm <strong>(3) trường học</strong> một trăm năm trước. Nó được chuyển đổi thành một bưu điện khoảng năm 1950, sau đó bưu điện chuyển đi và tòa nhà được chia thành hai ngôi nhà.<strong>Khách hàng:</strong> Vậy nó có nhiều tầng không?<strong>Chủ nhà:</strong> Không, nó đều nằm trên một tầng. Có một phòng khách lớn, một nhà bếp được trang bị đầy đủ, một phòng ngủ và một phòng tắm có bồn và vòi sen. Ồ, rất đẹp. Từ phòng khách, bạn có thể đi ra <strong>(4) hiên</strong>, đó là một nơi tuyệt vời để dùng bữa khi thời tiết đẹp.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><strong>Customer:</strong> That sounds fantastic. Can you see the <strong>(5) river</strong> that flows through the town from the cottage? You sure can. It’s close by, you can see it from the bedroom. Okay. Uh, would we need to bring anything? Bedding, say? That’s provided, but we make a small charge for <strong>(6) towels</strong> unless you bring your own, of course. Oh, okay, I’ll do that. Uh, because we’ll be driving, there’ll be plenty of room in the car for things like that. Oh, that reminds me, is there a <strong>(7) garage</strong> that we can use? I’m afraid there isn’t one, uh, but you can usually get a parking spot on the street right in front of the cottage, no problem. We probably won’t use the car much while we’re there anyway, we like to go for walks.</p>\n<blockquote data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<p><strong>Dịch:</strong> <strong>Khách hàng:</strong> Nghe tuyệt vời quá. Có thể nhìn thấy <strong>(5) con sông</strong> chảy qua thị trấn từ ngôi nhà không?<strong>Chủ nhà:</strong> Chắc chắn rồi. Nó ở gần, bạn có thể nhìn thấy nó từ phòng ngủ.<strong>Khách hàng:</strong> Được rồi. À, chúng tôi có cần mang theo gì không? Chẳng hạn như chăn ga gối đệm?<strong>Chủ nhà:</strong> Cái đó được cung cấp, nhưng chúng tôi tính một khoản phí nhỏ cho <strong>(6) khăn tắm</strong> trừ khi bạn tự mang theo.<strong>Khách hàng:</strong> Ồ, được rồi, tôi sẽ tự mang. Vì chúng tôi sẽ lái xe nên có nhiều chỗ trong xe cho những thứ như vậy. Ồ, điều đó làm tôi nhớ ra, có <strong>(7) gara</strong> nào chúng tôi có thể sử dụng không?<strong>Chủ nhà:</strong> Tôi e rằng không có, nhưng bạn thường có thể đậu xe trên đường ngay trước ngôi nhà, không vấn đề gì.<strong>Khách hàng:</strong> Dù sao thì chúng tôi có lẽ cũng sẽ không sử dụng xe nhiều khi ở đó, chúng tôi thích đi bộ.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><strong>Narrator:</strong> Before you hear the rest of the conversation, you have some time to look at questions eight to ten on page two. Now listen and answer questions eight to ten.</p>\n<p><strong>Customer:</strong> Oh, and what about the town itself? Are there any restaurants in the neighborhood?</p>\n<p><strong>Owner:</strong> There are a few, all within walking distance. A lot of people like the fish restaurant, but in my opinion, the <strong>(8) Chinese</strong> restaurant has got to be the best for miles around. That’s good to know. We might end up eating out every evening. Well, why not? Our friend said the town is pretty famous for <strong>(9) antique</strong> stores. That’s right, there’s a whole bunch of them, at least ten on the main street. Marvelous. Okay, I’d like to make the booking please.</p>\n<p><strong>Owner:</strong> Great. We ask for a deposit of <strong>(10) two hundred dollars</strong>, and final payment at least six weeks before your stay. But we’ll be away ourselves for much of August, so let’s say no later than the last day of <strong>(10) July</strong>. Is that okay with you?</p>\n<p><strong>Customer:</strong> Fine. Okay, then let me give you our details so you can send the deposit.</p>\n<blockquote data-path-to-node=\"26\">\n<p><strong>Dịch:</strong> <strong>Người dẫn chuyện:</strong> Trước khi bạn nghe phần còn lại của cuộc hội thoại, bạn có thời gian để xem các câu hỏi 8 đến 10. Bây giờ hãy lắng nghe và trả lời các câu hỏi 8 đến 10.<strong>Khách hàng:</strong> Ồ, còn về thị trấn thì sao? Có nhà hàng nào trong khu vực lân cận không?<strong>Chủ nhà:</strong> Có một vài cái, tất cả đều có thể đi bộ được. Nhiều người thích nhà hàng cá, nhưng theo ý kiến của tôi, nhà hàng <strong>(8) Trung Quốc</strong> là ngon nhất trong khu vực.<strong>Khách hàng:</strong> Thật tốt khi biết. Có lẽ chúng tôi sẽ ăn ngoài mỗi tối.<strong>Chủ nhà:</strong> Chà, tại sao không chứ? Bạn chúng tôi nói thị trấn khá nổi tiếng với các cửa hàng đồ <strong>(9) cổ</strong>. Đúng vậy, có rất nhiều cửa hàng, ít nhất mười cửa hàng trên phố chính. Tuyệt vời.<strong>Khách hàng:</strong> Được rồi, tôi muốn đặt phòng.<strong>Chủ nhà:</strong> Tuyệt. Chúng tôi yêu cầu đặt cọc <strong>(10) hai trăm đô la</strong>, và thanh toán cuối cùng ít nhất sáu tuần trước kỳ nghỉ của bạn. Nhưng chúng tôi sẽ đi vắng suốt tháng Tám, vì vậy hãy nói là không muộn hơn ngày cuối cùng của <strong>(10) tháng Bảy</strong>. Bạn thấy ổn chứ?<strong>Khách hàng:</strong> Tốt. Được rồi, vậy thì để tôi cung cấp thông tin chi tiết của chúng tôi để bạn có thể gửi tiền đặt cọc.</p>\n</blockquote>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('4599a6da-b81c-4c89-a01b-470a8d300309', 'cdea869a-8e41-445e-90c0-5c57c37aa47b', 'fillup', 'Questions 11–16', '<p data-start="109" data-end="192">Complete the sentences below.<br data-start="138" data-end="141">Write <strong data-start="147" data-end="175">ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p data-section-id="16jkwan" data-start="199" data-end="225"><span style="font-size: 12pt;" role="text"><strong data-start="202" data-end="225">Reynolds Electrical</strong></span></p>
<ul data-start="227" data-end="626">
<li data-section-id="18a47rv" data-start="227" data-end="284">
<p>Tony Reynolds’ first business produced {cars}</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="9u4azu" data-start="285" data-end="347">
<p>Reynolds Electrical was started in the year {1928}</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1jkuuve" data-start="348" data-end="421">
<p>There was previously a {cinema} where the company is now based.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1gopwy6" data-start="422" data-end="498">
<p>The {quality} of the products is an important factor for customers.</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1glii0d" data-start="499" data-end="547">
<p>The company is building a new {factory}</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="155c2tp" data-start="548" data-end="626">
<p>The company recently won an award for its success in reducing {waste}</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 2: REYNOLDS ELECTRICAL</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Kathy:</strong> Hello and welcome to Reynolds Electrical. I''m Kathy Meredith and I''m in charge of your training program during the month you''re going to spend with us.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">Let me start by telling you a little about the company. The name Reynolds comes from Tony Reynolds. He was a local man born in 1905. When he was only 19, he started a small company that manufactured <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"199\">(Q11) cars</strong></span>. This was a failure, though, and he gave up in 1927. He then trained as an electrician and in the following year, rented a small workshop and set up a new company: Reynolds Electrical. So the company dates back to <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"424\">(Q12) 1928</strong></span>, and I''m pleased to say we''ve been successful more or less ever since.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">And we moved to our present site in 1955. There was a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">(Q13) cinema</strong></span> here which had to be demolished and new buildings were put up. Of course, in those days it was quite common to have factories close to town centres. The company has been more and more successful in the last few years. The main reason is a change in the pattern of sales. Another reason for our success is that despite strong competition from cheaper competitors, our customers are happy to pay a higher price for the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"484\">(Q14) quality</strong></span> of Reynolds goods.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">Because of this success, we''re feeling confident about the future and we''ve got some exciting plans. We''re now constructing a second <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"133\">(Q15) factory</strong></span> so that we can increase production. We''re also replacing our existing production machinery and making improvements to all the offices. One more point I''d like to make is that ever since Tony Reynolds started the business, we''ve always tried to be the best in our field. So earlier this year, we were delighted when we received an award for making a big reduction in <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"513\">(Q16) waste</strong></span>. Our policy is to recycle as much as we can.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">WEEKLY SCHEDULE (Questions 17–20)</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Kathy:</strong> Right, now I''ll give you an idea of what you''ll be doing in the next few days. You''ll spend most of this week with different members of our staff, working alongside them so that you can learn what their job involves. And we''ll get together at 3:00 every afternoon to focus on a different part of our work.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\">Every Monday we have a meeting of people from different parts of the company, and I''d like you to take part in this afternoon''s meeting. Today we''re going to discuss ways of getting higher levels of <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"199\">(Q17) safety</strong></span>, and we''ll be interested in any suggestions you might make. So think about it while you''re going around the factory today.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\">Tomorrow afternoon, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">Tuesday</strong></span>, I''ll introduce you to the IT department and they''ll update you about the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"102\">(Q18) website</strong></span> development (changes to our website). This is important because a growing number of people want to buy online.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\">Then on <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">Wednesday</strong></span>, we''ll talk about our communication with those very important people—<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"87\">(Q19) customers</strong></span>. Without them, of course, we''d soon go out of business. And that discussion will cover all sorts of things from advertising to research into what sort of people buy our products.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\">The next afternoon, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">Thursday</strong></span>, we''ll focus on recruitment and how we try to make sure we have the best staff to meet our needs. We seem to be doing well because mostly they stay with us for several years.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\">And finally for this week, at least on <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"39\">Friday</strong></span>, something that I think you''ll find more interesting than it sounds—and that''s how we ensure we have sufficient <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"158\">(Q20) money</strong></span> coming in to pay our bills and other expenses such as wages.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\">Right now, are there any questions before I go on?</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a8a52e4b-3b9d-4be3-9c38-c372587d20e3', 'a8fd8fd0-d1da-4e49-8bdf-e9aeee444201', 'fillup', 'Questions 24-26', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<p class="txt" style="text-align: left;">Complete the summary below.<br />Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p class="txt" style="text-align: center;"><strong>A study of insect decision-making</strong></p>
<p class="txt">A Bristol University study looked at how insects make decisions when their home has been {threatened}. The ants in the experiment relied on the use of individuals called {scouts} new nest and efficiently direct the others to go there. The study concluded that the effective implementation of the ants’ decision meant that the insects could change homes quickly. The study emphasized the necessity, for people well as insects, of having active {leaders} in order to execute decisions successfully.</p>
</div>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>24. A Bristol University study looked at how insects make decisions when their home has been <strong>threatened</strong>.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>threatened</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “…the problems associated with making a necessarily swift choice. If the ants’ existing nest become <strong>suddenly threatened</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>25. The ants in the experiment relied on the use of individuals called <strong>scouts</strong> to find a new nest and efficiently direct the others to go there.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"33\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>scouts</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “…the insects choose certain ants to act as <strong>scouts</strong> to find a new nest.”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>26. The study emphasized the necessity, for people as well as insects, of having active <strong>leaders</strong> in order to execute decisions successfully.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"35\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>leaders</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) “But it does suggest, even for humans, the importance of recruiting <strong>dynamic leaders</strong> to a cause, because the most important thing about collective decision-making, as shown by these insect experiments, is to get others to follow.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> “Dynamic leaders” (nhà lãnh đạo năng động) được coi là cần thiết để thực thi các quyết định.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7b0644c0-f428-4194-8bbf-7d71c8b67a92', '38912980-df05-46a3-9f2f-a9359e27a438', 'radio', 'Questions 27–30', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": " TRUE "}, {"content": " FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "It is uncertain when the Voynich manuscript was written."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": " TRUE "}, {"content": " FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Wilfrid Voynich donated the manuscript to the Beinecke Library."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": " TRUE "}, {"content": " FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Interest in the Voynich manuscript extends beyond that of academics and professional codebreakers."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": " TRUE "}, {"content": " FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The text of the Voynich manuscript contains just under 70 symbols."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>27. It is uncertain when the Voynich manuscript was written.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 1) &#8220;&#8230;an unprepossessing vellum manuscript&#8230; containing 240-odd pages of drawings and text of <strong>unknown age and authorship</strong>.&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả khẳng định niên đại (age) và tác giả (authorship) của bản thảo là <strong>không rõ</strong> (unknown), do đó thời điểm viết là không chắc chắn (uncertain).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>28. Wilfrid Voynich donated the manuscript to the Beinecke Library.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 1) &#8220;It&#8217;s known to scholars as the Voynich manuscript, after the American book dealer <strong>Wilfrid Voynich, who bought the manuscript from a Jesuit college in Italy in 1912</strong>.&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản chỉ nói Voynich đã <strong>mua</strong> bản thảo và hiện nó đang ở Thư viện Beinecke của Yale, nhưng <strong>không nói rõ</strong> ông có hiến tặng (donated) hay không.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>29. Interest in the Voynich manuscript extends beyond that of academics and professional codebreakers.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) &#8220;Over the years, the manuscript has attracted the attention of everyone from <strong>amateur dabblers to top codebreakers</strong>&#8230;&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Sự quan tâm bao gồm cả &#8220;amateur dabblers&#8221; (những người nghiệp dư), không chỉ giới học thuật (academics) hay chuyên gia giải mã (professional codebreakers).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>30. The text of the Voynich manuscript contains just under 70 symbols.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) &#8220;The precise size of the ‘alphabet&#8217; of the Voynich manuscript was unclear: it&#8217;s possible to make out <strong>more than 70 distinct symbols</strong> among the 170,000-character text.&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Bản thảo chứa <strong>hơn 70</strong> ký hiệu riêng biệt, mâu thuẫn với nhận định &#8220;just under 70&#8221; (chỉ dưới 70).</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
