<p> Example</p>
<p> Name: <strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><em>Anna Black</em></span></strong></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="height: 669.336px;">
<td style="border-color: #000000; border-width: 1px; padding: 1px;">
<p> Type of accommodation:                         a house</p>
<p> Preferred location:                                   <span class="citation-3305 citation-3306 citation-3307">the {southeast}<span class="citation-3305 citation-3306 citation-3307 citation-end-3307"> of the town</span></span></p>
<p> Facilities required:                                   <span class="citation-3305 citation-3306 citation-3307 citation-end-3307"><span class="citation-3302 citation-3303 citation-3304">furnished property- with a </span><span class="citation-3302 citation-3303 citation-3304 citation-end-3304">{washing machine}</span></span></p>
<p> Period of time required:                           <span class="citation-3302 citation-3303 citation-3304 citation-end-3304">one year</span></p>
<p> Start date of rental period:                       {15th May| 15 May| May 15th| May 15}</p>
<p> Present address:                                     <span class="citation-3302 citation-3303 citation-3304 citation-end-3304">56, Stone Street</span></p>
<p><span class="citation-3290 citation-3291 citation-3292 citation-end-3292"> Phone<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="22"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-3290 citation-3291"> number:                                        <span class="citation-3302 citation-3303 citation-3304 citation-end-3304">(mobile) 07942 326584</span></span></p>
<p><span class="citation-3290 citation-3291"><span class="citation-3289 citation-end-3289"> Re<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="25"><!----></sup></span>ference from:                                       <span class="citation-3302 citation-3303 citation-3304 citation-end-3304">her {employer}</span></span></p>
<p><span class="citation-3290 citation-3291"> Maximum rent:                                         <span class="citation-3302 citation-3303 citation-3304 citation-end-3304"><span class="math-inline" data-math="£" data-index-in-node="14">£</span> {675} per month</span></span></p>
<p><span class="citation-3290 citation-3291"> Appl<span class="citation-3287 citation-3288">icant’s job:                                         <span class="citation-3302 citation-3303 citation-3304 citation-end-3304">{a translator|translator }</span></span></span></p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong><span class="citation-3287 citation-3288"> Documents to be supplied</span></strong></p>
<p><span class="citation-3287 citation-3288"><span class="citation-3283 citation-3284"> ID check:</span>                                                   <span class="citation-3302 citation-3303 citation-3304 citation-end-3304">applicant’s passport</span></span></p>
<p><span class="citation-3287 citation-3288"> Credit check:                                             <span class="citation-3302 citation-3303 citation-3304 citation-end-3304"><span class="citation-3281 citation-3282">a {bank statement}</span><span class="citation-3281 citation-3282 citation-end-3282">.</span></span></span></p>
<p> </p>
<p id="p-rc_b53f6cabbef76016-98" data-path-to-node="7"><span class="citation-3279 citation-3280 citation-end-3280"> Viewing arrangements<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="34"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-3279 citation-end-3279"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="35"><!----></sup></span></p>
<p data-path-to-node="7"><span class="citation-3279 citation-3280 citation-end-3280"><span class="citation-3277 citation-3278"> Address of property:</span>                                  <span class="citation-3281 citation-3282 citation-end-3282"><span class="citation-3277 citation-3278">33, {Ainsworth}</span><span class="citation-3277 citation-3278 citation-end-3278"> Street</span></span></span></p>
<p data-path-to-node="7"><span class="citation-3279 citation-3280 citation-end-3280"> Viewing day and time:                               <span class="citation-3277 citation-3278 citation-end-3278">Saturday 4 p.m</span></span></p>
<p><span class="citation-3279 citation-3280 citation-end-3280"> To check:                                                   <span class="citation-3277 citation-3278 citation-end-3278"><span class="citation-3273 citation-3274">Is there a {telephone}</span><span class="citation-3273 citation-3274 citation-end-3274"> in the house?</span></span></span></p>
<p><span class="citation-3279 citation-3280 citation-end-3280"><span class="citation-3277 citation-3278 citation-end-3278"><span class="citation-3273 citation-3274 citation-end-3274">                                                                   <span class="citation-3273 citation-3274 citation-end-3274"><span class="citation-3271 citation-3272">Is there a {bus stop}</span><span class="citation-3271 citation-end-3271"> nearby?</span></span></span></span></span></p>
<p><!----><!----></p>
<p><span class="citation-3287 citation-3288"><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></span></p>
<p id="p-rc_b53f6cabbef76016-99" data-path-to-node="8,0,0"></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 1: ACCOMMODATION REQUEST</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Good morning, how can I help you?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> I''m interested in renting somewhere to live in town and was wondering what you had available.</p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_9cea803bb3ba25a6-161\" data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> <span class=\"citation-2101 citation-end-2101\">Excellent. I''ll just need to find out a bit more about what you''re looking for and then we can see what we''ve got. So your name is?</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><span class=\"citation-2101 citation-end-2101\"><strong>Anna:</strong>Anna Black </span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><span class=\"citation-2101 citation-end-2101\"><strong>Agent: </strong>Good, got that. And what sort of accommodation are you looking for ideal<sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"1\"><!----></sup></span>ly?</p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> Well, I don''t know if this is going to be possible, but ideally a house. I live in a flat at the moment and I''ve got really noisy neighbours. That''s the reason I want to move.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Oh dear. And I''m afraid most of the accommodation for rent in the city centre is flats. Would you be prepared to look elsewhere? There are a lot of nice properties in the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"178\">(Q1) southeast</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> Oh yes, that would be really convenient for me. Quite a few of my friends are there and it would be really close to my work.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> And there''s more chance of finding what you''re after there. I take it you''d be looking for a furnished place, would you?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> Yes. And I know it''s not always included, but I''d like to have a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"71\">(Q2) washing machine</strong></span>. I hate going to laundrettes and if I''m a bit further out of the city, it might be a problem to find one.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> I''ll see what I can do. Now, how long would you need the property for, bearing in mind that the minimum is six months?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> One year. I don''t want to chop and change too often and that''d give me the chance to see how things work out,and then I could reassess the situation after that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Mm-hmm. And when would you like to move in?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> I''ve got to be out of my present place by April 30th, then I''m going to visit my parents for a couple of weeks, so let''s say <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"131\">(Q3) 15th of May</strong> (or <strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"152\">15 May</strong>)</span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> And what''s your current address? I''d better make a note of that for our files,and I''ll put that you''re there only until the end of April.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong>Anna:</strong>56 Stone Street?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong>Agent:</strong>Mm-hmm.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> And is there a phone number I can get you on?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> Yes, the best one to use is my mobile and that''s 07942 326584.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Now of course we''ll need a reference before we''re able to proceed with any contract. Who would be able to supply you with a reference?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> I''m pretty sure my <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">(Q4) employer</strong></span> will do that for me. I don''t really know my doctor or anyone like that here.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Good. Now let''s see what we''ve got that might suit you. Oh, first, how much are you looking to pay?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> I''m paying £650 a month at the moment and the most I can go to is <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"72\">(Q5) 675</strong></span>. I really can''t go over that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> That shouldn''t be any problem. It''s a realistic figure. And can I ask what it is you do for a living?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> Since I came here, I''ve been working for various bodies within the city as a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"83\">(Q6) translator</strong></span>, you know, for the police and the hospital.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"26\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">DOCUMENTS &amp; VIEWING (Questions 7–10)</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Now, if we do find something, we''ll need to check your ID, so we''ll need to see your passport. And of course, to do the credit check, we''ll need to see a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"161\">(Q7) bank statement</strong></span> in order to complete all the paperwork.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> No problem, I can bring this in tomorrow.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Good. Now, we''ve got a small house to rent that I think might be just what you''re looking for. 33 <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"105\">(Q8) Ainsworth</strong></span> Street.That''s A-I-N-S-W-O-R-T-H Street. Here are the details.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> This looks great. Right size, right price.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Well, I can arrange for you to view it on Saturday around 4:00 pm if that''s convenient.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> Sounds good. I can''t see any mention of a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"48\">(Q9) telephone</strong></span> in the details, though. I''d need that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Hmm, I''ll look into that and I can double check when we''re at the property.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> And sorry, there''s another thing. Do you happen to know if there''s a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"75\">(Q10) bus stop</strong></span> reasonably close to the house so that I can get around easily?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"36\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"36\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Agent:</strong> Again, if I can''t find out before Saturday, I''ll check it out when we''re there.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"37\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Anna:</strong> Okay, so I''ll drop by tomorrow with those papers you need and then see you at the property Saturday at 4:00 pm.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37\"><strong>Agent:</strong> Excellent. </p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('0cc2e807-4a01-4d74-a7f4-a98fd7e2d1c5', '38912980-df05-46a3-9f2f-a9359e27a438', 'matrix', 'Questions 31–34', NULL, '<p>Use the information in the passage to match the people (listed A-H) with opinions or deeds below.</p>
<p>Choose the appropriate letters <strong>A-H</strong> in boxes <strong>31-34</strong>.</p>
<p><strong>NB </strong>you may use any letter more than once.</p>
', 'classification', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": "List of people", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "The number of times that some words occur make it unlikely that the manuscript is based on an authentic language.", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "Unlike some other similar objects of fascination, people can gain direct access to the Voynich manuscript.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "The person who wrote the manuscript may not have been entirely sane.", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "It is likely that the author of the manuscript is the same person as suggested by Wilfrid Voynich.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "Gordon Rugg", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "Roger Bacon", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "William Newbold", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "William Friedman", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "Rob Churchill", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "Gabriel Landini", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "Ren Zandbergen", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "Girolamo Cardano", "categoryLetter": "H"}]}', '[{"content": "<p><strong>31. The number of times some words occur make it unlikely that the manuscript is based on an authentic language.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>D (William Friedman)</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) Friedman <strong>&#8220;discovered that some words and phrases appeared more often than expected in a standard language, casting doubt on claims that the manuscript concealed a real language&#8230;&#8221;</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Phát hiện về tần suất từ ngữ bất thường của Friedman khiến ông nghi ngờ bản thảo là ngôn ngữ nhân tạo.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>32. Unlike some other similar objects of fascination, people can gain direct access to the Voynich manuscript.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>A (Gordon Rugg)</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) Tiến sĩ Gordon Rugg nói: &#8220;Most other mysteries involve second-hand reports&#8230; But this is one that you <strong>can see for yourself</strong>.&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Rugg nhấn mạnh khả năng tiếp cận trực tiếp bản thảo, khác với các bí ẩn khác.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>33. The person who wrote the manuscript may not have been entirely sane.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>E (Rob Churchill)</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 9) &#8220;Others, such as <strong>Churchill, have suggested that the sheer weirdness of the illustrations and text hint at an author who had lost touch with reality</strong>.&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Churchill gợi ý tác giả có thể đã mất liên lạc với thực tế (lost touch with reality/not entirely sane) vì sự kỳ lạ của minh họa và văn bản.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>34. It is likely that the author of the manuscript is the same person as suggested by Wilfrid Voynich.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>C (William Newbold)</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) <strong>&#8220;In 1921 Voynich&#8217;s view that Bacon was the writer appeared to win support from the work of William Newbold</strong>&#8230;&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Newbold đã công bố giải mã chứng minh Roger Bacon (người được Voynich đề xuất) là tác giả.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f6eac0c2-9b87-4e42-90f4-c7a78aedcb42', '597baadc-be27-4191-a973-89470c2898da', 'matching', 'Questions 25-30', '', '<p>What topic do students learn about in each of the following courses?</p>
<p>Choose <strong>SIX</strong> answers from the box and write the correct letter, <strong>A-G</strong></p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p><strong>Topics</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Understanding is Essential {workplace communication}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Foundations {PSWs’ role in health care}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>The Way We Work {biological systems}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Residence Care {independent living}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Dynamics {handling stress}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>The Power Within {memory stimulation activities}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "independent living"}, {"optionText": "the ageing process stages"}, {"optionText": "PSWs’ role in health care"}, {"optionText": "workplace communication"}, {"optionText": "memory stimulation activities"}, {"optionText": "handling stress"}, {"optionText": "biological systems"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', 'null', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('da2cc17f-7a07-4fee-93de-cc2f39d617f1', 'd3f00a39-e1a5-4849-85b3-65e5683a2218', 'matching', 'Questions 32–36', '', '<p>Complete the summary using the list of words, <strong>A-H</strong>, below.</p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: center;\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>The Zuni earthen architecture project</strong></span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The students in Zuni chose to renovate an old building which was being used for {D storage}. They came to an agreement that the building was worthy of rehabilitation based on its functional {C design}. At the beginning of the project, students were given the task to discover the history of the building through interviews with local residents. Through the course of the project, they learned where to locate {F resources} for the project. They also worked closely with a number of {A experts} on each step of the project. During the project, students were also given {G training} to build useful skills.</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A experts"}, {"optionText": "B location"}, {"optionText": "C design"}, {"optionText": "D storage"}, {"optionText": "E students"}, {"optionText": "F resources"}, {"optionText": "G training"}, {"optionText": "H businesses"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. D (storage) — {being used for storage}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn F):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Now it served as a place where <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">old furniture could be kept</strong>… now it was full of <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"102\">broken desks</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Một nơi dùng để cất giữ đồ đạc cũ (old furniture) và bàn ghế hỏng (broken desks) chính là mục đích lưu trữ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"120\">storage</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. C (design) — {based on its functional design}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn G):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The building’s <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"36\">design kept it relatively warm in the winter</strong>… and it <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">stayed cool in the summer</strong>… Because of this, my students agreed it was <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"163\">worth preserving</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các bạn học sinh đồng ý rằng tòa nhà xứng đáng được bảo tồn dựa trên các đặc điểm chức năng như giữ ấm mùa đông và làm mát mùa hè. Những yếu tố này đều thuộc về thiết kế (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"183\">design</strong>) của tòa nhà.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. F (resources) — {learn where to locate resources}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn G):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“She showed us where to find <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"49\">local supplies of sand and clay soil</strong> for the plaster mix.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Local supplies” (nguồn cung ứng địa phương) như cát và đất sét chính là các nguồn lực/nguyên liệu (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"112\">resources</strong>) cần thiết cho dự án.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. A (experts) — {worked closely with a number of experts}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn G):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">Preservationist</strong> Shalie Gasper arrived… To teach the traditional skills, Gasper and <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"106\">other local specialists</strong> joined us.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Những người như nhà bảo tồn (preservationist) hay chuyên gia địa phương (specialists) được gọi chung là các chuyên gia (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"132\">experts</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. G (training) — {students were also given training to build useful skills}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn G):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“They gave my class three full mornings of <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"63\">intensive workshops</strong> on history and preservation as well as mud-plastering <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"137\">technique</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc tổ chức các buổi hội thảo chuyên sâu (intensive workshops) để dạy về kỹ thuật chính là hình thức đào tạo (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"123\">training</strong>) để xây dựng kỹ năng cho học sinh.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e90be2e5-875b-4f5f-aa86-d4f115be4af0', 'da6d2547-4430-4e29-9c84-b2c1b983f9e4', 'fillup', 'Questions 1–6', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Manatees</strong></h2>
<p><strong>Appearance</strong><br />· look similar to dugongs, but with a differently shaped {tail}</p>
<p><strong>Movement</strong><br />· have fewer neck bones than most mammals<br />· need to use their {flippers} to help to turn their bodies around in order to look sideways<br />· sense vibrations in the water by means of {hair} on their skin</p>
<p><strong>Feeding</strong><br />· eat mainly aquatic vegetation, such as {seagrasses}</p>
<p>· grasp and pull up plants with their {lips}</p>
<p><strong>Breathing</strong><br />· come to the surface for air every 2–4 minutes when awake and every 15–20 while sleeping<br />· may regulate the {buoyancy} of their bodies by using muscles of diaphragm to store air internally</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', NULL, NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p>1. tail<br />(Đoạn 1: “However, the manatee has a broad, rounded tail, whereas the dugong’s is fluked, like that of a whale.”)<br />→ Manatee có đuôi (tail) tròn và rộng khác với dugong → đáp án là tail.</p>\n<p> <br />2. flippers<br />(Đoạn 2: “To see something on its left or its right, a manatee must turn its entire body, steering with its flippers.”)<br />→ Chúng phải dùng vây (flippers) để xoay người nhìn sang bên.</p>\n<p> <br />3. hair<br />(Đoạn 2: “They also have some hairs covering their bodies which help them sense vibrations in the water around them.”)<br />→ Manatee cảm nhận rung động nhờ lông (hair) trên da.</p>\n<p> <br />4. seagrasses<br />(Đoạn 3: “Seagrasses and other marine plants make up most of a manatee’s diet.”)<br />→ Thức ăn chính là rong biển (seagrasses).</p>\n<p> <br />5. lips<br />(Đoạn 4: “Manatees have lips which function like a pair of hands to help tear food away from the seafloor.”)<br />→ Chúng dùng môi (lips) để kéo và xé cây thủy sinh.</p>\n<p> <br />6. buoyancy<br />(Đoạn 5: “It’s thought that manatees use their muscular diaphragm and breathing to adjust their buoyancy.”)<br />→ Chúng điều chỉnh độ nổi (buoyancy) của cơ thể khi lặn hoặc nổi.</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('b7616adf-ff91-4252-83c6-33fcea70770a', 'bfa65954-af3c-4d93-af06-b5b89885571c', 'fillup', 'Questions 31–40', '<p data-start="105" data-end="173">Complete the notes below.</p>
<p data-start="105" data-end="173">Write <strong data-start="139" data-end="156">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer.</p>
<h3 data-start="180" data-end="203"><strong data-start="184" data-end="203">Photic sneezing</strong></h3>
<p data-start="205" data-end="338"><strong data-start="205" data-end="219">Background</strong><br data-start="219" data-end="222">Some people react to sunlight by:<br data-start="255" data-end="258">• a prickle in the nose       |<br data-start="281" data-end="284">• faster {breathing}            |⇒ relieved by a sneeze<br data-start="320" data-end="323">• watery eyes                    |</p>
<p data-start="340" data-end="426">This ‘photic’ sneeze cannot be controlled and is a {common} reflex.</p>
<p data-start="428" data-end="719"><strong data-start="428" data-end="451">Sneezing in general</strong><br data-start="451" data-end="454">• A sneeze is caused by some kind of irritation in the nose.<br data-start="514" data-end="517">• Nerve endings in the {face} are stimulated, leading to an explosion of air.<br data-start="615" data-end="618">• It is coordinated by the same mechanism that controls the production of {tears}</p>
<p data-start="721" data-end="1025"><strong data-start="721" data-end="754">Research into photic sneezing</strong><br data-start="754" data-end="757">The condition has been known for thousands of years.<br data-start="809" data-end="812">Aristotle: Why does the sun cause sneezing while a {fire} does not?<br data-start="900" data-end="903">Bacon showed the cause was light.<br data-start="936" data-end="939">Everett found 80% of photic sneezers shared the habit with {relatives}</p>
<p data-start="1027" data-end="1257"><strong data-start="1027" data-end="1041">Indicators<br></strong>Photic sneezers usually produce the same {number} of sneezes.<br data-start="1124" data-end="1127">The reaction is caused by a {contrast} in brightness.<br data-start="1197" data-end="1200">The sneeze takes {time} to recharge.</p>
<p data-start="1259" data-end="1461"><strong data-start="1259" data-end="1274">Application</strong><br data-start="1274" data-end="1277">The condition was often ignored apart from some research on photic sneezing among {pilots}<br data-start="1386" data-end="1389">But studying it may result in breakthroughs for more serious conditions.</p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>PART 4: </strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Welcome to this lecture in the health sciences, intended to inspire you and get you thinking about your research project. Today, I want to show you how even ordinary human behavior like sneezing, which normally happens when you get a cold, may be worth studying.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Have you ever been walking outside when a bright shaft of sunlight hits you between the eyes? The reaction of some people is immediate: an unpleasant prickling in the nose, an increase in their <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(31) breathing</strong></span></span> rate, and an uncontrollable watering of the eyes. Then, almost as quickly, they sneeze and gain relief. This may happen every time they go into the sun. This so-called “photic” or light sneeze is a reflex, which means it can’t be controlled, and it’s very <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(32) common</strong></span></span>—anything between one in ten and one in three people might be affected.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">In fact, a sneeze is triggered by an irritation of some sort in the linings of the nostrils. The result is a cascade of reactions, beginning with the stimulation of the nerve endings all over the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(33) face</strong></span> and generating an explosive expulsion of air at up to 95 miles an hour, like an extremely localized personal hurricane. The body’s coordination of such reactions is complicated and belongs to the subconscious control hardware that regulates other things—for example, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(34) tears</strong></span> in the eyes.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">People have been interested in the phenomenon of photic sneezing for thousands of years. The Greek philosopher Aristotle asked why the sun prompted us to sneeze, whereas th<span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">e heat </span>of a <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\">(35) </span></strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\">fire</span> </strong></span>does not. A partial answer came 2,000 years later when the English philosopher Francis Bacon showed that his photic sneeze had nothing to do with heat. If he closed his eyes when going into the sun, he didn’t sneeze, even though the heat was still there.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Henry Everett, a consultant psychiatrist at Johns Hopkins University Hospital in Baltimore, was the first to make a systematic attempt to understand the condition, noting in 1964 that 30% of the staff employed in the Medical Department were photic sneezers. Everett did some further investigation; he found that while 80% of sneezers reported other sneezers among their <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(36) relatives</strong></span>, only 20% of non-sneezers did.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Now, there are factors that are certain indicators of a photic sneeze. First of all, those with the condition almost always sneeze a set <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\">(<strong>37)</strong></span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong><span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"> </span>number</strong></span> of <span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">times </span>on exposure to light. In addition to this, the sneeze depends on a<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> <span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(38) contrast</strong></span></span> in visible brightness, such as when the sun moves out from behind a cloud. And the sneezing fit won’t be repeated immediately—the body needs <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(39) time</strong></span> before it can be recharged. So, if you go back into a darkened space and then immediately re-enter bright light, you will not sneeze again.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Now, on to possible applications of research in this area. The photic sneeze had long been overlooked because its effects are generally less than serious, although the government did once study it as a risk factor for <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(40) pilots</strong>.</span> Yet, work on such a simple disorder might lead to important discoveries on more acute conditions, such as migraine or epilepsy, which are also caused by “crossed wires” in the nervous system. That is why I encourage you to select something similar for your first investigative medical project. It could be the beginning of something even more useful.</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Now, let’s talk about the project timetable…</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('67d7c6b2-88fd-4817-af35-0c86666c812d', 'a9d226e2-abdb-421e-be6f-e32d48e0e63c', 'radio', 'Questions 11 – 14', '', '<div class="s-block-item s-repeatable-item s-block-sortable-item s-blog-post-section blog-section">
<div class="container">
<div class="sixteen columns">
<div class="s-blog-section-inner">
<div class="s-component s-text ">
<div class="">
<div class="s-component-content s-font-body">
<p>Choose the correct letter, <strong>A</strong>, <strong>B</strong>, or <strong>C</strong>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="s-block-item s-repeatable-item s-block-sortable-item s-blog-post-section blog-section">
<div class="container">
<div class="sixteen columns">
<div class="s-blog-section-inner">
<div class="s-component s-text ">
<div class="">
<div class="s-component-content s-font-body">
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Canadian Festival Theatre</strong></span></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. They can see a second play at a reduced price"}, {"option_text": "B. They can buy two tickets and get two free"}, {"option_text": "C. They can get a discount on Mondays"}], "question": "What special offer is there for regular theatre-goers in this season?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A. They are handed out at the theatre"}, {"option_text": "B. They provide information on the actors"}, {"option_text": "C. They give ideas for discussion"}], "question": "What information is given about the study guides?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A. It is only for those over 65"}, {"option_text": "B. It applies to a number of productions"}, {"option_text": "C. It includes a 5% reduction on gifts"}], "question": "What information is given about the ''Bring a friend'' special?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. He may retire from acting soon"}, {"option_text": "B. He writes his own plays"}, {"option_text": "C. He prefers acting in films to performing live"}], "question": "What does Michael say about the actor Christopher Plunket?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SECTION 2: CANADIANA FESTIVAL THEATRE SEASON</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Host:</strong> Michael McKay, the executive director of the Canadiana Festival Theatre is here with us to talk about the season starting in June. Welcome!</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Michael:</strong> Thank you. We have an amazing season this year with some great deals for our clients. You know, we have a lot of regular theater-goers who will be happy to know that we have some great specials for the upcoming season. For example, <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"241\">(11) if you order two tickets to any play performed at the theater, you can get 50% off the price of the next play [Answer: A – second play at reduced price]</strong> </span>we put on. This replaces the special offer we had last season, which was for 50% off all performances on Mondays.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">It is good to get youth interested in theater, so many schools arrange class trips to our theater. This year, we will send a special study guide to each class so the students can familiarize themselves with the play beforehand. Having some background information always makes the experience of watching the actors perform the play more enjoyable. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"347\">(12) Each guide has suggestions for classroom discussion [Answer: C]</strong></span> after seeing the show, which teachers find useful for a follow-up activity.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">Also, we mustn’t forget the “Bring a Friend” special for our senior citizens on Tuesday and Wednesday afternoons. Everyone over 60 can buy one ticket and get one free. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"168\">(13) The offer includes all the musicals plus the plays [Answer: B – a number of productions]</strong></span>, so there is lots of choice. We also include $5 off any gift shop purchase for those clients who spend more than $30 there.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">So, what would you say is the best play you have this year?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Michael:</strong> Ha! All the plays are great, but the “must-see” play is called <em data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"72\">Something to Say</em>. It stars the amazing actor Christopher Plunkett.<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"139\">(14) This likely will be the last year we see him perform [Answer: A – retire soon]</strong></span> as he has been on stage for over 60 years. Actually, for the first time, he helped write this play, and it really is a commentary on his amazing career as an actor. You may have seen him in supporting roles in movies, but acting on stage is his first love. He has been in so many fantastic dramas. I can’t think of him ever not being on stage</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">THE SEASON’S MUSICALS (Questions 15–20)</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Michael:</strong> Now let’s talk about the season’s musicals.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\">The first one is called <strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"24\"><em data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">The Climb</em></strong>. Of course, the best part is that we have that really amazing singer Justin McDonald playing the part of the hero. It is an inspiring story of a man called Steven who starts working for a newspaper in a very junior job in the mail room. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"271\">(15) After many years and many promotions, he finally gets to the top position [Answer: B – achieving success]</strong></span>. He becomes editor-in-chief of the newspaper.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\">Then we have that wonderful classic that we show every two years because it is so popular: <strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"91\"><em data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">The Voyagers</em></strong>. It is a wonderful story of a <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"134\">(16) Canadian farming family in the late 1800s [Answer: A – different century]</strong></span>, and how they settled their land near Kingston, Ontario. The musical gives a good description of the times, the struggles and the way of life in that period.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\">The next musical, <strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"18\"><em data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"18\">Joey Brown</em></strong>, is a comical story of a piano player who writes songs for kids’ TV shows. However, he ends up having a terrible time when he gets a new boss who always criticizes him and makes his life difficult. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"227\">(17) Poor Joey has to learn how to win over the boss [Answer: H – handling conflict]</strong></span>. The show has a couple of funny twists and a surprise ending.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\">In <strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"3\"><em data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"3\">Main Street</em></strong>, Karen Heinz stars in the true story of a young woman whose dream is to compete in the Olympics. She is such a powerful actress in this role. It is about a gymnast who is <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"186\">(18) crushed when, during a practice session, she breaks her ankle just one week before the games [Answer: E – experiencing disappointment]</strong>.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\">Now for <strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"8\"><em data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">Milly and Mike</em></strong>, what a story this is. Stephanie James and Peter Doomis are only 10 years old, but they star in the musical as the twins Milly and Mike. They have a wonderful <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"182\">(19) upbringing with their grandmother, who teaches them life’s lessons [Answer: D – growing up]</strong></span> through song.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\">The final must-see is so whimsical. In <strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"39\"><em data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"39\">Windswept</em></strong>,<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">(20) a land of imaginary creatures, the flowers and trees dance and the enchanted animals talk [Answer: F – magical place]</strong></span>. It is delightful and we even have a very talented actor who is amazing as he travels with us through the world of make-believe. Kids love this one. The music is fun and their imagination goes wild</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Michael:</strong> That all sounds wonderful. Now, tell me about the restaurants in the theater district…</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('d8ee723c-4bc3-471b-ad39-2d39aede3b31', 'a9d226e2-abdb-421e-be6f-e32d48e0e63c', 'matching', 'Questions 15 – 20', '', '<p>What is the main theme of each of the following musicals?<br>Choose <strong>SIX</strong> answers from the box and write the correct letter, <strong>A-H</strong></p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p><strong>Musicals</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>The Climb {managing to achieve success}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>The Voyagers {living in a different century}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Joey Brown {handling conflict}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Main Street {experiencing disappointment}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Millie and Mike {growing up}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Windswept {living in a magical place}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "living in a different century"}, {"optionText": "managing to achieve success"}, {"optionText": "ageing slowly"}, {"optionText": "growing up"}, {"optionText": "experiencing disappointment"}, {"optionText": "living in a magical place"}, {"optionText": "overcoming poverty"}, {"optionText": "handling conflict"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('43399f9b-7a63-40ff-aa28-96f5f97d21f1', '38912980-df05-46a3-9f2f-a9359e27a438', 'fillup', 'Questions 35–39', '<p>Choose the correct answer.Complete the sentences below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Voynich Researchers</strong></span></p>
<p>William Newbold believed that the author of the Voynich manuscript had been able to look at cells through a {microscope} Other researchers later demonstrated that there were flaws in his argument.</p>
<p>William Friedman concluded that the manuscript was written in an artificial language that was based on {concepts}</p>
<p>He couldn’t find out the meaning of this language but he believed that the {computer} would continue to bring advances in codebreaking.</p>
<p>Dr Gabriel Landini used a system known as {spectral analysis} his research, and claims to have demonstrated the presence of genuine words.</p>
<p>Dr Gordon Rugg’s system involved a grille, that made it possible to quickly select symbols that appeared in a {table} Rugg’s conclusion was that the manuscript lacked genuine meaning.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>35. William Newbold believed that the author of the Voynich manuscript had been able to look at cells through a microscope.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>microscope</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) &#8220;&#8230;the manuscript proved that Bacon had access to a <strong>microscope</strong> centuries before they were supposedly first invented.&#8221;</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>36. William Friedman concluded that the manuscript was written in an artificial language that was based on concepts.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"26\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>concepts</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) &#8220;&#8230;whose words are devised from <strong>concepts</strong>, rather than linguistics.&#8221;</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>37. He couldn&#8217;t find out the meaning of this language but he believed that the computer would continue to bring advances in codebreaking.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"28\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>computer</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) &#8220;&#8230;he suspected that major insights would come from using the device that had already transformed codebreaking: the <strong>computer</strong>.&#8221;</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>38. Dr Gabriel Landini used a system known as spectral analysis in his research, and claims to have demonstrated the presence of genuine words.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"30\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>spectral analysis</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 7) &#8220;&#8230;Dr Gabriel Landin&#8230; published the results of his study of the manuscript using a pattern-detecting method called <strong>spectral analysis</strong>.&#8221;</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>39. Dr Gordon Rugg&#8217;s system involved a grille, that made it possible to quickly select symbols that appeared in a table.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"32\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>table</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 8) &#8220;&#8230;Using a system&#8230; in which a specially constructed grille issued to pick out symbols from a <strong>table</strong>&#8230;&#8221;</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('40ee70cb-504c-469e-9345-b2d8276812d8', 'f1531fd3-1d8d-410d-bf9e-3434bc7d8337', 'fillup', 'Questions 31–40', '<p>Complete the notes below.<br data-start="145" data-end="148">Write <strong data-start="154" data-end="171">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p data-section-id="1on1lml" data-start="195" data-end="244"><span role="text"><strong data-start="198" data-end="244">Finding and re-using old supplies of metal</strong></span></p>
<p data-section-id="13xvd8f" data-start="246" data-end="281"><span role="text"><strong data-start="250" data-end="281">Historic use of scrap metal</strong></span></p>
<p data-start="283" data-end="368">In ancient Greece and Rome, scrap metal was sometimes used to make a {statue}</p>
<p data-start="370" data-end="485">In the 19th century, metal dealers in the US profited from disused equipment that had been used on a<strong data-start="471" data-end="485"> {farm}</strong></p>
<p data-section-id="9otgw8" data-start="492" data-end="534"><span role="text"><strong data-start="496" data-end="534">Why we need more scrap metal today</strong></span></p>
<p data-start="536" data-end="617">The {economy} of many countries is improving, leading to increased demand.</p>
<p data-start="619" data-end="689">The {quality} of the copper from the remaining sources is poor.</p>
<p data-start="691" data-end="753">The rapidly growing {electronics} industry is very wasteful</p>
<p data-section-id="ajmgsf" data-start="760" data-end="802"><span role="text"><strong data-start="764" data-end="802">Where scrap and metal can be found</strong></span></p>
<p data-start="804" data-end="873">In the UK, platinum is in {cars} at the sides of the roads.</p>
<p data-start="875" data-end="903">In Sweden, metal is found:</p>
<ul data-start="904" data-end="988">
<li data-section-id="1v87a5r" data-start="904" data-end="936">
<p>in old cotton {factories} in {pipes} under the ground used for gas</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-section-id="15vbyny" data-start="995" data-end="1043"><span role="text"><strong data-start="999" data-end="1043">How metals are separated from each other</strong></span></p>
<p data-start="1045" data-end="1113">It is possible to use a big {magnet} for some types of metal</p>
<p data-start="1115" data-end="1184">A potential new method in the UK is through the use of {bacteria}</p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 4: RECYCLING OF METAL</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lecturer:</strong> Hello, this is the second in our series of lectures on the subject of recycling. Today we''re looking at scrap metal—that is, pieces of metal that have been thrown away or I suppose, metal which is no longer serving any kind of practical function.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">Now, you might think that recycling is a modern phenomenon, but throughout history, people have always done this kind of thing in one way or another. Take the ancient Greeks and Romans with their scrap metal, copper or bronze—that is, they might turn it into a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"261\">(Q31) statue</strong></span>. So yes, nothing was wasted. In fact, scrap metal was considered valuable, and the Greeks and Romans used it in a variety of similar ways.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">Since then, the use of scrap metal has been turned into a whole industry. In some countries, it''s become a major export. In the US, for instance, dealing in scrap metal started back in the 19th century. This was a time of immense urban migration, and metal dealers knew they could make money out of the little machinery and tools that had been left behind on a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"240\">(Q32) farm</strong></span> when whole families had moved away to the city. And some of those dealers are now huge corporations selling scrap metal to buyers in other countries.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">So why do we need scrap metal today? First of all, there have been positive changes to the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">(Q33) economy</strong></span> in many countries, and because people have more money, this is driving up demand for goods, and you need metal to make many of those things.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\">Then, there are issues relating to specific types of metal. For example, take copper. The thing is, there are still plenty of sources for copper, but the issue is the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"167\">(Q34) quality</strong></span>—it''s just not as good as it used to be.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">Another reason why we need to locate and reuse old metals is due to an industry that''s really been developing over the last few decades, and of course it''s <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"156\">(Q35) electronics</strong></span>. Think about all the stuff you''ve bought and then replaced in the last few years. What happens to the things you get rid of? Well, a lot of them just end up being thrown away and the metal components go to waste.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\">So where do people look for scrap metal? Researchers and engineers are now investigating new sources in the UK. One place they''re looking at is the sides of the roads. That''s because tiny bits of a metal called platinum are emitted by cars and this can eventually be reused.And they''re also looking at the side of the road because with some types of <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(Q36) </strong><strong>plants </strong></span>that grow there, it''s been proved that they can absorb metals really effectively.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\">Sweden is also a country where a lot of work in this area is being done. Sweden used to manufacture a lot of cotton and so researchers there are looking at old <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"160\">(Q37) factories</strong></span> which used to produce it but are now closed down. There is so much metal in the walls and in the flooring that could be melted down again. And in the same country, deep below ground, are many, many <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"374\">(Q38) pipes</strong></span> that once provided gas to the surrounding neighborhood. It’s all there waiting to be excavated.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\">But the trick is how to do this without causing huge disruption to local residents and the traffic flow..So once we find our waste metals, how do we get at them? How are they separated? Well, if you''re trying to separate iron and steel from, say, silver or gold, perhaps in a computer or a cellphone, you could use a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"277\">(Q39) magnet</strong></span> provided it was larger than the components it was trying to attract.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\">But again, engineers are also being innovative in this area too. One researcher in the UK is carrying out an experiment with <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"125\">(Q40) bacteria</strong></span> that hopefully could be used to help recover precious metals from waste materials. Let me explain how that works exactly...</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('fc5fdefc-724a-4023-ad81-3594d90e41d4', 'd3f00a39-e1a5-4849-85b3-65e5683a2218', 'radio', 'Questions 37–40', '', '<p>Choose <strong>YES</strong> if the statement agrees with the claims of the writer, choose <strong>NO</strong> if the statement contradicts the claims of the writer, or <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong>  if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this.</p>', 'yes_no_not_given', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The price of materials is one drawback to using traditional architecture."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Earthen structures can easily be built in all regions of the U.S."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Working with a traditional earthen structure can have physical benefits."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "A traditional architecture curriculum is best suited to middle school level students."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. The price of materials is one drawback to using traditional architecture. — {NO}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn C):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Traditional architectural materials, such as earth, clay and straw, are <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"93\">cheap, easy to work with and readily available</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả khẳng định các vật liệu truyền thống như đất, sét và rơm thì <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"81\">rẻ</strong> (cheap) và dễ kiếm. Do đó, nói giá cả vật liệu là một “trở ngại” (drawback) là sai (contradicts) với quan điểm của người viết.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. Earthen structures can easily be built in all regions of the U.S. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn D):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“In New Mexico, examples of hand-built earthen structures still abound… Traditional building materials and the land that supplies them are so accessible that handcrafting a house still remains feasible.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ đề cập đến việc xây dựng nhà bằng đất rất khả thi tại <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">New Mexico</strong> (Tây Nam Hoa Kỳ). Tác giả <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"115\">không đưa ra khẳng định</strong> nào về việc liệu kiến trúc này có thể dễ dàng xây dựng ở <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"196\">tất cả các vùng khác</strong> (all regions) của Mỹ hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. Working with a traditional earthen structure can have physical benefits. — {YES}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn E):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“During the project, a student will get to know the materials… solve problems, work with classmates, and <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"127\">exercise muscles</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ “exercise muscles” (rèn luyện cơ bắp/vận động cơ bắp) chính là minh chứng cho các lợi ích về mặt thể chất (physical benefits) mà học sinh nhận được khi tham gia dự án.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. A traditional architecture curriculum is best suited to middle school level students. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn I):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“This experiment in adobe conservation with middle school students convinced me that traditional architecture deserves a place in the <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"154\">regular curriculum</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả khẳng định kiến trúc truyền thống xứng đáng có một vị trí trong <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"84\">chương trình học chính quy</strong> (regular curriculum) sau khi thực hiện thành công với học sinh trung học (middle school). Tuy nhiên, tác giả <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"220\">không hề nói</strong> rằng nó “phù hợp nhất” (best suited) cho cấp học này so với các cấp học khác.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a7210b02-f961-42e3-8e7c-6116a9f6a736', 'cdf96d67-2b3c-47b1-aeb5-87712f37ef13', 'matching', 'Questions 32-37', NULL, '<p>Complete each sentence with the correct ending, A-H, below.</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A. Suggested music was an essential part of every individual."}, {"optionText": "B. Made no link between music and language in a comprehensive study."}, {"optionText": "C. Believes that early language was very musical."}, {"optionText": "D. Felt that the origin of language should not be debated."}, {"optionText": "E. States that early language was made up of basic words used in an unsystematic way."}, {"optionText": "F. Devoted 17 chapters of a book to music."}, {"optionText": "G. Believes that proto-language had no individual words."}, {"optionText": "H. Referred to music in part of a book about the development of human beings."}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "The Société de Linguistique de Paris ", "correctAnswer": "D. Felt that the origin of language should not be debated.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Charles Darwin ", "correctAnswer": "H. Referred to music in part of a book about the development of human beings.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "John Blacking ", "correctAnswer": "A. Suggested music was an essential part of every individual.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Christiansen and Kirby ", "correctAnswer": "B. Made no link between music and language in a comprehensive study.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Derek Bickerton ", "correctAnswer": "E. States that early language was made up of basic words used in an unsystematic way.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Alison Wray ", "correctAnswer": "G. Believes that proto-language had no individual words.", "sectionContent": null}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"1\">Câu 32: The Société de Linguistique de Paris — D</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 1, dòng 5-7.</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…in 1866 the influential Société de Linguistique de Paris banned all discussions about the origin of language.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Hiệp hội này đã ban hành lệnh cấm tất cả các cuộc thảo luận về nguồn gốc ngôn ngữ, điều này đồng nghĩa với việc họ cảm thấy chủ đề này “không nên được tranh luận” (should not be debated).</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\">Câu 33: Charles Darwin — H</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 3, dòng 9-11.</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “One is the aforementioned Charles Darwin who, in his 1871 book on human evolution, The Descent of Man, devoted several pages to the development of music.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trong cuốn sách về sự tiến hóa của loài người (human evolution/development of human beings), Darwin đã dành một phần (vài trang) để nói về âm nhạc.</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">Câu 34: John Blacking — A</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 3, dòng 11-13.</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…John Blacking, whose 1973 book, How Musical is Man?, broached the idea that music is an inherent and universal human quality.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Blacking cho rằng âm nhạc là một đặc tính “vốn có và phổ quát” (inherent and universal) của con người, tương ứng với ý nói âm nhạc là “phần thiết yếu của mỗi cá nhân” (essential part of every individual).</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">Câu 35: Christiansen and Kirby — B</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 4, dòng 6-8.</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…Morten Christiansen and Simon Kirby’s book, Language Evolution (2000)… failed to mention music in any of its 17 chapters.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Dù viết một cuốn sách toàn diện về sự tiến hóa ngôn ngữ, hai tác giả này đã không hề nhắc đến âm nhạc, tức là “không tạo ra mối liên kết nào” (made no link) giữa âm nhạc và ngôn ngữ.</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">Câu 36: Derek Bickerton — E</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 7, dòng 4-6.</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “But Bickerton’s idea that the precursor of modern language consisted of words strung together with limited, if any, grammar is, I believe, fundamentally mistaken.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bickerton cho rằng tiền thân của ngôn ngữ bao gồm các từ đơn lẻ xâu chuỗi lại với nhau mà ít có ngữ pháp, tương đồng với ý “các từ cơ bản được dùng một cách không hệ thống” (basic words used in an unsystematic way).</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\">Câu 37: Alison Wray — G</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 8, dòng 3-7.</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “She argues that proto-language was ‘holistic’… a communication system composed of ‘messages’ rather than words…”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Alison Wray tin rằng tiền ngôn ngữ mang tính “tổng thể”, bao gồm các “thông điệp” chứ không phải được cấu thành từ các “từ riêng lẻ” (no individual words).</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('692ca01f-1468-472e-97d5-4d66d1c2ed72', 'b158a618-83fe-4d41-ada5-6dab14d91c2c', 'fillup', 'Questions 9-13', '<p data-path-to-node="17">Complete the summary below.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="17">Choose <strong data-path-to-node="17" data-index-in-node="35">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 9-13 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p><strong><span style="font-size: 12pt;">The history of some dyes</span></strong></p>
<p><strong>Highly valued dyes</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Tyrian purple</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Mucus from {shellfish} found in the Mediterranean</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>
<p>Cochineal (a red dye)</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Made from {insects} found in Latin America</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>
<p>Saffron (a yellow dye)</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Initially made from crocuses found on the island of Crete</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>
<p>Indigo (a blue dye)</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Made from plant leaves from India</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p>17th Century Europe</p>
<p><strong>Dyes made by country people:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>{blackberries} had two uses</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Jam</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Blue dye</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>
<p>Liquid from cleaning {beehives} had two uses</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Making mead</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Yellow dye</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>19th Century Europe</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Progress in study of {chemistry} led to synthetic dyes</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. shellfish — {Mucus from shellfish found in the Mediterranean}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…the mucus found in certain species of <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"62\">shellfish</strong> produced the deep rich <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"95\">Tyrian purple</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Màu tím Tyrian huyền thoại được chiết xuất từ chất nhầy của một loài động vật có vỏ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"97\">shellfish</strong>) ở vùng Địa Trung Hải.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. insects — {Cochineal (a red dye) … Made from insects}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 4):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…and <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"28\">cochineal</strong> was the name given to the red dye from Latin America… [which] was extracted from <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"121\">insects</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cochineal là loại thuốc nhuộm đỏ nổi tiếng được lấy từ một loài côn trùng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"87\">insects</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. blackberries — {blackberries had two uses: Jam / Blue dye}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“People who picked <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"39\">blackberries</strong> to make <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">jam</strong> soon recognized this wild fruit as a source for a <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"114\">blue dye</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ở vùng nông thôn, quả dâu tằm/mâm xôi đen (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"55\">blackberries</strong>) vừa được dùng làm mứt (jam), vừa là nguồn tạo ra thuốc nhuộm màu xanh.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. beehives — {Liquid from cleaning beehives had two uses: Making mead / Yellow dye}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Washing <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">beehives</strong> in preparation for making <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"64\">mead</strong>… yielded a liquid that could be used as a <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"113\">yellow dye</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc tẩy rửa các tổ ong (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"37\">beehives</strong>) để lấy nguyên liệu làm rượu mật ong (mead) tạo ra một loại dung dịch dùng để nhuộm màu vàng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. chemistry — {Progress in study of chemistry led to synthetic dyes}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“With the tremendous rise of interest in <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"61\">chemistry</strong> in the mid-19th century, several important innovations in dyeing came about [synthetic dye].”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sự tiến bộ và hứng thú trong nghiên cứu hóa học (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"61\">chemistry</strong>) vào giữa thế kỷ 19 đã dẫn đến sự ra đời của thuốc nhuộm tổng hợp (synthetic dyes).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('05518160-9f7a-4eef-a6b1-303f6eee5de8', 'ff3fb549-766c-42a1-a26f-54ecb7420100', 'fillup', 'Questions 1–10', '<p data-start="61" data-end="161">Write <strong data-start="116" data-end="144">ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<article class="text-token-text-primary w-full focus:outline-none [--shadow-height:45px] has-data-writing-block:pointer-events-none has-data-writing-block:-mt-(--shadow-height) has-data-writing-block:pt-(--shadow-height) [&amp;:has([data-writing-block])&gt;*]:pointer-events-auto [content-visibility:auto] supports-[content-visibility:auto]:[contain-intrinsic-size:auto_100lvh] scroll-mt-[calc(var(--header-height)+min(200px,max(70px,20svh)))]" dir="auto" tabindex="-1" data-turn-id="cc66c4fd-cf13-408c-afa0-554e22fc322e" data-testid="conversation-turn-395" data-scroll-anchor="false" data-turn="assistant">
<div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto [--thread-content-margin:--spacing(4)] @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:--spacing(6)] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:--spacing(16)] px-(--thread-content-margin)">
<div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn" tabindex="-1">
<div class="flex max-w-full flex-col grow">
<div class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" dir="auto" data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="33d60d0f-598d-47e8-870c-3f6d18878bd1" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-2">
<div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[1px]">
<div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full wrap-break-word light markdown-new-styling">
<h3 data-start="163" data-end="200">Enquiries on Hot Air Balloon Trip</h3>
<p data-start="202" data-end="248">The lowest price: {125} per person</p>
<p data-start="250" data-end="330">Each participant will be given a free {certificate} at the end of the flight</p>
<p data-start="332" data-end="383">The exact date can only be booked {online}</p>
<p data-start="385" data-end="449">The balloon can fly a maximum height of {1800} metres</p>
<p data-start="451" data-end="492">There are no flights at {night}</p>
<p data-start="451" data-end="492">The best time of year to go is in {autumn}</p>
<p data-start="547" data-end="618">Flights may be cancelled because of bad weather, e.g. {thunderstorm}</p>
<p data-start="620" data-end="672">It is advised to wear a jacket and {helmet}</p>
<p data-start="674" data-end="726">There is no {age} restriction for adults</p>
<p data-start="728" data-end="795" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">Participants must be able to {stand} throughout the flight</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="z-0 flex min-h-[46px] justify-start"> </div>
</div>
</div>
</article>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 1</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> Good morning, Smart Travel. Jason speaking.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Hi, good morning. I saw your advert in today’s paper about hot air balloon trips. It sounds pretty exciting and I wonder how much it costs.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> Well, the price may vary depending on the location, number of participants and add-ons. A single ride may cost you up to £280 per person, but if you choose group booking, there is a discount and the cheapest flight is <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #f4d24a;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"225\">(1) 125</strong></span></span> each for a group booking of at least 10 people.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Oh, that’s not too bad. What do you mean by add-ons?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> They are optional items like taking photos for you during the ride, champagne and sit-down breakfast after the flight. Upon completing the trip, we will provide each participant with a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f4d24a;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"192\">(2) certificate</strong></span>, and that is entirely free of charge.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Can I book a ride over the phone?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> Yes, that’s an option. Reservations can be made one year ahead of your trip by telephone, but to pick a specific date, you must book<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> <span style=\"background-color: #f4d24a;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"140\">(3) online</strong>.</span></span> A confirmation email will be sent to you right afterwards.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> How high can the balloons go?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> A hot air balloon’s height is limited by the temperature of the air and how much fuel it can carry. And the highest altitude ever recorded for a ride is <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #f4d24a;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"160\">(4) 1800</strong> </span></span>meters, but most rides stay below 300 meters.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Oh boy, that’s impressive. How long is a single ride?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> The average hot air balloon ride lasts about an hour. The entire ballooning experience, which includes ground preparation, flight and post-flight packing up and celebration, may take two to three hours.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> And what time are the flights?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> Our flights generally meet about an hour before sunrise on the day. You will be notified of the exact meeting time the evening before your flight. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f4d24a;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"154\">(5) Night</strong></span> flights are avoided due to weather conditions. Fair enough</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Which month do you recommend for a hot air balloon trip?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #f4d24a;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"7\">(6) Autumn</strong> </span></span>is the best time of year to take the trip. Not only can you see the changing hues of the trees from above, but it is a great way to spend time with the whole family before it gets too cold.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> I see.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> But please note that our flight may be cancelled and you will be notified by phone the day before.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Why is that?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> It can be quite dangerous to fly under bad weather conditions like a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f4d24a;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">(7) thunderstorm</strong></span>, so our experienced pilots will not go under such conditions.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> What should I wear for the ride?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> We suggest wearing comfortable clothing like a jacket. Multiple layers are always better. Wearing a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f4d24a;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"107\">(8) helmet</strong></span> for safety concerns is also a good idea. Sandals are not permitted.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Can children or older people participate?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> All children must be above the minimum <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f4d24a;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"46\">(9) age</strong></span> of 9 years old and they have to be accompanied by at least a parent or guardian. However, an adult has no age limit as long as they meet the health requirements.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> What exactly are the health requirements?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> Participants must at least be in fair physical condition. For example, they shall have no significant knee, hip or back problems, and no recent surgeries or broken bones. They must also <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f4d24a;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"193\">(10) stand</strong></span> unassisted for an hour during the flight. It is the required position during the whole flight.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\">As the balloon comes to land, all passengers will need to adopt the landing position with knees bent in front of them.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Are those rides safe?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> Hot air balloon companies are required to have a commercial balloon pilot licence and all our pilots go through rigorous training before they are allowed to fly. It is a relatively gentle activity; however, the impact of a balloon landing can vary drastically depending on factors like wind speed. Sometimes it is similar to the momentum of jumping off a small chair. If you cannot jump off a small chair, speaking to your doctor before booking a balloon flight is best.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Thank you very much. I think that’s all I need to know.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> Thanks for calling. Goodbye.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('84f37d59-597a-40b6-a0dd-71506140e06a', '43d77116-f432-4490-a102-40d76eedd863', 'radio', 'Questions 21–26', '', '<p data-start="84" data-end="110">Choose the correct answer.</p>
<p data-start="112" data-end="166"><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Feedback on second year of Performance Arts Course</span></strong></p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "has a very good reputation"}, {"option_text": "has links with various theatres."}, {"option_text": "has an international flavour"}], "question": "Gina chose to study performance arts at this university because the course"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "Movement Analysis"}, {"option_text": "Dance and Drama"}, {"option_text": "The Body in Dance"}], "question": "Which of the options they chose have Gina and Charlie both found useful?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "He worked in a costume department"}, {"option_text": "He performed with a ballet company."}, {"option_text": "He helped out at a dance school for children"}], "question": "What did Charlie do during his work experience?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "how to organise her time better"}, {"option_text": "how to work better in a team"}, {"option_text": "how to cope when under pressure"}], "question": "What does Gina say she learnt from her work experience?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "He wanted it to be different from those of other students"}, {"option_text": "He had already done an assignment in this area"}, {"option_text": "He was inspired to choose it by a performance he saw."}], "question": "What does Charlie say about his dissertation topic?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "finding enough to say"}, {"option_text": "doing the background reading"}, {"option_text": "presenting it in an appropriate way"}], "question": "Which aspect of writing a dissertation is Gina worried about?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SECTION 3: PERFORMANCE ARTS COURSE FEEDBACK</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Charlie:</strong> So Gina, we’ve got to give our tutor some feedback on how we feel about the course, now we’ve come to the end of our second year. Is it okay with you if we have a chat together before we go and see him?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gina:</strong> Sure, Charlie.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Charlie:</strong> So, did you choose this university to do Performance Arts because it’s got such a good reputation? That’s what hooked me in.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gina:</strong> Well, there are other good places which I also considered, but when I looked into things further,<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"104\">(21) I was impressed by the connections this course has with a whole range of theatres of different types [Answer: B]</strong></span>. So even though I was tempted to go and study abroad, I decided to come here in the end.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Charlie:</strong> And you don’t regret it?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gina:</strong> No, it’s been brilliant, especially the options this year. The Body and Dance option I did for this term has been particularly stimulating.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Charlie:</strong> Hmm, I’m sorry I didn’t go for that one too, but I did Dance and Drama which was brilliant too. I think <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"113\">(22) the most valuable option I’ve done was the Movement Analysis course we did in the first year [Answer: A]</strong>.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gina:</strong> Absolutely. It’s provided a great foundation for all our other work since then. So let’s talk about our work experience. Last summer you went to Finland, didn’t you?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Charlie:</strong> That’s right. I was at their National Ballet Theatre. I didn’t get the chance to go on stage, but <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"107\">(23) I helped out with sewing clothes for current productions and even with designing some for future shows [Answer: A – costume department]</strong></span>. It was brilliant. I got to know a lot of students studying at the local dance school, and I may get the chance to go back there next summer.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gina:</strong> Hmm, I’ve been offered more work at the place where I was working in Canada.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Charlie:</strong> Great! So, what do you think you gained most from the experience? I think I’ve got much better at controlling my stress levels.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gina:</strong> For me, it was probably<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"30\">(24) the fact that I learned a lot about collaborating with others rather than working independently [Answer: B – work better in a team]</strong>.</span> I was lucky to be able to do that in a situation that wasn’t too stressful. Also, I had to organize my time well, but I’ve always been reasonably good at that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Charlie:</strong> That’s good. So, we’ve got quite a few things ready to say to our tutor. It would be a good chance to ask him any questions we have too.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gina:</strong> Of course. I also think it could be helpful to discuss our future plans, for example, what we’re planning to do our dissertations on.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Charlie:</strong> Sure. I was unsure about whether to focus on globalisation in dance or on stage design. I did an essay on globalisation in my first year and really enjoyed it, but then <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"178\">(25) I saw a spectacular production at the Royal Opera House and that settled me on stage design [Answer: C]</strong></span>. I know another student who’s planning to work on that too, so we can discuss things together a bit.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gina:</strong> OK, that could be useful. I’m planning to do something on current trends in contemporary dance for my dissertation.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Charlie:</strong> That sounds pretty challenging. It’s a big topic. It might not be easy to organize in a coherent way.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gina:</strong> I’ve thought about it quite a lot and I think that’ll be OK, and I feel confident about how to write a longer piece of work. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"131\">(26) I’m in a bit of a panic though about how I’ll get through all the literature. There seems to be so much [Answer: B – background reading]</strong></span>. Hopefully, it won’t all be relevant.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">CAREER PLANS (Questions 27–30)</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Charlie:</strong> So have you made any career plans yet?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gina:</strong> I’m still undecided. I’ve thought about <strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"46\">performance</strong>, of course.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Charlie:</strong> Yes, I think lots of graduates from here take that route. But it’s a hard life involving lots of tough repetitive practice as well as actually appearing on stage.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gina:</strong> Yes, but <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"15\">(27) the performers I’ve met know that’s essential for the job and say they wouldn’t change what they do for the world [Answer: E]</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Charlie:</strong> I know lots of graduates go into <strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">education</strong>, teaching at various levels.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gina:</strong> But<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"10\">(28) that means doing some kind of post-grad certificate [Answer: C]</strong></span>, but I think it would be interesting, rewarding work.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Charlie:</strong> I was wondering about <strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"31\">theatre management</strong> as a possible option. That’s what our tutor did before he got into teaching, isn’t it?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gina:</strong> Yes, but he said he quickly realized it wasn’t for him. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"62\">(29) He wasn’t earning enough to live on [Answer: A]</strong></span>. I can imagine his communication skills are better than his business skills as well.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Charlie:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"9\">Marketing</strong>’s a possibility, of course.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Gina:</strong> Sure. I’ve read something saying it can be an interesting career, though <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"79\">(30) I don’t think many graduates go for this [Answer: F]</strong></span>, but that might mean there’s not so much competition as in many other fields of dance.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Charlie:</strong> Right, so now should we make a list…</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('4b4ad4c3-f032-4807-b431-33f4b2c7f15c', '43d77116-f432-4490-a102-40d76eedd863', 'matching', 'Questions 27–30', '', '<p>What do the students say about each of the following types of careers in performance arts?<br data-start="180" data-end="183">Choose <strong>FOUR</strong> correct answers, <strong>A</strong>–<strong>F</strong></p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p><strong>Types of careers</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Performance {People with experience feel very positive about it}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Education {An additional qualification is required}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Theatre management {The pay can be low}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Marketing {It is a relatively unpopular choice}</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "The pay can be low"}, {"optionText": "There is a lot of competition"}, {"optionText": "An additional qualification is required"}, {"optionText": "Good communication skills are required"}, {"optionText": "People with experience feel very positive about it"}, {"optionText": "It is a relatively unpopular choice"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e80efbfa-6968-4b16-818b-b834beeb8d55', 'b158a618-83fe-4d41-ada5-6dab14d91c2c', 'radio', 'Questions 1-8', '', '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE</strong> if the statement agrees with the information,<strong>FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information,<strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this</p>', 'true_false_not_given', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Ochre was used in paintings before it was used in fabric dyes."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Natural dyes that need a mordant are rare."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "In medieval times, people sometimes wore fabric made of undyed wool."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Silk has always been more expensive than cotton and wool."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Cotton imported from India was dyed upon arrival in Europe."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Perkin became more famous than his teacher, von Hofmann."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Very few synthetic dyes were produced in Europe in the second half of the 19th century."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "TRUE"}, {"option_text": "FALSE"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Today, the commercial production of natural dyes is limited to a small number of isolated communities."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. Ochre was used in paintings before it was used in fabric dyes. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 1):</strong> * <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"22\">“Scientists have been able to date the… pigments made from <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"83\">ochre, used in cave paintings, to over 15,000 BCE</strong>.”</em></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5,0,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,1,0,0\"><em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">“With the development of fixed settlements and agriculture, around <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">7,000 to 2,000 BCE</strong>, people began to produce <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"111\">fabrics and used natural substances such as ochre to color them</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Mốc 15,000 BCE (tranh hang động) diễn ra trước mốc 7,000 BCE (nhuộm vải). Do đó, Ochre được dùng làm tranh trước khi dùng làm thuốc nhuộm vải là chính xác.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. Natural dyes that need a mordant are rare. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 2):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">Most</strong> natural dyes are adjective dyes and <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"62\">require the application of a mordant solution</strong> to the fibers at some point in the dyeing process.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc dùng từ <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"28\">“Most”</strong> (phần lớn/hầu hết), trong khi câu hỏi dùng từ <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"81\">“rare”</strong> (hiếm). Hai thông tin này đối lập hoàn toàn nên đáp án là False.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. In medieval times, people sometimes wore fabric made of undyed wool. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“It [wool] was a common <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"44\">medieval</strong> fabric worn in <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"68\">both dyed and natural colors</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Natural colors” (màu tự nhiên của lông cừu) đồng nghĩa với việc vải không qua nhuộm (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"98\">undyed wool</strong>). Vì vậy, khẳng định người xưa đôi khi mặc vải len chưa nhuộm là đúng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. Silk has always been more expensive than cotton and wool. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> Đoạn này có nhắc Silk được nhập từ Trung Quốc và yêu cầu thuốc nhuộm chất lượng cao nhất; Cotton thì được coi là “luxury fabric” (vải xa xỉ) ở châu Âu.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nêu đặc điểm của từng loại vải chứ <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">không thực hiện phép so sánh giá cả</strong> (more expensive) giữa Silk với Cotton và Wool xuyên suốt lịch sử. Chúng ta không có căn cứ để xác nhận thông tin này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. Cotton imported from India was dyed upon arrival in Europe. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Cotton… was imported all the way from India and <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"71\">was dyed before it was shipped</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói cotton được nhuộm khi vừa đến châu Âu (upon arrival), nhưng dẫn chứng khẳng định nó được nhuộm ở Ấn Độ <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"127\">trước khi được vận chuyển đi</strong> (before shipped).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. Perkin became more famous than his teacher, von Hofmann. — {NOT GIVEN}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“W.H. Perkin, a student of celebrated European scientist Wilhelm von Hofmann, accidentally discovered the first synthetic dye…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ giới thiệu mối quan hệ thầy trò và thành tựu của Perkin (mở nhà máy, phát triển thuốc nhuộm tổng hợp), nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"133\">không hề so sánh ai nổi tiếng hơn ai</strong> (more famous than).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. Very few synthetic dyes were produced in Europe in the second half of the 19th century. — {FALSE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Synthetic dye production grew in Europe, and <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"66\">hardly a year passed until the end of the century without a new synthetic dye being patented</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cấu trúc “hardly a year passed without…” (hầu như không năm nào trôi qua mà không có…) ám chỉ sự bùng nổ, rất nhiều thuốc nhuộm mới ra đời. Điều này trái ngược với thông tin <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"190\">“very few”</strong> (rất ít).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. Today, the commercial production of natural dyes is limited to a small number of isolated communities. — {TRUE}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…now the use of natural dyes on a commercial scale <strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"74\">only exists in a few remote areas</strong> where people have… little access to synthetic dyes…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “A few remote areas” (một vài vùng xa xôi) đồng nghĩa với “a small number of isolated communities” (một số ít các cộng đồng biệt lập). Khẳng định này khớp với bài đọc.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('766b0122-0975-4415-8557-2923ed0eb170', 'cdf96d67-2b3c-47b1-aeb5-87712f37ef13', 'checkbox', 'Questions 38-40', '', '<p>Choose <strong>THREE </strong>correct answers.</p>
<p>According to the writer, which <strong>THREE </strong>of the following areas have not been studied enough in order to understand the origin of language?</p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": true, "option_text": "Evidence from prehistoric times"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "Intelligence"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "Individual sounds"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "Music"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "Emotions"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "Human intellect"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "Children’s language"}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"1\">Câu 38: Evidence from prehistoric times</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 2, dòng 1-3.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The first is an <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"28\">insufficient concern with the archaeological and fossil proof</strong> of the brains and behaviour of our human ancestors.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả chỉ ra rằng các nhà nghiên cứu chưa chú trọng đúng mức đến các bằng chứng khảo cổ và hóa thạch từ thời tiền sử (prehistoric times) của tổ tiên loài người.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\">Câu 39: Music</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 3, dòng 1-3.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…<strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"15\">insufficient concern</strong> with the other major aural and vocal communication system of modern humans: <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"112\">music</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đây là lý do thứ hai khiến tiến độ nghiên cứu bị hạn chế. Tác giả cho rằng âm nhạc thường bị ngó lơ hoặc bị tách rời khỏi các cuộc thảo luận về ngôn ngữ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">Câu 40: Emotions</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn 6, dòng 1-3.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…a third reason for our lack of progress… an <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"61\">insufficient concern with emotion</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả khẳng định đời sống cảm xúc của tổ tiên đã bị “bỏ rơi” (neglected) trong khi các nhà khoa học lại quá tập trung vào khả năng trí tuệ, điều này làm cản trở việc hiểu về nguồn gốc ngôn ngữ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('c1a58c1c-60dd-429e-8f29-9c7f7eeafd0c', '1c4126b5-d544-47fa-a01e-a2cef4b46daa', 'fillup', 'Questions 24-26', '<p>Complete the sentences below.<br />Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>Corals have a number of {tentacles} which they use to collect their food.<br />Algae gain {protection} from being inside the coral.<br />Increases in the warmth of the sea water can remove the {colour} from coral.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', NULL, NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p>24. tentacles<br />(Đoạn 2: “Corals are composed of tiny animals… with tentacles for capturing small marine creatures.”)<br />→ San hô có tentacles (xúc tu) để bắt thức ăn. → tentacles.</p>\n<p> <br />25. protection<br />(Đoạn 2: “The algae… get protection, while their photosynthesising provides nutrients…”)<br />→ Tảo sống bên trong san hô và được bảo vệ (protection). → protection.</p>\n<p> <br />26. colour<br />(Đoạn 4: “Rising ocean temperatures are triggering bleaching events that strip reefs of their colour.”)<br />→ Nhiệt độ tăng làm san hô mất màu sắc (colour). → colour</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 3);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('3a919a01-b440-48e6-9c0e-b9bf005b5e5e', '340078e0-049a-4d1b-ae24-056c31c79632', 'radio', 'Questions 7–13', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple-choice', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": " TRUE "}, {"content": " FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "A group of professional researchers are in charge of the Brooklyn project."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": " TRUE "}, {"content": " FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Brooklyn project team carries out their assessment of stores without the owner’s knowledge."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": " TRUE "}, {"content": " FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Brooklyn project has experienced technical difficulties setting up the website."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": " TRUE "}, {"content": " FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The city government has taken a considerable interest in the Brooklyn project website."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": " TRUE "}, {"content": " FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Michele Ver Ploeg believes the Brooklyn project website should contain additional information."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": " TRUE "}, {"content": " FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The rate of internet use in Brooklyn is unlikely to increase in the near future."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": " TRUE "}, {"content": " FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Jeffrey Heehs would like more people to assist with the Brooklyn project research."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>7. A group of professional researchers are in charge of the Brooklyn project.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The Brooklyn project differs in that it’s run by a local core of five <strong>volunteers</strong> who have worked on the project for the past year, rather than trained, academic <strong>researchers</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Dự án do một nhóm tình nguyện viên địa phương thực hiện, chứ không phải các nhà nghiên cứu chuyên nghiệp được đào tạo.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>8. The Brooklyn project team carries out its assessment of stores without the owner’s knowledge.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"23\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…simply go to individual stores with pre-printed surveys in hand, and once the <strong>storekeeper’s permission has been obtained</strong>, check off boxes on their list…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Họ phải xin phép chủ cửa hàng trước khi đánh giá.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>9. The Brooklyn project has experienced technical difficulties setting up the website.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"25\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> Văn bản mô tả công nghệ được sử dụng (mapping software, GPS-related smart phones, Google Maps, Open Street Map), nhưng không đề cập đến việc họ gặp khó khăn kỹ thuật (technical difficulties) khi thiết lập trang web.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>10. The city government has taken a considerable interest in the Brooklyn project website.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"27\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Their website <strong>hasn’t caught them much local or official attention yet</strong>, however.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Trang web chưa thu hút được nhiều sự chú ý từ chính quyền thành phố (official attention).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>11. Michele Ver Ploeg believes the Brooklyn project website should contain additional information.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “To make the map more helpful to both residents and policy makers, she would like to see <strong>price data for healthy products, too</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Michele Ver Ploeg muốn trang web có thêm dữ liệu về giá (additional information).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>12. The rate of internet use in Brooklyn is unlikely to increase in the near future.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> Văn bản chỉ nêu ra số liệu hiện tại: một phần đáng kể cư dân Brooklyn không có internet và 8% dùng dial-up. <strong>Không có thông tin</strong> về xu hướng tăng hay giảm sử dụng internet trong tương lai gần.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>13. Jeffrey Heehs would like more people to assist with the Brooklyn project research.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"33\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “He also hopes warmer days in the spring will draw out <strong>fresh volunteers to spread awareness and to finish surveying</strong>, as they have about two-thirds of Brooklyn left to cover.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Jeffrey Heehs (người lãnh đạo dự án) hy vọng có thêm tình nguyện viên mới để hoàn thành khảo sát (assist with the research).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5f576891-aed8-4fb4-bf3c-a743a89a1222', '9de8c968-7092-49be-bf3b-c9a23bb1bdbd', 'fillup', 'Questions 5–7', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal; background: white; vertical-align: baseline;"><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif; mso-fareast-font-family: ''Times New Roman''; color: #15191e; mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;">Complete the flow-chart below.</span></p>
