</tbody>
</table>
', NULL, 'fill-in-the-blank', NULL, NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p>5. Phase 1: Larval stage takes place in the <strong>open ocean</strong>.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>open ocean</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) “Most coral reef fish have a life cycle consisting of an <strong>open ocean larval phase</strong>…”</li>\n</ul>\n<p>6. Phase 2: Juvenile stage takes place close to the <strong>reef</strong>.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>reef</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) “…followed by a juvenile to adult phase <strong>near the reef</strong>.”</li>\n</ul>\n<p>7. <strong>Mortality</strong> rates are high in the early part of this stage.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>mortality</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) “This point is commonly known as ‘settlement’. Not surprisingly, it is also characterised by increased levels of <strong>mortality</strong> in the first 48 hours following settlement…”</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f119436c-92e8-4c46-a5ba-f82e721cc014', 'cdea869a-8e41-445e-90c0-5c57c37aa47b', 'fillup', 'Questions 17–20', '<p data-start="109" data-end="177">Complete the table below.</p>
