INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('4f9e164c-c542-482f-85eb-6142331d3e09', '2bf85cb9-d6e3-4f91-b1d5-eda8252081cf', 'checkbox', 'Questions 21 and 22', '', '<p>Choose <strong>TWO</strong> letters, A-E.</p>
<p>Which are the <strong>TWO </strong>main duties for Personal Support Workers (PSWs)?</p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": false, "option_text": "talking with clients"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "helping clients to eat and drink"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "helping with physical needs"}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "ensuring clients are well and safe"}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "managing clients'' pills"}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 3: PERSONAL SUPPORT WORKER PROGRAM</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> Becky, hi! What are you doing here at the college?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Becky:</strong> Hi Jason. Just using the library. What about you?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> I''m taking the PSW program—you know, Personal Support Worker.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Becky:</strong> You''re kidding! I''ve just qualified as a PSW.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> Really? I''d love to talk to you about the program.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Becky:</strong> Okay. Well, first off, the main duties they taught me here were exactly what I needed on the job.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> You mean like bathing and dressing people?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Becky:</strong> Yes, young and old need this. You''ll work with people of all ages, from young people with disabilities to seniors. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"122\">(Q21/22 - C: helping with physical needs)</strong></span>. But you know, nothing really prepares you for how alone many people are. They crave conversation and I don''t mind chatting with them while I work, though that''s not officially in my job description.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> I think I''d like to focus on seniors care. And with the country''s older population growing, maybe I''ll get a job fast. Do we have to be responsible for any medication?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Becky:</strong> No, that''s not for us to do. And while you will prepare meals, you won''t feed people. But working to keep clients healthy and able to live on their own, without risk as long as possible, is always the goal.And we''re recognizing that with life spans increasing, long-term care facilities won''t be able to keep up with the number of people who will need care. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"214\">(Q21/22 - D: ensuring clients are well and safe)</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> I almost didn''t meet the requirements for entry into the PSW program. I was one course short getting my <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"111\">(Q23/24 - A: high school completion)</strong></span> diploma, so I had to go back to summer school. I took science because I''m no good at math.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong>Jason:</strong>Oh, and speaking of not getting in, having my <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">(Q23/24 - E: First Aid training)</strong></span> certificate was a real piece of luck. I would have been turned down without that too.</p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_94e6262a860d0b2b-164\" data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong>Becky:</strong>Hmm, <span class=\"citation-2112 citation-end-2112\">and I would have had a problem with immunizations except that I traveled the year before and when the doctor checked my records, they were up to date. I also had to hand in a written essay on why I wanted to be <sup class=\"superscript\" data-turn-source-index=\"1\"><!----></sup></span>a PSW.</p>\n<div class=\"source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted\"><!----><!----></div>\n<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>\n<p> </p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">COURSE TOPICS (Questions 25–30)</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> So Becky, what did you think about the courses you had to take in the Personal Support Worker program?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Becky:</strong> Well, I used to think I got my points across pretty well until I took the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"81\">Understanding is Essential</strong></span> course. For starters, it taught me how to express myself much more effectively. I also learned a lot about preparing clear reports for my supervisors and dealing in a better way with people in general—you know, like giving facts without personal views. You''ll find that you need those skills every single day. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"259\">(Q25 - D: workplace communication)</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> I''m enjoying the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">Foundations</strong> </span>course. I''m taking it now and I''m getting a lot out of it. Because support workers are a newer level of care in the province, I think we absolutely have to understand <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"115\">(Q26 - C: PSWs’ role in health care)</strong></span> how we fit into the overall system. It''s a great place to voice your opinions freely, some are quite personal. Did you have to take a course called <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"44\">The Way We Work</strong></span>? I didn''t know psychology was part of the program.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Becky:</strong> Hmm, that course was a favorite of mine, but it''s probably not what you''re thinking, Jason. It''s about what happens on the inside of the body and covers <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"160\">(Q27 - G: biological systems)</strong></span> the functions that keep our bodies operating well.Even if you''re not a PSW, the course is really interesting. I learned so much.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> What do you think about <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"31\">Residence Care</strong></span>?I know the thinking now is that long-term care facilities aren''t the answer for our aging population.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Becky:</strong> Hmm, right. And so this course zeros in on the changes people can make to their homes so they can stay there <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"97\">(Q28 - A: independent living)</strong></span>, like installing higher toilets, for example. You''ll also learn about specialized equipment people can get to help themselves: safety bars for the shower and so on.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> Do any of the courses focus on the families of our clients?After all, any kind of illness or disability affects everybody.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Becky:</strong> So true. And yes, there is one called <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"32\">Dynamics</strong></span>. You usually get that in your last term.You''ll learn different strategies to help relieve some of the anxiety and <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"116\">(Q29 - F: handling stress)</strong></span> strain that happens within the family.I got a lot out of that course. It''s the only one that focuses on emotions rather than facts, I think. Giving people this kind of help is just as valuable as any kind of expensive equipment they buy to help themselves.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jason:</strong> The course I''m really looking forward to is <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"51\">The Power Within</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Becky:</strong> Oh, it''s terrific! Getting old has quite an impact on the mind, as you know, but you''ll be taught ways to help clients keep the mind active so they''re not so forgetful <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"113\">(Q30 - E: memory stimulation activities)</strong></span>. You''d be surprised how much improvement you can see in clients when you apply these methods. </p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('18e58a89-d695-4ff8-a5ae-f2f46a2c588c', '6a8b3e3d-6c8f-41b3-8773-8ea314c27346', 'fillup', 'Questions 31-40', '<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY </strong>for each answer.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong>Food Safety Standards</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>Risk assessment</strong></p>
<p>Scientists have to consider potential problems with:</p>
<ul>
<li>the products {ingredients} (could they attract harmful bacteria?)</li>
<li>method of preparation (will it eliminate harmful micro-organisms?)</li>
<li>how products are {stored} and distributed</li>
<li>supermarkets (e.g. changes in {temperature} affecting the condition of frozen food)</li>
<li>end-users (how is food usually handled in the home?)</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Factors affecting food consumption</strong></p>
<p><strong>Legislation</strong></p>
<p>Consumer attitudes</p>
<ul>
<li>e.g. dislike of additives → growth of the {organic} food market in Australia</li>
</ul>
<div class="s-block-item s-repeatable-item s-block-sortable-item s-blog-post-section blog-section">
<div class="container">
<div class="sixteen columns">
<div class="s-blog-section-inner">
<div class="s-component s-text ">
<div class="">
<div class="s-component-content s-font-body">
<p><strong>The food industry</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>supermarkets may use price or {image} as their selling strategy (but the main concern is profitability)</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>The mass media</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>now the main source of {information} for many</li>
<li>negative effect because not objective:
<ul>
<li>concern for {sales}</li>
<li>news is now a form of {entertainment}, which can mislead the public</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Personal opinion</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>few programmes deal with food safety or {nutrition}</li>
<li>Importance of education: as with benefits of exercise, many children can influence their {parents}</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="s-block-item s-repeatable-item s-block-sortable-item s-blog-post-section blog-section">
<div class="container">
<div class="sixteen columns"> </div>
</div>
</div>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 4: FOOD SAFETY STANDARDS</strong></h3>\n<p id=\"p-rc_a8cb76ec0e49ec8f-161\" data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lecturer:</strong> <span class=\"citation-3391 citation-3392 citation-3393 citation-3394 citation-3395 citation-end-3395\">Good morning everyone. In today’s lecture, I’m going to talk about food safety and the factors involved in setting standards for the food industry, with particular reference to the situation here in Australia</span><span class=\"citation-3391 citation-3392 citation-3393 citation-3394 citation-end-3394\">.</span></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_a8cb76ec0e49ec8f-162\" data-path-to-node=\"4\"><span class=\"citation-3387 citation-3388 citation-3389 citation-3390 citation-end-3390\">Now, before anyone can decid</span><span class=\"citation-3387 citation-3388 citation-3389 citation-end-3389\">e what kind of standards need to be s</span><span class=\"citation-3387 citation-3388 citation-end-3388\">et for ensuring that any specific food product is safe, scientists have to carry out a risk assessment. And in doing this, they have to consider several potential problems.</span></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_a8cb76ec0e49ec8f-163\" data-path-to-node=\"5\"><span class=\"citation-3385 citation-3386 citation-end-3386\">Firstl</span><span class=\"citation-3385 citation-end-3385\">y, they have to consider t</span>he <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"35\">(31) <span class=\"citation-3383 citation-3384\">ingredients</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-3383 citation-3384 citation-end-3384\"> of the product. They have to decide whether any of these might make the finished product more susceptible to harmful bacteria. Then they have to consider the process used in the preparation of the food, and whether or not it includes a step designed to eliminate unwanted microor</span><span class=\"citation-3383 citation-end-3383\">ganisms.</span></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_a8cb76ec0e49ec8f-164\" data-path-to-node=\"6\"><span class=\"citation-3382 citation-end-3382\">After that, they’ve got to consider the way products are</span> <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"57\">(32) <span class=\"citation-3380 citation-3381\">stored</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-3380 citation-3381 citation-end-3381\">, for instance in warehouses or cold stores, and distributed to retailers. And it doesn’t end there—the analysts even have to be aware of problems that might occur after the food has reached the supermarket, thi</span><span class=\"citation-3380\">ngs like frozen foods being defrosted and then refrozen because the </span><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"347\"><span class=\"citation-3380 citation-end-3380\">(</span>33) <span class=\"citation-3379\">temperature</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-3379 citation-end-3379\"> fluctuated, or foods being kept past their expiry date.</span></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_a8cb76ec0e49ec8f-165\" data-path-to-node=\"7\"><span class=\"citation-3378 citation-end-3378\">And finally, any assessment of the overall risk has to take into account the way the end users—consumers—normally handle food at home. So as you see, the risk assessment is quite complica</span>ted.</p>\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">FACTORS AFFECTING FOOD CONSUMPTION</strong></h3>\n<p id=\"p-rc_a8cb76ec0e49ec8f-166\" data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lecturer:</strong> <span class=\"citation-3377 citation-end-3377\">Now, there are several factors affecting what kind of food we eat. Only one of which is legislation. Another is the attitudes of consumers. A good example of this is the dislike that many Australians have for additives in their food, even when these additives are considered safe and without them products have a shorter shelf life or a substandard appearance</span>. This has led to the phenomenal expansion of the market for <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"350\">(34) organic</strong></span> food in Australia.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\">Another important influence on what we eat is the food industry itself. In some large supermarkets, low prices are the main strategy for attracting customers, while for more upscale marketers, <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"193\">(35) image</strong></span> is more important. But we should bear in mind for all of them, the key consideration is profitability.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\">Finally, there is the influence of the mass media, which is the most important source of <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">(36) information</strong></span> for most people. Unfortunately, this has a rather negative effect because, in general, they are not very objective. For one thing, the prime motivation of the media, as with the food industry, is <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"302\">(37) sales</strong></span>, and this has a major influence on the way in which the topic is dealt with.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\">A further problem is that news is regarded as a type of <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"56\">(38) entertainment</strong>.</span> Often the issues that get top billing are those that are sensational or controversial, so it’s not at all surprising if the public ends up with a rather distorted understanding of food and food safety.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PERSONAL OPINION AND EDUCATION</strong></h3>\n<p id=\"p-rc_a8cb76ec0e49ec8f-167\" data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lecturer:</strong> On top of that, up till now, food safety and <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"55\">(39) nutrition</strong></span> have never been considered a really int<span class=\"citation-3376 citation-end-3376\">eresting topic for the public. Very few TV or radio shows address the issues, and even those shows that are devoted to cooking or eating generally ignore them.</span></p>\n<p id=\"p-rc_a8cb76ec0e49ec8f-168\" data-path-to-node=\"17\"><span class=\"citation-3375 citation-end-3375\">At this point, I’ll just offer a personal opinion on this subject. I firmly believe in food safety education starting </span>at primary schools. We know that many children who have been taught about the benefits of exercise come home and lecture their <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"245\">(40) parents</strong> </span>about it. So the same could be done for food and food preparation.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\">And at the same time, the countless educational television shows…</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('dcbe7a14-38af-47a2-a887-c09519fd3381', '38912980-df05-46a3-9f2f-a9359e27a438', 'radio', 'Questions 40', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "explain the meaning of the manuscript."}, {"content": "determine the true identity of the manuscript''s author."}, {"content": "describe the numerous attempts to decode the manuscript."}, {"content": "identify which research into the manuscript has had the most media coverage."}], "question": "The writer''s main aim in this passage is to"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>40. The writer’s main aim in this passage is to</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"36\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>describe the numerous attempts to decode the manuscript.</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Toàn bộ bài đọc liệt kê các nỗ lực giải mã qua nhiều thời kỳ và bởi nhiều chuyên gia khác nhau (Newbold, Friedman, Landini, Rugg), chứng minh bản thảo vẫn là một bí ẩn chưa có lời giải.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 3);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('be5d8ec8-3299-40fd-bc5c-4e906d6920dd', 'bd1ff2eb-dfa8-4ab1-992f-304152e7adb8', 'radio', 'Questions 21–24', '', '<p>Choose the correct answers</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "They are easy to copy."}, {"option_text": "They are complex."}, {"option_text": "They are childish."}], "question": "What does Josh think about Jackson Pollock''s paintings?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "it lacked documentation."}, {"option_text": "it was too cheap."}, {"option_text": "it featured the wrong colours."}], "question": "The $5 painting was considered to be a fake because"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "what was on the back of the painting"}, {"option_text": "the type of paint used"}, {"option_text": "how the paint was applied"}], "question": "What made the International Foundation for Art Research reject the $5 painting?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "Only an experienced critic can evaluate a painting''s authenticity."}, {"option_text": "Modern scientific methods have replaced the traditional approach."}, {"option_text": "Experts from the science and art worlds should work together."}], "question": "What do Josh and Emily agree about art evaluation?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"1\">Part 3</h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Josh:</strong> Hi Emily!</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Emily:</strong> Hi Josh! Are you ready to work on the assignment?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Josh:</strong> Yeah. Now, we need to describe how modern scientific techniques are being used in the field of art history.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Emily:</strong> Right. And Doctor Abbott suggested that we choose some famous cases to illustrate the argument.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Josh:</strong> Okay, so what have you found?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Emily:</strong> Well, there’s a Canadian forensic scientist called Biro.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Josh:</strong> Yes, I think I’ve heard of him. What do you know about him?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Emily:</strong> Well, I’m a big fan of Jackson Pollock, the modern American artist.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Josh:</strong> Hmm… didn’t he paint those really huge abstract paintings?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Emily:</strong> That’s him. I guess it would be pretty easy to fake one of those paintings.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Josh:</strong> No way, Emily! I know a lot of people think that even a child could paint one. To the untrained eye they might look simple, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\">but <strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"134\">(21) they’re incredibly intricate works of art [Answer: B – complex]</strong>.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Emily:</strong> Well sorry, but I really can’t agree with you. Anyway, what did Biro find out?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Josh:</strong> Well, Biro worked on a case where a client asked him to prove that a painting she bought for only $5 was an authentic Jackson Pollock.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Emily:</strong> So was it a fake?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Josh:</strong> Well, Biro found evidence to show it was a genuine Pollock, but the art world didn’t accept his findings.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Emily:</strong> Why?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Josh:</strong> Well, one critic said that compared to other Pollocks, the white and yellow lines on the painting were too straight.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Emily:</strong> Come on Josh, that doesn’t seem that convincing.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Josh:</strong> No, you’re right, it is a bit weak. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\">But <strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"46\">(22) the strongest argument was that there were no records of previous owners. For the painting to be authentic, you really should be able to trace the painting all the way back to the artist’s studio [Answer: A – lacked documentation]</strong>.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Josh:</strong> Well, that’s true, I suppose. Did they consult with anyone else?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Emily:</strong> Hmm… The International Foundation for Art Research got involved.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Josh:</strong> And what was their verdict?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Emily:</strong> Well, they saw a definite similarity in the painting techniques used.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Josh:</strong> You mean the way Pollock dripped the oils on the canvas?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Emily:</strong> Yeah. And they noted the dirt and paint marks on the back, which all of Pollock’s paintings have.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Josh:</strong> Why is that?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Emily:</strong> He used to lie his canvases down on the ground when he painted them.<span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\"> But <strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"80\">(23) the foundation were worried about the acrylic paint that was used on the painting. It’s quite common now, but it was very unusual back in Pollock’s day, so it was probably painted much later [Answer: B – type of paint used]</strong>.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Josh:</strong> Right. So, whose side are we on in this argument?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Emily:</strong> When it comes to art, you can see the art critic’s point. If their knowledge and expertise tells them that it definitely isn’t a Pollock painting, shouldn’t we believe them? I mean, that is usually how it works in the art world, isn’t it?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Josh:</strong> Art historians have always judged paintings, but things are changing now. If we have modern scientific techniques like fingerprint analysis, why not use them?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Emily:</strong> Hmm… That’s true. Well, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"33\">(24) maybe we need a combination. I think you’re right [Answer: C – experts from the science and art worlds should work together]</strong>.</span></p>\n<hr>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Emily:</strong> So did you find out anything else Josh?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"36\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"36\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Josh:</strong> Well, have you ever heard of a painting called <em data-path-to-node=\"36\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">The Battle of Anghiari</em>?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"37\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Emily:</strong> I have actually. It’s the lost masterpiece by Leonardo da Vinci, the famous Italian artist.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"38\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"38\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Josh:</strong> What about it?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"39\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"39\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Emily:</strong> Well, an Italian art analyst called Seracini thinks he knows where it is and he’s using scientific techniques to help locate it.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"40\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"40\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Josh:</strong> How?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"41\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"41\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Emily:</strong> Well, art historians knew where the painting was last seen.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"42\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"42\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Josh:</strong> That’s right, in the Hall of the 500 in Florence.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"43\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"43\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Emily:</strong> Right. So, Seracini had a theory that the painting was still there and he set out to prove it. He used a lot of different technology like radar and thermographic cameras. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\">But initially <strong data-path-to-node=\"43\" data-index-in-node=\"192\">(25) he scanned every inch of the hall with a laser in order to make a really accurate 3D model of the building’s design [Answer: D – a laser scanner]</strong>.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"44\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"44\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Josh:</strong> Did he think the painting was hidden in the building somewhere?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"45\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"45\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Emily:</strong> Exactly. Then to find out what the hall looked like in Leonardo’s time,<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"45\" data-index-in-node=\"79\">(26) he took pictures of it with a thermographic camera [Answer: G – a thermographic camera]</strong>.</span></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"46\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"46\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Josh:</strong> Couldn’t he have used ultrasound to do that?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"47\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"47\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Emily:</strong> Not really. Different types of building materials produce different amounts of radiat<span class=\"citation-1739 citation-end-1739\">ion and you can really see those differences in a thermal image.</span> <span class=\"citation-1738 citation-end-1738\">So brick would look different from wood or glass, for example.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"48\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"48\" data-index-in-node=\"0\"><span class=\"citation-1737\">Josh:</span></strong><span class=\"citation-1737 citation-end-1737\"> Yes. Seracini worked out what the building looked like when it was first</span> built and what renovations took place after that. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\">He found that <strong data-path-to-node=\"48\" data-index-in-node=\"143\">(27) two large glass windows on the east wall had been removed and filled in [Answer: F – glass]</strong>,</span> by the time da Vinci started work on his painting leaving a space big enough for it.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"49\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"49\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Emily:</strong> But why hasn’t the painting been seen for 400 years?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"50\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"50\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Josh:</strong> Hmm… To answer that question, Seracini needed to study that wall even more closely.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"51\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"51\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Emily:</strong> Did he use the thermographic camera again?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"52\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"52\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Josh:</strong> No. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"52\" data-index-in-node=\"10\">(28) This time he used another kind of technology: radar. And what did that show? It showed there were, in fact, two walls there [Answer: E – a radar machine]</strong></span>, an older one and a newer one built in front of it.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"53\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"53\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Emily:</strong> So does Seracini believe that da Vinci’s painting is on the concealed wall?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"54\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"54\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Josh:</strong> Yes, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"54\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">(29) on a stone wall concealed by the newer brick wall [Answer: C – stone]</strong>.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"55\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"55\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Emily:</strong> So what’s the next stage in the investigation?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"56\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"56\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Josh:</strong> Well, he isn’t allowed to remove any plaster or bricks, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\">so <strong data-path-to-node=\"56\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">(30) he’s now experimenting with a gamma-ray camera to try and verify his theory [Answer: B – gamma-ray technology]</strong>.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"57\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"57\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Emily:</strong> Well, I think we’ve got some really strong examples there of how science can help art. Let’s see if we can type up an outline.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ca6e36de-7c11-4b37-9d83-856dddd714a7', 'bd1ff2eb-dfa8-4ab1-992f-304152e7adb8', 'matching', 'Questions 25 – 30', '', '<p>Complete the flow-chart below.</p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p data-start=\"1229\" data-end=\"1293\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong data-start=\"1229\" data-end=\"1293\">Seracini''s search for Leonardo Da Vinci''s Battle of Anghiari</strong></span></p>\n<p data-start=\"1229\" data-end=\"1293\"> </p>\n<p>• Seracini used {D. a laser scanner} to help make a model of the building.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>• Seracini used {G. a thermographic camera} to reveal different materials in the walls. He found the original architecture.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>• Seracini guessed that Da Vinci painted his masterpiece on the east wall, in a space that used to hold {F. glass}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>• Seracini analysed the wall using {E. a radar machine} and discovered a second wall behind it.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>• Seracini hypothesised that the Da Vinci painting is still there on the original {C. stone} wall.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>• Seracini is using {B. gamma-ray technology} to prove his theory.</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A. ultrasound"}, {"optionText": "B. gamma-ray technology"}, {"optionText": "C. stone"}, {"optionText": "D. a laser scanner"}, {"optionText": "E. a radar machine"}, {"optionText": "F. glass"}, {"optionText": "G. a thermographic camera"}, {"optionText": "H. brick"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1</p>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('c327d86c-e29e-4c9e-ba9a-97d409d469a1', '132887aa-f8a8-484b-bb10-c5f7f43b6af9', 'matching', 'Questions 14-19', '', '<p>Write the correct number, <strong>i-vii</strong>, in boxes 14-19 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'matching_paragraph_information', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": "", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i New terminology reflecting changing attitudes to waste disposal"}, {"optionText": "ii Fundamental changes in behaviour in the past and future"}, {"optionText": "iii Ways of rewarding the public for recycling"}, {"optionText": "iv A surprising approach to waste disposal by several countries"}, {"optionText": "v Difficult choices for individuals and businesses"}, {"optionText": "vi Arguments against incineration from a country that uses it"}, {"optionText": "vii A number of justifications for the use of incineration"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. Paragraph A — {iv. A surprising approach to waste disposal by several countries}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Norway, however, appears to be <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"43\">burning its way through a sizable chunk of Europe’s municipal waste</strong>, using the heat… to warm and power homes… Germany, Sweden, Belgium and the Netherlands all burn significant quantities…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Surprising approach” chính là việc các quốc gia này (Na Uy, Đức, Thụy Điển…) không chỉ đốt rác của mình mà còn nhập khẩu rác từ nước khác để biến thành năng lượng sưởi ấm. Đây là cách tiếp cận khá lạ lẫm so với quan niệm cũ rằng đốt rác là “lười biếng” hay độc hại.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. Paragraph B — {vii. A number of justifications for the use of incineration}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Those who support burning waste say that a <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"55\">new generation of incinerators has made it a more attractive option</strong>. Filters and scrubbing mechanisms now capture harmful substances… Above all… incineration is the <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"224\">only way of preventing the long-term impacts of landfill</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Justifications” (sự lý giải/bào chữa) nằm ở việc liệt kê các ưu điểm: công nghệ lọc khí thải hiện đại (filters/scrubbing), sự tiến hóa trong kỹ thuật đốt và là giải pháp cấp bách để thay thế bãi chôn lấp đang quá tải.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. Paragraph C — {vi. Arguments against incineration from a country that uses it}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“Lars Haltbrekken, chairman of Friends of the Earth in <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"66\">Norway [a country that uses it]</strong>, is concerned that incineration plants appear to generate demand… ‘But in a broader perspective, it’s a <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"204\">lazy way</strong> of getting rid of waste; you <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"242\">don’t stimulate the goals of reducing, reusing and recycling</strong>.’”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Lars Haltbrekken (đại diện từ Na Uy – quốc gia đang đốt rác mạnh mẽ nhất) lại đưa ra các luận điểm phản đối (arguments against): việc xây quá nhiều nhà máy đốt rác khiến họ lười tái chế và làm giảm động lực thực hiện các mục tiêu bảo vệ môi trường bền vững.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. Paragraph D — {i. New terminology reflecting changing attitudes to waste disposal}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“We used to call this the <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"37\">‘cradle to grave’</strong> life cycle; now, the talk is of <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"87\">‘cradle to cradle’</strong> and an even more comprehensive concept known as <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"154\">‘zero waste’</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “New terminology” chính là các thuật ngữ mới như “Cradle to Cradle” (Từ nôi đến nôi) hay “Zero waste” (Không rác thải), phản ánh sự thay đổi trong tư duy: sản phẩm phải được thiết kế để tái sinh thay vì bị vứt bỏ sau khi sử dụng (Cradle to Grave).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. Paragraph E — {v. Difficult choices for individuals and businesses}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“…it’s not always clear-cut… Supermarkets keep their shelves stocked even when demand isn’t there… <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"116\">that cost is less to them than the cost in brand damage of having empty shelves</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Difficult choices” ở đây là bài toán kinh tế khó khăn: Siêu thị (businesses) phải chọn giữa việc bỏ phí thức ăn (waste) hay để kệ hàng trống gây ảnh hưởng thương hiệu. Người tiêu dùng (individuals) cũng đối mặt với việc lãng phí thực phẩm trị giá hàng tỷ bảng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. Paragraph F — {ii. Fundamental changes in behaviour in the past and future}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">“If someone back in the <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"35\">1980s [the past]</strong> had suggested what waste would be like now, they would be completely wrong… Consumerism has developed at a pace we never expected… Perhaps we can align the environmental message to these <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"243\">deep-seated values [the future]</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này nhìn lại quá khứ (thập niên 80) để thấy rác thải điện tử và thói quen tiêu dùng đã thay đổi thế nào, đồng thời gợi mở về tương lai: cần thay đổi hành vi dựa trên các giá trị cốt lõi và vai trò dẫn dắt của chính phủ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('0b56d454-9a1b-4847-9f8a-529ad24a3a6f', '132887aa-f8a8-484b-bb10-c5f7f43b6af9', 'matching', 'Questions 20-23', '', '<p>Write the correct letter, <strong>A-G</strong>, in boxes 20-23 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'matching_sentence_endings', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": "", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "Incineration does not encourage responsible attitudes to waste disposal."}, {"optionText": "Recycling can sometimes create serious problems for the future."}, {"optionText": "Greater consumerism leads to higher levels of waste."}, {"optionText": "Proper systems are needed for the recycling of environmentally-friendly products."}, {"optionText": "Landfill is better for the environment than incineration."}, {"optionText": "Incineration of waste is now relatively harmless to the environment."}, {"optionText": "Efforts to reduce waste may affect profits for some types of companies."}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "Ted Michaels", "correctAnswer": "F"}, {"questionPart": "Joergen Fenhann", "correctAnswer": "C"}, {"questionPart": "Joan Marc Simon", "correctAnswer": "D"}, {"questionPart": "Tim Burns", "correctAnswer": "G"}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. Ted Michaels — {F. Incineration of waste is now relatively harmless to the environment.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn B):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">According to <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"33\">Ted Michaels</strong>, president of the US-based Energy Recovery Centre, ‘There has been constant evolution in combustion engineering… and the <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"169\">output from these facilities is now minuscule</strong>.’</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm “output… is now minuscule” (lượng chất thải ra giờ đây là cực nhỏ/không đáng kể) tương ứng với việc việc đốt rác giờ đây tương đối vô hại (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"157\">relatively harmless</strong>) đối với môi trường nhờ công nghệ hiện đại.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. Joergen Fenhann — {C. Greater consumerism leads to higher levels of waste.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn C):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">‘It’s a problem for the developed nations,’ says <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"69\">Joergen Fenhann</strong>… ‘<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">The more you develop, the more you produce, buy and throw away</strong>.’</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu nói “Càng phát triển, bạn càng sản xuất, mua sắm và vứt bỏ nhiều hơn” chính là sự khẳng định rằng chủ nghĩa tiêu dùng tăng cao (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"144\">greater consumerism</strong>) dẫn đến mức độ rác thải lớn hơn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"198\">higher levels of waste</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. Joan Marc Simon — {D. Proper systems are needed for the recycling of environmentally-friendly products.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn D):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">As <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"23\">Simon</strong> points out, however, without the <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"62\">right mechanisms</strong> in place ‘<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">nothing guarantees that this bottle will end up being properly collected and treated</strong> in the appropriate recycling facility’.</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Right mechanisms” tương ứng với “proper systems”. Simon lập luận rằng dù sản phẩm có thân thiện với môi trường đến đâu (như cái chai được thiết kế tốt), nếu không có hệ thống phù hợp để thu gom và xử lý thì cũng vô ích.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">23. Tim Burns — {G. Efforts to reduce waste may affect profits for some types of companies.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn E):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">Tim Burns</strong>… says… ‘You can argue about… not buying it in the first place — if you do that, then <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"121\">that’s money the retailers don’t get</strong>, so it’s not always clear-cut.’</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Retailers don’t get money” chính là việc ảnh hưởng đến lợi nhuận của các công ty bán lẻ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"102\">affect profits</strong>). Tim Burns chỉ ra rằng việc giảm tiêu thụ/giảm rác thải sẽ khiến các nhà bán lẻ thất thu.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('b61f864b-9dda-4768-9530-1f535331394a', '8a9e9ff4-95f9-4a2e-a915-f7ac3c9109c1', 'fillup', 'Questions 31–40', '<article class="text-token-text-primary w-full focus:outline-none [--shadow-height:45px] has-data-writing-block:pointer-events-none has-data-writing-block:-mt-(--shadow-height) has-data-writing-block:pt-(--shadow-height) [&amp;:has([data-writing-block])&gt;*]:pointer-events-auto scroll-mt-[calc(var(--header-height)+min(200px,max(70px,20svh)))]" dir="auto" tabindex="-1" data-turn-id="43fe7f54-581b-4dd6-98a4-ba74f9737acc" data-testid="conversation-turn-415" data-scroll-anchor="false" data-turn="assistant">
<div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto [--thread-content-margin:--spacing(4)] @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:--spacing(6)] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:--spacing(16)] px-(--thread-content-margin)">
<div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn" tabindex="-1">
<div class="flex max-w-full flex-col grow">
<div class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" dir="auto" data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="43fe7f54-581b-4dd6-98a4-ba74f9737acc" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-2">
<div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden first:pt-[1px]">
<p data-start="53" data-end="152">Write <strong data-start="109" data-end="135">NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;" data-start="159" data-end="181"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Company Outsourcing</strong></span></p>
<p><strong data-start="183" data-end="217">Case study – TCP Technologies:</strong></p>
<p class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full wrap-break-word light markdown-new-styling">Manager: Manjeet Khanna</p>
<p class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full wrap-break-word light markdown-new-styling">Main target: to create a {democratic} environment</p>
<p data-start="314" data-end="685"><strong data-start="314" data-end="336">Grading for staff:</strong></p>
<p data-start="314" data-end="685">• Every month grades are published on an {internal website}</p>
<p data-start="314" data-end="685">• The cultural openness increased the quantity of incoming contracted opportunities.</p>
<p data-start="314" data-end="685">• The cultural openness improved the level of {transparency} of the company.</p>
<p data-start="314" data-end="685">• The increased rate of staff satisfaction has led to growth of 32% in the {company’s income}</p>
<p data-start="314" data-end="685"><strong data-start="687" data-end="708">Recent interview:</strong></p>
<p data-start="687" data-end="854">• A company is not an entity comprised of components, but a living organism composed of cells.</p>
<p data-start="687" data-end="854">• Manjeet’s motto is {employee first}</p>
<p data-start="856" data-end="1055"><strong data-start="856" data-end="889">Benefits of management style:</strong></p>
<p data-start="856" data-end="1055">• The rate of staff turnover has been reduced.</p>
<p data-start="856" data-end="1055">• A {solution} can be from any other company.</p>
<p data-start="856" data-end="1055">• Grades are not used for {promotion}</p>
<p data-start="1057" data-end="1476" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node=""><strong data-start="1057" data-end="1088">Features of managing style:</strong></p>
<p data-start="1057" data-end="1476" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">• Personally, the manager wrote emails to respond to the complaints.</p>
<p data-start="1057" data-end="1476" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">• The complaint form known as a {ticket} has access to all employees online.</p>
<p data-start="1057" data-end="1476" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">• The manager can receive any complaints concerning air conditioning, food quality and {vacation} entitlement.</p>
<p data-start="1057" data-end="1476" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="">• A {ban} on the anonymous complaint was introduced in the new system.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="z-0 flex min-h-[46px] justify-start"> </div>
</div>
</div>
</article>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"1\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"1\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 4</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dr. Toby Bennett:</strong> Welcome class to your very first lecture in this series on business in the modern world, conducted by myself, Doctor <span class=\"citation-2809 citation-end-2809\">Toby Bennett. Today we will be looking into the practice of company outsourcing, using TCP Technologies as a case study.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><span class=\"citation-2808 citation-end-2808\">Now, for those of you who are unfamiliar with this practice, I will give you a summative definition. Company outsourcing involves the contracting of various business activities by one company to another. This practice will sometimes occur from a western c</span>ompany to a party based in a third world country. The rationale being to make significant financial savings on lower international labour rates and to potentially increase quality.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dr. Toby Bennett:</strong> Now our case study for today is TCP Technologies, a party located in India that receives outsourced tasks from western companies. The manager of TCP Technologies is a man called Manjit Karnal, <span class=\"citation-2806 citation-2807 citation-end-2807\">who has personally developed a series of aims and philosophies by which the company is expected to operate.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><span class=\"citation-2804 citation-2805 citation-end-2805\">He claims that the most important of these philosophies is to create a workplace where each individual member has the opportunity to contribute their opinion to the operations of the company. </span><span class=\"citation-2804 citation-end-2804\">That is to say that he found it important to de</span>velop a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"247\">(31) democratic</strong> </span>environment as a means of ensuring quality from every individual.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dr. Toby Bennett:</strong> <span class=\"citation-2803 citation-end-2803\">At TCP Technologies, a grading system has been developed that encourages an ethos of hard work and recognizes accomplishment. This grading of individuals is based upon a series of factors such as turnover, hours worked an</span>d efficiency.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\">Every month, Karnal publishes the grades on an<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">(32) <span class=\"citation-2802\">internal website</span></strong></span></span><span class=\"citation-2802 citation-end-2802\"> where staff can access not only their own grades but also compare it to others. A spirit of playful competitiveness has developed through this method, which has resulted in increased efficiency and turnover across the com</span>pany.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dr. Toby Bennett:</strong> Karnal <span class=\"citation-2801 citation-end-2801\">also saw it as essential to develop a culturally diverse group of employees as a means of presenting a multifaceted image that would appeal to a host of potential employees from across the globe. This cultural openness has n</span>ot only increased the quantity of incoming contracted opportunities by 7% but has also benefited the company itself significantly</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\">A level of <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">(33) <span class=\"citation-2799 citation-2800\">transparency</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-2799 citation-2800 citation-end-2800\"> now exists that had not before been apparent. According to questionnaires carried out recently, these newly introduced measures have significantly increased the rate of staff satisfaction, which has subsequently led to an increas</span><span class=\"citation-2799 citation-end-2799\">e of 32% in </span>the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"274\">(34) company’s income</strong></span>. These figures are truly admirable and serve as a testament to the measures that Karnal has introduced to the workplace at TCP Technologies.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dr. Toby Bennett:</strong> <span class=\"citation-2797 citation-2798 citation-end-2798\">In a recent interview published by The Economist, he declared, “The figures speak for themselves. My system works.” When asked if he had any advice for companies on methods they could employ to streamline workflow and increase turnover, he re</span><span class=\"citation-2797 citation-end-2797\">plied: “It’s simple really. A company must see itself not as one entity comprised of nameless components, but instead as a living organism composed of cells, each on</span>e essential to the functioning of the whole. I suggest that the motto by which your management operates will be <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"537\">(35) employee first</strong></span>.”</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dr. Toby Bennett:</strong> Many benefits have been reaped from the aforementioned ch<span class=\"citation-2796\">anges in management style, such as a significant decrease in staff turnover. This improvement alone has solved many problems that had before stunted the growth of the company. A lot of these improvements came from the realization that the </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"314\"><span class=\"citation-2796\">(36) solution</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-2796 citation-end-2796\"> does not have to be p</span>roduced internally but ca<span class=\"citation-2795 citation-end-2795\">n come from any other company.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><span class=\"citation-2794\">The grading system also immeasurably enhanced the dynamics of the company. The fact that this measuring system is solely produced for staff members and inaccessible by management means that it cannot be used as a judging criterion for </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"235\"><span class=\"citation-2794\">(37) promotion</span></strong></span><span class=\"citation-2794 citation-end-2794\">. It has proven itself a relaxed and i</span>nformal means of stimulating workflow.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dr. Toby Bennett:</strong> When asked about specific features of his managing style, Karnal mentioned that it is important for him to respond persona<span class=\"citation-2793 citation-end-2793\">lly to any complaints filed by staff members. Having found the existing complaints process slow and ineffective, he introduced a new online system that created a direct line of communication between Karnal and all employees of the company.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><span class=\"citation-2792 citation-end-2792\">The comp</span>laint form, dubbed by Karnal as a<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> <span style=\"background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">(38) ticket</strong>,</span></span> eradicates the middleman, is easily accessible <span class=\"citation-2791 citation-end-2791\">to all employees online, and has an interface that can be instinctively navigated. Any staff-related complaint, such as those relating to air conditioning and food quality, can be submitted directly to Karnal via this online system.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\">Entitlement to <strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\">(39) Vacation</span></strong> is also a popular issue discussed through this forum. The main benefit of using the system is that staff must include their personal details on the ticket before they are able to submit it. In the past, anonymous complaints had been the root of much confusion and caused many wasted work hours. So, the new system has put a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f3db7b;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"350\">(40) ban</strong></span> on this form of complaint.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\">That wraps up the lecture for today. Please remember that attendance is mandatory.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('8fdb397d-d8e5-40d1-bd1a-42f8faa098c0', 'b11a3056-77f7-4f34-b9fc-62622338e8e3', 'radio', 'Questions 11–16', '', '<p>Choose the correct answer.<br> </p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "There will be free entry."}, {"option_text": "There will be fewer people."}, {"option_text": "There will be special classes."}], "question": "Why does Jane recommend visiting the Music Tent on Tuesday?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "weekends only"}, {"option_text": "every evening"}, {"option_text": "every afternoon"}], "question": "When do the educational workshops take place in the Music Tent?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "The tickets will be cheaper there"}, {"option_text": "You can get tickets in advance there"}, {"option_text": "It''s easier to get tickets there than in the city"}], "question": "Why does Jane recommend going to the library to buy a ticket?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "its gardens"}, {"option_text": "its architecture"}, {"option_text": "its location"}], "question": "What will history lovers find interesting about Macquarie House?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "it will be much larger than before."}, {"option_text": "there will be free entertainment."}, {"option_text": "the food will be cooked by international chefs."}], "question": "The Big Barbecue is different this year because"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "see a steam engine working"}, {"option_text": "dress up in a railway worker''s uniform"}, {"option_text": "have a meal inside an old train"}], "question": "What can you do at the Railway Museum?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Host:</strong> Good afternoon listeners, thanks for tuning in to 4KB. Jane Lewis is with us from Tourism Queensland to tell us about the annual Queensland Festival. Jane, welcome.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jane:</strong> Morning John. So much is going on for the next couple of weeks in our festival here in the state’s capital of Brisbane. The Music Tent opens this week, and this will be an event not to be missed. As the name suggests, the Music Tent is an enormous tent where musical performances and activities will be going on throughout the day for the next two weeks.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">Monday is going to be really busy as it’s a public holiday and the first day of the event. It’s going to be lots of fun, but <strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"125\"><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(Q11) if you’re free, it’s probably a better option to leave it till Tuesday unless you love crowds</span>.</strong> The following day is when the master classes take place, and this requires pre-registration, so you can’t just turn up, I’m afraid. The weekend educational workshops were so popular last year that they have been extended this year. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"458\">(Q12) They now run each afternoon from 1:00 till 4:00, before the evening performances start from 5:00.</strong></span> If you’re learning to play an instrument, these workshops are great fun, so make sure you get along there.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">Tickets for the Music Tent events are available from the door, or you can purchase them at the ticket office located in the city centre. For the best deal, though, take proof of your home address to any library. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"212\">(Q13) As a local resident, you will be able to purchase discounted tickets.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">Apart from music, we’ll also be celebrating our local history with a special walking tour around Brisbane’s city centre. Not to be missed on the walk is a tour of Macquarie House, the home of Queensland’s first governor. It has lovely gardens you can walk around or picnic in. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"277\">(Q14) This building has a fascinating history because it was built on the very same spot where the first settlers landed</strong></span>, so it’s really worth a visit if you enjoy learning about our local history.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\">No Australian event is complete without a Barbie, and I think the big barbecue is going to be fantastic. It’s not quite as big as the Millennium Year barbecue, but <strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"164\"><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">(Q15) there’ll be local and international bands playing on the main stage for the first time this year at no extra cost</span>.</strong> As always, the food will be prepared by top local chefs—my mouth is watering already!</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">I really recommend going along to the Railway Museum during the festival because trains are such an important part of Queensland’s history. On loan from Queensland Rail at the moment is our very first steam train. You won’t be able to see it in operation, but <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"260\">(Q16) you can hop on board and have a meal in the old dining carriage.</strong></span> There is also a wonderful display of uniforms that have been worn over the last 100 years.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Narrator:</strong> Now listen and answer questions 17 to 20.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jane:</strong> Another really special opportunity is a return trip on our only remaining steam train, which runs from Ipswich to Toowoomba. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"131\">(Q17-18) If you purchase a family ticket, as well as a trip on the train, you receive a free Australian flag each to wave while aboard.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\">There is a small charge for the Ipswich Museum tour, but I think it’s worth it as it makes an educational day out. The documentary film you can see there is interesting, and it’s well worth the two-dollar entry fee. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"216\">(Q17-18) On the return train journey, the kids get a lovely activity book designed to teach them about the history of the steam train.</strong></span> Don’t forget to bring your sunscreen and hats—it’s going to be hot up there in Toowoomba at this time of year!</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\">And finally, I’m going to tell you about an event called “Our Favourite Place”. This is an opportunity for the public to vote for their favourite spot anywhere in the state—maybe a park or a restaurant, it’s up to you. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"219\">(Q19-20) You can vote even if you’re not living in the area at the moment.</strong><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"294\"> You can vote as often as you like by sending in the voting form</strong>,</span> or if you prefer, send a text message from any Australian mobile phone number with the name of the location. It’s so easy! Not much time left, though, so get those votes in as soon as possible. The winning location will be announced on the last Saturday of the festival. <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"639\">(Q19-20) Also, remember that no age limit applies for this one</strong></span>, so this is a great way to get the whole family involved.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Host:</strong> Well, thank you very much for that, Jane. Now we have music…</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('c44b1441-4e75-4077-bf43-55c31a96d205', '2bf85cb9-d6e3-4f91-b1d5-eda8252081cf', 'matching', 'Questions 25-30', '', '<p>What topic do students learn about in each of the following courses?</p>
<p>Choose <strong>SIX</strong> answers from the box and write the correct letter, <strong>A-G</strong></p>', 'matching_name', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p><strong>Topics</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Understanding is Essential {workplace communication}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Foundations {PSWs’ role in health care}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>The Way We Work {biological systems}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Residence Care {independent living}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Dynamics {handling stress}</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>The Power Within {memory stimulation activities}</p>", "optionsTitle": "Courses", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "independent living"}, {"optionText": "the ageing process stages"}, {"optionText": "PSWs’ role in health care"}, {"optionText": "workplace communication"}, {"optionText": "memory stimulation activities"}, {"optionText": "handling stress"}, {"optionText": "biological systems"}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "Understanding is Essential", "correctAnswer": "D"}, {"questionPart": "Foundations ", "correctAnswer": "C"}, {"questionPart": "The Way We Work ", "correctAnswer": "G"}, {"questionPart": "Residence Care ", "correctAnswer": "A"}, {"questionPart": "Dynamics ", "correctAnswer": "F"}, {"questionPart": " The Power Within ", "correctAnswer": "E"}]}', 'null', '[{"content": ""}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('110f1489-b043-4678-9a2b-6d60b15ac293', '132887aa-f8a8-484b-bb10-c5f7f43b6af9', 'fillup', 'Questions 24-26', '<p>Complete the summary below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p>Write your answers in boxes 24-26 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>What recent history tells us about recycling</strong></span></p>
<p>Richard Fisher, a researcher from Cranfield University, points out that the pace of consumerism has increased more quickly than was predicted in the 1980s. There has, for example, been unexpected growth in waste from {electronic} products. He suggests that the need to protect the environment should be linked to basic values, and adds that it might be better if consumers had more influence over {business} and more direction was provided by {government}.</p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. electronic — {unexpected growth in waste from electronic products}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn F):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“Consumerism has developed at a pace we never expected. Nobody would have said there would be so much <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"122\">electronic</strong> waste.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Richard Fisher nhấn mạnh rằng không ai có thể ngờ tới lượng rác thải điện tử (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"90\">electronic</strong>) lại lớn đến như vậy. Từ “unexpected growth” trong tóm tắt tương ứng với cụm “nobody would have said… so much” trong bài.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. business — {it might be better if consumers had more influence over business}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn F):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“We need to look at whether it’s <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">business</strong> that drives consumers or the <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">other way around</strong>.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cấu trúc “the other way around” (theo chiều ngược lại) ám chỉ việc người tiêu dùng dẫn dắt/có ảnh hưởng lên doanh nghiệp (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"134\">business</strong>), thay vì doanh nghiệp định hướng người tiêu dùng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. government — {more direction was provided by government}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn F):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“You need <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"30\">government</strong> to play a <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"51\">leadership role</strong>, whereas countries such as the UK seem to be stepping away…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Leadership role” (vai trò lãnh đạo) đồng nghĩa với việc đưa ra định hướng và chỉ dẫn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">direction</strong>). Tác giả cho rằng chính phủ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"139\">government</strong>) cần đóng vai trò chủ chốt này thay vì né tránh.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f12b33b6-aee5-46a6-bfe8-f7a4b8ef8122', 'd862c204-ffd7-4688-ab4d-39c3ef3d7416', 'fillup', 'Questions 31–40', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong data-start="154" data-end="171">ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p data-section-id="1on1lml" data-start="195" data-end="244"><span style="font-size: 14pt;" role="text"><strong data-start="198" data-end="244">Finding and re-using old supplies of metal</strong></span></p>
<p data-section-id="13xvd8f" data-start="246" data-end="281"><span role="text"><strong data-start="250" data-end="281">Historic use of scrap metal</strong></span></p>
<ul>
<li data-start="283" data-end="368">
<p>In ancient Greece and Rome, scrap metal was sometimes used to make a {statue}</p>
</li>
<li data-start="370" data-end="485">
<p>In the 19th century, metal dealers in the US profited from disused equipment that had been used on a {farm}</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-section-id="9otgw8" data-start="492" data-end="534"><span role="text"><strong data-start="496" data-end="534">Why we need more scrap metal today</strong></span></p>
<ul>
<li data-start="536" data-end="617">
<p>The {economy} of many countries is improving, leading to increased demand.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="619" data-end="689">
<p>The {quality} of the copper from the remaining sources is poor.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="691" data-end="753">
<p>The rapidly growing {electronics} industry is very wasteful</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-section-id="ajmgsf" data-start="760" data-end="802"><span role="text"><strong data-start="764" data-end="802">Where scrap and metal can be found</strong></span></p>
<ul>
<li data-start="804" data-end="873">
<p>In the UK, platinum is in {plants} at the sides of the roads.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="875" data-end="903">
<p>In Sweden, metal is found:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>in old cotton {factories} in {pipes} under the ground used for gas</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-section-id="15vbyny" data-start="995" data-end="1043"><span role="text"><strong data-start="999" data-end="1043">How metals are separated from each other</strong></span></p>
<ul>
<li data-start="1045" data-end="1113">
<p>It is possible to use a big {magnet} for some types of metal</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1115" data-end="1184">
<p>A potential new method in the UK is through the use of {bacteria}</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 4: RECYCLING OF METAL</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Lecturer:</strong> Hello, this is the second in our series of lectures on the subject of recycling. Today we''re looking at scrap metal—that is, pieces of metal that have been thrown away or I suppose, metal which is no longer serving any kind of practical function.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">Now, you might think that recycling is a modern phenomenon, but throughout history, people have always done this kind of thing in one way or another. Take the ancient Greeks and Romans with their scrap metal, copper or bronze—that is, they might turn it into a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"261\">(Q31) statue</strong></span>. So yes, nothing was wasted. In fact, scrap metal was considered valuable, and the Greeks and Romans used it in a variety of similar ways.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\">Since then, the use of scrap metal has been turned into a whole industry. In some countries, it''s become a major export. In the US, for instance, dealing in scrap metal started back in the 19th century. This was a time of immense urban migration, and metal dealers knew they could make money out of the little machinery and tools that had been left behind on a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"240\">(Q32) farm</strong></span> when whole families had moved away to the city. And some of those dealers are now huge corporations selling scrap metal to buyers in other countries.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\">So why do we need scrap metal today? First of all, there have been positive changes to the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">(Q33) economy</strong></span> in many countries, and because people have more money, this is driving up demand for goods, and you need metal to make many of those things.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\">Then, there are issues relating to specific types of metal. For example, take copper. The thing is, there are still plenty of sources for copper, but the issue is the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"167\">(Q34) quality</strong></span>—it''s just not as good as it used to be.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">Another reason why we need to locate and reuse old metals is due to an industry that''s really been developing over the last few decades, and of course it''s <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"156\">(Q35) electronics</strong></span>. Think about all the stuff you''ve bought and then replaced in the last few years. What happens to the things you get rid of? Well, a lot of them just end up being thrown away and the metal components go to waste.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\">So where do people look for scrap metal? Researchers and engineers are now investigating new sources in the UK. One place they''re looking at is the sides of the roads. That''s because tiny bits of a metal called platinum are emitted by cars and this can eventually be reused.And they''re also looking at the side of the road because with some types of <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(Q36) </strong><strong><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\">p</span>lants </strong></span>that grow there, it''s been proved that they can absorb metals really effectively.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\">Sweden is also a country where a lot of work in this area is being done. Sweden used to manufacture a lot of cotton and so researchers there are looking at old <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"160\">(Q37) factories</strong></span> which used to produce it but are now closed down. There is so much metal in the walls and in the flooring that could be melted down again. And in the same country, deep below ground, are many, many <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"374\">(Q38) pipes</strong></span> that once provided gas to the surrounding neighborhood. It’s all there waiting to be excavated.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\">But the trick is how to do this without causing huge disruption to local residents and the traffic flow..So once we find our waste metals, how do we get at them? How are they separated? Well, if you''re trying to separate iron and steel from, say, silver or gold, perhaps in a computer or a cellphone, you could use a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"277\">(Q39) magnet</strong></span> provided it was larger than the components it was trying to attract.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\">But again, engineers are also being innovative in this area too. One researcher in the UK is carrying out an experiment with <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"125\">(Q40) bacteria</strong></span> that hopefully could be used to help recover precious metals from waste materials. Let me explain how that works exactly...</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('785f16ae-2fad-42ff-85b3-a02b8dd3f06d', '84a2fc46-71dc-404c-ad22-6cb99216a895', 'fillup', 'Questions 31–40', '<p data-start="107" data-end="171">Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY </strong>for each answer.</p>
<p data-start="178" data-end="223"><strong><span style="font-size: 14pt;">Sea lion tracking study (Western Australia)</span></strong></p>
<p data-start="225" data-end="248"><strong>Reason for the study</strong></p>
<ul data-start="249" data-end="413">
<li data-start="249" data-end="302">
<p data-start="251" data-end="302">The Australian sea lion is an endangered species.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="303" data-end="352">
<p data-start="305" data-end="352">Until 1892, numbers were affected by hunting.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="353" data-end="413">
<p data-start="355" data-end="413">Sea lions are now affected by nets used to control {sharks}.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="420" data-end="446"><strong>Animal tracking systems</strong></p>
<ul data-start="447" data-end="800">
<li data-start="447" data-end="529">
<p data-start="449" data-end="529">Considerations when choosing a tracking method include {cost} and ease of use.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="530" data-end="582">
<p data-start="532" data-end="582">Plastic tags: the animal must be easy to {catch}.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="583" data-end="628">
<p data-start="585" data-end="628">GPS tracking will not work in the {ocean}.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="629" data-end="711">
<p data-start="631" data-end="711">In isolated regions, some animals are tracked by {helicopter} (e.g. the polar bear).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="712" data-end="800">
<p data-start="714" data-end="800">Some animals are identified by markings (e.g. the dolphin is identified by its scars).</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="807" data-end="842"><strong>Challenges of tracking sea lions</strong></p>
<ul data-start="843" data-end="1046">
<li data-start="843" data-end="935">
<p data-start="845" data-end="935">Perth study: the sea lions lost their tags. (They rubbed against {rocks} to remove them.)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="936" data-end="1046">
<p data-start="938" data-end="1046">Californian researchers used {paint} to identify sea lions. (This was unreliable due to regular loss of fur.)</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1053" data-end="1065"><strong>Our study</strong></p>
<p data-start="1067" data-end="1076">Aims:</p>
<p data-start="1077" data-end="1188">i) to find out if sea lions’ whiskers can be used to identify them<br data-start="1143" data-end="1146">ii) to create a {diagram} to use as a guide</p>
<p data-start="1190" data-end="1202">Methods:</p>
<p data-start="1203" data-end="1294">i) contacting {zoos} in Australia for photographs<br data-start="1252" data-end="1255">ii) asking the {public} to get involved</p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">SECTION 4: SEA LION TRACKING STUDY</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Presenter:</strong> Hello everybody. I’m here today to tell you about a new research study that my team here at the university is doing on the sea lions that live along the coast of Western Australia.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\">You may be wondering why we’ve been studying this animal. Well, Australian sea lions have been identified as an endangered species, so there’s a real need to count them and find out just how many there are.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\">Up until 1892, the population of these animals was severely depleted because of hunting—that’s no longer allowed. But today there is a new danger. Sea lions often forage for food in the same areas along the coastlines where there are nets used to catch<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"253\">(31) sharks</strong></span>. Unfortunately, they tend to get caught up in the nets by accident and drown.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">ANIMAL TRACKING SYSTEMS</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Presenter:</strong> Now, we wanted to monitor the population of sea lions in this area, but we weren’t sure of the best way to do it. There are several different animal tracking methods which vary in their effectiveness, and there are different factors to consider.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\">One of the most important of these is the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">(32) cost</strong></span>, but you also have to consider how easy your chosen method is to use. You may choose a traditional method like a plastic tag. They’re relatively straightforward to attach, but they’re really only suitable to use with animals that you can <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"290\">(33) catch</strong></span> quite easily.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\">You might also go with a more modern method like GPS tracking, which uses satellite technology to transmit data on the animal around the clock. One drawback for marine animals though is that they don’t transmit a signal in the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"227\">(34) ocean</strong></span>; you only get data when they’re on land.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\">There are certain large animals in remote areas that have to be tracked using a <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"80\">(35) helicopter</strong></span>—the polar bear is a good example.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">CHALLENGES OF TRACKING SEA LIONS</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Presenter:</strong> Now, an important part of tracking is being able to clearly identify the animal. Some, like zebras, are identified by markings such as their stripes, while the dolphin usually has distinguishing scars on its body that can help tell them apart.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\">Sea lions don’t have any markings like this, which is just one of the challenges of tracking them. When researchers in Perth tried to use electronic tags in a sea lion study, they found that the sea lions had removed their tracking devices by deliberately rubbing up against <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"275\">(36) rocks</strong></span>. This was something the researchers hadn’t anticipated.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\">Researchers in California studying American sea lions tried a different method: they applied <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"93\">(37) paint</strong></span> to the animals. They thought this would be a better, less invasive means of identification. Unfortunately, this didn’t work so well either because sea lions molt every year and shed their fur along with the identifying mark.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">OUR STUDY</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Presenter:</strong> So let’s look at our current study. We have several aims that we’d like to achieve.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\">The first of these is to try to establish whether sea lions can be identified from the whiskers on their face. These are much coarser than a cat’s whiskers, so easier to see. Our theory is that the pattern of these whiskers may be as individual as a fingerprint on a human. If this is in fact true, then we think this could be an effective way to identify them.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\">Our second aim is to come up with a <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"36\">(38) diagram</strong></span> of sea lion whisker patterns so this can be used as a guide for us and other studies.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\">We’re using a few different methods to help us do all this. We know that we need to build up a wide range of visual data. So firstly, we’ve been in touch with <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"159\">(39) zoos</strong></span> around Australia to gather photographs from them of the faces of any sea lions they have.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\">This won’t be enough to achieve our purpose though, so we’re also broadening our search by inviting the <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"104\">(40) public</strong></span> to take part in our research. We’re hoping this will result in hundreds of useful images we can use.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('1e550e0a-8a57-4b6e-b23b-1180328ed7e2', '041a2320-11a2-4d8f-b9f8-b4bcf8e88477', 'radio', 'Questions 27–31', '', '<p>Choose <strong data-start="157" data-end="164">YES</strong> – if the statement agrees with the claims of the writer, <strong data-start="223" data-end="229">NO</strong> – if the statement contradicts the claims of the writer, <strong data-start="288" data-end="301">NOT GIVEN</strong> – if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this</p>', 'yes_no_not_given', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Onge language has a particularly poor chance of survival"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Most linguists oppose the idea of a single global language"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Many citizens of the Roman Empire chose to become Latin speakers"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Majority languages such as Spanish and English are now spreading faster within smaller communities than larger ones"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "YES"}, {"option_text": "NO"}, {"option_text": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "There is a greater proportion of English used on the internet nowadays than in the 1990s"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. NO</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Consequently, it would be considered less threatened than a language such as Chipweyan in Canada...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi khẳng định tiếng Onge có cơ hội sống sót đặc biệt thấp (<em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">particularly poor chance of survival</em>). Tuy nhiên, bài đọc chỉ ra rằng vì tiếng Onge là bản ngữ của toàn bộ trẻ em trên đảo nên nó được đánh giá là ít bị đe dọa hơn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"241\">less threatened</strong>) so với tiếng Chipweyan ở Canada. Thông tin mâu thuẫn trực tiếp nên đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"335\">NO</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. YES</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“The majority of linguists argue, however, that when it comes to language, diversity matters.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói phần lớn các nhà ngôn ngữ học phản đối ý tưởng về một ngôn ngữ toàn cầu duy nhất (<em data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"106\">oppose the idea of a single global language</em>). Điều này trùng khớp với lập luận của bài: phần lớn các nhà ngôn ngữ học cho rằng sự đa dạng mới là điều quan trọng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"268\">diversity matters</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. YES</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“There was some prestige associated with the language – it was the medium of trade and administration – and people who wanted to get on in life tended to learn it.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi nói nhiều công dân của Đế quốc La Mã đã tự lựa chọn học tiếng La-tinh (<em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"91\">chose to become Latin speakers</em>). Bài đọc xác nhận vì tiếng La-tinh mang lại vị thế và là công cụ giao thương, những người muốn tiến thân trong cuộc sống có xu hướng tự học nó (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"267\">tended to learn it</strong>). Đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"298\">YES</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30. NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“In recent decades, the mass media have reinforced this process further and extended the penetration of metropolitan languages like English and Spanish beyond urban centres into smaller communities.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nêu thông tin các ngôn ngữ lớn đang mở rộng tầm ảnh hưởng vượt ra ngoài các trung tâm đô thị để thâm nhập vào các cộng đồng nhỏ hơn, chứ <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"161\">hoàn toàn không có sự so sánh</strong> xem tốc độ lan rộng ở cộng đồng nhỏ có nhanh hơn (<em data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"241\">spreading faster</em>) cộng đồng lớn hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. NO</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“However, these fears proved to be unfounded, as the diversity of languages on the web increased rapidly in the years that followed.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Câu hỏi khẳng định tỷ lệ tiếng Anh được sử dụng trên Internet ngày nay lớn hơn so với những năm 1990 (<em data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"114\">greater proportion... than in the 1990s</em>). Ngược lại, bài đọc chỉ ra rằng nỗi sợ tiếng Anh độc bá đã không diễn ra, vì sự đa dạng của các ngôn ngữ khác trên mạng đã tăng trưởng nhanh chóng (<em data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"303\">diversity of languages on the web increased rapidly</em>), đồng nghĩa với việc tỷ lệ tiếng Anh đã bị giảm đi chứ không tăng lên. Do đó đáp án là <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"443\">NO</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('732d1801-b399-442d-a1eb-82dc16609e8e', 'e225b4e7-8b95-431d-a0d6-e757f56927d0', 'radio', 'Questions 1–6', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if there is no information on this</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE "}, {"content": "FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Bocherens’ findings on cave bears involve measuring the length of complete bones."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE "}, {"content": "FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Bocherens was the first person to conduct analytical research on cave bears in a laboratory."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE "}, {"content": "FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Cave bears have been extinct for 25,000 years."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE "}, {"content": "FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "At one time people thought the excavated remains of bears were those of dragons."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE "}, {"content": "FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Modern grizzly bears are similar in size to cave bears."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE "}, {"content": "FALSE "}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Neanderthals understood cave bear behaviour better than modern humans did."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>1 NOT GIVEN<br />(Đoạn 1: “He dissolves 30,000-year-old animal bones in hydrochloric acid… until what’s left is a speck of powder weighing less than one-hundredth of an ounce.”)<br />→ Đoạn này chỉ nói Bocherens phân tích xương bằng phương pháp hóa học, không có thông tin nào về việc đo chiều dài của xương nguyên vẹn.</p>\n<p> <br />2 NOT GIVEN<br />(Đoạn 1: “Bocherens is at the forefront of research on the bear, a European species that died out 25,000 years ago.”)<br />→ Bài nói Bocherens đang dẫn đầu trong nghiên cứu, nhưng không khẳng định ông là người đầu tiên thực hiện nghiên cứu này trong phòng thí nghiệm.</p>\n<p> <br />3 TRUE<br />(Đoạn 1: “&#8230;a European species that died out 25,000 years ago.”)<br />→ Gấu hang động đã tuyệt chủng cách đây 25.000 năm, đúng như phát biểu.</p>\n<p> <br />4 TRUE<br />(Đoạn 1: “In the Middle Ages, the massive skulls were attributed to dragons.”)<br />→ Vào thời Trung Cổ, người ta từng nhầm tưởng xương gấu là của rồng.</p>\n<p> <br />5 FALSE<br />(Đoạn 2: “Males weighed up to 1,500 pounds, 50 percent more than the largest modern grizzly bears.”)<br />→ Gấu hang động to hơn khoảng 50% so với gấu xám hiện đại, nên câu nói “similar in size” là sai.</p>\n<p> <br />6 FALSE<br />(Đoạn 3: “There’s no way to tell if it was just curiosity that made someone put a skull on the rock, or if it had religious significance.”)<br />→ Bocherens khẳng định không thể biết chắc người Neanderthal hiểu rõ hành vi của gấu hay không → chứng tỏ họ không hiểu rõ hơn người hiện đại.<br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /> </p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('d74902f8-7cb3-45c1-bc4e-69f9c0915e4c', '1c9eba9b-3398-4a72-a658-fcbf65d2b9dd', 'radio', 'Questions 25 – 30', '', '<p data-start="115" data-end="156">Choose the correct letter, <strong data-start="142" data-end="155">A, B or C</strong>.</p>
<p data-start="163" data-end="190"><span style="font-size: 14pt;"><strong data-start="166" data-end="190">Teaching handwriting</strong></span></p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A Children often lack motivation to learn that way"}, {"option_text": "B Children become fluent relatively quickly"}, {"option_text": "C Children react more positively if they make a mistake"}], "question": "What does the woman say about using laptops to teach writing to children with dyslexia?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A cursive writing disadvantages a certain group of children"}, {"option_text": "B print writing is associated with lower academic performance"}, {"option_text": "C most teachers in the UK prefer a traditional approach to handwriting"}], "question": "When discussing whether to teach cursive or print writing, the woman thinks that"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A There is evidence to suggest grades are affected by poor handwriting"}, {"option_text": "B Neat handwriting is less important now than it used to be"}, {"option_text": "C Candidates write more slowly and produce shorter answers"}], "question": "According to the students, what impact does poor handwriting have on exam performance?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A Touch typing will be taught before writing by hand"}, {"option_text": "B Children will continue to learn to write by hand"}, {"option_text": "C People will dislike handwriting on digital devices"}], "question": "What prediction does the man make about the future of handwriting?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A take detailed notes"}, {"option_text": "B spell and punctuate"}, {"option_text": "C read old documents"}], "question": "The woman is concerned that relying on digital devices has made it difficult for her to"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"option_text": "A concerned they are unable to write quickly"}, {"option_text": "B embarrassed by comments made about it"}, {"option_text": "C regretful that they have lost the habit"}], "question": "How do the students feel about their own handwriting?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('23a97a74-8e8d-46b3-9f1d-dbf5469a2226', '6734b872-a71b-414c-b6ff-9dae25445d03', 'fillup', ' Questions 14–17', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<p>Complete the summary below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="quests-des">
<div class="content-write">
<p class="ql-align-center" style="text-align: center;"><strong>Malaria in 19th-century Italy</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">Up until the late nineteenth century, experts failed to make the connection between malaria and {insects}. The most popular belief at the time was the {miasma} theory, which upheld the idea that diseases were carried by unclean air. Another common idea was that malaria was a {hereditary} disease, and as a result people from certain parts of the country were often held responsible for the spread of epidemics. Malaria was particularly widespread in rural regions, where {life expectancy} could be extremely short.</p>
</div>
</div>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 14: …experts failed to make the connection between malaria and {insects}.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> insects</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Others made a link between swamps, water and malaria, but did not make the further leap towards <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"108\">insects</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc nêu rõ các chuyên gia thời đó chưa thể kết nối mối liên hệ giữa bệnh và côn trùng (cụ thể là muỗi).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 15: The most popular belief at the time was the {miasma} theory…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> miasma</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “But in the 19th century most experts subscribed to the theory of ‘<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">miasma</strong>‘ or ‘poisoning of the air’.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Lý thuyết phổ biến nhất thời bấy giờ về nguyên nhân gây bệnh là thuyết “miasma” (khí độc).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 16: Another common idea was that malaria was a {hereditary} disease…</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> hereditary</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…given the widespread belief that malaria was <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">hereditary</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Một niềm tin sai lầm khác là bệnh sốt rét có tính di truyền.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 17: …where {life expectancy} could be extremely short.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> life expectancy</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “In warm, damp, malarial zones, the <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">life expectancy</strong> of land workers was a terrifying 22.5 years.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tại các vùng nông thôn bị ảnh hưởng, tuổi thọ trung bình của người dân rất thấp.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ab93506f-a836-4204-8fa2-fc117df3e628', '62865638-b9a5-4641-85c9-90076e4a96e7', 'matching', 'Questions 14-19', NULL, '<p>Reading passage 2 has six paragraphs.</p>
<p>Choose the correct heading for each paragraph from the list of heading below.</p>
<p>Choose the correct number, i-ix, in boxes <strong>14-19</strong>.</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i. Experimenting with an old idea"}, {"optionText": "ii. Life cycle of Madagascar spiders"}, {"optionText": "iii. Advances in the textile industry"}, {"optionText": "iv. Resources needed to meet the project’s demands"}, {"optionText": "v. The physical properties of spider silk"}, {"optionText": "vi. A scientific analysis of spider silk"}, {"optionText": "vii. A unique work of art"}, {"optionText": "viii. Importance of the silk textile market"}, {"optionText": "ix. Difficulties of raising spiders in captivity"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>14. Paragraph 1</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>vii. A unique work of art</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 1) Văn bản mô tả một loại vải dệt hiếm (<em>rare textile</em>) làm từ lụa nhện, là <strong>tác phẩm duy nhất và lớn nhất</strong> (<em>“the only large piece of cloth made from natural spider silk existing in the world today”</em>) được trưng bày tại bảo tàng New York.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>15. Paragraph 2</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>v. The physical properties of spider silk</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) Đoạn này liệt kê các thuộc tính vật lý đặc biệt của tơ nhện: <strong>độ đàn hồi cao</strong> (<em>“very elastic”</em>), <strong>sức bền kéo</strong> (<em>“tensile strength”</em>) lớn hơn Kevlar và thép, <strong>siêu nhẹ</strong> (<em>“extremely lightweight”</em>), và <strong>dẻo</strong> (<em>“ductile”</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>16.Paragraph 3</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>ix. Difficulties of raising spiders in captivity</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) Đoạn này giải thích tại sao tơ nhện khó sản xuất hàng loạt: <strong>“spiders have a habit of chomping off each other’s heads when housed together”</strong> (nhện ăn thịt lẫn nhau khi bị nuôi nhốt).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>17. Paragraph 4</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>i. Experimenting with an old idea</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) Peers nảy ra ý tưởng dệt tơ nhện sau khi biết về nhà truyền giáo Pháp Jacob Paul Camboue, người đã sử dụng nhện ở Madagascar vào những năm <strong>1880-1890</strong>. Peers đã <strong>xây dựng một bản sao</strong> (<em>“build a replica”</em>) của chiếc máy kéo tơ 24 nhện của Camboue.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>18. Paragraph 5</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>iv. Resources needed to meet the project’s demands</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) Để sản xuất lượng tơ cần thiết, các chuyên gia phải <strong>thuê hàng tá người bắt nhện</strong> (<em>“hiring dozens of spider handlers”</em>) và cuối cùng đã sử dụng <strong>hơn 1 triệu con nhện</strong> (<em>“more than 1 million female golden orb spiders”</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>19. Paragraph 6</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>vi. A scientific analysis of spider silk</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) Đoạn này thảo luận về các nỗ lực khoa học để sản xuất tơ nhện trong phòng thí nghiệm (chèn gen vào vi khuẩn/động vật) và vai trò của các chuyên gia như Todd Blackledge trong việc <strong>phân tích cách nhện áp dụng lực</strong> (<em>“apply force to rearrange the protein’s molecular structure”</em>) để biến protein lỏng thành tơ rắn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
