</td>
<td style="width: 134.828px; border-width: medium 1pt 1pt medium; border-style: none solid solid none; border-color: currentcolor windowtext windowtext currentcolor; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 48.4pt;" valign="top" width="146">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif;">Resembles {glass}</span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 153.969px; border-width: medium 1pt 1pt medium; border-style: none solid solid none; border-color: currentcolor windowtext windowtext currentcolor; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 48.4pt;" valign="top" width="170">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif;">food containers; toy</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr style="mso-yfti-irow: 8; mso-yfti-lastrow: yes; height: 56.85pt;">
<td style="border-width: medium 1pt 1pt; border-style: none solid solid; border-color: currentcolor windowtext windowtext; border-image: initial; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 56.85pt; width: 96.4688px;" valign="top">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal;"><strong><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif;">Polyurethane</span></strong></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 87.0938px; border-width: medium 1pt 1pt medium; border-style: none solid solid none; border-color: currentcolor windowtext windowtext currentcolor; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 56.85pt;" valign="top" width="99"> </td>
<td style="width: 101.484px; border-width: medium 1pt 1pt medium; border-style: none solid solid none; border-color: currentcolor windowtext windowtext currentcolor; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 56.85pt;" valign="top" width="112">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif;">Germany</span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 134.828px; border-width: medium 1pt 1pt medium; border-style: none solid solid none; border-color: currentcolor windowtext windowtext currentcolor; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 56.85pt;" valign="top" width="146">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif;">Usually manufactured as a {foam}</span></p>
</td>
<td style="width: 153.969px; border-width: medium 1pt 1pt medium; border-style: none solid solid none; border-color: currentcolor windowtext windowtext currentcolor; padding: 0in 5.4pt; height: 56.85pt;" valign="top" width="170">
<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 0in; line-height: normal;"><span style="font-family: ''Arial'',sans-serif;">insulation</span></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>1. Celluloid… Common uses: photographic film</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>photographic film</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) “But perhaps the best-known celluloid product was <strong>photographic film</strong>…”</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>2. Name: Bakelite</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Bakelite</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) “Leo Baekeland… invented a different kind of plastic, by causing phenol and formaldehyde to react together. Baekeland called it <strong>Bakelite</strong>…”</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>3. Bakelite… Common uses: electrical switches</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>electrical switches</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) “…it was soon being used in the manufacture of <strong>electrical switches</strong> as well as a variety of domestic items.”</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>4. Polythene… Country of origin: Britain</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Britain</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) “In the 1930s, chemists in <strong>Britain</strong> discovered that the gas ethylene would polymerize under heat and pressure to form a thermoplastic they called polythene.”</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>5. Rigid PVC… Properties: Is fireproof</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>fireproof</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) “…produced rigid PVC (polyvinyl chloride), a <strong>fireproof</strong> plastic suitable for drains and gutters.”</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>6. Polystyrene… Properties: Resembles glass</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>glass</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “<strong>Polystyrene</strong>, a hard, clear material <strong>like glass</strong>, was developed during the 1930s in Germany…”</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>7. Polyurethane… Usually manufactured as a foam</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>foam</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “<strong>Polyurethane</strong>, developed in the same country, was commonly produced as a <strong>foam</strong> which was very useful in the production of insulating materials.”</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('b149aedf-6529-48f9-b8f9-b14f4ed2b1b8', 'b841479a-69b2-4b96-b63d-2f904822c0ee', 'radio', 'Questions 8–13', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information  <strong>FALSE</strong> if the statement contradicts the information  <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if there is no information on this</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The chemical structure of rubber is very different to that of plastics"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "John Wesley Hyatt was an industrial chemist"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Celluloid and Bakelite react in the same way to heat"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "If an object is made of several plastics, these prove hard to break down and reuse"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Adding starch to plastic makes it more durable"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Containers which are designed to decompose need particular storage conditions."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>8. The chemical structure of rubber is very different to that of plastics.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 1) “Chemically, rubber is a <strong>polymer</strong>… The same bonding principle-<strong>polymerization</strong>-is the basis of the creation of a huge range of <strong>plastics</strong>…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Cả cao su và nhựa đều là polymer, dựa trên cùng một nguyên tắc liên kết hóa học, do đó cấu trúc của chúng tương đồng chứ không khác biệt rất nhiều.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>9. John Wesley Hyatt was an industrial chemist.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) “The prize was won by <strong>John Wesley Hyatt</strong>, with a material called celluloid.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản nêu tên John Wesley Hyatt nhưng <strong>không cung cấp thông tin</strong> về nghề nghiệp hay lĩnh vực chuyên môn của ông.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>10. Celluloid and Bakelite react in the same way to heat.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) “<strong>Celluloid can be repeatedly softened and reshaped by heat</strong>, and is known as a thermoplastic. …Bakelite… was the first of the <strong>thermosets</strong>-plastic that can be cast and moulded while hot, but <strong>cannot be softened by heat and reshaped once they have set</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Celluloid (thermoplastic) có thể làm mềm, Bakelite (thermoset) thì không thể, tức là chúng phản ứng khác nhau.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>11. If an object is made of several plastics, these prove hard to break down and reuse.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 8) “Nor is it very easy to recycle plastics, as <strong>different types of plastic are often found in the same items and call for different treatments</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Nhiều loại nhựa khác nhau trong cùng một vật phẩm cần quy trình xử lý khác nhau, khiến việc tái chế (break down and reuse) rất khó khăn.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>12. Adding starch to plastic makes it more durable.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 9) “Plastics can be made biodegradable by incorporating into their structure a material such as <strong>starch, which is attacked by bacteria and causes the plastic to fall apart</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Thêm tinh bột làm nhựa bị phân hủy (fall apart), tức là <strong>ít bền</strong> hơn, mâu thuẫn với “more durable” (bền hơn).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>13. Containers which are designed to decompose need particular storage conditions.</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Đáp án: TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 9) “…although bottles made of such materials have to be <strong>stored in the dark</strong>, to ensure they do not disintegrate before they have been used.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Các chai lọ làm từ vật liệu phân hủy sinh học cần được lưu trữ trong bóng tối (particular storage conditions).</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('80d521d9-cab5-4edb-813d-0f18151d0fac', '3db83e53-a345-4780-b470-0f6519bc6860', 'fillup', 'Questions 1–6', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>DATA ON FOOD DESERTS AND THEIR EFFECTS ON HEALTH</strong></p>
<p><strong>The Brooklyn Food Association</strong></p>
<p>– The online map provides users with a store’s name, {location} and details of its produce.</p>
<p>– One goal of the mapping project is to help develop new {policies} on food.</p>
<p>– Citizen maps are sometimes made when {government} maps are unsatisfactory.</p>
<p><strong>Reasons for the development of food deserts</strong></p>
<p>– New research suggests that people living in food deserts often have low {incomes}.</p>
<p>– Some supermarkets are unable to buy enough {land} inside cities for their stores.</p>
<p>– Small grocery stores in cities often cannot cope with supermarket {competition}.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', NULL, NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong>1. The online map provides users with a store’s name, location and details of its produce.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>location</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Over the last few months, a survey has been carried out… colorful dots appear on their online map, which display the specific <strong>location</strong> of each of the food stores in a handful of central Brooklyn neighborhoods.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Bản đồ trực tuyến hiển thị vị trí cụ thể của từng cửa hàng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong>2. One goal of the mapping project is to help develop new policies on food.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>policies</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The aim of the project is also to assist government officials in assessing food availability, and in forming future <strong>policies</strong> about what kind of food should be sold and where.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Mục tiêu của dự án là hỗ trợ các quan chức chính phủ xây dựng các chính sách tương lai về thực phẩm.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong>3. Citizen maps are sometimes made when government maps are unsatisfactory.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>government</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “According to Michael Goodchild… citizen map makers may make maps because there is no good <strong>government</strong> map, or to record problems such as burned-out traffic lights.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Người dân tự lập bản đồ khi bản đồ của chính phủ không tốt.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong>4. New research suggests that people living in food deserts often have low incomes .</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>incomes</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “According to recent studies, people at higher risk of chronic disease and who receive <strong>minimal incomes</strong> for the work they do, frequently live in neighborhoods located in food deserts.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Những người sống trong food deserts thường có thu nhập tối thiểu (minimal incomes / low incomes).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong>5. Some supermarkets are unable to buy enough land inside cities for their stores.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>land</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Linda Alwitt and Thomas Donley… found that supermarkets often can’t afford the amount of <strong>land</strong> required for their stores in cities.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Các siêu thị gặp khó khăn trong việc mua đủ đất (land) trong thành phố.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong>6. Small grocery stores in cities often cannot cope with supermarket competition .</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>competition</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> “City planning researcher Cliff Guy and colleagues… found in 2004 that smaller urban groceries tend to close due to <strong>competition</strong> from suburban supermarkets.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Các cửa hàng tạp hóa nhỏ đóng cửa do sự cạnh tranh từ các siêu thị ngoại ô.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a7941efb-8a3d-4c35-a1ca-ea7baf994b1a', '527a8990-5cea-4f20-a0e8-a0a04e0f3ab1', 'matching', 'Questions 14–19', NULL, '<p>Reading Passage 2 has six paragraphs. Choose the correct heading for each section and move it into the gap.</p>
', 'matching', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i Different areas of professional expertise"}, {"optionText": "ii Reasons why it is unfair to criticise lawyers"}, {"optionText": "iii The disadvantages of the legal system"}, {"optionText": "iv The law applies throughout our lives"}, {"optionText": "v The law has affected historical events"}, {"optionText": "vi A negative regard for lawyers"}, {"optionText": "vii Public’s increasing ability to Influence the law"}, {"optionText": "viii Growth in laws"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>14. (Đoạn 1)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>iv The law applies throughout our lives</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 1) &#8220;The law influences all of us virtually all the time. It governs almost all aspects of our behavior, and even what happens to us when we are no longer alive. It affects us from the embryo onwards.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn văn nhấn mạnh luật pháp điều chỉnh và ảnh hưởng đến <strong>tất cả các khía cạnh</strong> cuộc sống của chúng ta, từ khi là phôi thai trở đi, cho thấy sự áp dụng liên tục và xuyên suốt.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>15. (Đoạn 2)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>vii Public’s increasing ability to influence the law</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) &#8220;&#8230;it is becoming easier for people to take an interest in law, and for the <strong>general population to help actually shape the law</strong> in many countries.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn văn tập trung vào sự phát triển gần đây, trong đó <strong>công chúng</strong> (<em>general population</em>) ngày càng có khả năng <strong>định hình luật pháp</strong> (<em>shape the law</em>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>16. (Đoạn 3)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>i Different areas of professional expertise</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) &#8220;Those people, for example, with knowledge of computers, the internet, and communications technology are relied upon by the rest of us&#8230; But <strong>legal understanding is just as vital and as universally needed</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn văn so sánh hiểu biết về luật pháp với các chuyên môn khác (như IT) và kết luận rằng <strong>kiến thức pháp lý cũng quan trọng và cần thiết phổ quát</strong> như các lĩnh vực chuyên môn khác.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>17. (Đoạn 4)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>viii Growth in laws</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) &#8220;<strong>The number of laws has never been greater.</strong>&#8230; The legislative output of the British Parliament has <strong>more than doubled</strong> in recent times&#8230;&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này cung cấp bằng chứng thống kê về việc <strong>số lượng luật đang tăng lên</strong> (<em>&#8220;Growth in laws&#8221;</em>), với số lượng đạo luật và trang lập pháp tăng gấp đôi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>18. (Đoạn 5)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>vi A negative regard for lawyers</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) &#8220;However, despite their important role in developing the rules, <strong>lawyers are not universally admired</strong>. Anti-lawyer jokes have a long history going back to the ancient Greeks.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn văn thảo luận về sự thiếu ngưỡng mộ và các câu chuyện cười (<em>jokes</em>) chống lại luật sư, cho thấy thái độ tiêu cực đối với họ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>19. (Đoạn 6)</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li>\n<p><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>ii Reasons why it is unfair to criticise lawyers</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) &#8220;But, in general, it is <strong>no more just to say that lawyers are bad</strong> because they make a living from people’s problems than it is to make the same accusation in respect of nurses or IT consultants.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn này cung cấp các lý do (ví dụ: công việc công ích, nhu cầu soạn thảo tài liệu) để lập luận rằng việc chỉ trích luật sư là không công bằng (&#8220;unfair to criticise&#8221;).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('95877d0c-cc28-45cf-95ac-3c6d98b21d48', '39e1f6ca-cafc-48b9-99d7-e814b1416aea', 'fillup', 'Questions 8–13', '<p><span class="citation-32543 citation-end-32543">Complete the notes below.<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="3"><!----></sup></span></p>
<div class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></div>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
<p><span class="citation-32542">Choose </span><strong data-path-to-node="16" data-index-in-node="7"><span class="citation-32542">ONE WORD ONLY</span></strong><span class="citation-32542 citation-end-32542"> from the passage for each answer.<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="4"><!----></sup></span></p>
<div class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></div>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
<p><span class="citation-32541 citation-end-32541">Write your answers in <sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="5"><!----></sup></span>boxes 8–13 on your answer sheet.</p>
<table style="border-collapse: collapse; width: 99.9592%; height: 2px; border-spacing: 2px; border: 2px solid #000000;" border="1"><colgroup><col style="width: 99.8776%;"></colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td style="border-width: 2px; padding: 2px; border-color: #000000;">
<p style="text-align: center;" data-path-to-node="18,0"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong data-path-to-node="18,0" data-index-in-node="0">Archaeological findings on Obi</strong></span></p>
<p id="p-rc_4f1578aca6ced318-326" data-path-to-node="18,1"><span class="citation-32539 citation-32540">Excavations of rock shelters inside {caves}</span><span class="citation-32539 citation-32540 citation-end-32540"> near the village of Kelo revealed:<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="6"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-32539 citation-end-32539"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="7"><!----></sup></span></p>
<p class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></p>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="18,2">
<li>
<p id="p-rc_4f1578aca6ced318-327" data-path-to-node="18,2,0,0"><span class="citation-32537 citation-32538 citation-end-32538">axes from around 14,000 years ago, probably used to make canoes<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="8"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-32537 citation-end-32537"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="9"><!----></sup></span></p>
<p class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></p>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
</li>
<li>
<p id="p-rc_4f1578aca6ced318-328" data-path-to-node="18,2,1,0"><span class="citation-32535 citation-32536">axes made out of {stone}</span><span class="citation-32535 citation-32536 citation-end-32536"> , dating from around 11,700 years ago<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="10"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-32535 citation-end-32535"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="11"><!----></sup></span></p>
<p class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></p>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
</li>
<li>
<p id="p-rc_4f1578aca6ced318-329" data-path-to-node="18,2,2,0"><span class="citation-32533 citation-32534 citation-end-32534">{bones} of an animal: evidence of what<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="12"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-32533 citation-end-32533"> ancient islanders ate<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="13"><!----></sup></span></p>
<p class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></p>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
</li>
<li>
<p id="p-rc_4f1578aca6ced318-330" data-path-to-node="18,2,3,0"><span class="citation-32532 citation-end-32532">evidence of travel between islands:<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="14"><!----></sup></span></p>
<p class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></p>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
<ul data-path-to-node="18,2,3,1">
<li>
<p id="p-rc_4f1578aca6ced318-331" data-path-to-node="18,2,3,1,0,0"><span class="citation-32531 citation-end-32531">obsidian: a material that is no<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="15"><!----></sup></span>t found naturally on Obi</p>
<p class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></p>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="18,2,3,1,1,0">{beads} which resembled ones found on other islands.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-path-to-node="18,3">It is thought that from 8,000 years ago, Obi islanders:</p>
<ul data-path-to-node="18,4">
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="18,4,0,0">may have switched from hunting to fishing</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="18,4,1,0">had {pottery} as well as items made out of metal</p>
</li>
<li>
<p data-path-to-node="18,4,2,0">probably took part in the production and sale of {spices} .</p>
</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p> </p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. caves — {Excavations of rock shelters inside caves near the village of Kelo revealed}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 3):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"Just inland from the village of Kelo... Shipton and his colleagues found <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">two caves containing prehistoric rock shelters</strong> that were suitable for excavation.\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các mái đá tiền sử (rock shelters) được tìm thấy nằm bên trong hai hang động (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"90\">caves</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. stone — {axes made out of stone, dating from around 11,700 years ago}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"Roughly 11,700 years ago... the first <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"59\">axes crafted from stone</strong> rather than sea shells appear...\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Vào mốc thời gian khoảng 11.700 năm trước, những chiếc rìu làm bằng đá (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"84\">stone</strong>) bắt đầu xuất hiện để thay thế cho rìu vỏ sò.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. bones — {bones of an animal: evidence of what ancient islanders ate}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"Judging by the <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"36\">bones</strong> which the researchers unearthed in the Kelo caves, <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"93\">people living there mainly hunted the Rothschild''s cuscus</strong>...\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc tìm thấy xương (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"33\">bones</strong>) của loài thú cuscus là bằng chứng cho thấy đây là thức ăn chính (chúng bị săn bắn để ăn) của cư dân cổ đại trên đảo.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. beads — {beads which resembled ones found on other islands}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 7):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"It also revealed particular types of <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">beads</strong>, <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">similar to those previously found on islands in southern Wallacea</strong>.\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Similar to\" đồng nghĩa với \"resembled\" (trông giống với/tương tự). Những hạt chuỗi (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"97\">beads</strong>) được tìm thấy giống hệt với những loại ở các hòn đảo khác.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. pottery — {had pottery as well as items made out of metal}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 9):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"...until about 1,000 years ago, when they were re-occupied by people who owned <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"100\">pottery</strong> as well as items made out of <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"137\">gold and silver</strong>.\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Người dân quay lại đây vào khoảng 1.000 năm trước sở hữu đồ gốm (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"77\">pottery</strong>) và các vật dụng bằng vàng, bạc (vàng và bạc chính là kim loại - metal).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. spices — {probably took part in the production and sale of spices}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 9):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"...final phase of occupation also saw the Kelo shelters used by people involved in the historic <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"117\">trade in spices</strong>...\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Trade\" (buôn bán/giao thương) tương ứng với cụm \"production and sale\" (sản xuất và bán). Cư dân giai đoạn này tham gia vào việc buôn bán gia vị (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"158\">spices</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('2e8a1304-5a91-4ca2-a711-9ca84d2307e9', '72b933da-2f0a-46b1-9251-ff875c987079', 'fillup', 'Questions 1–10', '<p data-start="92" data-end="184">Write <strong data-start="125" data-end="167">NO MORE THAN ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<h3 data-section-id="1kac3yy" data-start="186" data-end="214">Fearnley Sports Center</h3>
<p data-start="215" data-end="245"><strong data-start="215" data-end="245">Lifeguard Application Form</strong></p>
<p data-start="247" data-end="267"><strong data-start="247" data-end="267">Personal details</strong></p>
<p data-start="269" data-end="292"><strong data-start="269" data-end="278">Name: </strong>Peter Smith</p>
<p data-start="294" data-end="350"><strong data-start="294" data-end="311">Home address: </strong>130 South Main Street, Lake {Elsinore}</p>
<p data-start="352" data-end="396"><strong data-start="352" data-end="371">Contact number: </strong>{077896245} (cell phone)</p>
<p data-start="398" data-end="421"><strong data-start="398" data-end="421">Present occupation:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="422" data-end="535">
<li data-section-id="a095v2" data-start="422" data-end="467">
<p data-start="424" data-end="467">has temporary job as a part-time {waiter}</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="1rjyow8" data-start="468" data-end="488">
<p data-start="470" data-end="488">is studying<strong> </strong>PE</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="8pgyqo" data-start="489" data-end="535">
<p data-start="491" data-end="535">wants to be a high school {baseball} coach</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-section-id="12f3so4" data-start="542" data-end="560">Qualifications</h3>
<p data-start="562" data-end="607"><strong data-start="562" data-end="580">Already holds: </strong>water safety certificate</p>
<p data-start="609" data-end="646"><strong data-start="609" data-end="636">Certificate expires in: </strong>{October}</p>
<h3 data-section-id="lry4qy" data-start="653" data-end="681">Relevant work experience</h3>
<p><strong data-start="683" data-end="700">Lifeguard at: </strong>the {beach} in Fearnley</p>
<p data-start="730" data-end="774">Additional relevant skills: {diving}</p>
<p data-section-id="qr901a" data-start="781" data-end="802"><strong>Other Information</strong>: is happy to</p>
<ul data-start="804" data-end="876">
<li data-section-id="m8s095" data-start="804" data-end="849">
<p data-start="806" data-end="849">work on <strong>{Saturday} </strong>mornings</p>
</li>
<li data-section-id="14it1z5" data-start="850" data-end="876">
<p data-start="852" data-end="876">start at {six| 6}o’clock</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="883" data-end="952">How did the applicant find out about this job? on the<strong> </strong>{radio}</p>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong>IELTS LISTENING PART 1: FERNLEY SPORTS CENTER JOB APPLICATION</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> Hello, Fernley Sports Center. How can I help you?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> Yes, I’d like to apply for one of the lifeguard jobs you advertised this week.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> Right. We can do that now over the phone. I’ll just need some information from you. Let me get a form. OK, so let’s start with your name.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> Peter Smith.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> OK. Can you let me have your home address?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> It’s 130 South Main Street, Lake<span style=\"background-color: #f4d24a;\"> <strong>(1) </strong><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"40\">Elsinore</strong>.</span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> Okay, I’m new around here. Can you spell that for me?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> Yes, it’s E-L-S-I-N-O-R-E.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> Uh-huh, okay, got that. And your phone number?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> My home number’s 951 674 3124. But it’s best to ring me on my cell phone. That’s<span style=\"background-color: #f4d24a;\"><strong> (2) 077896245.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> Okay. Now, what do you do? Are you still in college or are you working full time?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> I’m in my second year here at Fernley. And this vacation I’ve got a job as a part-time <span style=\"background-color: #f4d24a;\"><strong>(3) waiter.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> Okay. I guess if you’re at Fernley College, you’ll be studying Physical Education. They all seem to do that there.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> That’s right. Then I hope to go on and coach <span style=\"background-color: #f4d24a;\"><strong>(4) </strong><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">baseball</strong> </span>in high school, something like that. I guess it all depends on how I do in my final exams.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> Okay, sounds good to me.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><em data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">(Pause – Questions 5 to 10)</em></p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> Now the next part of the form deals with qualifications. Do you have the water safety certificate? We absolutely insist on that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> Yes, I do.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> So how long will it last before you have to do a refresher course?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> I took it last November, so it will run out in<span style=\"background-color: #f4d24a;\"><strong> (5) October.</strong></span></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> OK, good. Now, what about work experience as a lifeguard?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> Well, I’ve had about four months’ experience.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> Which swimming pool was that at? I need to have details of your employer obviously, so we can get a reference.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> Oh, it was at the <span style=\"background-color: #f4d24a;\"><strong>(6) </strong><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"25\">beach</strong></span> here in Fernley. I can get the number of the person you need to contact.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> Good. And do you have any other additional skills I can put down?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> You can put down <span style=\"background-color: #f4d24a;\"><strong>(7) diving</strong></span>. I’ve done that for a long time now. I’m also keen on rock climbing, but that’s not really relevant here.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> No, okay. And I need to ask when you would prefer to work. You can choose either <strong><span style=\"background-color: #f4d24a;\">(8) Saturday</span> </strong>mornings or anytime Monday to Friday. We’ve got enough people on Sundays at the moment.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> Well, not Monday to Friday, because I’m at the restaurant weekday evenings.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> Okay. We open at<span style=\"background-color: #f4d24a;\"><strong> (9) six.</strong></span> Could you start that early?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> No, that’s fine. I’d prefer that to working late. </p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> Okay. Now I need to speak to the committee who run the sports center here, but you should hear back from us pretty soon and then they’ll probably arrange an interview.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"36\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"36\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> Thanks very much.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"37\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> Great. Now before you go, I’d just like to ask you how you found out about our advertisement. We always ask this. Was it from the newspaper or the <span style=\"background-color: #f4d24a;\"><strong>(10) radio</strong></span>?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"38\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"38\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Peter:</strong> I heard the advertisement this morning when I was driving into college. I don’t usually read the local paper. </p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"39\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"39\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Manager:</strong> Alright, thanks. Well, that’s all. Hope to see you soon.</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('5c6535c5-be92-489c-83ed-db4764d572f3', '53565693-8342-4eab-8fb9-b732f264e9c8', 'matrix', 'Questions 14–17', '', '<p><span class="citation-36778 citation-36779 citation-36780 citation-36781 citation-36782">Write the correct letter, </span><strong data-path-to-node="5" data-index-in-node="26"><span class="citation-36778 citation-36779 citation-36780 citation-36781 citation-36782">A–H</span></strong><span class="citation-36778 citation-36779 citation-36780 citation-36781 citation-36782 citation-end-36782">, in boxes 14–17 on your answer sheet.</span></p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "reference to the need to ensure that inhabitants of wetland regions continue to benefit from them", "correctCategoryLetter": "G"}, {"itemText": "the proportion of wetlands which have already been lost", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "reference to the idea that people are beginning to appreciate the value of wetlands", "correctCategoryLetter": "H"}, {"itemText": "mention of the cultural significance of wetlands", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "H", "categoryLetter": "H"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. reference to the need to ensure that inhabitants of wetland regions continue to benefit from them — {G}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">\"...we recognise there’s a <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">need to provide an income for local people</strong>... ''The idea is that people in a developing country will only protect wetlands if they <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"168\">value and profit from them</strong>,'' says McCartney.\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Inhabitants of wetland regions\" chính là người dân địa phương (local people / people in a developing country). Việc đảm bảo họ tiếp tục có thu nhập (provide an income) và có lợi nhuận (profit from them) tương ứng hoàn toàn với cụm từ \"continue to benefit from them\".</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. the proportion of wetlands which have already been lost — {A}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">\"...according to the World Wide Fund for Nature (WWFN), <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"67\">half of the world''s wetlands have disappeared since 1990</strong>...\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Half\" (một nửa / 50%) chính là tỷ lệ/tỷ trọng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">the proportion</strong>). Bài viết nêu rõ một nửa diện tích đất ngập nước trên thế giới đã biến mất (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"152\">disappeared / been lost</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. reference to the idea that people are beginning to appreciate the value of wetlands — {H}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">\"''<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"13\">Awareness of the importance of wetlands is growing</strong>,'' he says... ''but my impression is that <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"104\">things are slowly changing</strong>.''\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Awareness... is growing\" (nhận thức đang tăng lên) đồng nghĩa với việc mọi người đang bắt đầu (beginning to). \"Appreciate the value\" (trân trọng giá trị) tương ứng với cụm \"importance of wetlands\".</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. mention of the cultural significance of wetlands — {B}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">\"...Consequently, they are of <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"41\">considerable religious, historical and archaeological value</strong> to many communities around the world.\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các giá trị về mặt tôn giáo (religious), lịch sử (historical) và khảo cổ (archaeological) chính là những biểu hiện cụ thể cấu thành nên ý nghĩa về mặt văn hóa (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"172\">cultural significance</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('881b1602-45e2-4e4f-aa5d-5f486fb87180', '62865638-b9a5-4641-85c9-90076e4a96e7', 'matrix', 'Questions 20-23', NULL, '<p>Look at the following statements (Questions 20-23) and the list of researchers below.</p>
<p>Choose each statement with the correct researcher, <strong>A</strong>, <strong>B </strong>or <strong>C</strong>.</p>
<p><strong>NB </strong>You may use any letter more than once.</p>
', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": "List of researchers", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "It takes a tremendous number of spiders to make a small amount of silk.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "Scientists want to use the qualities of spider silk for medical purposes.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "Scientists are making some progress in their efforts to manufacture spider silk.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Spider silk compares favourably to materials known for their strength.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "Simon Peers", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "Nicholas Godley", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "Todd Blackledge", "categoryLetter": "C"}]}', '[{"content": "<p>20.  It takes a tremendous number of spiders to make a small amount of silk.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>B (Nicholas Godley)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) Godley nói: “<strong>Fourteen thousand spiders yield about an ounce of silk</strong>… The numbers are overwhelming.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Godley là người đưa ra con số định lượng về số lượng nhện khổng lồ cần thiết cho một lượng tơ nhỏ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>21.  Scientists want to use the qualities of spider silk for medical purposes.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>A (Simon Peers)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) Peers nói: “there’s scientific research going on all over the world right now trying to replicate the tensile properties of spider silk to apply it to all sorts of areas in <strong>medicine</strong> and industry…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Peers chỉ ra mục đích y tế (medicine) là một lĩnh vực ứng dụng mà các nhà khoa học đang hướng tới.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>22. Scientists are making some progress in their efforts to manufacture spider silk.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>C (Todd Blackledge)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) Todd Blackledge nói: “Every year <strong>we’re getting closer and closer to being able to mass-produce it</strong>, but we’re not there yet.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Blackledge thừa nhận có tiến bộ (<em>“getting closer and closer”</em>) trong việc sản xuất hàng loạt tơ nhện.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>23.Spider silk compares favourably to materials known for their strength.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"26\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>A (Simon Peers)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) Simon Peers nói: “Spider silk is very elastic and strong <strong>compared with steel or Kevlar</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Peers là người so sánh tơ nhện với các vật liệu bền khác như thép và Kevlar.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a7aee886-9d77-48e5-a561-3cc9fc543529', '53565693-8342-4eab-8fb9-b732f264e9c8', 'fillup', 'Questions 18–22', '<p><span class="citation-36758 citation-36759 citation-end-36759">Complete the sentences below.<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="34"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-36758 citation-end-36758"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="35"><!----></sup></span></p>
<div class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></div>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
<p><span class="citation-36756 citation-36757">Choose </span><strong data-path-to-node="10" data-index-in-node="7"><span class="citation-36756 citation-36757 citation-end-36757">ONE WOR<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="36"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-36756">D ONLY</span></strong><span class="citation-36756 citation-end-36756"> from the passage for each answer.<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="37"><!----></sup></span></p>
<div class="source-inline-chip-container ng-star-inserted"><!----><!----></div>
<p><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----><!----></p>
<p><span class="citation-36755 citation-end-36755">Write your answers in boxes 18–22 on your answer s<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="38"><!----></sup></span>heet.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Peatlands which have been drained begin to release {carbon} instead of storing it.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Once peatland areas have been cleared, {fires} are more likely <span class="citation-36753 citation-36754 citation-end-36754">to occur.<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="39"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-36753 citation-end-36753"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="40"><!----></sup></span></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><span class="citation-36751 citation-36752 citation-end-36752">Clearing peatland forests to make way for oil palm plantations destroys the {biodiversity}} of the local environment.<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="41"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-36751 citation-end-36751"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="42"><!----></sup></span></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><span class="citation-36749 citation-36750 citation-end-36750">Water is drained out of peatlands through the {ditches} which are created by logging companies.<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="43"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-36749 citation-end-36749"><sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="44"><!----></sup></span></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><span class="citation-36747 citation-36748 citation-end-36748">Draining peatlands leads to {subsidence}: a serious problem which can eventually<sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="45"><!----></sup></span><span class="citation-36747 citation-end-36747"> result <sup class="superscript" data-turn-source-index="46"><!----></sup></span>in coastal flooding and land loss.</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. carbon — {Peatlands which have been drained begin to release carbon instead of storing it.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn D):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"When peatlands are drained for cultivation, they become <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"77\">net carbon emitters</strong> instead of <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"108\">active carbon stores</strong>...\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Net carbon emitters\" (nơi phát thải các-bon) tương ứng với cụm \"release carbon\". \"Active carbon stores\" (nơi lưu trữ các-bon) tương ứng với \"storing it\". Khi bị thoát nước, đất than bùn sẽ giải phóng các-bon (<strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"222\">carbon</strong>) thay vì tích trữ nó.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. fires — {Once peatland areas have been cleared, fires are more likely to occur.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn D):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"The clearance of peatlands for planting also <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"66\">increases the risk of forest fires</strong>...\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> \"Increases the risk of...\" (làm tăng nguy cơ...) đồng nghĩa với cụm \"are more likely to occur\" (có nhiều khả năng xảy ra hơn). Sự cố dễ xảy ra hơn ở đây là các vụ hỏa hoạn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"185\">fires</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. biodiversity — {Clearing peatland forests to make way for oil palm plantations destroys the biodiversity of the local environment.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn D):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"''We’re seeing huge peatland forests with <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"62\">extremely high biodiversity value being lost</strong> for a few decades of <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"128\">oil palm revenues</strong>,'' says Silvius.\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc phá rừng than bùn để lấy doanh thu từ cây dầu cọ (oil palm plantations) sẽ làm mất đi/phá hủy giá trị đa dạng sinh học (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"137\">biodiversity</strong>) của môi trường nơi đó.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. ditches — {Water is drained out of peatlands through the ditches which are created by logging companies.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn E):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"The damage starts when <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"44\">logging companies</strong> arrive to clear the trees. <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">They dig ditches to enter the peat swamps</strong>... These are then <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"149\">used to drain water out of the peatlands</strong>...\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các công ty khai thác gỗ (logging companies) đào các con mương (<strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">ditches</strong>) để vào đầm lầy, và sau đó chính những con mương này được sử dụng để thoát nước ra khỏi đất than bùn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">22. subsidence — {Draining peatlands leads to subsidence: a serious problem which can eventually result in coastal flooding and land loss.}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn E):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">\"...in a process known as <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"46\">subsidence</strong>... ''In the tropics, <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"77\">peat subsides</strong> at about four centimetres a year, so within half a century, very large landscapes... <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"176\">will become flooded</strong>... Some provinces <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"214\">will lose 40 per cent of their landmass</strong>.''\"</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Quá trình thoát nước làm cho chất rắn di chuyển xuống dưới, gọi là hiện tượng sụt lún (<strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">subsidence</strong>). Hậu quả nghiêm trọng của nó là gây ngập lụt (flooding) và mất đất (lose landmass/land loss).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('ecc1b55a-afa8-468a-88aa-1c21e35535f6', '041a2320-11a2-4d8f-b9f8-b4bcf8e88477', 'matching', 'Questions 32–35', '', '<p data-start="827" data-end="888">Complete the summary using the list of words, <strong data-start="873" data-end="880">A–I</strong>, below.</p>
<p data-start="890" data-end="965">Write the correct letter, <strong data-start="916" data-end="923">A–I</strong></p>', 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p data-section-id=\"1dr7tvv\" data-start=\"967\" data-end=\"1020\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>Disappearing languages in today''s globalised world</strong></span></p>\n<p data-start=\"1022\" data-end=\"1255\">If everybody spoke the same language, whether Spanish, English or Chinese, there would certainly be less chance of {misunderstandings} between people. But would society suffer if there were one global language? Experts agree that it would.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1257\" data-end=\"1547\">According to Marcus Colchester, people''s use of native languages is key to how they relate to their {surroundings}. He also emphasises the link between indigenous people''s traditional {occupations} and the recounting of the myths and folk tales which are integral to their sense of identity.</p>\n<p data-start=\"1549\" data-end=\"1734\">Louisa Maffi describes how loss of language diversity leads to a loss of collective human knowledge, so there could be fewer {ideas} available to help solve problems in the world.</p>", "optionsTitle": "List of Words", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A ideas"}, {"optionText": "B speakers"}, {"optionText": "C connections"}, {"optionText": "D surroundings"}, {"optionText": "E families"}, {"optionText": "F occupations"}, {"optionText": "G relationship"}, {"optionText": "H words"}, {"optionText": "I misunderstandings"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. I (misunderstandings)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“It might bring us closer together, and we would certainly be more likely to make our ideas comprehensible.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nếu tất cả mọi người nói cùng một ngôn ngữ, chúng ta sẽ dễ dàng làm cho ý tưởng của mình trở nên dễ hiểu hơn (<em data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"122\">make our ideas comprehensible</em>). Điều này đồng nghĩa với việc sẽ giảm thiểu được khả năng xảy ra sự hiểu lầm giữa người với người (<strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"252\">less chance of misunderstandings</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. D (surroundings)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“People''s understanding of themselves, and their relationship with their environment are all framed in terms of concepts expressed in their own languages...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Từ khóa \"environment\" (môi trường sống xung quanh) trong bài đọc được thay thế bằng từ đồng nghĩa trong bảng từ là <strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"127\">surroundings</strong> (vùng không gian xung quanh).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. F (occupations)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Day-to-day activities such as hunting, fishing and farming are directly connected to spirits and mythic beings whose stories make these people who they are.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các hoạt động hằng ngày được bài đọc liệt kê bao gồm săn bắn, đánh cá và làm ruộng (<em data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"96\">hunting, fishing and farming</em>). Tất cả những hoạt động này được khái quát hóa bằng danh từ chỉ nghề nghiệp, công việc mưu sinh (<strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"223\">occupations</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. A (ideas)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"23\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“As we lose each language, we lose a repository of knowledge, values and beliefs that, in many cases, provide alternative solutions to human problems; we diminish that pool of creativity and inventiveness...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc mất đi một ngôn ngữ làm mất đi kho tàng tri thức và sự sáng tạo, khiến con người có ít các giải pháp (<em data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"119\">solutions</em>), phương án hoặc ý tưởng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"155\">ideas</strong>) hơn để giải quyết các vấn đề toàn cầu.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('76f21ed7-d1bd-461d-8048-56ad0bec5f62', 'c5510d0d-d693-46b0-bcfc-6a770e29343d', 'matrix', 'Questions 31-39', '', '<p data-path-to-node="2">Which paragraph contains the following information?</p>
<p data-path-to-node="3">Write the correct letter, <strong>A–H</strong>, in boxes 31–39 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'choose_a_title', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "the areas of study that help us understand risk", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "reference to key actions that might benefit the world", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "examples of statistical predictions that the majority of the public react to in the same way", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "the variety of contexts in which risk occurs", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "mention of a habit that has been proved to be very risky", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "reference to market forces motivating change", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "the writer''s current attitude towards risk", "correctCategoryLetter": "H"}, {"itemText": "a reason why some individuals avoid making a career change", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "how some people over-react to information about risk", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "H", "categoryLetter": "H"}]}', '[{"content": "<ul>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. the areas of study that help us understand risk — {B}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3,0,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…those risks can be clarified, at least in part, by <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"66\">science, technology or mathematics</strong>…” (Đoạn B)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các lĩnh vực nghiên cứu (areas of study) giúp làm rõ rủi ro bao gồm khoa học, công nghệ và toán học.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. reference to key actions that might benefit the world — {F}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…clarifying which critical decision would have the <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">highest pay-offs for the environment</strong>.” (Đoạn F)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các hành động then chốt (key actions/critical decisions) mang lại lợi ích lớn nhất cho môi trường (thế giới).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. examples of statistical predictions that the majority of the public react to in the same way — {C}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3,2,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,2,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Hearing the <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">prediction of 60% chance of rain</strong>… or… <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"66\">flu shot</strong>, <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">most people understand the right responses</strong>…” (Đoạn C)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,2,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Ví dụ về dự báo thời tiết hoặc tiêm chủng mà đa số mọi người đều có phản ứng đúng đắn giống nhau.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,3,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,3,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. the variety of contexts in which risk occurs — {A}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3,3,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,3,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,3,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Risks arise in <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,3,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"27\">sports, in business, in personal relationships… laboratory… political calculations, everywhere</strong>.” (Đoạn A)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,3,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,3,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Liệt kê hàng loạt các bối cảnh (contexts) khác nhau mà rủi ro xuất hiện, từ thể thao đến chính trị.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,4,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,4,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. mention of a habit that has been proved to be very risky — {B}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3,4,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,4,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,4,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…even when the evidence of high risk is clear – about <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,4,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"68\">smoking</strong>, for instance…” (Đoạn B)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,4,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,4,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thói quen hút thuốc được đưa ra làm ví dụ điển hình cho một hành vi cực kỳ rủi ro đã được chứng minh.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,5,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,5,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. reference to market forces motivating change — {E}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3,5,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,5,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,5,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…transformed by a <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,5,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"32\">flood of low-cost memory chips from Japan</strong>…” (Đoạn E)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,5,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,5,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sự xuất hiện của chip giá rẻ từ Nhật Bản là một áp lực thị trường (market forces) buộc Intel phải thay đổi chiến lược.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,6,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,6,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. the writer’s current attitude towards risk — {H}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3,6,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,6,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,6,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Nevertheless, I confess to being an <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,6,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"48\">optimist</strong>.” (Đoạn H)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,6,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,6,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả trực tiếp bày tỏ thái độ lạc quan (optimist) của mình ở đoạn cuối bài.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,7,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,7,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. a reason why some individuals avoid making a career change — {D}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3,7,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,7,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,7,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…won’t even risk pursuing an exciting job, if the current job… remains <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,7,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"87\">comfortable</strong>.” (Đoạn D)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,7,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,7,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Lý do mọi người ngại đổi việc là vì công việc hiện tại vẫn đang ở trong “vùng an toàn/thoải mái” (comfortable).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,8,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,8,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. how some people over-react to information about risk — {C}</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3,8,1\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,8,1,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,8,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…some, <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,8,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"21\">fearfully but irrationally, go to the extreme and stay at home and avoid all contact</strong>…” (Đoạn C)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,8,1,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,8,1,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Mô tả những phản ứng thái quá (over-react), cực đoan và phi lý trí của một số người khi nghe về rủi ro.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('dd866412-e188-4c75-a009-81f90ec00755', '6734b872-a71b-414c-b6ff-9dae25445d03', 'radio', 'Questions 18–20', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The volunteers in Giovanni Battista Grassi''s research came from all parts of Italy."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Experiments in Italy proved that it was possible to remain healthy despite being in malarial zones."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "In the early twentieth century, quinine was successfully administered to all inhabitants of vulnerable regions."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 18: The volunteers in Giovanni Battista Grassi’s research came from all parts of Italy.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> NOT GIVEN</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…Grassi was able to make the direct link between the insects and the disease… healthy human volunteers…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nhắc đến việc có các tình nguyện viên tham gia, nhưng không nêu rõ họ đến từ khắp nơi trên nước Ý hay chỉ ở một vùng nhất định.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 19: Experiments in Italy proved that it was possible to remain healthy despite being in malarial zones.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> TRUE</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…extraordinary series of experiments in Italy, where healthy people were introduced into malarial zones but kept free of mosquito bites – and <strong data-path-to-node=\"17,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"156\">remained well</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thí nghiệm chứng minh nếu không bị muỗi đốt, con người vẫn khỏe mạnh dù ở trong vùng có dịch.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 20: In the early twentieth century, quinine was successfully administered to all inhabitants of vulnerable regions.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> FALSE</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…peasants were often suspicious… and doctors were frequently met with hostility and <strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"100\">stubborn refusal</strong> to accept the treatment offered.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Mặc dù kế hoạch là phát quinine cho tất cả mọi người, nhưng thực tế nhiều người dân đã từ chối quyết liệt, nên không thể nói là “tất cả cư dân” đều đã uống thuốc thành công.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('87e97db6-ea28-493c-93be-c0d01af6bcfd', '749e667f-cadb-4923-bbd9-a1eef3ca95bc', 'fillup', ' Questions 1–7', '<p style="text-align: left;">Complete the notes below. Write ONE WORD ONLY from the passage for each answers.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>CHINESE SILK</strong></p>
<p><strong>Early Uses</strong></p>
<p><em>Clothing</em></p>
<p>– at first, silk only available to Chinese of high rank</p>
<p>– emperor wore {white} silk indoors</p>
<p><em>In industry</em></p>
<p>– silk items included parts of musical instruments, fishing strings and {paper}</p>
<p><em>Currency</em></p>
<p>– silk was used as payment of {taxes} as well as for wages and rewards</p>
<p>– silk replaced {gold} as a unit of value</p>
<p>– silk soon used as payment in {foreign} trade</p>
<p><strong>Evidence of silk trade</strong></p>
<p><em>1070 BC, Egypt:</em></p>
<p>– hair of a {mummy} contained silk</p>
<p><em>2nd century BC, Persia and Mesopotamia:</em></p>
<p>– gifts of silk were presented by Chinese ambassadors</p>
<p><em>1015 AD, north-west China:</em></p>
<p>– silk objects were hidden inside {caves}</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>1. Early Uses: Clothing – emperor wore white silk indoors.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>white</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 2) “Within the palace, the emperor is believed to have worn a robe of <strong>white</strong> silk…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Hoàng đế mặc áo choàng lụa trắng khi ở bên trong cung điện.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>2. In industry – Silk items included parts of musical instruments, fishing strings and paper.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>paper</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) “It was used in the production of musical instruments, as string for fishing, and even as the world’s first luxury <strong>paper</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Lụa được dùng làm giấy (paper), ngoài ra còn làm dây đàn và dây câu cá.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>3. Currency – silk was used as payment of taxes as well as for wages and rewards.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>taxes</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) “Farmers paid their <strong>taxes</strong> in grain and silk, and silk was used to pay civil servants and to reward subjects for outstanding services.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Nông dân dùng lụa để đóng thuế (taxes).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>4. Currency – silk replaced gold as a unit of value.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>gold</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) “Values were calculated in lengths of silk as they had previously been calculated in weight of <strong>gold</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Giá trị được tính bằng lụa, thay thế cho đơn vị tính bằng vàng trước đó.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>5. Currency – silk soon used as payment in foreign trade.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>foreign</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 4) “Before long, silk became a currency used in trade with <strong>foreign</strong> countries…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Lụa sớm trở thành đơn vị tiền tệ trong thương mại với các nước ngoài.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>6. Evidence of silk trade: 1070 BC, Egypt: hair of a mummy contained silk.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>mummy</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “An Egyptian <strong>mummy</strong> with a silk thread in her hair, dating from 1070 BC, has been discovered…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Sợi tơ lụa được tìm thấy trong tóc của một xác ướp (mummy) Ai Cập.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>7. Evidence of silk trade: 1015 AD, north-west China: silk objects were hidden inside caves.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"17\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>caves</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 5) “…Buddhist monks… had sealed more than ten thousand manuscripts and silk paintings, silk banners and textiles in <strong>caves</strong> near Dunhuang…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Các đồ vật bằng lụa và bản thảo đã được phong kín trong các hang động (caves).</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('1d9307b1-27b2-4895-9706-c904b553a21d', '749e667f-cadb-4923-bbd9-a1eef3ca95bc', 'radio', 'Questions 8–13', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Their first sight of silk created fear among Roman soldiers."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The quality of Chinese silk imported by the early Romans varied widely."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The Byzantine emperor first acquired silkworm eggs from the Chinese emperor."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The price of high-grade Chinese silk fell due to competition from Middle-Eastern producers."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Silk was produced in the Middle East several centuries before it was produced in Europe."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Global silk production has declined in recent years."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>8. Their first sight of silk created fear among Roman soldiers.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) “…at an important battle near the Euphrates River in 53 BC, the Roman soldiers were <strong>so startled by the bright silken banners of the enemy that they fled in panic</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Lính La Mã kinh ngạc (<em>startled</em>) và hoảng loạn (<em>fled in panic</em>) khi nhìn thấy cờ lụa sáng màu của kẻ thù, điều này cho thấy sự sợ hãi.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>9. The quality of Chinese silk imported by the early Romans varied widely.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"23\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) Văn bản chỉ nói lụa Trung Quốc được giới nhà giàu và quý tộc La Mã mặc (<em>“widely worn by the rich and noble families of Rome”</em>), <strong>không có thông tin</strong> về sự đa dạng về chất lượng (quality) của lụa nhập khẩu.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>10. The Byzantine emperor first acquired silkworm eggs from the Chinese emperor.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"25\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 7) “Records indicate that <strong>two monks</strong> from Constantinople… appeared at their emperor’s court with silkworm eggs <strong>which they had obtained secretly</strong>, and hidden in their hollow bamboo walking sticks.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Trứng tằm được mang về một cách bí mật (<em>obtained secretly</em>) bởi hai nhà sư (<em>two monks</em>), chứ không phải do hoàng đế Trung Quốc tặng.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>11. The price of high-grade Chinese silk fell due to competition from Middle-Eastern producers.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"27\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 7) “This allowed a silk industry to be established, <strong>undercutting the market for ordinary-grade Chinese silk</strong>. However, <strong>high quality silk textiles</strong>… <strong>continued to achieve high prices</strong> in the West…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Cạnh tranh chỉ làm giảm giá lụa loại thường (<em>ordinary-grade</em>), còn lụa loại cao cấp (<em>high quality</em>) vẫn giữ giá cao (<em>continued to achieve high prices</em>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>12. Silk was produced in the Middle East several centuries before it was produced in Europe.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>TRUE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 7) Lụa bắt đầu được sản xuất ở Trung Đông (<em>Middle East</em>) khoảng <strong>550 AD</strong>; nhưng mãi đến <strong>thế kỷ 13</strong> (<em>13th century</em>), Ý (Europe) mới bắt đầu sản xuất.</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> 550 AD là nhiều thế kỷ trước thế kỷ 13.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>13. Global silk production has declined in recent years.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>FALSE</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 8) “<strong>World silk production has approximately doubled during the last 30 years</strong> in spite of manmade fibres replacing certain uses of silk.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Sản lượng lụa toàn cầu đã <strong>tăng gấp đôi</strong> (<em>doubled</em>) trong 30 năm qua.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('fe09d260-44d7-4d91-ba69-10fb0708d035', '78d5c28d-afcb-4180-beb8-a846f79abc5a', 'radio', ' Questions 27–31', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>YES </strong>if the statement agrees with the claims of the writer, choose <strong>NO </strong>if the statement contradicts the claims of the writer, or <strong>NOT GIVEN</strong> if it is impossible to say what the writer thinks about this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Young people are easily persuaded by surveys that listening to music is beneficial."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Different studies share the same conclusions about the desirability of working in silence."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Some doctors recommend wearing headphones to lower blood pressure."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Nathaniel Baldwin was a respected government researcher."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The effect of the invention of headphones is comparable to the effect of the invention of the writing."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27. Young people are easily persuaded by surveys that listening to music is beneficial.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> NOT GIVEN</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “In survey after survey, people report with confidence that music makes them happier, better at concentrating, and more productive.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nói rằng người trẻ tham gia khảo sát và tự báo cáo rằng âm nhạc có lợi cho họ. Không có thông tin nào nói rằng họ bị “thuyết phục” bởi các khảo sát đó.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28. Different studies share the same conclusions about the desirability of working in silence.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> YES</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Scientists do not share this belief… ‘As silence has the best overall performance, it would still be advisable that people work in silence,’ another reporter dryly concluded.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các nhà khoa học và các nghiên cứu (nghiên cứu Đài Loan, nghiên cứu về pop song) đều thống nhất rằng làm việc trong im lặng đem lại hiệu quả tốt nhất.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29. Some doctors recommend wearing headphones to lower blood pressure.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> NOT GIVEN</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…evidence that music relaxes our muscles… and may even moderately reduce blood pressure…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc có nhắc đến bằng chứng cho thấy âm nhạc có thể giúp giảm huyết áp, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"93\">không đề cập</strong> đến việc có “bác sĩ” nào đưa ra lời khuyên đeo tai nghe để làm việc này hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30. Nathaniel Baldwin was a respected government researcher.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> NO</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…an eccentric inventor and repairman named Nathaniel Baldwin… he had built, in his kitchen, a new kind of headset…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nathaniel Baldwin được mô tả là một “nhà phát minh và thợ sửa chữa lập dị” làm việc tại bếp nhà mình, không phải là một “nhà nghiên cứu chính phủ đáng kính”.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. The effect of the invention of headphones is comparable to the effect of the invention of writing.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> YES</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…headphones have done what writing and literacy did for language – they made music private.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả trực tiếp so sánh tác động của tai nghe đối với âm nhạc cũng giống như tác động của chữ viết đối với ngôn ngữ: cả hai đều biến những thứ mang tính cộng đồng thành riêng tư.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('addaaa4d-179f-41c1-bc66-bb6f1ee8f814', '78d5c28d-afcb-4180-beb8-a846f79abc5a', 'radio', 'Questions 32–36', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answer.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "The work is mentally demanding."}, {"content": "It provides employment for younger workers."}, {"content": "It is a small part of a country’s economy."}, {"content": "Workers have to live in urban centres."}], "question": "What does the writer suggest about a service economy?"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "emphasizing the diversity of musical forms."}, {"content": "expressing his frustration with the limited archaeological evidence uncovered."}, {"content": "lending support to the view that music has been important in human history."}, {"content": "creating a geographical map of the evolution of music."}], "question": "When the writer mentions the historical evidence for early music he is"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "It has caused a reduction in the number of people who listen to music."}, {"content": "It has increased people’s participation in music events."}, {"content": "It has reduced the global variation of music styles."}, {"content": "It has changed the traditional role of music in society."}], "question": "What does the writer say about the social effects of listening to music through headphones?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "Americans are unique in their desire for personal independence."}, {"content": "Personal independence is something that can be purchased."}, {"content": "Striving for personal independence is a recent phenomenon."}, {"content": "Personal independence destroys social connections."}], "question": "What does the writer say about personal independence?"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "to support the writer’s own view"}, {"content": "to draw attention to an authoritative book about music"}, {"content": "to raise awareness of people’s loss of listening skills"}, {"content": "to illustrate how music brings people closer to each other"}], "question": "Why does the writer quote Jonah Lehrer in the last paragraph?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. What does the writer suggest about a service economy?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> The work is mentally demanding.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…moved… to a service economy, with an emphasis on jobs in offices that require higher levels of concentration, reflection and creativity.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nền kinh tế dịch vụ tập trung vào các công việc văn phòng đòi hỏi sự tập trung, suy ngẫm và sáng tạo cao (đòi hỏi về trí óc).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. When the writer mentions the historical evidence for early music he is</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"20\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> lending support to the view that music has been important in human history.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Music, together with dance, co-evolved biologically and culturally to serve as a technology of social bonding… evidence… dates back to Sumeria, 35,000 years ago…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc đưa ra các bằng chứng lịch sử (ký hiệu nhạc Sumeria, sáo xương) nhằm khẳng định âm nhạc đã luôn là một phần quan trọng và lâu đời trong lịch sử nhân loại.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. What does the writer say about the social effects of listening to music through headphones?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"22\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> It has changed the traditional role of music in society.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…which is a radical departure from music’s social purpose in history… headphones have… made music private.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tai nghe đã làm thay đổi vai trò truyền thống của âm nhạc (từ “chất keo xã hội” gắn kết mọi người thành một trải nghiệm cá nhân, riêng tư).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. What does the writer say about personal independence?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"24\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> Personal independence is something that can be purchased.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…wealth can buy – and modern technology can deliver – personal independence…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả khẳng định sự giàu có (tiền bạc) có thể mua được sự độc lập cá nhân thông qua công nghệ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. Why does the writer quote Jonah Lehrer in the last paragraph?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"26\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> to support the writer’s own view.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “However, with music… ‘The answers have been there all along. We just weren’t listening.’ In a crowded world… a headphone is a small invisible fence around our minds…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả trích dẫn Jonah Lehrer để củng cố quan điểm rằng âm nhạc giúp chúng ta hướng sự chú ý vào bên trong để giải quyết vấn đề sáng tạo.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('419491d6-7248-4d2e-8804-3788baef9816', '78d5c28d-afcb-4180-beb8-a846f79abc5a', 'matching', 'Questions 37–40', NULL, '<p>Complete the summary using the list of words, A-I, below.</p>
', 'matching_features', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "summary", "summaryText": "<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>HEADPHONES AND CITY LIVING</strong></p>\r\n<p>Dr Michael Bull believes that listening to music through headphones has changed the {B relationship} the wearers of headphones have with public spaces. Living in the centre of cities is becoming popular, as people become less keen on living in the {E suburbs}. In densely populated city centres, headphones form {G barriers} that isolate people from fellow citizens and from their environment. Wearers of headphones are treated with {A courtesy} that other people do not receive. This is because if we see someone wearing headphones, we believe they must be occupied in some way and should not be interrupted.</p>", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A courtesy"}, {"optionText": "B relationship"}, {"optionText": "C difficulty"}, {"optionText": "D countryside"}, {"optionText": "E suburbs"}, {"optionText": "F language"}, {"optionText": "G barriers"}, {"optionText": "H obstacles"}, {"optionText": "I disapproval"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 37</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> B relationship</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Dr Michael Bull… has repeatedly made the larger point that personal music devices change how we <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"110\">relate to</strong> public spaces.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trong bài đọc, cụm từ “relate to” (liên quan/tương tác với) được dùng để chỉ mối quan hệ giữa người dùng và không gian công cộng. Do đó, danh từ phù hợp nhất để điền vào chỗ trống là “relationship”.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 38</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> E suburbs</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…more people are moving from the <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">edges of cities</strong> to live in urban centers.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc đề cập đến việc mọi người di chuyển từ vùng “edges of cities” (rìa thành phố) vào trung tâm. Trong danh sách từ cho sẵn, “suburbs” (ngoại ô) là từ đồng nghĩa chính xác nhất với vùng rìa thành phố.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 39</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> G barriers</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Headphones create <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"30\">shields</strong> for wearers, separating them from other people and their surroundings.” và “…a headphone is a small <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"140\">invisible fence</strong> around our minds…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả sử dụng các hình ảnh so sánh như “shields” (tấm khiên) và “invisible fence” (hàng rào vô hình) để nói về chức năng của tai nghe. Từ “barriers” (rào cản) trong danh sách đáp án phản ánh đúng ý nghĩa của việc tạo ra sự ngăn cách này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 40</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> A courtesy</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Headphones have their own rules of <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">good manners</strong>… We assume that people wearing them are busy and we should <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"121\">respect their privacy</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Vì người xung quanh coi việc đeo tai nghe là biểu hiện của sự bận rộn và cần được tôn trọng quyền riêng tư (good manners/respect), nên người đeo tai nghe nhận được sự “courtesy” (sự lịch sự/nhã nhặn) từ người khác.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f5bd4e63-95ad-4c07-860a-6ed7f8d3a87d', '6734b872-a71b-414c-b6ff-9dae25445d03', 'matrix', 'Questions 21–26', NULL, '<p>Reading Passage 2 has eight paragraphs, <strong>A-H</strong>.</p>
<p>Which paragraph contains the following information?</p>
', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": " a figure showing the dramatic results of an anti-malarial drug programme", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "an important discovery about how malaria is spread", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": " mention of an expert''s decision not to halt the spread of the disease", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": " the significance of the malaria story for today''s readers", "correctCategoryLetter": "H"}, {"itemText": "examples of false assumptions which held back scientific understanding of malaria", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "reference to legislation to support the fight against malaria", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "H", "categoryLetter": "H"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 21: a figure showing the dramatic results of an anti-malarial drug programme</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"23\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> E</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Deaths from malaria fell by some <strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"45\">80%</strong> in the first decade of the 20th century…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn E đưa ra con số (80%) minh chứng cho hiệu quả của chương trình dùng thuốc quinine.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 22: an important discovery about how malaria is spread</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"25\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> C</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…Grassi demonstrated that the micro-organisms causing the disease were carried in the <strong data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"100\">digestive tract of the mosquito</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn C mô tả khám phá quan trọng về việc muỗi là vật trung gian truyền bệnh.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 23: mention of an expert’s decision not to halt the spread of the disease</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"27\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> F</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…Alberto Missiroli <strong data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"33\">refused to order the distribution of quinine</strong>, so allowing the epidemic to spread unchecked.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Chuyên gia Alberto Missiroli đã quyết định không phát thuốc quinine để tạo điều kiện cho một thí nghiệm mới.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 24: the significance of the malaria story for today’s readers</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> H</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “As there are still more than 1m deaths every year… Snowden’s book also has <strong data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"89\">contemporary relevance</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn H nhấn mạnh ý nghĩa của câu chuyện đối với độc giả ngày nay khi bệnh sốt rét vẫn còn tồn tại.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 25: examples of false assumptions which held back scientific understanding of malaria</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> B</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…theory of ‘miasma’… belief that malaria was hereditary.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn B liệt kê các giả thuyết sai lầm (khí độc, di truyền) đã cản trở việc hiểu đúng về bệnh.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 26: reference to legislation to support the fight against malaria</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"33\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> D</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Italy introduced a <strong data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"31\">quinine law</strong> and a <strong data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"49\">quinine tax</strong> in 1904…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn D nhắc đến việc ban hành luật và thuế liên quan đến quinine để hỗ trợ chống dịch.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a1a6d44e-8906-402e-87d9-6df8c6edfe58', '527a8990-5cea-4f20-a0e8-a0a04e0f3ab1', 'checkbox', 'Questions 20-21', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>correct answers.</p>
', 'multiple-select', 'null', '[{"option": "There should be a person with legal training in every hospital.", "correct": false}, {"option": "Lawyers with experience in commercial law are the most in demand.", "correct": false}, {"option": "Knowledge of the law is as important as having computer skills.", "correct": true}, {"option": "Society could not function effectively without legal experts.", "correct": true}, {"option": "Schools should teach students about the law.", "correct": false}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>20. Knowledge of the law is as important as having computer skills.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) Tác giả so sánh tầm quan trọng của luật pháp với công nghệ thông tin: &#8220;Those people, for example, with knowledge of computers, the internet, and communications technology are relied upon by the rest of us&#8230; But <strong>legal understanding is just as vital and as universally needed</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả khẳng định rằng hiểu biết về pháp luật (<strong>legal understanding</strong>) cũng quan trọng (<em>&#8220;just as vital&#8221;</em>) và cần thiết trên toàn cầu như kỹ năng công nghệ (computer skills).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>21. Society could not function effectively without legal experts.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 3) Tác giả sử dụng ví dụ về IT: &#8220;Without their knowledge, many parts of commercial and social life today <strong>would seize up in minutes</strong>.&#8221; Ngay sau đó, tác giả nói: &#8220;<strong>But legal understanding is just as vital and as universally needed</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Bằng cách so sánh, tác giả ngụ ý rằng nếu không có kiến thức pháp lý (legal experts), xã hội và thương mại sẽ bị đình trệ (<em>&#8220;seize up&#8221;</em>), tức là không thể hoạt động hiệu quả. Hơn nữa, luật sư là người hiểu rõ &#8220;luật chơi&#8221; (<em>&#8220;the lawyer is the only person who has read the inside of the top of the box&#8221;</em>), điều tối quan trọng cho một xã hội có tổ chức.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('d749c60b-ceea-48da-9adf-339c3e22903c', '527a8990-5cea-4f20-a0e8-a0a04e0f3ab1', 'fillup', 'Questions 22-26', '<p>Complete the summary below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>LAWYERS AS PROFESSIONALS</strong></p>
<p>People sometimes say that {Truth} is of little interest to lawyers, who are more concerned with making money. This may well be the case with some individuals, in the same way that some {Journalists} or scientific experts may also be driven purely by financial greed. However, criticizing lawyers because their work is concerned with people’s problems would be similar to attacking IT staff or {Nurses} for the same reason. In fact, many lawyers focus on questions relating, for example, to housing or civil liberties, which requires them to have {Dedication}, to their work. What’s more, a lot of lawyers’ time is spent writing {Documents} rather than dealing with people’s misfortunes.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>22. People sometimes say that <strong>Truth</strong> is of little interest to lawyers, who are more concerned with making money.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Truth</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) People sometimes make comments that characterise lawyers as professionals whose concerns put personal reward above <strong>truth</strong>, or who gain financially from misfortune.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Câu tóm tắt mở đầu bằng việc đề cập đến lời chỉ trích rằng luật sư coi trọng tiền bạc hơn sự thật (<strong>Truth</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>23. This may well be the case with some individuals, in the same way that some <strong>Journalists</strong> or scientific experts may also be driven purely by financial greed.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Journalists</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) There are undoubtedly lawyers that would fit that bill, just as there are some scientists, <strong>journalists</strong> and others in that category.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản so sánh hành vi tiêu cực của luật sư với các nhóm nghề nghiệp khác, bao gồm các nhà khoa học và nhà báo (<strong>Journalists</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>24. However, criticizing lawyers because their work is concerned with people&#8217;s problems would be similar to attacking IT staff or <strong>Nurses</strong> for the same reason.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Nurses</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) But, in general, it is no more just to say that lawyers are bad because they make a living from people’s problems than it is to make the same accusation in respect of <strong>nurses</strong> or IT consultants.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả sử dụng y tá (<strong>Nurses</strong>) và chuyên gia tư vấn IT để chỉ ra sự bất công khi chỉ trích luật sư kiếm sống từ vấn đề của người khác.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>25. In fact, many lawyers focus on questions relating, for example, to housing or civil liberties, which requires them to have <strong>Dedication</strong> to their work.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Dedication</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) Such work is not lavishly remunerated and the quality of the service provided by these lawyers relies on considerable professional <strong>dedication</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Công việc luật công (public law work) đòi hỏi sự <strong>tận tâm</strong> (<strong>Dedication</strong>) cao độ vì thù lao không hào phóng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>26. What&#8217;s more, a lot of lawyers&#8217; time is spent writing <strong>Documents</strong> rather than dealing with people&#8217;s misfortunes.</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Documents</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn 6) Moreover, much legal work has nothing to do with conflict or misfortune, but is primarily concerned with drafting <strong>documents</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Một phần lớn công việc pháp lý liên quan đến việc soạn thảo tài liệu (<strong>Documents</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('e4599d7d-87c1-404c-b834-37be48e29907', '39a3c971-d662-4795-87c5-73aa9cb2a5eb', 'matching', 'Questions 27–33', NULL, '<p>Reading Passage 3 has seven paragraphs, <strong>A-G</strong>.</p>
<p>Choose the correct heading for each paragraph from the list of headings below.</p>
<p>Choose the correct number, <strong>i-viii</strong>, in boxes <strong>27-33</strong>.</p>
', 'matching', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i. A negative reaction to receiving flowers"}, {"optionText": "ii. Some surprisingly strong responses to flowers"}, {"optionText": "iii. A mutually beneficial relationship?"}, {"optionText": "iv. Becoming more open about personal matters"}, {"optionText": "v. Some common social functions of flowers"}, {"optionText": "vi. Sensory appeal versus practical purpose of flowers"}, {"optionText": "vii. Bridging the gap between strangers in an enclosed space"}, {"optionText": "viii. An imperfect theory"}], "matchingItems": null}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>27. Paragraph A</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>v. Some common social functions of flowers</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn A) Đoạn này liệt kê các mục đích xã hội phổ biến khi tặng hoa: <strong>để chia buồn, ăn mừng, tán tỉnh, xin lỗi</strong> (<em>&#8220;To offer condolence&#8230; To celebrate. To woo. To ask for forgiveness&#8221;</em>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>28. Paragraph B</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>iv. Becoming more open about personal matters</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) Những người nhận hoa được đánh giá là có tâm trạng tích cực hơn và <strong>sẵn lòng trả lời các câu hỏi về vòng tròn xã hội và các cuộc trò chuyện thân mật</strong> (<em>&#8220;more willing to answer questions concerning their social circle and intimate conversations&#8221;</em>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>29. Paragraph C</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>vii. Bridging the gap between strangers in an enclosed space</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn C) Nghiên cứu diễn ra trong thang máy (<em>&#8220;inside an elevator&#8221;</em>), một không gian kín. Những người nhận hoa <strong>thu hẹp khoảng cách</strong> (<em>&#8220;closed up that space to a considerable extent&#8221;</em>) và tăng sự thân mật (<em>&#8220;significant affiliation&#8221;</em>) với người lạ.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>30. Paragraph D</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>ii. Some surprisingly strong responses to flowers</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn D) Một số đối tượng đã thể hiện <strong>sự bộc lộ cảm xúc phi thường</strong> (<em>&#8220;extraordinary emotional displays&#8221;</em>), chẳng hạn như <strong>ôm và hôn tự phát</strong> (<em>&#8220;spontaneous hugs and kisses&#8221;</em>) người giao hoa, điều mà các nhà tâm lý học không lường trước được.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>31. Paragraph E</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"14\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>viii. An imperfect theory</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) Đoạn này đưa ra một giả thuyết tiến hóa giải thích sở thích đối với hoa, nhưng sau đó chỉ ra <strong>sai sót</strong> (<em>&#8220;flaw in this argument&#8221;</em>) của nó (hoa đẹp nhất không cho ra sản phẩm ăn được).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>32. Paragraph F</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"16\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>vi. Sensory appeal versus practical purpose of flowers</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn F) Đoạn này so sánh sự hấp dẫn <strong>cảm giác</strong> (<em>&#8220;Sensory appeal&#8221;</em>) của màu sắc, kết cấu và mùi hương hoa với mục đích tiến hóa ban đầu (tìm trái cây chín), và kết luận rằng sự yêu thích đã <strong>tách rời khỏi mục đích tiến hóa chính</strong> (<em>&#8220;long been separated from their primary evolutionary use&#8221;</em>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>33. Paragraph G</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>iii. A mutually beneficial relationship?</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn G) Lý thuyết của nhóm Rutgers đề xuất mối quan hệ <strong>đồng tiến hóa giữa thực vật và con người</strong> (<em>&#8220;plant-human co-evolution&#8221;</em>), trong đó hoa khai thác (<em>&#8220;exploit&#8221;</em>) cảm xúc của con người. Tác giả kết luận: &#8220;they are using you just as much as you are using them&#8221; (mối quan hệ đôi bên cùng có lợi/mutually beneficial).</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f50c9f2a-23d9-4632-af20-5fc89209acfa', '39a3c971-d662-4795-87c5-73aa9cb2a5eb', 'matrix', 'Questions 34–37', NULL, '<p>Classify the following statements as referring to</p>
', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": "List of options", "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "The study focused on participants’ short-term reaction to receiving flowers.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "Participants were deliberately misled as to the aim of the study.", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "Receiving flowers had a notable effect on participants’ mental capacities.", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "Male and female responses were more uniform than expected.", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "the first study", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "the second study", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "the third study", "categoryLetter": "C"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"1\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"1\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. The study focused on participants’ short-term reaction to receiving flowers.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">B (the second study)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Vị trí:</strong> Đoạn chứa tiêu đề <em data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">vii. Bridging the gap between strangers in an enclosed space</em> (Nghiên cứu thứ hai).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;In the second study, the psychologists observed participants being handed single flowers&#8230; <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"104\">inside an elevator</strong>&#8230; both men and women presented with flowers were <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"173\">more likely to smile, to stand closer and to initiate conversation</strong>.&#8221;</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>35. Participants were deliberately misled as to the aim of the study.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"25\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>A (the first study)</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn B) “The women were unaware that the study was about the effect of the flowers on their emotions. <strong>They were told that it was a study about their daily moods</strong>…”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Đối tượng được thông báo sai về mục đích nghiên cứu (misled).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>36. Receiving flowers had a notable effect on participants’ mental capacities.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"27\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>C (the third study)</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn D) “The researchers found not only a profound elevation of mood, but also <strong>reliable improvements in other measures of cognitive function, like memory</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Cải thiện chức năng nhận thức (cognitive function/mental capacities) là kết quả của nghiên cứu thứ ba.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>37. Male and female responses were more uniform than expected.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>B (the second study)</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn C) “Contrary to predictions regarding <strong>gender differences, both men and women</strong> presented with flowers were <strong>more likely to smile, to stand closer and to initiate conversation</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Nghiên cứu thứ hai (trong thang máy) quan sát thấy phản ứng của nam và nữ đồng nhất hơn dự đoán.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('4733f973-5b84-4783-96b3-ea0053138bd3', 'fc3c63e2-33c1-4681-ab31-aed26f251a57', 'radio', 'Questions 20-22', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct letter, A, B, C, or D.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "keep written records of different goods traded"}, {"content": "monitor the balance between goods given and received"}, {"content": "produce more materials for trading purposes"}, {"content": "make money from trading goods and services"}], "question": "In section A, ‘reciprocity’ refers to our ancestors’ ability to:"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": " It is of a type only found in this particular area."}, {"content": "It has all been dyed to give the same shade of red."}, {"content": "It has been perfectly preserved despite its age."}, {"content": "It appears it was selected for its color."}], "question": "What is said about the ochre found around Blombos?"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": " They are a great variety of shapes and sizes."}, {"content": "They were found in large numbers, all grouped around each other."}, {"content": " They have patterns in many different colors."}, {"content": "They have holes and markings suggesting they were joined together"}], "question": "What made the researchers realize the purpose of the beads found at the Blombos caves?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. In section A, ‘reciprocity’ refers to our ancestors’ ability to:</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">B. monitor the balance between goods given and received</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…allowing individuals to keep a <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"46\">running tally</strong> of their interactions with others… the ability to keep track of the <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"130\">credits and debits</strong> that accrue…” (Đoạn A).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Reciprocity” (sự có đi có lại) được mô tả là khả năng “ghi chép nhẩm” (mental bookkeeping) để theo dõi các khoản nợ và có (credits and debits) trong quá trình trao đổi, đảm bảo sự cân bằng giữa những gì cho đi và nhận lại.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. What is said about the ochre found around Blombos?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">D. It appears it was selected for its color.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “For a start, it is <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"31\">predominantly red</strong>—any of the other colors available would have sufficed for curing…” (Đoạn C).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các nhà nghiên cứu tin rằng đất son (ochre) ở đây được dùng cho mục đích biểu tượng vì họ chủ yếu chọn màu đỏ, mặc dù các màu khác cũng có tác dụng bảo quản da thú tương tự. Điều này chứng tỏ màu sắc là yếu tố được ưu tiên lựa chọn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">21. What made the researchers realize the purpose of the beads found at the Blombos caves?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">D. They have holes and markings suggesting they were joined together.</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…consistently placed <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"35\">holes</strong>… all the beads display a pattern of <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"79\">wear suggesting friction</strong> from rubbing against thread, clothes, or other beads.” (Đoạn D).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Những lỗ thủng được đục đồng nhất và các vết mòn do ma sát với chỉ hoặc quần áo cho thấy những vỏ sò này được xâu chuỗi lại với nhau để làm đồ trang sức, chứ không phải là sự tích tụ tự nhiên.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('75810dc5-8169-4f03-a15d-de92cd17b9f8', '3763dda6-1ba8-4b1a-a5eb-7726b97d5a43', 'matrix', 'Question 27–32', NULL, '<p>Reading Passage 3 has six sections <strong>A–F</strong>.</p>
<p>Which section contains the following information?</p>
', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "simple", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "positive and negative possibilities for the use of insect-inspired robots", "correctCategoryLetter": "F"}, {"itemText": "how perceived size is used as an aid to navigation", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}, {"itemText": "an example of decision-making taking place in the limbs", "correctCategoryLetter": "E"}, {"itemText": "a description of a potential aid in space exploration", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "the range of skills that have inspired biorobotics", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "how a variety of navigational methods operate at the same time", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "A", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "B", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "C", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "D", "categoryLetter": "D"}, {"categoryText": "E", "categoryLetter": "E"}, {"categoryText": "F", "categoryLetter": "F"}, {"categoryText": "G", "categoryLetter": "G"}, {"categoryText": "H", "categoryLetter": "H"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 27: positive and negative possibilities for the use of insect-inspired robots</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> F</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “While some were concerned that the initial applications… may be military, others… predicted swarms of tiny cheap insect-like robots as society’s cleaners and collectors.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn F thảo luận về các khả năng tích cực (làm sạch, bảo vệ môi trường) và tiêu cực (mục đích quân sự) của biorobotics.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 28: how perceived size is used as an aid to navigation</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> B</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The landmarks are then scaled, from small to large, so that the robot can recognize whether it is getting closer to or further away from them.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn B mô tả cách robot của Dr. Zelinsky thay đổi tỉ lệ (scale) kích thước vật thể để xác định khoảng cách khi di chuyển.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 29: an example of decision-making taking place in the limbs</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> E</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “The key to the cockroach’s remarkable cross-country performance lies partly in the fact that its legs do a lot of the ‘thinking’ without having to consult the brain.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn E nói về việc chân của loài gián có khả năng tự “suy nghĩ” (đưa ra quyết định vận động) mà không cần thông qua não bộ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 30: a description of a potential aid in space exploration</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> D</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…to design a flying robot that can not only navigate but also stay aloft and hover in the thin atmosphere of Mars.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn D mô tả ‘Entomopter’ – một loại robot bay được thiết kế để khám phá sao Hỏa (không gian).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 31: the range of skills that have inspired biorobotics</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> A</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…insects constantly solve complex problems of movement, vision and navigation… How they do it is driving one of the most exciting new fields… biorobotics…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn A liệt kê hàng loạt các kỹ năng của côn trùng (di chuyển, thị giác, định vị) là nguồn cảm hứng cho lĩnh vực này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu 32: how a variety of navigational methods operate at the same time</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> C</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…the ant has many separate subroutines going on simultaneously. Using the ant’s ability to steer by polarised light and to store and reuse landscape images…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn C mô tả cách loài kiến sử dụng đồng thời nhiều phương pháp như ánh sáng phân cực và hình ảnh ghi nhớ để định vị.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('cf64bb1b-5ee1-476b-9348-7de805cc2ca9', '8c4b61ea-25c8-4bab-a818-d40fb6cc8e28', 'radio', 'Questions 27-30', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>YES </strong>if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>NO </strong>if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Most people understand how innovation happens."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The word \"innovation\" is overused in business in New Zealand."}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "There are many interpretations of what innovation means in business, according to one global study."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "YES"}, {"content": "NO"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Research and development projects have a higher priority today than in the past."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"1\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"1\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">27 Most people understand how innovation happens.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: NO</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 1, câu 3: “…however, the <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"43\">majority of us have little comprehension</strong> of the processes that actually lead to innovation occurring.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc khẳng định đa số chúng ta (the majority of us) có rất ít sự hiểu biết (little comprehension) về quá trình dẫn đến đổi mới. Điều này trái ngược hoàn toàn với ý “đa số mọi người hiểu” (most people understand) trong câu hỏi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">28 The word “innovation” is overused in business in New Zealand.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: YES</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 1, câu 5: “However, in company boardrooms across <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">New Zealand</strong>, the term is <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"90\">heard far too frequently</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cụm từ “heard far too frequently” (nghe thấy quá thường xuyên) đồng nghĩa với “overused” (bị lạm dụng/dùng quá nhiều). Văn bản xác nhận tình trạng này đang xảy ra tại các phòng họp công ty ở New Zealand.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">29 There are many interpretations of what innovation means in business, according to one global study.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: YES</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 1, câu 6: “Certainly, a recent <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">international survey</strong> showed that… different sectors of the business world… often <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"132\">defining innovation in their own way</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “International survey” tương ứng với “global study”. Việc các bộ phận khác nhau “định nghĩa theo cách riêng của họ” (defining… in their own way) chính là có “nhiều cách hiểu/giải thích khác nhau” (many interpretations).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">30 Research and development projects have a higher priority today than in the past.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 2, câu 1: “While there is an obvious attraction to the new, innovation is <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"90\">not always about large-scale research and development projects</strong>…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc có nhắc đến các dự án nghiên cứu và phát triển (R&amp;D) để nói rằng đổi mới không phải lúc nào cũng nằm ở những dự án quy mô lớn này. Tuy nhiên, bài đọc <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"170\">không hề so sánh</strong> mức độ ưu tiên của các dự án R&amp;D giữa “nay” và “xưa”.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('309c346d-a717-4302-a688-7da9fba30716', 'afd093ef-a03d-49d3-a5ac-b945c5a2e9c3', 'fillup', 'Questions 1–10', '<div class="quests-inner-desc">
<div class="txt">
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="quests-des">
<div class="content-write">
<p class="ql-align-center" style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Places to visit with children</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>Alma Park</strong></p>
<ul>
<li data-list="bullet">Go to the zoo.</li>
<li data-list="bullet">A family ticket is $ {65} .</li>
<li data-list="bullet">The fastest bus takes about {40} minutes.</li>
<li data-list="bullet">You can hold some animals and have a {photo} for a small fee.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>The Entertainment Room</strong></p>
<ul>
<li data-list="bullet">John {Rosie} is performing.</li>
<li data-list="bullet">Performance run from Tuesday to {Saturday} .</li>
<li data-list="bullet">There is a {discount} on tickets for Monday night’s preview.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>The City</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Go to the city center {museum} to see a special exhibition.</li>
<li data-list="bullet">Do origami – we’ll need to take a small {box} .</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Bunyabbie Island</strong></p>
<ul>
<li data-list="bullet">Explore with a four-wheel drive.</li>
<li data-list="bullet">Go snorkelling at Salty Lake – it’s on the {Ocean} side of the Island.</li>
<li data-list="bullet">You’re not allowed to {camp} on the island.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', NULL, NULL, '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', '{"layoutType": ["standard"], "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": null, "matrixCategories": null}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 1</strong></p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> Good afternoon can I help you?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Yes I’m looking for some places to visit when my sister and her children come to stay. They arrive this weekend from overseas. I’m new to the area and don’t really know what to recommend. Do you have any ideas?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> What about going to Alma Park to visit the zoo?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Ooh I like the idea of that. Is it reasonably priced?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> Yes, it’s not a bad price. A standard adult ticket is normally $30 but there’s a special deal for families of $<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\">(1) </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\">65</span></strong>, which is a saving of $35.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> That’s a great deal. How do we get there from the city?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> You can go by bus.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Is it very far?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> The 385 will get you there in approximately <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(2) 40</strong></span><span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"> <span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">minutes depending on traffic<strong>.</strong></span></span> There is another bus, the 388, but it takes 20 minutes longer, so it’s worth waiting a few more minutes for the more direct bus.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Okay. Are there any special things to do there? Can you feed the animals or anything like that?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> <span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">They’ve stopped that but most tourists love the fact that you’re allowed to hold some of the animals and get your </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong>(3) photo</strong> </span><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">taken</span>. They just ask you to make a small payment to help with costs.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Oh, the kids would love that. My sister also likes going to the theatre. Is there anything good on at the moment? She especially likes comedies.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> There’s a place called the Entertainment Room in Ascot. I’ll just check their website… hmm yes, there’s a festival running at the moment with John<span style=\"background-color: #ffe786;\"> <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"158\">(4) Rosie</strong></span></span> as the main entertainer. He’s really funny.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> How do we spell that? Is it R O Z Y?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> No it’s R O S I E.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Got it. And when is it on next week?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> It says it starts on Tuesday with a special matinee show on the Wednesday. It was supposed to finish on Friday but because of the demand it’s been extended to <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"168\">(5) Saturday</strong></span>.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> It must be good then. Is it expensive?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> I don’t think so let’s see… oh it says there’s a special preview show on a Monday and they’re offering a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21\" data-index-in-node=\"116\">(6) discount</strong></span> on tickets that night.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> We’ll try and go then. I also wanted to spend a day in the city centre. The children will get bored just looking at the shops. Is there anything else for them to do?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> What’s the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">(7) museum</strong></span> like? It’s very popular with children and there’s a very hands-on exhibition on at the moment.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> They’d love that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> Sounds good and there’s a workshop on where they learn how to do origami.</p>\n<div class=\"attachment-container search-images\">\n<div class=\"image-container ng-star-inserted\" data-full-size-image-uri=\"https://encrypted-tbn3.gstatic.com/licensed-image?q=tbn:ANd9GcSsL7bIKNlQ84dHAGLL6OyQ4uin6slj-hS8b4sWHTzX6uY7IFajBVttnDQpypuI7FCzPvfjU5CVjdykaV21oxg-gtYjjP6Cv7RXfKTKDoLsa8isCjw\">\n<div class=\"overlay-container ng-star-inserted\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Will they need to bring anything special for that?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> On this leaflet it says that things like scissors and all of the paper are provided. They just advise children to bring a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"131\">(8) box</strong></span> to carry the completed origami home in. Just a little one will do.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> I’m also looking for a weekend activity. I’ve heard Bunyabbie Island is great. Would we need a car to get around the island?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> A 4-wheel drive is a great way to explore. You should also try snorkelling at Salty Lake.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Is that in the centre of the island near the mountain?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> No it’s on the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"24\">(9) Ocean</strong></span> side.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Woman:</strong> Okay I’ll get a map and check it out. I’d like to stay there at least one night and I quite like the idea of taking a tent and sleeping out in the open air. Are you allowed to <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffe786;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"183\">(10) camp</strong></span> there?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Officer:</strong> That would be lovely, but I’m afraid that’s not allowed on the island to protect the wildlife.</p>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('a3365b61-c9e5-4ad9-a18d-7e61c6c043e9', '39a3c971-d662-4795-87c5-73aa9cb2a5eb', 'fillup', 'Questions 38–40', '<p>Complete the summary below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>A possible explanation for the appeal of flowers</strong></p>
<p>It has been suggested that our intense response to flowers originates in prehistoric times. The presence of flowers might indicate a potential source of {Food} in a particular location, and primitive humans would search for such signs when looking for a suitable site to raise their {Children}. The interpretation of these signs was essential for the survival of our ancestors. However, the problem with this idea is that the plants producing the most attractive flowers do not usually have fruit which is {Edible}.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>38. It has been suggested that our intense response to flowers originates in prehistoric times. The presence of flowers might indicate a potential source of Food in a particular location&#8230;</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"34\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Food</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) &#8220;&#8230;for early man, finding them in a particular location predicted <strong>future food supplies</strong>&#8230;&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Việc tìm thấy hoa có thể báo hiệu nguồn cung cấp thức ăn (food) trong tương lai.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>39. &#8230;and primitive humans would search for such signs when looking for a suitable site to raise their Children.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"36\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Children</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) &#8220;&#8230;predicted future food supplies and possibly a better place to rear <strong>children</strong>.&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Hoa cũng có thể báo hiệu một nơi tốt hơn để nuôi dạy con cái (children).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>40. However, the problem with this idea is that the plants producing the most attractive flowers do not usually have fruit which is Edible.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"38\">\n<li><strong>Đáp án:</strong> <strong>Edible</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Dẫn chứng:</strong> (Đoạn E) &#8220;&#8230;the showy flowers which humans seem to find most visually attractive are generally found on those plants which yield no <strong>edible</strong> products.&#8221;</li>\n<li><strong>Giải thích:</strong> Sai sót của giả thuyết là hoa hấp dẫn nhất lại không cho ra sản phẩm ăn được (edible).</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('dede7f2c-6e08-4b5e-9c3d-f46d96a7d167', 'e225b4e7-8b95-431d-a0d6-e757f56927d0', 'fillup', 'Questions 7–13', '<p data-start="77" data-end="228">Complete the notes below.<br data-start="106" data-end="109">Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.<br data-start="167" data-end="170">Write your answers in boxes 7–13 on your answer sheet.</p>
<h2 style="text-align: center;" data-start="235" data-end="297">Research into the existence and disappearance of cave bears</h2>
<h3 data-start="299" data-end="345">Evidence from the Chauvet cave in France</h3>
<ul data-start="346" data-end="596">
<li data-start="346" data-end="387">
<p data-start="348" data-end="387">Paintings on the walls include bears.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="388" data-end="505">
<p data-start="390" data-end="505">Over a hundred {skeletons} of cave bears together with paw prints were found on the floor of the cave.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="506" data-end="596">
<p data-start="508" data-end="596">The {skull} of a cave bear was found in a prominent position in the cave.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="603" data-end="673"> </h3>
<h3 data-start="603" data-end="673">Evidence from the Hohle Fels cave in the Swabian Jura in Germany</h3>
<ul data-start="674" data-end="780">
<li data-start="674" data-end="780">
<p data-start="676" data-end="780">Bones and tools found in the cave indicate it provided {shelter} for both bears and humans.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="787" data-end="818"> </h3>
<h3 data-start="787" data-end="818">Susanne Munzel’s findings</h3>
<ul data-start="819" data-end="962">
<li data-start="819" data-end="901">
<p data-start="821" data-end="901">A spear point in the vertebra of a bear indicates that a hunt had taken place.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="902" data-end="962">
<p data-start="904" data-end="962">Marks on the bones of bears indicate the removal of flesh.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="969" data-end="1001"> </h3>
<h3 data-start="969" data-end="1001">Hervé Bocherens’s findings</h3>
<ul data-start="1002" data-end="1102">
<li data-start="1002" data-end="1102">
<p data-start="1004" data-end="1102">Isotopes from the bones indicate that {plants} were the cave bears’ preferred food.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 data-start="1109" data-end="1168"> </h3>
<h3 data-start="1109" data-end="1168">Factors leading to the disappearance of the cave bear</h3>
<p data-start="1169" data-end="1470"><strong data-start="1169" data-end="1189">• Climate change</strong><br data-start="1189" data-end="1192">– The Ice Age changed vegetation growth in {teeth}<br data-start="1258" data-end="1261">– Bears were forced to migrate.<br data-start="1292" data-end="1295">– Support for the above explanation comes from a study of changes in the DNA in the {population} of the population of cave bears near the Danube River at this time.</p>
<p data-start="1472" data-end="1639"><strong data-start="1472" data-end="1504">• Human population expansion</strong><br data-start="1504" data-end="1507">– Competition from Neanderthals and modern humans for caves may have reduced opportunities for cave bears to {Hibernate}</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p>7 skeletons<br />(Đoạn 3: “The walls of France’s Chauvet cave are painted with lions, hyenas and bears; &#8230; the floor is covered with 150 cave bear skeletons.”)<br />→ Trên sàn hang Chauvet, có hơn 100 bộ xương gấu hang động được tìm thấy cùng dấu chân.</p>\n<p> <br />8 skull<br />(Đoạn 3: “Most dramatically, a cave bear skull was perched on a stone slab in the center of one chamber, placed deliberately by some long-gone cave inhabitant.”)<br />→ Một hộp sọ gấu hang được đặt cố ý trên phiến đá giữa hang.</p>\n<p> <br />9 shelter<br />(Đoạn 4: “Long ago, as shown by the bones and tools that archaeologists have found, cave bears and human beings seeking shelter here from winter weather.”)<br />→ Các công cụ và xương trong hang Hohle Fels cho thấy hang là nơi trú ẩn của cả gấu và người.</p>\n<p> <br />10 plants<br />(Đoạn 6: “After studying hundreds of bones… Bocherens has found that cave bears ate mainly plants.”)<br />→ Kết quả cho thấy thức ăn chủ yếu của gấu hang là thực vật.</p>\n<p> <br />11 vegetation<br />(Đoạn 7: “This Ice Age shortened or eliminated growing seasons, and altered the distributions of plant species across Europe.”)<br />→ Kỷ Băng Hà đã làm thay đổi sự phát triển của thảm thực vật, khiến nguồn thức ăn của gấu bị giảm.</p>\n<p> <br />12 population<br />(Đoạn 7: “The cave bear population there was relatively stable… But about 28,000 years ago, newcomers with different DNA patterns arrived.”)<br />→ Nghiên cứu DNA cho thấy sự thay đổi trong quần thể gấu hang gần sông Danube vào thời điểm đó.</p>\n<p> <br />13 hibernate<br />(Đoạn cuối: “As Neanderthals, and then modern humans moved into the caves… cave bears had fewer safe places to hibernate.”)<br />→ Khi con người chiếm hang, gấu không còn nhiều nơi an toàn để ngủ đông, góp phần dẫn đến tuyệt chủng.<br /> <br /> <br /> </p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}, {"content": "<p>1</p>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('9facbd04-095c-48af-8149-74a61839ee99', '66edec72-e7cc-440a-8e29-b7b59f7b2f69', 'matching', 'Questions 14-18', '<p></p>', '<p>Reading&nbsp;Passage&nbsp;2&nbsp;has&nbsp;seven&nbsp;sections,&nbsp;A–G.</p><p>Which&nbsp;section&nbsp;contains&nbsp;the&nbsp;following&nbsp;information?</p><p><strong>NB&nbsp;</strong>You&nbsp;may&nbsp;use&nbsp;any&nbsp;letter&nbsp;more&nbsp;than&nbsp;once.</p>', 'matching', NULL, NULL, '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": null, "matchingItems": null}', NULL, NULL, 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('6e6eec98-736f-4c64-ad22-acb0e2c2dd0d', '8c4b61ea-25c8-4bab-a818-d40fb6cc8e28', 'radio', 'Questions 31-35', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answers</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "A. Criticizing the conclusions of one publication"}, {"content": "B. Praising the contribution of a famous inventor"}, {"content": "C. Dismissing one common idea about innovation"}, {"content": "D. Suggesting that innovation changes over time"}], "question": "What is the writer doing in the third paragraph?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "A. Each industry will innovate in its own way."}, {"content": "B. There are pros and cons to strong leaders."}, {"content": "C. Some individuals are more innovative than others."}, {"content": "D. Leadership requires building teams that work together."}], "question": "What is the writer''s main point in the fourth paragraph?"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "A. Compare how two different innovations developed."}, {"content": "B. Illustrate an exception to his point about innovation."}, {"content": "C. Show why one approach to innovation was correct."}, {"content": "D. Give an example of a general rule about innovation."}], "question": "The writer refers to Gutenberg''s printing press in order to:"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "A. Companies should cooperate to turn ideas into products."}, {"content": "B. A company tends to make profits from its own innovations."}, {"content": "C. Science and business can often have common goals."}, {"content": "D. Competition between businesses produces innovation."}], "question": "What is the writer''s main point in the seventh paragraph?"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"content": "A. Have published valuable research about innovation."}, {"content": "B. Help companies recruit people with skills in innovation."}, {"content": "C. Run university courses teaching innovation skills."}, {"content": "D. Can be hired to give businesses advice about innovation."}], "question": "According to the writer, companies like Previously Unavailable:"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">31. What is the writer doing in the third paragraph?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">C. Dismissing one common idea about innovation.</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 3, câu 1 và câu cuối: <em data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">“There seems to be a widespread belief that the world’s best ideas are sudden and intuitive… Thus, business managers… must <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"165\">reject the false assumption</strong> that innovation is just a moment of brilliance waiting to strike.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả nêu lên một niềm tin phổ biến (widespread belief) rằng đổi mới là sự đột phá tức thời, sau đó dùng ví dụ về sự nỗ lực của Edison để bác bỏ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"160\">reject/dismiss</strong>) quan điểm sai lầm này.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">32. What is the writer’s main point in the fourth paragraph?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">B. There are pros and cons to strong leaders.</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 4, câu 3 và câu cuối: <em data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">“…it was the fuel for his visionary innovations… but his <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">egotistical behavior could have undesirable consequences</strong>, too… affects sickness rates and group morale, which in turn may squash creativity…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả trình bày hai mặt của Steve Jobs: một mặt sự quyết liệt của ông là động lực cho đổi mới (pros), nhưng mặt khác tính cách ích kỷ và khắt khe lại gây ra hậu quả xấu cho tinh thần nhân viên (cons).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">33. The writer refers to Gutenberg’s printing press in order to:</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">D. Give an example of a general rule about innovation.</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 6, câu cuối: <em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">“A good case to cite in support of this <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"69\">universal truth</strong> would be Gutenberg’s printing press… the press also affected an unrelated industry by causing a rise in demand for reading glasses.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả nhắc đến máy in Gutenberg như một ví dụ điển hình để minh chứng cho một “sự thật phổ quát” (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"112\">universal truth</strong>) – quy luật chung rằng tiến bộ ở một lĩnh vực có thể thúc đẩy sự phát triển ở một lĩnh vực khác không liên quan.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">34. What is the writer’s main point in the seventh paragraph?</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">A. Companies should cooperate to turn ideas into products.</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 7, câu cuối: <em data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">“Instead, Kode’s approach is to <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"61\">collaborate with similar nanotechnology businesses</strong>, which take its innovations and develop them into commodities that can be sold…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thông qua ví dụ về Kode Biotech, tác giả nhấn mạnh rằng các công ty nên hợp tác (<strong data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"93\">collaborate/cooperate</strong>) với nhau để biến các phát minh thành sản phẩm thực tế có giá trị thương mại.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">35. According to the writer, companies like Previously Unavailable:</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">D. Can be hired to give businesses advice about innovation.</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 8, câu 4 và 6: <em data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"31\">“Previously Unavailable, a <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">specialist innovation consultancy</strong>… will <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"100\">lease a team of innovation experts</strong> on a short-term basis to client organizations to assist with conceiving, developing…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả mô tả Previously Unavailable là một công ty tư vấn chuyên nghiệp (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">consultancy</strong>), nơi các doanh nghiệp khác có thể thuê (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"139\">lease</strong>) các chuyên gia để nhận lời khuyên và hỗ trợ thực hiện quá trình đổi mới.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('7c9239b5-7154-4381-a5fd-7ac237288799', '8c4b61ea-25c8-4bab-a818-d40fb6cc8e28', 'matching', 'Questions 36-40', NULL, '<p>Complete each sentence with the correct ending, A-G, below.</p>', 'matching', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "summaryText": null, "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "A Innovators do not get enough credit for their own ideas."}, {"optionText": "B Innovation may influence a completely different field."}, {"optionText": "C Expressing what everyone already knows is pointless."}, {"optionText": "D Innovation can be enhanced through collaboration with similar companies."}, {"optionText": "E Innovation requires a great deal of hard work."}, {"optionText": "F Copying ideas that already exist is not true innovation."}, {"optionText": "G Certain personality types can limit innovation."}], "matchingItems": [{"questionPart": "A book about the life and work of Thomas Edison suggests that", "correctAnswer": "E Innovation requires a great deal of hard work.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "People who have worked for CEOs like Steve Jobs claim that", "correctAnswer": "G Certain personality types can limit innovation.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Critics of Harford''s 2011 TED Talk argue that", "correctAnswer": "C Expressing what everyone already knows is pointless.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Steven Johnson''s hummingbird effect proposes that", "correctAnswer": "B Innovation may influence a completely different field.", "sectionContent": null}, {"questionPart": "Kode Biotech CEO Steve Henry believes that", "correctAnswer": "D"}]}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. A book about the life and work of Thomas Edison suggests that</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: E. Innovation requires a great deal of hard work.</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 3, câu 2: <em data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“…the book Edison: His Life and Inventions shows that Edison’s own inspiration usually resulted from <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"129\">laborious experimentation</strong>, rather than a moment of genius.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cuốn sách về Edison chỉ ra rằng những phát minh của ông là kết quả của quá trình thử nghiệm gian khổ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"114\">laborious experimentation</strong>), tương ứng với cụm từ <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"163\">“a great deal of hard work”</strong> (rất nhiều công sức).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. People who have worked for CEOs like Steve Jobs claim that</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: G. Certain personality types can limit innovation.</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 4, câu cuối: <em data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">“Jobs’ former employees have suggested this type of <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"81\">demanding behavior</strong> affects sickness rates and group morale, which in turn may <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"159\">squash creativity and innovation</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Những nhân viên cũ cho rằng tính cách khắt khe (personality type/demanding behavior) của các CEO như Jobs có thể dập tắt (<strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"134\">squash/limit</strong>) sự sáng tạo và đổi mới.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. Critics of Harford’s 2011 TED Talk argue that</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: C. Expressing what everyone already knows is pointless.</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 5, câu 2: <em data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“It sounds like common sense, and some commentators have claimed Harford’s TED Talk was <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"114\">not persuasive because it was stating the obvious</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Những người chỉ trích cho rằng bài nói của Harford không thuyết phục vì nó chỉ đang nói những điều hiển nhiên (<strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"123\">stating the obvious</strong>), tương ứng với ý <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"161\">“expressing what everyone already knows”</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. Steven Johnson’s hummingbird effect proposes that</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: B. Innovation may influence a completely different field.</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 6, câu 3: <em data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“This points out that progress in a specific area or discipline can end up <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"101\">triggering small but significant developments elsewhere entirely</strong>.”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Hiệu ứng chim ruồi (hummingbird effect) mô tả việc tiến bộ ở một lĩnh vực này có thể tạo ra tác động hoặc sự phát triển ở một lĩnh vực hoàn toàn khác (<strong data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"163\">elsewhere entirely/completely different field</strong>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. Kode Biotech CEO Steve Henry believes that</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: D. Innovation can be enhanced through collaboration with similar companies.</strong></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 7, câu cuối: <em data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">“Instead, Kode’s approach is to <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"61\">collaborate with similar nanotechnology businesses</strong>, which take its innovations and develop them into commodities…”</em></li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Steve Henry khẳng định phương pháp của Kode là hợp tác (<strong data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"68\">collaborate</strong>) với các doanh nghiệp tương tự để tối ưu hóa việc đưa đổi mới vào thị trường.</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('8caa4b10-3c60-4fe7-aa55-18b706b85add', '041a2320-11a2-4d8f-b9f8-b4bcf8e88477', 'radio', 'Questions 37–40', '', '<p data-start="21" data-end="65">Choose the correct letter, <strong data-start="48" data-end="64">A, B, C or D</strong>.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. a key factor in determining how endangered a language is"}, {"option_text": "B. alternative methods of interpreting data about languages at risk"}, {"option_text": "C. different reasons why a minority language might be under threat"}, {"option_text": "D. difficulties involved in assessing a language''s survival prospects"}], "question": "In the first paragraph, the writer mentions two particular languages in order to indicate"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A. the growth of international trade"}, {"option_text": "B. the shift towards living in more extended social groups"}, {"option_text": "C. the attitude of governments towards minority languages"}, {"option_text": "D. the speed with which minority languages fall out of use"}], "question": "What similarity between the Roman Empire and the present day does Nicholas Ostler mention?"}, {"correct": 3, "options": [{"option_text": "A. it is more difficult for minority-language speakers to access education"}, {"option_text": "B. majority-language speakers can participate better in national life"}, {"option_text": "C. their national government is opposed to the use of minority languages"}, {"option_text": "D. they need to choose between being a minority- or majority-language speaker"}], "question": "According to Louisa Maffi, many people wrongly believe that"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"option_text": "A. younger people''s perceptions of their mother tongue"}, {"option_text": "B. breakdown of communication between the generations"}, {"option_text": "C. older people''s attitudes to their children''s language use"}, {"option_text": "D. generational differences in ability to access the mass media"}], "question": "What problem among minority-language speakers is mentioned in the eighth paragraph?"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A. the variety of media it can use"}, {"option_text": "B. the freedom its users can have"}, {"option_text": "C. the wide geographical area it can reach"}, {"option_text": "D. the range of people it can be accessed by"}], "question": "What does Peter Austin see as the main advantage of the internet for minority language groups?"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">36. A — a key factor in determining how endangered a language is.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"27\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“However, the total number of speakers is not always a clear indication of the health of a language.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả mượn ví dụ về tiếng Onge (ít người nói nhưng trẻ em vẫn dùng) và tiếng Chipweyan (nhiều người thuộc nhóm dân tộc đó nhưng thế hệ trẻ không dùng) để làm nổi bật luận điểm: tổng số lượng người nói không phải là thước đo duy nhất, mà việc thế hệ trẻ có kế thừa ngôn ngữ đó hay không mới là yếu tố mấu chốt (<strong data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"324\">a key factor</strong>) để xác định mức độ nguy cấp của một ngôn ngữ.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">37. B — the shift towards living in more extended social groups</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“The Romans succeeded in making people live in larger communities, what we now call urbanisation.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nicholas Ostler chỉ ra điểm tương đồng giữa thời La Mã và thời hiện đại là xu hướng dịch chuyển từ nông thôn ra thành thị, khiến con người sống trong các cộng đồng lớn hơn (<strong data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"185\">live in larger communities / shift towards living in more extended social groups</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">38. D — they need to choose between being a minority- or majority-language speaker.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“There is essentially a misconceived either/or ideology: either you maintain your mother tongue... or you forget your mother tongue and learn the majority language.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Louisa Maffi cho rằng mọi người đang bị áp đặt một tư tưởng sai lầm \"hoặc/hoặc\" (<em data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"93\">misconceived either/or ideology</em>): hoặc giữ tiếng mẹ đẻ, hoặc quên nó đi để học ngôn ngữ phổ thông. Tư tưởng sai lầm này khiến họ lầm tưởng rằng mình bắt buộc phải chọn lựa giữa việc trở thành người nói tiếng thiểu số hay tiếng phổ thông (<strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"331\">need to choose between...</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">39. A — younger people''s perceptions of their mother tongue</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"33\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"33,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“All of the images children see in the media are of the glamorised lifestyle of the majority... So it becomes very difficult for them to find a reason to value their own language.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đoạn số 8 đề cập đến vấn đề truyền thông đại chúng vẽ ra lối sống hào nhoáng của nhóm đa số, khiến trẻ em và người trẻ tuổi không còn tìm được lý do để trân trọng ngôn ngữ truyền thống của dân tộc mình. Đây chính là góc nhìn, nhận thức của người trẻ về tiếng mẹ đẻ (<strong data-path-to-node=\"33,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"278\">younger people''s perceptions of their mother tongue</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. B — the freedom its users can have</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"35\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng câu tốt nhất:</strong> &gt; <em data-path-to-node=\"35,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"26\">“Unlike most TV or radio, the web isn''t in the hands of big media corporations... Minority groups around the world... are now taking advantage of this autonomy to document their language...”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Peter Austin nhận định lợi thế lớn nhất của Internet là nó không bị kiểm soát bởi các tập đoàn truyền thông lớn. Bất kỳ ai cũng có thể tự tạo tài khoản và sản xuất nội dung. Sự tự trị, tự chủ này (<em data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"209\">autonomy</em>) mang lại quyền tự do hành động rất lớn cho người dùng (<strong data-path-to-node=\"35,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"274\">the freedom its users can have</strong>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('3d63e2df-6704-4441-bc04-9f22a75e413c', '6a45cfea-1f8b-4031-82fd-b931cebd3ecb', 'checkbox', 'Questions 21 and 22', '', '<p>Choose <strong>TWO </strong>letters, <strong>A-E</strong>.<br>Which <strong>TWO </strong>points did students most frequently make about their musical background before starting a music degree?</p>', 'multiple_choice', 'null', '[{"correct": false, "option_text": "A. They had already composed music."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "B. They had several music qualifications.     "}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "C. They could play more than one instrument. "}, {"correct": true, "option_text": "D. They had performed in public."}, {"correct": false, "option_text": "E. They had had piano lesson"}]', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong>Lorna:</strong> So Gareth, we need to organise the findings from our survey on music students for the final presentation.</p>\n<p><strong>Gareth:</strong> Yes, Lorna, I think we’ve got some very interesting results. Obviously we need to start by saying that we interviewed all the third year students doing a music degree and state the objective of our research project, that is to find out about their attitudes to performing.</p>\n<p><strong>Lorna:</strong> And then we should talk about the students’ musical backgrounds before coming to university. The most important points to make are that although most people have actually composed music during the course, that wasn’t the case when they arrived. And the other thing they had in common was the piano—well they’d had access to a piano at some point, but not all had studied it formally. I thought the most interesting finding was that before coming here, almost everyone was involved in a chamber orchestra or band or singing in a choir, and <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(21/22) playing in front of live audiences (D)</strong></span> but varying enormously in size. Some had only played in tiny venues. I think it’s worth saying that.</p>\n<p><strong>Gareth:</strong> Okay. And as you might expect from people wanting to study music, they all had a degree of proficiency in <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(21/22) at least two instruments (C)</strong></span> but in most cases one of the instruments was dominant. Right.</p>\n<h3>II. Thái Độ Luyện Tập (Attitudes to Music Practice)</h3>\n<p><strong>Gareth:</strong> We need to talk about attitudes to music practice. The most striking thing here is that even students who you’d expect to practice for hours every day until they get it perfect, say it’s being <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(23/24) terrified of failing (C)</strong></span> that really makes them practice. I know, I’m the same.</p>\n<p><strong>Lorna:</strong> Me too. It’s interesting what was said about practicing alone; some people preferred that because they could focus more on their weak points, but that wasn’t a majority view. What most of them agree on is <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(23/24) that there’s nothing more rewarding than mastering something that’s really hard to learn (E)</strong>.</span></p>\n<p><strong>Gareth:</strong> That’s right.</p>\n<h3>III. Lựa Chọn Tác Phẩm &amp; Thái Độ Biểu Diễn (Selecting Pieces &amp; Performing)</h3>\n<p><strong>Gareth:</strong> Okay, after that, we should talk a bit about the pieces that students select for assessed performances. There wasn’t quite so much consensus on this, was there? A few people prefer to do pieces which are relatively unknown, while others choose the ones they think will show off their technical ability, but they were in the minority. I think the first thing to say is that a high percentage said they would always try to <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(25/26) learn their pieces by heart (C)</strong></span> because it’s too easy to get lost if you’re trying to read and play when you’re nervous.</p>\n<p><strong>Lorna:</strong> Okay, and quite a lot of them said it helps to<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong>(25/26) listen to other people playing (A)</strong> </span>your chosen piece—preferably recordings, but even just other students.</p>\n<p><strong>Lorna:</strong> So finally, we need to look at the findings for students’ attitudes to performing. We should point out that this includes informal and formal public performances as well as assessed ones.</p>\n<p><strong>Gareth:</strong> Yes, that’s important. I expected to find that<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong>(27) performing solo</strong></span> would make students very nervous, but in fact that isn’t the case. They do find it hugely challenging to start with, but they appreciate the challenge and find it <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(27) stimulating (B)</strong></span>. Right.</p>\n<p><strong>Lorna:</strong> I was surprised by what students said about <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(28) deciding which pieces to perform</strong></span>. I thought they’d all say this was easy. For me, it’s always been quite straightforward: which pieces do I like best and which pieces can I play well? And my repertoire is quite limited anyway.But the most commonly cited answer was that <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(28) it took them ages to make their minds up (E)</strong></span>. I suppose it’s because there are so many factors involved .You need to consider your audience, the venue, the time available to learn the piece—especially if it’s complicated. You need to think about all these things… and you can’t do that in a hurry. That’s true.</p>\n<p><strong>Gareth:</strong> Then there’s<span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"> <strong>(29) performing with musicians from a different genre</strong>,</span> like a classical musician playing with a jazz group. That can really be fun, but most of the music students had <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(29) never even considered it (G)</strong></span>. Right.</p>\n<p><strong>Lorna:</strong> For <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(30) performing with musicians who play the same instrument</strong></span>, almost everyone put the same thing.</p>\n<p><strong>Gareth:</strong> Yes, they all said it was <span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong>(30) incredibly helpful (A)</strong></span> and not at all intimidating. Which says a lot for the department’s ethos.</p>\n<p><strong>Lorna:</strong> Yes, that’s a good point. OK, what I think we should sort out now is…</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('67c148f4-9478-447a-82d8-a5429651da7f', '66ade43a-36ed-424f-9b52-32afe7047f03', 'matrix', 'Questions 1-6', NULL, '<p>Choose the correct answers from the options given.</p>
<p>NB You may use any letter more than once.</p>
', 'other', 'null', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "standard", "legendTitle": null, "matrixItems": [{"itemText": "very expensive", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "a food flavouring", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "used as currency", "correctCategoryLetter": "D"}, {"itemText": "sweet-smelling", "correctCategoryLetter": "A"}, {"itemText": "referred to by Herman Melville", "correctCategoryLetter": "C"}, {"itemText": "can be seen through", "correctCategoryLetter": "B"}], "matrixCategories": [{"categoryText": "ambergris only", "categoryLetter": "A"}, {"categoryText": "amber only", "categoryLetter": "B"}, {"categoryText": "both ambergris and amber", "categoryLetter": "C"}, {"categoryText": "neither ambergris nor amber", "categoryLetter": "D"}]}', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"1\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"1\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. Very expensive (Rất đắt đỏ)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2\">\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: C (Both ambergris and amber)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> * &#8220;ambergris was worth its <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"38\">weight in gold</strong>&#8221; (Đoạn 1).</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2,1,1\">\n<li>\n<p>&#8220;<strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"1\">Both substances were rare costly</strong>, and both were associated with the sea&#8221; (Đoạn 2).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc sử dụng các cụm từ &#8220;đắt ngang vàng&#8221; cho long diên hương và &#8220;cả hai đều đắt đỏ, quý hiếm&#8221; để khẳng định giá trị kinh tế cao của cả hai chất này.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. A food flavouring (Gia vị thực phẩm)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: A (Ambergris only)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;was widely used as a <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"33\">spice</strong>, which was believed to be an aphrodisiac when added to <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"94\">food or wine</strong>&#8221; (Đoạn 1).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Long diên hương được ghi nhận là một loại gia vị (spice) dùng cho thức ăn và rượu. Ngược lại, hổ phách (amber) được mô tả là nhựa cây hóa thạch, cứng và không có thông tin nào nói về việc dùng làm thực phẩm.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. Used as currency (Được dùng làm tiền tệ)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: D (Neither ambergris nor amber)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"11\">Không có đoạn văn nào chứa thông tin này.</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Mặc dù cả hai đều rất đắt tiền (costly), nhưng bài đọc không hề nhắc đến việc chúng được sử dụng như một loại tiền tệ (currency) để thanh toán hay trao đổi hàng hóa thay cho tiền.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. Sweet-smelling (Có mùi thơm)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: A (Ambergris only)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> * <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"13\">Ambergris:</strong> &#8220;Ambergris itself is <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"45\">pleasantly aromatic</strong>&#8221; (Đoạn 1) và &#8220;ambergris is&#8230; so <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"98\">highly fragrant</strong> that it is largely used in perfumery&#8221; (Đoạn 2).</p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8,1,1\">\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Amber:</strong> &#8220;amber is a hard, transparent, brittle, <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,1,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"47\">odorless</strong> substance&#8221; (Đoạn 2).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc tạo ra sự đối lập rõ rệt: long diên hương rất thơm (fragrant) và dùng làm nước hoa, trong khi hổ phách hoàn toàn không có mùi (odorless).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. Referred to by Herman Melville (Được Herman Melville nhắc đến)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"10\">\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: C (Both ambergris and amber)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;In Chapter 92 of Moby Dick, the American writer <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"60\">Herman Melville</strong> pours scorn on those who believed the <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"114\">two substances to be the same</strong>: ‘Though the word <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"162\">ambergris</strong> is but the French compound for grey <strong data-path-to-node=\"10,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"208\">amber</strong>. Yet the two substances are quite distinct.’&#8221; (Đoạn 2).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả trích dẫn lời của Melville trong tiểu thuyết <em data-path-to-node=\"10,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">Moby Dick</em>, nơi ông đề cập đến cả tên gọi và sự khác biệt giữa long diên hương và hổ phách để tránh nhầm lẫn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. Can be seen through (Có thể nhìn xuyên qua)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"12\">\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án: B (Amber only)</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> &#8220;amber is a hard, <strong data-path-to-node=\"12,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"29\">transparent</strong>, brittle, odorless substance&#8221; (Đoạn 2).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"12,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Từ &#8220;transparent&#8221; (trong suốt) có nghĩa là có thể nhìn xuyên qua được. Đây là đặc điểm của hổ phách. Long diên hương được mô tả là sáp (waxy) và màu xám (grey), nghĩa là nó đục và không thể nhìn xuyên qua.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('be6255fb-e60a-40f1-9217-e0543190a805', '12ce4f88-e9e8-40aa-bcdb-71f446533e80', 'fillup', 'Questions 24-26', '<div class="s-block-item s-repeatable-item s-block-sortable-item s-blog-post-section blog-section">
<div class="container">
<div class="sixteen columns">
<div class="s-blog-section-inner">
<div class="s-component s-text ">
<div class="">
<div class="s-component-content s-font-body">
<p>Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.<br />Write your answers in boxes <strong>24-26</strong> on your answer sheet.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Celebrities Achieve a Global Status</strong></span></p>
<p>The development of the publishing industry in the 1700s signalled the beginning of international fame. A growing number of people could read, which meant they had the chance to become informed about their favourite figures by reading {newspapers}. This exposure to celebrities expanded further when radio and television became popular, and it was mass media attention that resulted in higher status and fame for some celebrities. The recent rise of reality television has also meant that a person’s {appearance} rather than their talent can bring fame. With this type of television programme, fame may be entirely dependent on the response of the {audience}.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"1\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">24. newspapers</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 6, câu 4: “Suddenly, the lives of authors, politicians, war heroes, and other celebrities could now be read about in <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"133\">newspapers</strong> around the world.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Văn bản cho biết nhờ sự phát triển của ngành in ấn và số người biết đọc tăng lên, công chúng có thể tìm hiểu về các nhân vật họ ngưỡng mộ thông qua việc đọc <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"169\">báo chí</strong> (newspapers).</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">25. appearance</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 7, câu 5-6: “…reality television shows… allowed all kinds of people with little ability to enjoy a short burst of fame… All you needed, it seemed, was an attractive <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"187\">appearance</strong>.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Trong các chương trình truyền hình thực tế hiện đại, thay vì tài năng, một người có thể trở nên nổi tiếng chỉ nhờ vào <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"130\">ngoại hình</strong> (appearance) thu hút của mình.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">26. audience</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 7, câu 7: “…with the <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"39\">audience</strong> deciding whether someone deserves to become a celebrity or not.”</li>\n<li><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Đối với loại chương trình truyền hình này, sự nổi tiếng phụ thuộc hoàn toàn vào việc <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"97\">khán giả</strong> (audience) quyết định xem người đó có xứng đáng trở thành ngôi sao hay không.</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('413815a3-d595-4cca-bc23-3bd55b2b9ff1', '66ade43a-36ed-424f-9b52-32afe7047f03', 'fillup', 'Questions 7-9', '<p>Complete the flow-chart below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS</strong> from the passage for each answer.<br />
Write your answers in boxes 7-9 on your answer sheet.</p>
<p class="ql-align-center" style="text-align: center;"><strong>How ambergris is formed</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-center" style="text-align: center;">Ambergris is formed in whales because of problems digesting the {beaks}<span class="fill-history-correct"> </span>of giant squid.</p>
<h3 class="ql-align-center" style="text-align: center;"><strong>↓</strong></h3>
<p class="ql-align-center" style="text-align: center;">Black liquid is produced and is {vomited up| vomited}from time to time</p>
<h3 class="ql-align-center" style="text-align: center;"><strong>↓</strong></h3>
<p class="ql-align-center" style="text-align: center;">The liquid {hardens}<strong> </strong>on contact with the air.</p>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. beaks</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu hỏi thường gặp:</strong> Cá voi nhà táng không thể tiêu hóa được bộ phận nào của mực khổng lồ?</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“It is from the problems the whales have in digesting the <strong data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"78\">beaks</strong> of such creatures that ambergris has its origins.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Cá voi ăn mực khổng lồ, nhưng mỏ mực (<strong data-path-to-node=\"3,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">beaks</strong>) rất cứng và sắc nhọn, khiến hệ tiêu hóa của cá voi không thể phân hủy được.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. (lower) intestine</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu hỏi thường gặp:</strong> Những bộ phận sắc nhọn này gây kích ứng cho bộ phận nào của cá voi?</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“The beak is sharp and irritates the whale’s <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"65\">lower intestine</strong>…”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Những chiếc mỏ mực này không trôi đi mà gây trầy xước, kích ứng bên trong <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"86\">ruột dưới</strong> (lower intestine) của cá voi.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. vomited (up)</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Câu hỏi thường gặp:</strong> Cá voi phản ứng lại sự kích ứng này bằng cách làm gì với hỗn hợp đó?</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 5):</strong> <em data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"20\">“…from time to time large quantities of the liquid are <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"77\">vomited up</strong> by the whale.”</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Để bảo vệ ruột, cá voi tiết ra một chất lỏng đen bọc lấy mỏ mực, sau đó định kỳ <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"92\">nôn ra</strong> (vomit/vomited up) hỗn hợp này ra biển.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('b6c49569-4c48-472f-a1a0-a5ce4c521220', '66ade43a-36ed-424f-9b52-32afe7047f03', 'radio', 'Questions 10-13', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "In the 20th century, most of the world’s ambergris came from processing dead whales."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "The value of ambergris has increased recently."}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Ambergris remains an important ingredient in perfume."}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "New uses have recently been found for ambergris."}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"1\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"1\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. In the 20th century, most of the world’s ambergris came from processing dead whales — TRUE</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"2\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> “In 1963-64 alone… and over 90 per cent of the annual worldwide total was acquired in this way, <strong data-path-to-node=\"2,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"118\">as a by-product of commercial whaling</strong>.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Việc săn bắt cá voi thương mại (thế kỷ 20) để lấy các bộ phận (carcasses/dead whales) đã cung cấp hơn 90% lượng long diên hương. “Over 90%” tương ứng với “most”.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. The value of ambergris has increased recently — NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"4\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Bài đọc đề cập ở đoạn 1 rằng “At one time, ambergris was worth its weight in gold”. Đoạn cuối nói về việc nó bị thay thế bởi các chất khác.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc có nói về giá trị rất cao của nó trong quá khứ, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"74\">không có thông tin so sánh</strong> nào về việc giá trị của nó <strong data-path-to-node=\"4,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"128\">tăng lên trong thời gian gần đây (recently)</strong>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. Ambergris remains an important ingredient in perfume — FALSE</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"6\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng (Đoạn 6):</strong> “…so ambergris was <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"41\">supplanted</strong> in the making of perfume by <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"80\">other materials</strong>, some natural and some synthetic in origin.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Từ <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"15\">“supplanted”</strong> có nghĩa là <strong data-path-to-node=\"6,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"40\">bị thay thế</strong>. Vì long diên hương đã bị thay thế bởi các nguyên liệu tự nhiên và tổng hợp khác, nó không còn giữ vai trò là thành phần quan trọng (important ingredient) như trước nữa.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. New uses have recently been found for ambergris — NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"8\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> Đoạn 1 liệt kê các công dụng cổ xưa (thuốc, gia vị, nước hoa).</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ tập trung vào các công dụng truyền thống và lịch sử của long diên hương. <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"97\">Không có thông tin</strong> nào đề cập đến việc người ta tìm ra những <strong data-path-to-node=\"8,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"158\">công dụng mới (new uses)</strong> cho nó trong thời gian gần đây.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 2);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('cad3286d-fc06-4ca1-b81e-c788f0a211db', '3c862165-e1d2-47af-a129-abcdcdbc832a', 'radio', 'Questions 1-6', NULL, '<p>Choose <strong>TRUE </strong>if the statement agrees with the information given in the text, choose <strong>FALSE </strong>if the statement contradicts the information, or choose <strong>NOT GIVEN </strong>if there is no information on this.</p>
', 'multiple_choice_single', '[{"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Bocherens'' findings on cave bears involve measuring the length of complete bones"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Bocherens was the first person to conduct analytical research on cave bears in a laboratory"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Cave bears have been extinct for 25,000 years"}, {"correct": 0, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "At one time, people thought the excavated remains of bears were those of dragons"}, {"correct": 1, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Modern grizzly bears are similar in size to cave bears"}, {"correct": 2, "options": [{"content": "TRUE"}, {"content": "FALSE"}, {"content": "NOT GIVEN"}], "question": "Neanderthals understood cave bear behavior better than modern humans did"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">1. Bocherens’ findings on cave bears involve measuring the length of complete bones.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “He dissolves 30,000-year-old animal bones in hydrochloric acid… until what’s left is a speck of powder… biography of a cave bear as told through its chemical components.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc mô tả rất kỹ quy trình Bocherens dùng hóa chất để biến xương thành bột nhằm phân tích thành phần hóa học (isotopes). Tuy nhiên, bài <strong data-path-to-node=\"5,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"152\">không đề cập</strong> đến việc ông có đo chiều dài của những khúc xương còn nguyên vẹn hay không.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">2. Bocherens was the first person to conduct analytical research on cave bears in a laboratory.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Bocherens is at the forefront of research on the bear…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả nói Bocherens là người “đi đầu” (<em data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">at the forefront</em>) trong lĩnh vực này, nhưng điều đó không đồng nghĩa với việc ông là người “đầu tiên” (<em data-path-to-node=\"7,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"156\">the first</em>) thực hiện nghiên cứu trong phòng thí nghiệm.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">3. Cave bears have been extinct for 25,000 years.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…a European species that died out 25,000 years ago.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Thông tin trong câu hỏi khớp hoàn toàn với dẫn chứng trong bài (died out = extinct).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">4. At one time, people thought the excavated remains of bears were those of dragons.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">TRUE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…in the Middle Ages, the massive skulls were attributed to dragons…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Vào thời Trung cổ, người ta từng cho rằng những hộp sọ khổng lồ khai quật được là của loài rồng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">5. Modern grizzly bears are similar in size to cave bears.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">FALSE</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Males weighed up to 1,500 pounds—50% more than the largest modern grizzly bears.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Gấu hang nặng hơn 50% so với loài gấu xám lớn nhất hiện nay, vì vậy chúng không thể có kích thước “tương đương” (<em data-path-to-node=\"13,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"125\">similar</em>) được.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">6. Neanderthals understood cave bear behavior better than modern humans did.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Đáp án:</strong> <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"8\">NOT GIVEN</strong></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “Initially, cave bears shared the continent of Europe… with Neanderthals… Modern humans arrived… and were soon aware of the bears.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Bài đọc chỉ nói cả người Neanderthal và người hiện đại đều tiếp xúc với loài gấu này, nhưng <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,2,0\" data-index-in-node=\"104\">không có sự so sánh</strong> nào về việc ai hiểu tập tính của chúng tốt hơn.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('b90d6b12-a0b5-4593-8da8-365351f6626c', '12ce4f88-e9e8-40aa-bcdb-71f446533e80', 'matching', 'Questions 14-20', '', '<p>Choose the correct heading for each paragraph from the list of headings below. Write the correct number, <strong>i-x</strong>, in boxes 14-20 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'matching_headings', 'null', 'null', '{"layoutType": "heading", "summaryText": "", "answerOptions": [{"optionText": "i. Why it is necessary to explain the meaning of the word celebrity"}, {"optionText": "ii The influence of non-human celebrities on societies"}, {"optionText": "iii. The impact of broadcasting on concepts of celebrity"}, {"optionText": "iv. Creativity having greater value"}, {"optionText": "v. Admiration for physical achievement"}, {"optionText": "vi. The advantages of celebrity status in the ancient world"}, {"optionText": "vii A result of hardship"}, {"optionText": "viii Literacy and widespread celebrity"}, {"optionText": "ix. Attitudes of celebrities towards the media"}, {"optionText": "x. The original definition of celebrity"}], "matchingItems": []}', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"2\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"2\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">14. Đoạn 1: x. The original definition of celebrity</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"3\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> “The word ‘celebrity’ has its </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"41\">roots</strong><span class=\"\"> in the language of the ancient Roman civilization…</span><span class=\"\"> derived from the </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"117\">Latin word ‘celeber’</strong><span class=\"\">,</span><span class=\"\"> meaning frequented or populous.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"3,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Đoạn này tập trung vào nguồn gốc ngôn ngữ học và ý nghĩa sơ khai của từ “celebrity” trong tiếng Latin.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">15. Đoạn 2: ii. The influence of non-human celebrities on societies</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"5\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> “The celebrities of the ancient world were the </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"58\">powerful and awesome deities</strong><span class=\"\"> of Greece and Rome…</span><span class=\"\"> believed in a vast number of </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"138\">immortals</strong><span class=\"\">…</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"5,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> “Non-human” (không phải con người) ở đây chính là các vị thần (deities/immortals).</span><span class=\"\"> Đoạn văn giải thích tầm ảnh hưởng của các vị thần này đối với đời sống con người thời cổ đại.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">16. Đoạn 3: v. Admiration for physical achievement</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"7\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> “Victors in the ancient </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"35\">Olympic Games</strong><span class=\"\">…</span><span class=\"\"> gladiators…</span><span class=\"\"> revered…</span><span class=\"\"> for their heroics and </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"7,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"99\">seemingly superhuman strength</strong><span class=\"\">.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"7,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Thành tựu thể chất (physical achievement) thể hiện qua sức mạnh của các đấu sĩ và vinh quang của các vận động viên Olympic.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">17. Đoạn 4: vii. A result of hardship</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"9\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> “spiritual figures lent excitement to the lives of common people…</span><span class=\"\"> as they faced </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"93\">war, disease, and food shortages</strong><span class=\"\">.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"9,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> “Hardship” (sự gian khổ) chính là chiến tranh,</span><span class=\"\"> dịch bệnh và thiếu thốn thực phẩm.</span><span class=\"\"> Sự nổi tiếng của các nhân vật tôn giáo là cứu cánh tinh thần cho người dân trong giai đoạn này.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">18. Đoạn 5: iv. Creativity having greater value</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"11\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> “This period of </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"27\">appreciation for the arts</strong><span class=\"\">…</span><span class=\"\"> artists began to </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"11,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"73\">surpass political and religious individuals</strong><span class=\"\"> for supreme celebrity.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"11,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> “Creativity” (sự sáng tạo) đại diện cho giới nghệ sĩ (artists).</span><span class=\"\"> Thời kỳ Phục hưng coi trọng giá trị sáng tạo nghệ thuật hơn là quyền lực chính trị hay tôn giáo.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">19. Đoạn 6: viii. Literacy and widespread celebrity</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"13\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong><span class=\"\"> “…</span><span class=\"\">huge rise in the number of </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"42\">common people who could read</strong><span class=\"\">…</span><span class=\"\"> allowing a </span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"13,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"85\">mass audience</strong><span class=\"\"> to find out about celebrities for the first time.</span><span class=\"\">“</span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\"><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong><span class=\"\"> Khả năng biết chữ (</span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"31\">Literacy</strong><span class=\"\">) tăng cao giúp danh tiếng của các cá nhân lan tỏa rộng rãi (</span><strong class=\"\" data-path-to-node=\"13,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"100\">widespread</strong><span class=\"\">) thông qua báo chí và sách vở.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">20. Đoạn 7: iii. The impact of broadcasting on concepts of celebrity</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"15\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…as <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"18\">radio and film</strong> took off in the 1900s… Then, the rise of <strong data-path-to-node=\"15,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"76\">television</strong> in the 1950s…”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> “Broadcasting” (truyền thông quảng bá) bao gồm đài phát thanh, phim ảnh và tivi đã thay đổi hoàn toàn cách thức con người trở nên nổi tiếng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('f551d72a-5403-4951-8f81-6e7139b1b732', '3c862165-e1d2-47af-a129-abcdcdbc832a', 'fillup', 'Questions 7-13', '<p>Complete the notes below.</p>
<p>Choose <strong>ONE WORD ONLY</strong> from the passage for each answer.</p>
<div class="s-block-item s-repeatable-item s-block-sortable-item s-blog-post-section blog-section">
<div class="container">
<div class="sixteen columns">
<div class="s-blog-section-inner">
<div class="s-component s-text ">
<div class="">
<div class="s-component-content s-font-body" style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Research into the existence and disappearance of cave bears</strong></span></div>
<div class="s-component-content s-font-body">
<p><strong>Evidence from the Chauvet Cave in France</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Paintings on the walls include bears.</li>
<li>Over a hundred {skeletons} of cave bears together with paw prints were found on the floor of the cave.</li>
<li>The {skull} of a cave bear was found in a prominent position in the cave.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Evidence from the Hohle Fels Cave in the Swabian Jura in Germany</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Bones and tools found in the cave indicate it provided {shelter} for both bears and humans.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Susanne Munzel’s Findings</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>A spear point in the vertebra of a bear indicates that a hunt had taken place.</li>
<li>Marks on the bones of bears indicate the removal of flesh.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Hervé Bocherens’ Findings</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Isotopes from the bones indicate that {plants} were the cave bears’ preferred food.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Factors Leading to the Disappearance of the Cave Bear</strong></p>
<p><strong>Climate Change</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>The Ice Age changed vegetation growth in {Europe}.</li>
<li>Bears were forced to migrate.</li>
<li>Support for the above explanation comes from a study of changes in the DNA in the {teeth} of the population of cave bears near the Danube River at this time.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Human Population Expansion</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Competition from Neanderthals and modern humans for caves may have reduced opportunities for cave bears to {hibernate}.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
', NULL, 'gap_filling', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">7. skeletons</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"19\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…the floor is covered with 150 cave bear <strong data-path-to-node=\"19,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"55\">skeletons</strong>…” (Đoạn 6)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sàn hang Chauvet có tới 150 bộ xương gấu hang.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">8. skull</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…a cave bear <strong data-path-to-node=\"21,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"27\">skull</strong> was perched on a stone slab in the center of one chamber…” (Đoạn 6)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"21,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Một hộp sọ gấu được đặt ở vị trí trang trọng trên một phiến đá giữa phòng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">9. shelter</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"23\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…cave bears and human beings sought <strong data-path-to-node=\"23,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"50\">shelter</strong> here from winter weather.” (Đoạn 8)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"23,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Các bằng chứng cho thấy hang Hohle Fels là nơi trú ẩn của cả gấu và người.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">10. plants</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"25\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…Bocherens has found that cave bears ate mainly <strong data-path-to-node=\"25,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"62\">plants</strong>.” (Phần Why Did Cave Bears Go Extinct?)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Phân tích Isotopes (đồng vị) cho thấy thức ăn ưa thích của loài này là thực vật.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">11. Europe</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"27\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…altered the distribution of plant species across <strong data-path-to-node=\"27,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"64\">Europe</strong>.” (Phần Why Did Cave Bears Go Extinct?)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Kỷ băng hà đã làm thay đổi sự phân bố thực vật trên khắp châu Âu.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">12. teeth</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"29\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…according to a DNA analysis of <strong data-path-to-node=\"29,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"46\">teeth</strong> found near the Danube River.” (Phần Why Did Cave Bears Go Extinct?)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Nghiên cứu DNA trên răng gấu tìm thấy ở sông Danube hỗ trợ cho giả thuyết về sự di cư.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">13. hibernate</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"31\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…cave bears had fewer safe places to <strong data-path-to-node=\"31,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"51\">hibernate</strong>.” (Đoạn cuối)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Sự gia tăng dân số của con người chiếm dụng các hang động khiến gấu hang không còn chỗ để ngủ đông.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n"}]', 1);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('4608b8c5-c28a-43e3-a658-4e7c7d825185', '6b69ec17-70c6-4e0d-8b76-9f395ed6b83a', 'fillup', 'Questions 1 - 10', '<p>Complete the form below.</p>
<p>Write <strong>ONE WORD AND/OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><strong>Booking a residential workshop</strong></span></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Course required: drama workshop</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Full name of participant: Jan {Creswick}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Previous course attended: Writing for the {theater|theatre}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Address: 20, Gregory {place}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Current occupation: {waitress}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Date chosen course begins: {13 June| 13th June| June 13th| June 13} </p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Estimated arrival time: {5.30|5:30} pm</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Special dietary requests: no {milk} products</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Preferred afternoon course: {comic} work</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>First source of course information: {internet}</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Pre-course material requested: the {leaflet} mentioned in the publicity</p>
</li>
</ul>', NULL, 'summary_completion', 'null', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<h3 data-path-to-node=\"3\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"3\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">PART 1: BOOKING A RESIDENTIAL WORKSHOP</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"4\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"4\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Hello, Creative Centre.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"5\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> Hello there. I''m phoning to book a place on your next two-day drama workshop.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"6\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> OK, let me just check... um, yes, we''ve still got room on that course.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"5\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan: </strong>Great.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"6\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man: </strong>Can I have your full name?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"7\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> Yes, it''s Jan <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"19\">(Q1) Creswick</strong></span>. Uh, that''s C-R-E-S-W-I-C-K.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"8\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"8\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Thanks, Jan. And are you coming on your own?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"9\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"9\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> Yes.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"10\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"10\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> And have you done any of our courses before?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"11\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"11\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> Yes, I did one a couple of years ago.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"12\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"12\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Great, so you may be on our computer records. Um, which course did you do?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"13\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> The <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"13\" data-index-in-node=\"9\">(Q2) Theatre</strong></span> course (Writing for the Theatre).</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"14\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"14\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> OK, right, yes, here we are. Oh, so that''s 20 Gregory Avenue?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"15\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> Uh, Gregory <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"15\" data-index-in-node=\"17\">(Q3) Place</strong></span>, actually.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"16\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"16\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Okay, I''ll correct that on the computer. Uh-huh. And can I ask if you work?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> Yes. I want to be an actor, but I''m working as a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"54\">(Q4) waitress</strong></span> at the moment.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> After this course, who knows? Right, back to the paperwork. So we''re enrolling you on the two-day course that starts tomorrow, May 30th?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"19\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> Oh, uh, sorry, no, on the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"31\">(Q5) 13th of June</strong> (or <strong data-path-to-node=\"19\" data-index-in-node=\"53\">13 June</strong>)</span>. I meant the one starting in two weeks. Is that still alright?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"20\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"20\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Oh, that''s fine.</p>\n<hr data-path-to-node=\"21\">\n<h3 data-path-to-node=\"22\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"22\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">ACCOMMODATION &amp; DETAILS (Questions 6–10)</strong></h3>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> Can you tell me something about accommodation?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"23\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man: </strong>Yes, people usually come the evening before the course starts. The cost of the course includes accommodation for 2 nights.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"24\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> Well, I''ll make sure I''m there in good time so I can meet the others that evening and settle in. Is <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"24\" data-index-in-node=\"105\">(Q6) 5:30</strong></span> too early to arrive?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"25\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"25\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> No, that''s fine. And you''ll finish no later than 5:00 on the last day.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"26\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> Right.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"26\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> okay.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"27\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"27\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Right, just a few other things. Any dietary information we should know? All the food is provided and we use organic produce as often as we can.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"28\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> Oh, that sounds great. But I don''t eat anything that''s made from <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"28\" data-index-in-node=\"70\">(Q7) milk</strong></span>.I know that can be difficult.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"29\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"29\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Oh, it''s not a problem. What about meat? Do you eat that?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"30\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"30\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> I don''t eat much of it, but that''s fine. You don''t need to note that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"31\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Sure.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"31\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan: </strong>Yes.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"32\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"32\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> Hey, I am really looking forward to this.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"33\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Haha, great. I don''t know if you know this, but we may divide into two groups in the afternoon if we have more than 16 people on the course. If we do that, there''ll be a choice of doing <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"191\">(Q8) comic</strong></span> or what we call classic work.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"34\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> Oh, I''d always go with comedy. I''m much more interested in that.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"34\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"33\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man: </strong>Now, how did you find out about this course? Was it the advert in the Sunday newspaper?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"35\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> No, in fact, I looked for drama courses on the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"52\">(Q9) internet</strong></span> and I saw that you were doing one. When I read about it, I just thought hey, why not?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"36\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"36\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Okay.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"36\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan: </strong>I saw that you send out some pre-course material?</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"36\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Yes.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"37\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"35\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Jan:</strong> I don''t have much time to read any of the books you''re recommending, but I''d be grateful for your <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #f1c40f;\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"37\" data-index-in-node=\"108\">(Q10) leaflet</strong></span></span>, the one you mentioned in your publicity.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"38\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"38\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man:</strong> Sure, I''ll put a copy in the post to you.</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"38\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"7\" data-index-in-node=\"1725\">Jan:</strong> Thanks a lot. I can''t wait!</p>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"38\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"38\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Man: </strong>Haha, wait till you see...</p>"}]', 0);
INSERT INTO public.questions VALUES ('81850583-1e37-4ec1-a72e-b3ccd56e3488', 'c5510d0d-d693-46b0-bcfc-6a770e29343d', 'radio', 'Question 40', '', '<p data-path-to-node="8">Choose the correct letter,<strong> A</strong>, <strong>B</strong>, <strong>C</strong> or<strong> D</strong>.</p>
<p data-path-to-node="9">Write the correct letter in box 40 on your answer sheet.</p>', 'multiple_choice', '[{"correct": 1, "options": [{"option_text": "A risk is something we must try to avoid."}, {"option_text": "B experts should be truthful about risk to the public."}, {"option_text": "C optimists are better able to deal with risk than pessimists."}, {"option_text": "D it is important to take risks in order to fulfil social obligations."}], "question": "At the end of the passage the writer concludes that"}]', 'null', 'null', 'null', '[{"content": "<p data-path-to-node=\"17\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"17\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">40. At the end of the passage the writer concludes that — {B} experts should be truthful about risk to the public.</strong></p>\n<ul data-path-to-node=\"18\">\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Dẫn chứng:</strong> “…everyone in our scientific and engineering community has a social responsibility: <strong data-path-to-node=\"18,0,0\" data-index-in-node=\"97\">measure with care and portray with honesty the level of risk</strong>…” (Đoạn H)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\"><strong data-path-to-node=\"18,1,0\" data-index-in-node=\"0\">Giải thích:</strong> Tác giả kết luận rằng trách nhiệm xã hội của cộng đồng khoa học là phải đo lường cẩn thận và mô tả trung thực (portray with honesty) mức độ rủi ro cho công chúng.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>"}]', 2);
SET session_replication_role = DEFAULT;
